"Year","Date","Event"
1789,"January 7","1789 United States presidential elections and House of Representatives elections are held."
1789,"March 4","At Federal Hall in New York City, the 1st United States Congress meets and declares the new United States Constitution to be in effect."
1789,"April 7","Selim III (1789-1807) succeeds Abd-ul-Hamid I (1773-1789) as Ottoman Sultan ."
1789,"June 17","In France, representatives of the Third Estate at the Estates-General declare themselves the National Assembly."
1789,"June 23","Louis XVI of France makes a conciliatory speech urging reforms to a joint session and orders the three estates to meet together."
1789,"July 11","The King of France fires popular Chief Minister Necker."
1789,"August 4","In France, members of the Constituent Assembly take an oath to end feudalism and abandon their privileges."
1789,"August 7","The United States Department of War is established."
1789,"August 26","The Declaration of the Rights of Man is proclaimed in France."
1789,"September 25","The United States Congress proposes a set of 12 amendments for ratification by the states. Ratification for 10 of these proposals is completed on December 5, 1791, creating the United States Bill of Rights."
1789,"November 21","North Carolina ratifies the United States Constitution and becomes the 12th U.S. state."
1789,"November 26","A national Thanksgiving Day is observed in the United States as recommended by President George Washington and approved by Congress."
1789,"December 23","A leaflet circulated in France accuses marquis de Favras of plotting to rescue the royal family."
1790,"February 4","Louis XVI of France declares to the National Assembly that he will maintain the constitutional laws."
1790,"February 11","Two Quaker delegates petition the United States Congress for the abolition of slavery."
1790,"March 4","France is divided into 83 départements, which cut across the former provinces, in an attempt to dislodge regional loyalties based on noble ownership of land."
1790,"March 21","Thomas Jefferson reports to President George Washington in New York as the new United States Secretary of State."
1790,"April 10","The United States patent system is established."
1790,"May 13","Battle of Reval: Gustav III of Sweden sends the battlefleet to eliminate the Russian squadron wintering at Reval (Estonia), but is defeated: 8 Russians, 51 Swedes are killed, 250 captured, and 2 ships are sunk."
1790,"May 29","Rhode Island ratifies the United States Constitution and becomes the last of the 13 original states to do so."
1790,"July 9","Russo-Swedish War - Second Battle of Svensksund: In a massive Baltic Sea battle of 300 ships, the Swedish navy captures one third of the Russian fleet: 304 Swedes are killed, 3,500 Russians killed and 6,000 captured, 51 Russian ships are sunk and 22 are taken."
1790,"July 16","The signing of the Residence Bill establishes a site along the Potomac River as the District of Columbia, the capital district of the United States."
1790,"July 27","The Convention of Reichenbach is signed between Prussia and Austria."
1790,"August 4","A newly passed U.S. tariff act creates the system of cutters for revenue enforcement (later named the United States Revenue Cutter Service), the forerunner of the Coast Guard."
1790,"circa","Prime Minister of Great Britain William Pitt refuses to recognize Belgian independence."
1790,"circa","The 1790 United States Census is taken."
1791,"August 4","The Treaty of Sistova is signed, ending the Ottoman-Habsburg wars."
1791,"August 26","John Fitch is granted a patent for the steamboat in the United States."
1791,"September 28","Louis XVI of France accepts the final version of the completed constitution."
1791,"circa","The metric system is adopted in France."
1792,"January 9","The Treaty of Jassy ends Russia's war with the Ottoman Empire over Crimea."
1792,"March 16","King Gustav III of Sweden is shot in the back by Jacob Johan Anckarström at a midnight masquerade at the Royal Opera in Stockholm; he lives until March 29, and is succeeded by Gustav IV Adolf."
1792,"April 20","France declares war against Austria."
1792,"May 18","War in defence of the constitution: Russia invades Poland."
1792,"May 21","An old lava dome collapses in Kyushu, Japan when Mount Unzen volcano erupts; the resulting avalanche and tsunami kills about 14,300 people."
1792,"June 1","Kentucky becomes the 15th state of The United States of America."
1792,"June 4","Captain George Vancouver claims Puget Sound for Great Britain."
1792,"June 13","Prussia declares war against France."
1792,"August 10","French Revolution: The Tuileries Palace is stormed, and Louis XVI of France is arrested and taken into custody."
1792,"September 20","Battle of Valmy: French revolutionary army defeats Prussians under the Duke of Brunswick after 7-hour artillery duel."
1792,"October 13","Foundation of Washington, DC: The cornerstone of the United States Executive Mansion, known as the White House after 1818, is laid."
1792,"December 3","George Washington is re-elected President of the United States."
1792,"December 26","The trial of Louis XVI of France begins."
1793,"January 2","Russia and Prussia partition the Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth."
1793,"February 1","France declares war on Great Britain and the Netherlands."
1793,"February 27","The Giles resolutions are introduced to the United States House of Representatives, asking the House to condemn Alexander Hamilton's handling of loans."
1793,"March 1","John Langdon becomes President Pro Tempore of the United States Senate until March 3."
1793,"March 4","George Washington is sworn in as President of the United States in Philadelphia, for his second term."
1793,"March 5","French troops are defeated by Austrian forces and Liège is recaptured."
1793,"March 7","France declares war on Spain."
1793,"April 1","The Unsen volcano erupts in Japan and causes an earthquake; about 53,000 are killed."
1793,"April 6","The Committee of Public Safety is established in France with Georges Danton as its head."
1793,"August 23","The following universal conscription decree is enacted in France: ""The young men shall go to battle and the married men shall forge arms. The women shall make tents and clothes and shall serve in the hospitals; children shall tear rags into lint. The old men will be guided to the public places of the cities to kindle the courage of the young warriors and to preach the unity of the Republic and the hatred of kings""."
1793,"September 5","In France, the French National Convention votes to implement terror measures to repress 'counter-revolutionary' activities. The ensuing [i]Reign of Terror[/i] lasts until the spring of 1794 and causes the deaths of 35,000-40,000 people."
1793,"October 12","The cornerstone of Old East, the oldest state university building in the United States, is laid in Chapel Hill, North Carolina, on the campus of the University of North Carolina (the 12th of October is now celebrated at the University as University Day)."
1793,"October 31","Arrested Girondist leaders are executed in France, by guillotine."
1793,"circa","Roman Catholicism is banned in France."
1793,"circa","The First Coalition against France is formed."
1793,"circa","The Holy Roman Empire declares war on France."
1793,"circa","The metric system is adopted in France."
1793,"circa","As part of their campaign against France, the British invade Haiti and take all of its coastal cities."
1794,"June 26","Battle of Fleurus: French forces defeat the Austrians."
1794,"circa","Coffee is forbidden by royal decree in Sweden."
1794,"circa","France occupies Aachen."
1794,"circa","Britain agrees to evacuate border forts in the Northwest Territory (roughly the area north of the Ohio River and east of the Mississippi) and thereby end British support for the Indians."
1794,"circa","President Washington peacefully ends the Whiskey Rebellion, leading 15,000 troops and showing the new power of the Federal Government under the United States Constitution."
1795,"January 16","The French occupy Utrecht, Netherlands."
1795,"February 7","The 11th Amendment to the United States Constitution is passed."
1795,"April 7","France adopts the metre as the unit of length."
1795,"May 15","First Coalition: Napoleon I of France enters Milan in triumph."
1795,"October 1","Austrian Netherlands is annexed to the French Republic as the [i]Belgian departments[/i]."
1795,"October 27","The United States and Spain sign the Treaty of Madrid, which establishes the boundaries between Spanish colonies and the United States."
1795,"circa","Spain cedes its half of Hispaniola to France."
1795,"circa","Sans-culottes revolt in France."
1796,"April 27","Case of the Lyons Mail: During the night of April 27, 5 highwaymen attack the mail between Paris and Lyon, kill the postmen, and steal the funds sent to the armies in Italy."
1796,"May 10","Persian Expedition of 1796: Russian troops storm Derbent."
1796,"May 10","War of the First Coalition - Battle of Lodi: General Napoleon Bonaparte defeats Austrian rearguard in forcing a crossing of the bridge over the River Adda in Italy. The Austrians lose some 2,000 men, 14 guns, and 30 ammunition wagons."
1796,"July 11","The United States takes possession of Detroit from Great Britain under the terms of the Jay Treaty."
1796,"September 8","French Revolutionary Wars - Battle of Bassano: French forces defeat Austrian troops."
1796,"November 4","The Treaty of Tripoli (between the United States and Tripoli) is signed at Tripoli."
1796,"November 17","French Revolutionary Wars - Battle of Arcole: French forces defeat the Austrians in Italy."
1796,"circa","Spanish government lifts the restrictions against neutrals trading with the colonies, thus acknowledging Spain's inability to supply the colonies with needed goods and markets."
1797,"January 3","The Treaty of Tripoli (a peace treaty between the United States and Tripoli) is signed at Algiers."
1797,"January 7","The parliament of the Cisalpine Republic adopts the Italian green-white-red tricolour as the official flag (this is considered the birth of the flag of Italy)."
1797,"February 22","The Last invasion of Britain begins. French forces under the command of American Colonel William Tate land near Fishguard in Wales."
1797,"March 4","John Adams is sworn in as the 2nd President of the United States of America."
1797,"May 12","First Coalition: Napoleon I of France conquers Venice, ending the city's 1,070 years of independence. The last doge of Venice, Ludovico Manin, steps down."
1797,"October 21","In Boston Harbor, the 44-gun United States Navy frigate [i]USS Constitution[/i] is launched to fight Barbary pirates off the coast of Tripoli."
1797,"circa","The XYZ Affair inflames tensions between France and the United States."
1798,"January 22","A coup d'état is staged in the Netherlands (Batavian Republic). Unitarian Democrat Pieter Vreede makes an end to the power of the parliament (with a conservative-moderate majority)."
1798,"April 7","The Mississippi Territory is organized from territory ceded by Georgia and South Carolina and is later twice expanded to include disputed territory claimed by both the U.S. and Spain."
1798,"April 26","France annexes Geneva."
1798,"May 23","Irish republicans and nationalists known as the Society of United Irishmen launch a rebellion against British rule in expectation of support from France. The United Irishmen are unique amongst Irish nationalist movements in that they manage to unify Catholics and Protestants around republican ideals. The rebellion rages sporadically but is swiftly ended by October."
1798,"June 12","Another moderate coup d'état in the Netherlands (Batavian Republic) deposes Pieter Vreede."
1798,"July 7","Quasi-War: The United States Congress rescinds treaties with France, sparking the war."
1798,"July 11","The United States Marine Corps is re/established."
1798,"July 21","Battle of the Pyramids: Napoleon defeats Ottoman forces near the Pyramids."
1798,"July 31","A second round of elections are held in the Netherlands (Batavian Republic); no general elections this time."
1799,"January 9","British Prime Minister William Pitt the Younger introduces an income tax of two shillings to the pound to raise funds for Great Britain's war effort in the Napoleonic Wars."
1799,"March 1","Federalist James Ross becomes President Pro Tempore of the United States Senate."
1799,"July 25","At Aboukir in Egypt, Napoleon Bonaparte defeats 10,000 Ottoman Mamluk troops under Mustafa Pasha."
1799,"August 27","The British and Russians send an expedition to the Batavian Republic (now the Netherlands)."
1799,"October 18","Anglo-Russian expedition forces surrender in Holland."
1800,"circa","World Population: ~1 Billion."
1800,"May 15","Napoleon Bonaparte crosses the Alps and invades Italy."
1800,"June 14","Battle of Marengo: Napoleon defeats the Austrian troops near Marengo, Italy."
1800,"September 30","The Convention of 1800, or Treaty of Mortefontaine, is signed between France, Britain, and the United States of America, ending the Quasi-War."
1801,"January 3","Toussaint L'Overture triumphantly entered in Santo Domingo, the capital of former Spanish colony of Santo Domingo, which became a colony of the Napoleonic France."
1801,"January 21","John Marshall is appointed Chief Justice of the United States."
1801,"February 16","The Treaty of Lunéville ends the war (Second Coalition) between France and Austria."
1801,"February 19","An electoral tie between Thomas Jefferson and Aaron Burr is resolved, when Jefferson is elected President of the United States and Burr Vice President by the United States House of Representatives."
1801,"March 4","Thomas Jefferson succeeds John Adams as the President of the United States of America."
1801,"March 23","The Russian Tsar Paul I is murdered. He is succeeded by his son Alexander I of Russia."
1801,"May 10","The pascha of Tripoli declares war on the United States by having the flagpole on the consulate chopped down."
1801,"June 7","Portugal and Spain sign the Treaty of Badajoz; Portugal loses the city of Olivenza."
1801,"October 17","A coup d'état is staged in the Netherlands (Batavian Republic)."
1801,"circa","Aachen is officially annexed by France."
1802,"March 16","United States Military Academy of West Point is established."
1802,"March 25","(March 25 - March 27) The Treaty of Amiens between France and the United Kingdom ends the War of the Second Coalition."
1802,"April 26","A general amnesty signed by Napoleon Bonaparte allows all but about 1,000 of the most notorious émigrés of the French Revolution to return to France, as part of a reconciliary gesture to make peace with the various factions of the [i]Ancien Regime[/i] that ultimately consolidates his own rule."
1802,"July 4","At West Point, New York the United States Military Academy opens."
1802,"October 2","War ends between Sweden and Tripoli. The United States also negotiates peace, but war continues over the size of compensation."
1803,"February 24","[i]Marbury v. Madison[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States establishes the principle of judicial review."
1803,"April 30","Louisiana Purchase is made by the United States from France."
1803,"May 18","The United Kingdom resumes war on France after France refuses to withdraw from Dutch territory."
1803,"October 20","The Senate ratifies the Louisiana Purchase Treaty, doubling the size of the United States."
1803,"November 30","At the Cabildo building in New Orleans, Spanish representatives Governor Manuel de Salcedo and the Marqués de Casa Calvo, officially transfer the Louisiana Territory to French representative Prefect Pierre Clément de Laussat (just 20 days later, France transfers the same land to the United States as the Louisiana Purchase)."
1803,"circa","France - the Livre Tournois (Tours Pound) is replaced by the Franc."
1804,"March 10","Louisiana Purchase: In St. Louis, a formal ceremony is conducted to transfer ownership of Louisiana Territory from France to the United States."
1804,"November 30","The Democratic-Republican-controlled United States Senate begin an impeachment trial against Federalist-partisan Supreme Court of the United States Justice Samuel Chase (he was charged with political bias but was acquitted by the United States Senate of all charges on March 1, 1805)."
1804,"December 12","Spain declares war on Britain."
1804,"circa","World population reaches 1 billion people."
1805,"March 4","Thomas Jefferson is sworn in for a second term as President of the United States."
1805,"April 27","United States Marines and Berbers attack the Tripolitan city of Derna (The ""Shores of Tripoli"")."
1805,"October 17","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Ulm: Austrian General Mack von Leiberich is forced to surrender his entire army to Napoleon after being surrounded."
1805,"October 21","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Trafalgar: British naval fleet led by Admiral Horatio Nelson defeats a combined French and Spanish fleet off the coast of Spain; however, Admiral Nelson is fatally shot."
1805,"November 11","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Dürenstein: 8,000 French troops attempt to slow the retreat of a vastly superior Russian and Austrian force."
1805,"November 16","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Schöngrabern: - Russian forces under Pyotr Bagration delay the pursuit by French troops under Murat."
1805,"December 2","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Austerlitz: French troops under Napoleon decisively defeat a joint Russo-Austrian force."
1805,"December 26","The Peace of Pressburg is signed between France and Austria."
1805,"circa","Sweden declares war on France."
1806,"July 4","Battle of Maida: Britain defeats France in Calabria."
1806,"July 15","Pike expedition: Near St. Louis, Missouri, United States Army Lieutenant Zebulon Pike leads an expedition from Fort Belle Fountaine to explore the west."
1806,"October 14","Battle of Jena-Auerstädt: Napoleon defeats the Prussian army of Prince Hohenlohe at Jena while Marshal Davout defeats the main Prussian army under the Duke of Brunswick, who is killed."
1806,"November 24","The last major Prussian field force, under Gebhard Leberecht von Blücher, surrenders to the French near Lübeck. Frederick William III has by this time fled to Russia."
1806,"December 26","Battles of Pultusk and Golymin. Battle of Pultusk: Russian forces under General Bennigsen narrowly escape from a direct confrontation with Napoleon, who goes into winter quarters. Battle of Golymin: Russian forces under General Golitsyn fight a successful rearguard action against French forces under Marshall Murat."
1807,"February 7","Battle of Eylau: Napoléon's French Empire begins fighting against Russian and Prussian forces of the Fourth Coalition."
1807,"February 8","Battle of Eylau: Napoleon fights a hard, but inconclusive battle against the Russians under Bennigsen."
1807,"February 19","In Alabama, Former Vice President of the United States Aaron Burr is tried for conspiracy and acquitted."
1807,"March 2","The U.S. Congress passes an act to ""prohibit the importation of slaves into any port or place within the jurisdiction of the United States....from any foreign kingdom, place, or country"" (to take effect 1 January 1808)."
1807,"May 22","A grand jury indicts former Vice President of the United States Aaron Burr for treason."
1807,"June 14","Battle of Friedland: Napoleon decisively defeats Bennigsen's Russian army."
1807,"July 7","(July 7 - July 9) The Peace of Tilsit is signed between France, Prussia and Russia. Napoleon and Russian Emperor Alexander I ally together against the British. The Prussians are forced to cede more than half their territory, which is formed into the Duchy of Warsaw in their former Polish lands and the Kingdom of Westphalia in western Germany."
1807,"October 9","Serfdom is abolished in Prussia by law."
1807,"circa","Ottoman Emperor Selim III (1789-1807) is deposed in favour of his nephew Mustafa IV,."
1807,"circa","World's oldest international football stadium opens in Wrexham."
1808,"January 1","The importation of slaves into the United States is banned; this is also the earliest day under the United States Constitution that an amendment can be made restricting slavery."
1808,"February 21","Finnish War: Russian troops cross the border into Finland without a declaration of war."
1808,"March 2","Russian troops occupy Helsinki and threaten Sveaborg."
1808,"March 11","Russian troops occupy Tampere."
1808,"March 13","Upon the death of Christian VII, Frederick VI becomes king of Denmark. The next day (March 14), Denmark declares war on Sweden."
1808,"March 22","Russian troops occupy Turku."
1808,"March 26","Charles IV of Spain abdicates in favor of his son, Ferdinand VII."
1808,"April 16","Troops under colonel Carl von Döbeln clash with Russian troops in Pyhäjoki, Finland."
1808,"May 3","Finnish War: The fortress of Sveaborg is lost by Sweden to Russia."
1808,"July 14","Troops under Colonel Adlercreutz force the Russians to withdraw in Lapua."
1808,"August 10","Troops under Carl von Döbeln defeat a Russian attack in Kauhajoki."
1808,"September 27","The Congress of Erfurt between the emperors Napoleon I of France and Alexander I of Russia starts."
1808,"September 29","A truce is declared between Swedish and Russian troops in Finland; it ends on October 19."
1808,"November 15","Mahmud II (1808-1839) succeeds Mustafa IV (1807-1808) as sultan of the Ottoman Empire."
1809,"January 5","The Treaty of the Dardanelles between Britain and the Ottoman Empire is concluded."
1809,"February 8","Franz I of Austria declares war on France."
1809,"February 20","A decision by the Supreme Court of the United States states that the power of the federal government is greater than any individual state."
1809,"March 4","James Madison succeeds Thomas Jefferson as the President of the United States."
1809,"March 13","A military coup ousts Gustav IV Adolf of Sweden; he is confined in the Gripsholm Castle."
1809,"March 29","At the Diet of Porvoo, Finland's four Estates pledge allegiance to Alexander I of Russia, commencing the secession of the Grand Duchy of Finland from Sweden."
1809,"March 29","King Gustav IV Adolf of Sweden abdicates after a coup d'état and is later exiled."
1809,"April 14","Battle of Abensberg, Bavaria: Napoleon I defeats Austria."
1809,"April 19","Battle of Raszyn: The armies of Austria are defeated by the Duchy of Warsaw as a part of the struggles of the Fifth Coalition (1809)."
1809,"April 22","Battle of Eckmühl: French troops under Napoleon I and Marshal Davout defeat the Austrians under Archduke Charles."
1809,"May 17","Napoleon I of France orders the annexation of the Papal States to the French Empire. When he announces that the Pope's secular power has ended, the Pope excommunicates him."
1809,"May 21","Battle of Aspern-Essling: Austrian troops under Archduke Karl beat the French under Napoleon in a hard fought battle."
1809,"June 6","Sweden promulgates a new Instrument of Government, which restores political power to the Riksdag of the Estates after authoritarian rule since 1772."
1809,"July 5","(July 5 - July 6) Battle of Wagram: Napoleon defeats the Austrians."
1809,"July 10","French Marshal Marmont engages in the inconclusive Battle of Znaim against the Austrians."
1809,"August 10","Ecuador declares independence from Spain."
1809,"September 17","The Peace of Hamina is signed between Russia and Sweden in the Finnish War. The territory to become the Grand Duchy of Finland is ceded to Russia by the Treaty of Fredrikshamn."
1809,"October 8","Prince Klemens von Metternich becomes Austrian foreign minister."
1809,"October 14","The Treaty of Schoenbrunn cedes the Illyrian provinces to France."
1810,"March 11","Napoleon marries Marie-Louise of Austria."
1810,"May 25","May Revolution: Armed citizens of Buenos Aires expel the Viceroy from Spain and establish a provincial government for Argentina."
1810,"July 20","Colombia declares its independence from Spain."
1810,"August 21","Jean-Baptiste Bernadotte, Marshal of France, is elected Crown Prince of Sweden by the Swedish Riksdag of the Estates."
1810,"September 23","The Republic of West Florida declares independence from Spain."
1810,"October 27","The United States annexes the Republic of West Florida."
1810,"circa","Russia acquires Sukhumi through a treaty with the Abkhazian dukes, and declares a protectorate over the whole of Abkhazia."
1810,"circa","Palm oil sales from West Africa to Britain reach 1,000 tons."
1810,"circa","4,500 chests of opium are sold in China."
1811,"May 14","Paraguay declares independence from Spain."
1811,"May 16","Battle of Albuera: Spain, Portugal and Great Britain defeat the French."
1811,"July 5","Venezuela declares its independence from Spain."
1812,"January 1","The [i]Allgemeines bürgerliches Gesetzbuch[/i] (the Austrian civil code) enters into force in the Austrian Empire."
1812,"February 2","Russia establishes a fur trading colony at Fort Ross, California."
1812,"May 28","Russian Field Marshal Mikhail Kutuzov signs the Treaty of Bucharest, ending the Russo-Turkish War, 1806-1812 and making Bessarabia a part of Imperial Russia."
1812,"June 1","War of 1812: U.S. President James Madison asks the U.S. Congress to declare war on Great Britain."
1812,"June 18","The War of 1812 begins between the United States and the British Empire."
1812,"June 24","Napoleon's Grande Armée crosses the Niemen River and invades Russia."
1812,"July 18","Russia's Patriotic War - Battle of Klyastitsy: Kulnev defeats Oudinot but sustains a mortal wound."
1812,"July 22","Peninsular War - Battle of Salamanca: British forces led by Lord Wellington defeat French troops near Salamanca in Spain."
1812,"October 18","(October 18 - October 20) Second Battle of Polotsk - Russia."
1812,"October 24","Napoleonic Wars - Battle of Maloyaroslavets: An inconclusive encounter between the French vanguard and a Russian force leads Napoleon to decide to retreat along the same line as his advance, with disastrous results."
1813,"March 4","James Madison is sworn in as President of the United States, for his second term."
1813,"April 27","War of 1812 - Battle of York: United States troops raid, destroy, but do not hold the capital of Ontario, York (present day Toronto, Ontario)."
1813,"August 23","Battle of Großbeeren: Napoleon is defeated by Prussia and Sweden."
1813,"August 26","Battle of Katzbach: Napoleon's troops are defeated by Prussia and Russia."
1813,"August 29","(August 29 - August 30) Battle of Kulm: Napoleon's troops are defeated by Russia, Prussia and Austria."
1813,"August 31","After besieging San Sebastian, allied troops of Spain rampage, ransack and burn down the town almost entirely."
1813,"September 6","Battle of Dennewitz: The armies of Napoleon are again defeated by Prussia and Russia."
1813,"October 24","(October 24 - November 5) Persia and Russia sign the Treaty of Gulistan of 1813 at the end of theRusso-Persian War by which Persia (Iran) loses all its territories to the north of Aras River to the Russians."
1813,"November 21","An independent government is restored in the Netherlands."
1813,"circa","Russian troops reach and take Berlin without a fight after the French garrison evacuates the city."
1814,"January 14","Denmark cedes Norway to Sweden in exchange for west Pomerania, as part of the Treaty of Kiel."
1814,"March 10","Napoleon is defeated at the Battle of Laon in France."
1814,"March 27","War of 1812 - Battle of Horseshoe Bend: In northern Alabama, United States forces under General Andrew Jackson defeat the Creek Indians."
1814,"April 6","Emperor Napoleon abdicates; Louis XVIII becomes King of France."
1814,"May 3","The Duke of Provence, the future Louis XVIII of France, returns to Paris."
1814,"May 17","The occupation of Monaco changes from French to Austrian hands."
1814,"May 30","The First Treaty of Paris is signed returning France's borders to their 1792 extent. Napoleon I of France is exiled to Elba on the same day."
1814,"August 7","Pope Pius VII decrees the bull Sollicitudo omnium ecclesiarum reestablishing the Society of Jesus (Jesuits) all over the world, after having approved their survival and existence in Russia."
1814,"circa","Guyana is transferred from the Netherlands to Britain; it is renamed [i]British Guiana[/i]."
1815,"January 3","Austria, Britain, and Bourbon-restored France form a secret defensive alliance treaty against Prussia and Russia."
1815,"March 1","Napoleon returns to France from his banishment on Elba."
1815,"March 15","Joachim Murat, King of Naples declares war on Austria in an attempt to save his throne, starting the Neapolitan War."
1815,"March 16","William I becomes King of the Netherlands."
1815,"April 23","The Second Serbian Uprising against Ottoman rule takes place in Takovo, Serbia. By the end of the year Serbia is acknowledged as a semi-independent state; the ideals of the First Serbian Uprising have thus been temporarily achieved."
1815,"May 3","Battle of Tolentino: Austria defeats the Kingdom of Naples, which quickly ends the Neapolitan War. Joachim Murat, the defeated King of Naples, is forced to flee to Corsica and is later executed."
1815,"June 16","Battle of Ligny: Napoleon beats the Prussians."
1815,"July 8","Louis XVIII returns to Paris, and is 'restored' as King of France (he had declared himself king on 8 June 1795, at the death of his nephew, 10-year-old Louis XVII, and had lived in Westphalia, Verona, Russia, and England)."
1815,"July 17","In France, Napoleon surrenders at Rochefort to British forces."
1815,"October 3","The Chassigny Mars meteorite falls in Chassigny, Haute-Marne, France."
1815,"October 15","Napoleon I of France begins his exile on Saint Helena in the Atlantic Ocean."
1815,"circa","In Britain, use of the pillory is limited to punishment for perjury."
1816,"January 1","Tsar Alexander I of Russia signs an order for the expulsion of the Jesuits from the Russian Empire."
1816,"July 9","Argentina gains independence from Spain."
1816,"circa","The Second Bank of the United States obtains its charter."
1816,"circa","The Ottomans grant Serbia local autonomy."
1817,"March 4","James Monroe succeeds James Madison as President of the United States of America."
1817,"October 31","Emperor Ninko accedes to the throne of Japan."
1818,"February 12","Chile proclaims its independence from Spain."
1818,"April 4","The U.S. Congress adopts the flag of the United States as having 13 red and white stripes and one star for each state (20 stars) with additional stars to be added whenever a new state is added to the Union."
1818,"May 11","Charles XIV of Sweden-Norway is crowned king of Sweden."
1818,"September 7","Carl III of Sweden-Norway is crowned king of Norway, in Trondheim."
1819,"February 15","The United States House of Representatives agrees to the Tallmadge Amendment barring slaves from the new state of Missouri (the opening vote in a controversy that leads to the Missouri Compromise)."
1819,"February 22","Spain cedes Florida to the United States."
1819,"March 6","[i]McCulloch v. Maryland[/i]: The U.S. Supreme Court rules that the Bank of the United States is constitutional."
1819,"circa","By terms of the Adams-Onís Treaty, Spain ceded Florida to the United States in exchange for the American renunciation of any claims on Texas that they might have from the Louisiana Purchase and $5 million."
1820,"January 28","A Russian expedition led by Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen and Mikhail Petrovich Lazarev approaches the Antarctic coast."
1820,"March 3","(March 3 and March 6) Slavery in the United States: The Missouri Compromise becomes law."
1820,"March 9","King Ferdinand VII of Spain accepts the new constitution, beginning the Liberal Triennium (""Trienio Liberal"")."
1820,"May 1","The last hanging, drawing and quartering in Britain is meted out to the Cato Street conspirators for treason (only hanged and beheaded)."
1820,"May 20","John Stuart Mill sets out on his formative boyhood trip to France."
1820,"October 9","Guayaquil declares independence from Spain."
1820,"October 25","(October 25 - November 20) The Congress of Troppau (Opava) is convened between the rulers of Russia, Austria and Prussia."
1821,"March 4","James Monroe is sworn in for his second term as President of the United States."
1821,"March 25","Julian calendar)/April 6 (Gregorian calendar) - Greece declares its liberation from the Ottoman Empire, beginning the Greek War of Independence."
1821,"April 10","Ecumenical Patriarch Patriarch Gregory V of Constantinople is blamed by the Ottoman government for being unable to suppress Greek independence and is hung outside the main gate of the Patriarchal Cathedral immediately after the celebration of Easter."
1821,"June 14","King Badi VII of Sennar surrenders his throne and realm to Ismail Pasha, general of the Ottoman Empire, ending the existence of that Sudanese kingdom."
1821,"June 19","The Philikí Etaireía are decisively defeated by the Ottomans at Dragasani (in Wallachia)."
1821,"June 24","Battle of Carabobo: Simón Bolívar wins Venezuela's independence from Spain."
1821,"July 10","The United States takes possession of its newly bought territory of Florida from Spain."
1821,"July 19","George IV is crowned king of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland."
1821,"July 28","Peru declares independence from Spain."
1821,"August 21","Jarvis Island is discovered by the crew of the Eliza Frances."
1821,"September 15","Guatemala, El Salvador, Honduras, Nicaragua and Costa Rica gain independence from Spain."
1821,"September 27","Mexico gains its independence from Spain (Mexican War of Independence)."
1821,"November 28","Panama declares independence from Spain."
1822,"July 13","Greek War of Independence: Greeks defeat Ottoman forces at Thermopylae."
1822,"circa","Coffee is no longer banned in Sweden."
1822,"circa","Britain repeals the death penalty for over 100 crimes."
1823,"July 1","The congress of Central America declares absolute independence from Spain, Mexico, and any other foreign nation, including North America and a Republican system of government is established."
1824,"August 16","Lafayette visits the United States, departing in September 7, 1825."
1824,"September 16","Charles X succeeds Louis XVIII as King of France."
1824,"circa","The [i]Cimetière du Montparnasse[/i] is established in Paris, France."
1825,"February 9","After no presidential candidate receives a majority of electoral votes, the United States House of Representatives elects John Quincy Adams President of the United States."
1825,"February 12","The Creek cede the last of their lands in Georgia to the United States government, and migrate west."
1825,"March 4","John Quincy Adams succeeds James Monroe as President of the United States."
1825,"April 17","Charles X of France recognizes Haiti, 21 years after it expelled the French following the successful Haitian Revolution, and demands the payment of 150 million gold francs, 30 million of which Haiti must finance through France itself, as down payment."
1825,"August 6","Bolivia gains its independence from Spain as a republic with the instigation of Simón Bolívar."
1825,"December 1","Nicholas I of Russia succeeds his older brother Alexander I."
1825,"circa","Artisans and skilled mechanics receive a right to leave Britain."
1825,"circa","The United States Postal Service started a dead letter office."
1826,"June 14","(June 14 - June 15) The Auspicious Incident: Mahmud II, sultan of Ottoman Empire, crushes the last mutiny of janissaries in Istanbul."
1826,"circa","Britain annexes Assam."
1827,"April 24","Greek War of Independence - Battle of Phaleron: Ottoman troops defeats the Greek rebels."
1827,"July 6","Greek War of Independence: The Treaty of London between France, Britain, and Russia, demands that the Turks agree to an armistice in Greece."
1827,"October 1","Russo-Persian War, 1826-1828: The Russians under Ivan Paskevich storm Yerevan, ending a millennium of Muslim domination in Eastern Armenia."
1827,"October 20","Greek War of Independence - Battle of Navarino: British, French, and Russian naval forces destroy the Turko-Egyptian fleet in Greece."
1828,"January 4","France: The Vicomte de Martignac succeeds the Comte de Villèle as Prime Minister of France."
1828,"February 22","Treaty of Turkmenchay: Russian-Persian peace treaty: Russia captures Eastern Armenia from Persia."
1828,"May 26","Feral child: Kaspar Hauser is discovered in Nuremberg, Germany."
1828,"September 29","Russo-Turkish War, 1828-1829: Varna is taken by the Russian army."
1828,"December 3","U.S. presidential election: Andrew Jackson is elected President of the United States."
1828,"circa","A typhoon kills approximately 10,000 in Kyushu, Japan."
1829,"March 4","Andrew Jackson succeeds John Quincy Adams as the 7th President of the United States of America."
1829,"March 22","Greece receives autonomy from the Ottoman Empire. This effectively ends the Greek War of Independence. Greece continues to seek full independence through diplomatic negotiations with the Empire as well as with Russia, France and Britain."
1829,"July 2","Russo-Turkish War, 1828-1829: Russian Field-Marshal Hans Karl von Diebitsch launches the Transbalkan offensive, which brings the Russian army within 68 km of Istanbul."
1829,"August 8","France: The Prince de Polignac succeeds the Vicomte de Martignac as Prime Minister of France."
1829,"September 16","Russo-Turkish War, 1828-1829: The Treaty of Adrianople gains for Russia some territory at the mouth of the Danube and along the eastern coast of the Black Sea."
1830,"January 12","(January 12 - January 27) Robert Y. Hayne of South Carolina debates the question of states' rights vs. federal authority with Daniel Webster of Massachusetts in the United States Congress."
1830,"February 3","Greece is liberated from the Ottoman forces as the final result of the Greek War of Independence."
1830,"March 12","[i]Craig vs. Missouri[/i]: The United States Supreme Court rules that state loan certificates are unconstitutional."
1830,"July 5","France invades Algeria."
1830,"July 17","Barthélemy Thimonnier is granted a patent (#7454) for a sewing machine in France; it chains stitches at 200/minute."
1830,"July 27","France: The July Revolution begins."
1830,"August 9","France: Louis Philippe becomes King of the French."
1830,"August 13","France: Duc de Broglie becomes Prime Minister."
1830,"September 27","The Belgian Revolution ends by liberating Brussels from the United Kingdom of the Netherlands."
1830,"October 4","The Provisional Government in Brussels declares the creation of the independent state of Belgium, in revolt against the United Kingdom of the Netherlands."
1830,"November 2","France: Jacques Laffitte succeeds the Duc de Broglie as Prime Minister."
1830,"November 29","The Polish insurrection begins in Warsaw against Russian rule."
1830,"circa","10,000 chests of opium are sold in China."
1831,"February 20","Battle of Grochow: Polish rebel forces divide a Russian army."
1831,"March 29","The Great Bosnian uprising against the Ottoman Empire breaks out."
1831,"September 6","(September 6 - September 8) Battle of Warsaw: The Russians take the Polish capital and crush resistance."
1832,"February 12","Cholera breaks out in London, claiming at least 3,000 victims. It spreads to France and North America later this year."
1832,"May 10","The Egyptians, aided by Maronites, seize Acre from the Ottoman Empire after a 7-month siege."
1832,"May 30","Germany: Hambacher Fest, a demonstration for civil liberties and national unity ends with no result."
1832,"June 5","France: June Rebellion, Anti-monarchist riots briefly break out in Paris."
1832,"December 21","Battle of Konya: The Egyptians defeat the main Ottoman army in central Anatolia."
1832,"December 23","The Battle of Antwerp ends with the Netherlands losing the city."
1833,"January 23","Britain retakes the Falkland Islands in the South Atlantic."
1833,"March 4","Andrew Jackson is sworn in for his second term as President of the United States."
1833,"August 20","Future United States President Benjamin Harrison is born in Ohio. From this date until the death of Former U.S. President James Madison on June 28, 1836, there are a total of 19 Presidents of the United States (3 former, 1 current, and 15 known future) living; which is more than any other time period in U.S. history."
1833,"September 29","Three-year old Isabella II becomes Queen of Spain, under the regency of her mother, Maria Cristina of Bourbon-Two Sicilies. Her uncle Don Carlos, Conde de Molina challenges her claim, beginning the First Carlist War."
1834,"January 1","Zollverein: Customs charges are abolished at borders within Germany."
1834,"March 27","Andrew Jackson is censured by the Congress of the United States."
1834,"April 14","The Whig Party is officially named by United States Senator Henry Clay."
1834,"circa","The British East India Company monopoly on China trade ends."
1835,"January 8","The United States public debt contracts to $0 for the only time in history."
1835,"March 2","Ferdinand becomes Emperor of Austria."
1835,"December 29","The Treaty of New Echota is signed between the United States Government and members of the Cherokee Tribe."
1835,"circa","Edward Strutt Abdy publishes his [i]Journal of a Residence and Tour in the United States of North America: From April, 1833, to October 1834[/i]."
1836,"March 6","The Battle of the Alamo ends; 182 Texans are slaughtered by about 5,000 Mexicans. (Numbers from The World Book Encyclopedia, (C) 1970, U.S.A., Library of Congress catalog card number 70-79247)"
1836,"May 7","The settlement of Mayagüez, Puerto Rico is elevated to the royal status of villa by the government of Spain."
1836,"June 15","Arkansas is the 25th state admitted into the United States of America."
1836,"October 2","Charles Darwin returns to Britain aboard the HMS [i]Beagle[/i] with biological data he will later use to develop his theory of evolution."
1836,"December 28","Spain recognizes the independence of Mexico."
1837,"January 26","Michigan is the 26th state admitted to the United States of America."
1837,"March 4","Martin Van Buren succeeds Andrew Jackson as President of the United States."
1837,"circa","The Berlin Foundry Cup acquired for the Antikensammlung at Berlin, Germany."
1838,"circa","40,000 chests of opium are sold in China."
1839,"March 7","Baltimore City College, the third public high school in the United States, is established in Baltimore, Maryland."
1839,"July 1","Abd-ul-Mejid (1839-1861) succeeds Mahmud II (1808-1839) as Ottoman Emperor."
1839,"August 23","British forces seize Hong Kong as a base, as it prepares to wage war against Qing China. The ensuing 3-year conflict becomes known as the First Opium War."
1839,"August 31","The First Carlist war (Spain) ends with the Convenio de Vergara, also known as the Abrazo de Vergara (""the embrace in Vergara""; Bergara in Basque), between liberal general Baldomero Espartero, Count of Luchana and Carlist General Rafael Maroto."
1839,"November 4","The Newport Rising is the last large-scale armed rebellion against authority in mainland Britain."
1839,"circa","Half of the Limburg province of Belgium is added to the Netherlands (since 1839 there is a Belgian Limburg and Dutch Limburg)."
1839,"circa","The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland, backed by the Russian Empire and the Austrian Empire, compels July Monarchy France to abandon Muhammad Ali of Egypt, and it forces him to return Syria and Arabia to the Ottoman Empire."
1839,"circa","Tanzimat starts in the Ottoman Empire."
1840,"January 19","Captain Charles Wilkes circumnavigates Antarctica, claiming what becomes known as Wilkes Land for the United States."
1840,"March 1","Adolphe Thiers becomes prime minister of France."
1840,"July 15","The Austrian Empire, the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland, the Kingdom of Prussia, and the Russian Empire sign the London Treaty with the Sublime Porte, ruler of the Ottoman Empire."
1840,"September 10","Ottoman and British troops bombard Beirut and land troops on the coast to pressure Egyptian Muhammad Ali to retreat from the country."
1840,"September 30","The frigate [i]Belle-Poule[/i] arrives in Cherbourg, bringing back the remains of Napoléon from Saint Helena to France. He is buried in the Invalides."
1840,"October 7","Willem II becomes King of the Netherlands."
1840,"December 7","David Livingstone leaves Britain for Africa."
1841,"January 20","Charles Elliot of Britain and Qishan of the Qing Dynasty agree to the Convention of Chuenpee."
1841,"March 4","Martin Van Buren is succeeded as President of the United States by William Henry Harrison."
1841,"March 9","[i]Amistad[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules in the case that the Africans who seized control of the ship had been taken into slavery illegally."
1841,"August 16","U.S. President John Tyler vetoes a bill which called for the re-establishment of the Second Bank of the United States. Enraged Whig Party members riot outside the White House in the most violent demonstration on White House grounds in U.S. history."
1841,"September 24","The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland annexes Sarawak from Brunei; James Brooke is appointed rajah."
1842,"March 9","Giuseppe Verdi's third opera [i]Nabucco[/i] premieres in Milan; its success establishes Verdi as one of Italy's foremost opera writers."
1842,"August 9","The Webster-Ashburton Treaty is signed, establishing the United States-Canada border east of the Rocky Mountains."
1843,"July 19","The [i]SS Great Britain[/i] is launched from Bristol."
1843,"November 28","[i]Ka La Ku'oko'a[/i] (Hawaiian Independence Day): The Kingdom of Hawai`i is officially recognized by the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and July Monarchy France as an independent nation."
1844,"February 28","A gun on the USS [i]Princeton[/i] explodes while the boat is on a Potomac River cruise, killing 2 United States Cabinet members and several others."
1844,"March 8","King Oscar I ascends to the throne of Sweden-Norway."
1844,"August 28","Friedrich Engels and Karl Marx meet in Paris, France."
1845,"February 28","The United States Congress approves the annexation of Texas."
1845,"March 1","President John Tyler signs a bill authorizing the United States to annex the Republic of Texas."
1845,"March 4","James K. Polk succeeds John Tyler as President of the United States."
1845,"October 10","In Annapolis, Maryland, the Naval School (later renamed the United States Naval Academy) opens with 50 midshipmen students and 7 professors."
1845,"October 13","A majority of voters in the Republic of Texas approve a proposed constitution, that if accepted by the United States Congress, will make Texas a U.S. state."
1845,"December 2","Manifest Destiny: U.S. President James K. Polk announces to Congress that the Monroe Doctrine should be strictly enforced and that the United States should aggressively expand into the West."
1845,"December 27","American journalist John L. O'Sullivan claims in a newspaper article that the United States have a [i]""Manifest Destiny""[/i] to expand their borders. It's the second time he uses the term and it will have a huge influence on the American imperialistic movement of the 19th century."
1845,"circa","Ephraim Bee reveals that the Emperor of China has given him a special dispensation; that he has entrusted him with certain sacred and mysterious rituals through Caleb Cushing, the U.S. Commissioner to China, to ""extend the work and influence of the Ancient and Honorable Order of E Clampus Vitus"" in the new world."
1845,"circa","In the [i]United States Magazine and Democratic Review[/i] editor John L. O'Sullivan declares that foreign powers are trying to prevent American annexation of Texas in order to impede ""the fullfillment of our manifest destiny to overspread the continent allotted by Providence for the free development of our yearly multiplying millions""."
1846,"January 5","The United States House of Representatives votes to stop sharing the Oregon Territory with the United Kingdom."
1846,"March 10","Prince Osahito, fourth son of deceased Emperor Ninko of Japan, becomes Emperor Komei."
1846,"May 13","Mexican-American War: The United States declares war on Mexico."
1846,"June 15","The Oregon Treaty establishes the 49th parallel as the border between the United States and Canada, from the Rocky Mountains to the Strait of Juan de Fuca."
1846,"September 19","The Virgin Mary is said to have appeared to two children in La Salette, France."
1847,"March 9","Mexican-American War: United States forces under General Winfield Scott invade Mexico near Veracruz."
1847,"March 14","Verdi's [i]Macbeth (opera)[/i] premieres at Teatro della Pergola in Florence, Italy."
1847,"March 29","Mexican-American War: United States forces led by General Winfield Scott take Veracruz after a siege."
1847,"circa","The Ottoman Empire cedes Abadan Island to the Persian Empire."
1848,"February 2","Mexican-American War: The Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo is signed, ending the war and ceding to the United States virtually all of what is today the southwest of that country."
1848,"June 17","The Austrian army bombards Prague and crushes a working class revolt."
1848,"August 19","California Gold Rush: The [i]New York Herald[/i] breaks the news to the East Coast of the United States that there is a gold rush in California (although the rush started in January)."
1848,"November 4","France ratifies a new constitution. The Second Republic of France is set up, ending the state of temporary government lasting since the Revolution of 1848."
1848,"December 2","Emperor Ferdinand I of Austria abdicates in favor of his nephew, Franz Josef I."
1848,"circa","Prince Klemens von Metternich ends his work as Austrian foreign minister."
1849,"January 1","In Milan, anti-Austrian activists organize a smoking boycott in protest of the Austrian monopoly on tobacco. Protests erupt into brief riots."
1849,"January 12","Palermo, Sicily rises up against Austrian troops."
1849,"February 28","Regular steamboat service from the west to the east coast of the United States begins with the arrival of the SS [i]California[/i] in San Francisco Bay. The [i]California[/i] leaves New York Harbor on October 6, 1848, rounds Cape Horn at the tip of South America, and arrives at San Francisco, California after the 4 month 21 day journey."
1849,"March 3","Minnesota becomes a United States territory."
1849,"March 3","The United States Department of the Interior is established."
1849,"March 4","Zachary Taylor refuses to be sworn in office on a Sabbath (Sunday). Urban legend holds that David Rice Atchison, President pro tempore of the United States Senate was President [i]de jure[/i] for a single day."
1849,"March 5","Zachary Taylor, the 12th President of the United States of America, takes his oath of office."
1849,"April 1","After 10 days, the insurrection in Brescia is ended by Austrian troops."
1849,"April 14","Hungary declares independence from Austria."
1849,"July 6","The Danish Army beats the Prussian army at Fredericia, Jutland, thereby putting an end to the Prussian/Danish War until 1864."
1849,"August 8","Austria crushes the Hungarian rebellion with Russian aid."
1849,"August 24","Venice surrenders to Austrian troops after a 4-month siege."
1849,"November 16","A Russian court sentences Fyodor Dostoevsky to death for anti-government activities linked to a radical intellectual group, but his execution is cancelled at the last minute."
1850,"circa","World Population: ~1,250,000,000."
1850,"March 7","United States Senator Daniel Webster gives his ""Seventh of March"" speech in which he endorses the Compromise of 1850 in order to prevent a possible civil war."
1850,"April 19","Clayton-Bulwer Treaty is signed by the United States and Great Britain, allowing both countries to share Nicaragua and not claim complete control over the proposed Nicaragua Canal."
1850,"May 7","The Brigantine [i]USS Advance[/i] is loaned to the United States Navy."
1850,"June 1","The postage stamp issues of Austria begin with a series of imperforate typographed stamps featuring the coat of arms."
1850,"July 9","Vice President Millard Fillmore becomes the 13th President of the United States following the death of President Taylor."
1850,"September 9","The New Mexico Territory is organized by order of the United States Congress."
1850,"September 18","The Fugitive Slave Law is passed by the United States Congress."
1850,"November 29","The treaty called Punctation of Olmütz is signed in Olomouc. It means diplomatic capitulation of Prussia to the Austrian Empire, which takes over the leadership of the German Confederation."
1850,"circa","France begins to transport colonists to Algeria."
1851,"March 1","Victor Hugo uses the phrase [i]United States of Europe[/i] in a speech to the French National Assembly."
1851,"July 1","Serial poisoner Hélène Jégado is arrested in Rennes, France."
1851,"July 29","Annibale de Gasparis, in Naples, Italy discovers asteroid [i]15 Eunomia[/i]."
1851,"December 2","Louis Napoleon, president of France, dissolves the French National Assembly and declares a new constitution to extend his term. A year later he declares himself as Emperor Napoleon III, ending the Second Republic."
1851,"circa","The population of Britain reaches 21 million."
1852,"November 11","The new Palace of Westminster opens in Britain."
1853,"March 4","Franklin Pierce succeeds Millard Fillmore as the 14th President of the United States."
1853,"October 4","(October 4 - October 5) Crimean War: The Ottoman Empire starts war with Russia]."
1853,"October 28","Crimean War: The Ottoman army crosses the Danube into Vidin/Kalafat in Wallachia."
1853,"November 4","Crimean War - Battle of Oltenitza: Turkish victory over Russians."
1853,"November 30","Crimean War - Battle of Sinop: The Russian fleet destroys the Turkish fleet."
1853,"December 30","Gadsden Purchase: The United States buys land from Mexico to facilitate railroad building in the Southwest."
1853,"circa","Iesada succeeds Ieoshi as Japanese Shogun."
1853,"circa","The Late Tokugawa shogunate (the last part of the Edo period in Japan) begins."
1854,"February 14","Texas is linked by telegraph with the rest of the United States, when a connection between New Orleans and Marshall, Texas is completed."
1854,"February 27","Britain sends Russia an ultimatum to withdraw from two Ottoman provinces it had conquered, Moldavia and Wallachia."
1854,"March 11","A Royal Navy fleet sails from Britain under Vice Admiral Sir Charles Napier."
1854,"March 27","Crimean War: The United Kingdom declares war on Russia."
1854,"March 28","France declares war on Russia."
1854,"March 31","Commodore Matthew Perry of the U.S. Navy signs the Treaty/Convention of Kanagawa with the Japanese government (the Tokugawa Shogunate), opening the ports of Shimoda and Hakodate to American trade."
1854,"April 16","The United States packet ship Powhattan is wrecked off the New Jersey shore with more than 200 + victims."
1854,"May 27","Taiping Rebellion: United States diplomatic minister Robert McLane arrives at the Heavenly Capital aboard the American warship USS Susquehanna."
1854,"August 16","Russian troops in the island of Bomarsund in Åland surrender to French-British troops."
1854,"November 5","Crimean War - Battle of Inkerman: The Russians are defeated."
1855,"March 3","Alexander II of Russia ascends the Russian throne, upon the death of his father Nicholas I."
1855,"July 1","Quinault Treaty signed, Quinault and Quileute cede their land to the United States."
1855,"circa","Stamp duty is removed from newspapers in Britain, creating mass market media in the United Kingdom."
1855,"circa","Palm oil sales from West Africa to Britain reach 40,000 tons."
1856,"May 1","Isabela Province is created in the Philippines in honor of Queen Isabela II of Spain."
1856,"May 22","Congressman Preston Brooks of South Carolina beats Senator Charles Sumner with a cane in the hall of the United States Senate, for a speech Sumner had made attacking Southerners who sympathized with the pro-slavery violence in Kansas (""Bleeding Kansas""). Sumner is unable to return to duty for 3 years while he recovered; Brooks becomes a hero across the South."
1856,"October 8","The Second Opium War between several western powers and China begins with the [i]Arrow Incident[/i] on the Pearl River."
1856,"November 1","Anglo-Persian War: War is declared between Great Britain and Persia."
1856,"November 4","U.S. presidential election, 1856: Democrat James Buchanan defeats former President Millard Fillmore, representing a coalition of ""Know-Nothings"" and Whigs, and John C. Frémont of the fledgling Republican Party, to become the 15th President of the United States."
1856,"November 17","American Old West: On the Sonoita River in present-day southern Arizona, the United States Army establishes Fort Buchanan in order to help control new land acquired in the Gadsden Purchase."
1857,"March 3","France and the United Kingdom formally declare war on China in the Second Opium War."
1857,"March 4","James Buchanan succeeds Franklin Pierce as President of the United States."
1857,"March 6","[i]Dred Scott v. Sanford[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that Blacks are not citizens and slaves can not sue for freedom, driving the country further towards the American Civil War (the ruling is not overturned until the 14th Amendment in 1868)."
1857,"March 21","An earthquake in Tokyo, Japan kills over 100,000."
1857,"June 6","Sophia of Nassau marries the future King Oscar II of Sweden-Norway."
1857,"December 16","An earthquake with an estimated magnitude of 6.9 kills 11,000 people in Naples, Italy."
1857,"December 20","Emperor Franz Joseph I of Austria issues a decree, [i]Es ist Mein Wille[/i], which leads to the demolition of the city walls of Vienna, allowing the construction of the Ringstraße."
1857,"circa","Divorce without parliamentary approval becomes legal in Britain."
1858,"January 14","Felice Orsini and his accomplices fail to assassinate Napoleon III in Paris but their bombs kill 8 and wound 142 people. Because of the involvement of French émigrés living in Britain, there is a brief anti-British feeling in France, but the emperor refuses to support it. Orsini is executed by guillotine on March 13 of the same year."
1858,"January 25","The [i]Wedding March[/i] by Felix Mendelssohn becomes a popular wedding recessional after it is played on this day at the marriage of Queen Victoria's daughter Victoria, ""Vicky,"" the Princess Royal to Prince Friedrich of Prussia in St. James's Palace, London."
1858,"April 28","(April 28 - May 1) Battle of Grahovac (between Ottoman and Montenegrin forces)"
1858,"July 29","The United States and Japan sign the Harris Treaty."
1858,"circa","Feudalism and serfdom in Bulgaria are abolished in the Ottoman Empire (practically in 1880)."
1858,"circa","William I of Prussia becomes a regent."
1858,"circa","Abraham Lincoln accepts the Republican Party (United States) nomination for a seat in the US Senate."
1859,"January 28","The city of Olympia is incorporated in the Territory of Washington in the United States of America."
1859,"March 9","The army of Piedmont-Sardinia mobilizes against Austria, beginning the crisis which will lead to the Austro-Sardinian War."
1859,"April 26","Austro-Sardinian War: Giuseppe Garibaldi's Hunters of the Alps confront Austrian forces led by Field Marshal-Lieutenant Carl Baron Urban at Varese."
1859,"April 29","Austrian troops begin to cross the Ticino River to Piedmont."
1859,"May 30","Battle of Palestro: The Sardinians defeat the Austrian army."
1859,"June 4","Austro-Sardinian War - Battle of Magenta: The French and Sardinians defeat the Austrians."
1859,"July 8","Charles XV succeeds his father Oscar I of Sweden and Norway (as Charles IV)."
1859,"July 8","An armistice is declared between Austria and others."
1859,"July 11","By the preliminary treaty signed at Villafranca, Italy, Lombardy is ceded to the French (who immediately cede it to Sardinia), while the Austrians keep Venetia and the French promise to restore the Central Italian rulers expelled in the course of the war. This brings the Austro-Sardinian War effectively to a close."
1859,"circa","The island of Timor is divided between Portugal and the Netherlands."
1860,"March 22","The Grand Duchy of Tuscany is annexed to the newly formed Kingdom of Italy."
1860,"May 9","The U.S. Constitutional Union Party holds its convention and nominates John Bell for President of the United States."
1860,"July 11","Mutsuhito (the future Emperor Meiji) becomes Crown Prince of Japan."
1860,"September 3","(September 3 - September 5) The First International Chemistry Congress is held in Karlsruhe, Germany."
1860,"October 5","Austria, Britain, France, Prussia and the Ottoman Empire form a commission to investigate the causes of the massacres of Maronite Christians, committed by Druzes in Lebanon earlier in the year."
1860,"circa","Victor Emmanuel, King of Sardinia seizes the whole of the Papal States except Rome (Vatican City) and unites Italy."
1860,"circa","Britain produces 20% of the entire world's output of industrial goods."
1860,"circa","The Russian Empire has c. 1,250 miles (2,010 km) of railroads."
1860,"circa","China agrees in an unequal treaty imposed on it to allow missionaries to proselytize throughout the country."
1861,"January 21","American Civil War: Jefferson Davis resigns from the United States Senate."
1861,"February 18","Victor Emmanuel of Piedmont-Sardinia becomes King of Italy. See: Italian unification."
1861,"February 27","Russian troops fire upon a crowd in Warsaw protesting Russian rule over Poland, killing 5 protesters."
1861,"February 28","Colorado is organized as a United States territory."
1861,"March 2","Nevada is organized as a United States territory."
1861,"February 19","O.S.) - Serfdom is abolished in Imperial Russia."
1861,"March 17","The Kingdom of Italy is proclaimed, with Victor Emmanuel II as its king."
1861,"April 20","American Civil War: Robert E. Lee resigns his commission in the United States Army in order to command the forces of the state of Virginia."
1861,"May 14","The Canellas meteorite, an 859 gram chondrite type meteorite, strikes Earth near Barcelona, Spain."
1861,"June 9","Lebanon is separated from Syrian administration and reunited under an Ottoman governor with the approval of the European powers."
1861,"July 1","Battle of Shanghai (1861), China civil war."
1861,"July 2","Ivan Kasatkin lands on Hakodate and introduces the Eastern Orthodox Church into Japan."
1861,"August 27","Martin Doyle's is the last execution in Britain for attempted murder."
1861,"October 31","American Civil War: Citing failing health, Union General Winfield Scott resigns as Commander of the United States Army."
1861,"circa","In Britain, the death penalty is limited to murder, high treason, espionage, piracy with violence and acts of arson perpetrated upon docks or ammunition depots."
1862,"January 1","Britain annexes Lagos Island in modern-day Nigeria."
1862,"February 20","Ángel de Saavedra, Duke of Rivas, named director of Spain's La Real Academia Española de la Lengua ( Royal Academy of Spanish Language )."
1862,"April 1","The Spanish and the British end their alliance with France in the French intervention in Mexico.."
1862,"May 15","U.S. President Abraham Lincoln signs a bill into law creating the United States Bureau of Agriculture (later renamed USDA)."
1862,"September 22","Otto von Bismarck becomes prime minister of Prussia."
1862,"September 29","Bismarck delivers his [i]Blood and Iron[/i] speech to the Prussian Assembly."
1862,"circa","The Prussian Assembly rejects the military budget."
1863,"January 4","The New Apostolic Church, a Christian and chiliastic church, established in Hamburg, Germany."
1863,"January 8","Ground is broken in Sacramento, CA on the construction of the First Transcontinental Railroad in the United States."
1863,"January 22","The January Uprising breaks out in Poland, Lithuania and Belarus. The aim of the national movement is to liberate the Polish-Lithuanian-Ruthenian Commonwealth from Russian occupation."
1863,"February 24","Arizona is organized as a United States territory."
1863,"July 13","American Civil War - (New York Draft Riots): In New York City, opponents of conscription begin 3 days of violent rioting, which would later be regarded as the worst in the history of the United States."
1863,"October 5","The Brooklyn, Bath and Coney Island Rail Road starts operations in Brooklyn, New York; this is now the oldest right-of-way on the New York City Subway, the largest rapid transit system in the United States and one of the largest in the world."
1864,"January 16","Denmark rejects a Prussian-Austrian ultimatum to repeal the Danish Constitution."
1864,"February 1","Danish-Prussian War (Second war of Schleswig): 57,000 Austrian and Prussian troops cross the Eider River into Denmark."
1864,"March 1","Alejandro Mon Menéndez takes office as Prime Minister of Spain."
1864,"April 18","Danish-Prussian War (Second War of Schleswig) - Battle of Dybbøl: The Prussian army fielding 10,000 men defeats the Danish defending army of 9,200 at Dybbøl Mill, after an artillery bombardment from April 7 to April 18."
1864,"May 21","Circassian leaders sign Russian loyalty oaths, ending the Russian-Circassian War."
1864,"May 28","Montana is organized as a United States territory out of parts of Washington Territory and Dakota Territory, and is signed into law by President Abraham Lincoln."
1864,"October 30","The Second war of Schleswig is concluded. Denmark renounces all claim to Schleswig, Holstein and Lauenburg, which come under Prussian and Austrian administration."
1864,"November 20","The Judicial reform of Alexander II is launched in Imperial Russia."
1865,"January 13","American Civil War: The Second Battle of Fort Fisher begins when United States forces launch a major amphibious assault against the Confederate stronghold of Fort Fisher, North Carolina."
1865,"January 15","American Civil War: United States forces capture Fort Fisher."
1865,"April 15","Vice President Andrew Johnson becomes the 17th President of the United States, upon the death of President Abraham Lincoln."
1865,"December 18","The Thirteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution (which forever abolishes slavery) is declared ratified by 3/4 of the states of the United States."
1866,"January 6","Ottoman troops clash with men of a Maronite leader Karam in St. Doumit in Lebanon; the Ottomans are defeated."
1866,"April 4","Alexander II of Russia narrowly escapes an assassination attempt in the city of Kiev."
1866,"June 14","The Austro-Prussian War begins, when the Austrians and most of the medium German states declare war on Prussia."
1866,"June 20","The Kingdom of Italy declares war on Austria."
1866,"June 27","(June 27 - June 29) Battle of Langensalza: The Prussians defeat the Hanoverian army."
1866,"July 3","Battle of Königgratz: the Prussian army under King Wilhelm and Helmuth von Moltke defeats the Austrian army of Lajos Benedek, leading to a decisive Prussian victory in the Austro-Prussian War."
1866,"July 20","Naval Battle of Lissa: The Austrian fleet under Wilhelm von Tegetthoff defeats the Italian fleet of Carlo di Persano."
1866,"August 23","The Treaty of Prague ends the Austro-Prussian War."
1866,"October 12","The Treaty of Vienna ends the war between Austria and Italy; it formalizes the annexation of Venetia by Italy."
1866,"circa","In Sweden, the Riksdag of the Estates is replaced by an elected 2-chamber assembly, the Riksdag."
1866,"circa","Alfred Nobel invents dynamite in Germany."
1867,"February 3","Shogun Tokugawa Yoshinobu abdicates, and the late Emperor Komei's son, Prince Mutsuhito becomes Emperor Meiji of Japan, ending the Late Tokugawa shogunate."
1867,"February 19","Battle of inlon river in Hubei China."
1867,"March 30","Alaska is purchased for $7.2 million from Alexander II of Russia, about 2 cent/acre ($4.19/km²), by United States Secretary of State William H. Seward. The news media call this ""Seward's Folly""."
1867,"September 2","Emperor Meiji of Japan marries Empress Shoken (née Masako Ichijo). The Empress consort is thereafter known as [i]Lady Haruko[/i]."
1867,"September 30","The United States takes control of Midway Island."
1867,"circa","The Edo period gives way to the Meiji period in Japanese history."
1867,"circa","Otto von Bismarck organises a North German Confederation under the leadership of Prussia."
1867,"circa","The Prohibition National Committee is formed in the United States."
1867,"circa","The modern rose was born, with the introduction of Rosa 'La France' by Jean-Baptiste Guillot (1803-1882)."
1868,"March 5","A court of impeachment is organized in the United States Senate to hear charges against President Andrew Johnson."
1868,"May 16","President Andrew Johnson is acquitted during his impeachment trial, by one vote in the United States Senate."
1868,"May 26","Fenian bomber Michael Barrett becomes the last person publicly hanged in Britain."
1868,"July 25","Wyoming becomes a United States territory."
1868,"July 28","The 14th Amendment to the United States Constitution is adopted, guaranteeing African Americans full citizenship and all persons in the United States due process of law."
1868,"August 22","The Yangzhou riot in China targets a station of the China Inland Mission, and nearly leads to war between Britain and China."
1868,"November 27","Indian Wars - Battle of Washita River: In the early morning, United States Army Lieutenant Colonel George Armstrong Custer leads an attack on a band of Cheyenne living on reservation land with Chief Black Kettle, killing 103 Cheyenne."
1868,"circa","The Académie Julian, a major art school in Paris, France that admits women, is established."
1868,"circa","Herrenhauser Brewery is established in Hanover, Germany."
1868,"circa","Political leaders behind the Japanese emperor issue in his name a 5-point charter that promises representative government."
1868,"circa","The population of Japan reaches c. 30 million."
1868,"circa","Croatian-Hungarian Agreement (Croatian: [i]Hrvatsko-ugarska nagodba[/i], Hungarian: [i]Horvát-magyar kiegyezés[/i], German: [i]Kroatisch-Ungarischer Ausgleich[/i]) was a pact signed in 1868, that governed Croatia's political status in the Hungarian-ruled part of Austria-Hungary. It had lasted until the end of World War I."
1869,"March 4","Ulysses S. Grant succeeds Andrew Johnson as the 18th President of the United States of America."
1869,"March 6","Mendeleev makes a formal presentation to the Russian Chemical Society."
1869,"May 4","(May 4 - May 10) Naval Battle of Hakodate in Japan: The Imperial Japanese Navy defeats the Tokugawa shogunate."
1869,"September 24","The Fisk-Gould Scandal (also known as Black Friday) causes a financial panic in the United States."
1869,"circa","The Meiji Emperor of Japan accepts the surrender of the four most powerful clans - Choshu, Tosa, Hizen, and Satsuma - and reappoints the clan chiefs as Provincial Governors on reduced revenues."
1869,"circa","The opposition, consisting of republicans, monarchists and liberals, polls almost 45% of the vote in France."
1869,"circa","Marcus Jastrow arrives in the United States to become rabbi of Congregation Rodeph Shalom in Philadelphia."
1870,"January 6","The Musikverein, Vienna is inaugurated in Austria-Hungary."
1870,"February 3","The 15th Amendment to the United States Constitution, guaranteeing African-Americans the right to vote, is passed."
1870,"February 28","The Bulgarian Exarchate is established by decree of Sultan Abd-ul-Aziz of the Ottoman Empire."
1870,"March 30","The 15th Amendment to the United States Constitution, giving blacks the right to vote, is ratified."
1870,"June 22","The office of the Solicitor General of the United States is set up to supervise and conduct government litigation in the United States Supreme Court."
1870,"June 22","The U.S. Congress creates the United States Department of Justice."
1870,"June 26","Christmas is declared a federal holiday in the United States."
1870,"July 13","The [i]Ems Dispatch[/i] serves as a reason for a war between Prussia and France."
1870,"July 19","Franco-Prussian War: France declares war on Prussia."
1870,"September 4","Emperor Napoleon III of France is deposed and the Third Republic is declared. Empress Eugenie flees to England with her children."
1870,"October 2","A plebiscite held in Rome supports, by 133,681 votes to 1,507, the annexation of the city by Italy."
1870,"October 6","Rome becomes the capital of unified Italy."
1870,"November 16","The Spanish Cortes Generales proclaims Amadeo de Saboya as King Amadeus I of Spain."
1870,"December 30","Juan Prim, prime minister of Spain, is assassinated."
1871,"January 2","Amadeus I becomes King of Spain."
1871,"January 21","Giuseppe Garibaldi's group of French and Italian volunteer troops in support of the French Third Republic win a battle against the Prussians in Dijon."
1871,"May 10","France surrenders, ending the Franco-Prussian War."
1871,"August 29","The abolition of the han system is carried out in Japan."
1871,"October 8","Four major fires break out on the shores of Lake Michigan in Chicago, Illinois, Peshtigo, Wisconsin, Holland, Michigan, and Manistee, Michigan. The Great Chicago Fire is the most famous of these, leaving nearly 100,000 people homeless, although the Peshtigo Fire kills as many as 2,500 people, making it the deadliest fire in United States history."
1871,"October 27","The Comte de Chambord refuses to be crowned ""King Henry V of France"" until France abandons its tricolor and returns to the old Bourbon flag."
1871,"circa","The provinces of Alsace and Lorraine are transferred from France to Germany."
1871,"circa","Japan forms its own nationwide police force based on the French model."
1871,"circa","The Ameican minister to China takes five warships to attempt to ""open up"" Korea, but his forces leave after exchanges of fire result in 250 Koreans dying and the Korean government still unwilling to make any concessions."
1871,"circa","Virginia adopts a new Constitution, taking into account of, among other things, all of the counties that had left Virginia in 1863 to form the new non-slave state of West Virginia and became a new state of the United States, with all of the rights and privileges thereof. This exiting of one state to form a new one has never been done otherwise without the permission / consent of the Legislature of the one involved, as was done in the cases of Vermont, Kentucky, and Maine."
1872,"March 11","Work begins erecting the Seven Sisters Colliery, South Wales, located on one of the richest coal sources in Britain."
1872,"November 27","A meteor shower display is seen over France."
1872,"circa","A conscription law, modeled on the French version, is issued in Japan."
1872,"circa","Universal public schools are called for in Japan."
1873,"January 1","Japan adopts the Gregorian calendar."
1873,"March 4","President of the United States Ulysses S. Grant begins his second term."
1873,"March 29","The Rio Tinto Company is formed in Spain, following the February 17 purchase of the Rio Tinto mine from the Spanish government by a British investment group."
1873,"May 9","Battle of Montejurra: Navarra, Spain was fought during the Third Carlist War."
1873,"May 20","Levi Strauss and Jacob Davis received United States patent#139121 for using copper rivets to strengthen the pockets of denim work pants. Levi Strauss & Co. began manufacturing the famous Levi's brand of jeans, using fabric from the Amoskeag Manufacturing Company in Manchester, New Hampshire."
1873,"May 28","The city of Khiva falls to Imperial Russian forces, under the command of General Konstantin Petrovich Von Kaufman."
1873,"August 12","A peace treaty is signed between Imperial Russia and the Khanate of Khiva, making the khanate a Russian protectorate."
1873,"September 16","German troops leave France upon completion of payment of indemnity for the Franco-Prussian War."
1873,"circa","Britain puts pressure on Sultan Barghash Sayyid, who closes slave markets in Zanzibar."
1873,"circa","League of the Three Emperors is created. It links the conservative monarchs of Austria-Hungary, Germany and Russia in an alliance against radical movements."
1874,"January 23","Duke of Edinburgh, the second son of Queen Victoria, marries Grand Duchess Marie Alexandrovna of Russia, the only daughter of Emperor Alexander III of Russia."
1874,"March 18","Hawaii signs a treaty with the United States granting exclusive trading rights."
1874,"June 25","Battle of Monte Muru: Third Carlist War of Spain."
1874,"November 25","The United States Greenback Party is established as a political party, made primarily of farmers financially hurt by the Panic of 1873."
1875,"January 12","Kwang-su becomes emperor of China."
1875,"May 7","The Treaty of Saint Petersburg (1875) is signed between Japan and Russia."
1875,"November 9","Indian Wars: In Washington, D.C., Indian Inspector E.C. Watkins issues a report stating that hundreds of Sioux and Cheyenne associated with Sitting Bull and Crazy Horse are hostile to the United States (the Battle of the Little Bighorn is fought in Montana the next year)."
1875,"December 4","Notorious New York City politician Boss Tweed escapes from prison and flees to Cuba, then to Spain."
1875,"circa","The Ottoman state declares partial bankruptcy and places its finances in the hands of European creditors."
1875,"circa","Widespread nationalist rebellion in the Ottoman Empire has resulted in Turkish repression, Russian intervention and Great Power tensions."
1876,"February 27","The Third Carlist War (Spain):The Carlist forces did not succeed, and the promises were never fulfilled. The Carlist pretender (Carlos María de Borbón y Austria-Este-""duque de Madrid"" y ""conde de la Alcarria"") AKA:Carlos VII went into exile in France bringing the conflict to an end after four years of war."
1876,"May 11","(May 11 - May 12) Berlin Memorandum: Germany, Russia and Austria-Hungary propose an armistice between Turkey and its insurgents."
1876,"July 1","Serbia declares war on Turkey."
1876,"July 2","Montenegro declares war on Turkey."
1876,"July 4","The United States celebrates its centennial."
1876,"July 8","Reichstadt Agreement: Russia and Austria-Hungary agree on partitioning the Balkan peninsula."
1876,"August 31","Murat V, sultan of the Ottoman Empire is deposed and succeeded by his brother Abdul Hamid II."
1876,"November 23","Corrupt Tammany Hall leader William Marcy Tweed (better known as Boss Tweed) is delivered to authorities in New York City after being captured in Spain."
1876,"circa","Samurai are banned from carrying swords in Japan."
1876,"circa","Japan brings a fleet to Inchon, the port of Seoul. The Japanese force the Korean government to sign an unequal treaty, open 3 ports to Japanese trade and cease considering itself a tributary of China. On China's urging Korea also signs treaties with the European powers in effort to counterbalance Japan."
1876,"circa","Lars Magnus Ericsson and Carl Johan Andersson start a small mechanical workshop in Stockholm, Sweden, dealing with telegraphy equipment, which grows into the worldwide company [i]Ericsson[/i]."
1876,"circa","Tanzimat ends in the Ottoman Empire."
1877,"January 8","Indian Wars - Battle of Wolf Mountain: Crazy Horse and his warriors fight their last battle with the United States Cavalry in Montana."
1877,"January 20","The Conference of Constantinople ends with Ottoman Turkey rejecting proposals of internal reform and Balkan provisions."
1877,"March 4","Rutherford B. Hayes becomes President of the United States, succeeding Ulysses S. Grant."
1877,"April 24","Russo-Turkish War, 1877-1878: Russia declares war on the Ottoman Empire."
1877,"May 5","Indian Wars: Sitting Bull leads his band of Lakota into Canada to avoid harassment by the United States Army under Colonel Nelson Miles."
1877,"May 6","Realizing that his people are weakened by cold and hunger, Chief Crazy Horse of the Oglala Sioux surrenders to United States troops in Nebraska."
1877,"May 16","The May 16, 1877 political crisis occurs in France."
1877,"May 21","Romania declares itself independent from the Ottoman Empire (recognized in 1878 after the end of the Romanian independence war)."
1877,"July 10","The then villa of Mayagüez, Puerto Rico formally receives its city charter from the Royal Crown of Spain."
1877,"October 10","Following the recovery of Lieutenant-Colonel George Armstrong Custer's body from where he fell during the Battle of Little Big Horn the previous year, Custer is given a funeral with full military honors and is laid to rest at the United States Military Academy at West Point, New York."
1877,"December 14","Serbia restates its previous declaration of war against Turkey."
1877,"circa","After the defeat of the Dungan revolt in China, several thousand refugees cross the Tian Shan to settle in the Russian Empire, thus starting the future ""Soviet Dungan"" ethnic group."
1877,"circa","A professionally led army of draftees crushes a major rebellion by feudal elements protesting the loss of their privileges in Japan."
1877,"circa","Aceh War, Netherlands colonial war in Aceh (aka Thirty Years War) (1873-1904)"
1877,"circa","War between Russia and the Ottoman Empire (Russo-Turkish War, 1877-1878), leading to the formation of Bulgaria in 1878."
1878,"January 5","Battle of Shipka Pass IV: Russian and Bulgarian forces defeat the Ottoman Empire."
1878,"January 9","Humbert I becomes King of Italy."
1878,"January 17","Battle of Plovdiv: Russian troops defeat the Turks."
1878,"January 31","Turkey agrees to an armistice at Adrianople."
1878,"February 2","Greece declares war on Turkey."
1878,"February 8","The British fleet enters Turkish waters and anchors off Istanbul; Russia threatens to occupy Istanbul but does not carry out the threat."
1878,"February 24","Anti-Russian demonstrations occur in Hyde Park, London."
1878,"March 3","Bulgaria regains its independence from the Ottoman Empire."
1878,"March 25","Russia rejects a British proposal to lay the San Stefano treaty before a European congress."
1878,"March 27","In anticipation of war with Russia, Disraeli mobilizes the reserves and calls up Indian troops to Malta."
1878,"June 4","Cyprus Convention: The Ottoman Empire cedes Cyprus to the United Kingdom but retains the nominal title."
1878,"June 12","(June 12 - July 12) The Congress of Berlin convenes to discuss the Ottoman Empire."
1879,"February 15","Women's rights: American President Rutherford B. Hayes signs a bill allowing female attorneys to argue cases before the Supreme Court of the United States."
1879,"March 3","The United States Geological Survey is created."
1879,"March 13","The Duke of Connaught and Strathearn, third son of Queen Victoria, marries Princess Louise Marguerite of Prussia."
1879,"May 26","Russia and the United Kingdom sign the Treaty of Gandamak, establishing an Afghan state."
1879,"September 13","Tsutomu Sakuma, Japanese, The sixth submarine corps coxswain."
1879,"October 7","The Dual Alliance is formed by Germany and Austria-Hungary."
1879,"circa","Ferdinand Cheval begins to build his [i]Palais Idéal[/i] in France."
1879,"circa","Henrik Ibsen (while living in Italy) publishes his masterpiece, [i]A Doll's House[/i]."
1880,"June 1","Tinius Olsen awarded a United States Patent for the Little Giant Testing Machine."
1880,"June 29","France annexes Tahiti."
1880,"circa","4 million Jews of Europe's 7 million live in the Russian Empire."
1880,"circa","More than 100,000 Chinese men and 3,000 Chinese women are living in the western United States."
1881,"January 16","(January 16 - January 24) Siege of Geok Tepe: Russian troops under General Mikhail Skobelev defeat the Turkomans."
1881,"March 4","Inauguration of James A. Garfield as President of the United States."
1881,"March 13","Alexander II of Russia is killed near his palace when a bomb is thrown at him. He is succeeded by his son, Alexander III."
1881,"April 15","Anti-Semitic pogroms in Southern Russia start."
1881,"May 13","The Pacific island of Rotuma cedes to Great Britain, becoming a dependency of the Colony of Fiji."
1881,"May 21","The United States Tennis Association is established by a small group of tennis club members."
1881,"July 2","James Garfield, President of the United States, is shot by lawyer Charles Julius Guiteau. He survives the shooting but suffers from infection of his wound, dying on September 19."
1881,"July 20","Indian Wars: Sioux chief Sitting Bull leads the last of his fugitive people in surrender to United States troops at Fort Buford in Montana."
1881,"August 3","The Pretoria Convention peace treaty is signed, officially ending the war between the Boers and Britain."
1882,"March 28","Republican Jules Ferry makes primary education in France free, non-clerical (laique) and obligatory."
1882,"May 20","The Triple Alliance is formed between Germany, Austria-Hungary and Italy."
1882,"circa","The Personal Liberty League is established to oppose the temperance movement in the United States."
1882,"circa","Pogroms in Southern Russia end."
1883,"circa","A depression starts in Seattle, United States."
1884,"July 5","Germany takes possession of Cameroon."
1884,"October 6","The United States Naval War College is established in Newport, Rhode Island."
1884,"December 16","The World Cotton Centennial World's Fair opens in New Orleans, Louisiana."
1884,"circa","France conquers Vietnam."
1884,"circa","Police training schools are established in every prefecture in Japan."
1884,"circa","Reformers in Korea who admire the Meiji Restoration in Japan stage a coup with Japan's help. China intervens to rescue the king and help suppress the rebels. Afterward both China and Japan agree to withdraw their troops and military advisers."
1885,"February 21","United States President Chester A. Arthur dedicates the Washington Monument."
1885,"March 4","Grover Cleveland succeeds Chester A. Arthur as President of the United States."
1885,"March 26","The Prussian government, motivated by Otto von Bismarck, expels all ethnic Poles and Jews without German citizenship from Prussia in the Prussian deportations."
1885,"March 30","The Battle for Kushka triggers the Panjdeh Incident, which nearly gives rise to war between the British Empire and Russian Empire."
1885,"July 20","Professional football (soccer) is legalized in Britain."
1885,"circa","A cholera outbreak occurs in Spain."
1886,"January 16","A resolution is passed in the German Parliament, to condemn the Prussian deportations, the politically motivated mass expulsion of ethnic Poles and Jews from Prussia, initiated by Otto von Bismarck."
1886,"May 1","A general strike begins in the United States, which escalates into the Haymarket Riot and eventually wins the eight-hour workday in the U.S."
1886,"May 15","Portugal and France agree to regulate the borders of their colonies in Guinea."
1886,"June 2","U.S. President Grover Cleveland marries Frances Folsom in the White House, becoming the only president to wed in the executive mansion. She is 27 years his junior."
1886,"July 25","Robert Cecil, 3rd Marquess of Salisbury (Conservative Party (UK)) becomes Great Britain's 30th Prime Minister."
1886,"October 7","Spain abolishes slavery in Cuba."
1886,"circa","Horse-drawn streetcars of Austria-Hungary, France, Germany and Great Britain are carrying c. 900 million riders per year."
1887,"January 20","The United States Senate allows the Navy to lease Pearl Harbor as a naval base."
1887,"June 18","The Reinsurance Treaty is closed between Germany and Russia."
1887,"July 1","Construction of the metal structure of the Eiffel Tower starts in Paris, France."
1887,"August 13","The Hibernian F.C. defeats Preston North End to win the ""Championship of the World"" after the two teams win the Association football Cup competitions in their respective countries."
1887,"September 28","Start of the 1887 Yellow River flood in China, killing 900,000 to 2,000,000 people."
1887,"circa","Japan annexes Iwo Jima."
1888,"March 11","The ""Great Blizzard of '88"" begins along the eastern seaboard of the United States, shutting down commerce and killing more than 400."
1888,"May 1","The United States Congress establishes the Fort Belknap Indian Reservation."
1888,"November 6","U.S. presidential election, 1888: United States Democratic Party incumbent Grover Cleveland wins the popular vote, but loses the Electoral College vote to Republican challenger Benjamin Harrison, therefore losing the election."
1889,"January 30","Crown Prince Rudolf of Austria and his mistress Baroness Mary Vetsera commit a double suicide (or a murder suicide) in the Mayerling hunting lodge."
1889,"February 11","The Meiji Constitution of Japan is adopted; the 1st Diet convenes in 1890."
1889,"March 4","Grover Cleveland, 22nd President of the United States (1885-1889) is succeeded by Benjamin Harrison (1889-1893)."
1889,"May 2","Menelik II, Emperor of Ethiopia, signs a treaty of amity with Italy, giving Italy control over what will become Eritrea."
1889,"June 19","A Neapolitan baker named Raffaele Esposito invented the Pizza Margherita, named after the queen consort of Italy Margherita of Savoy. This was the forerunner of today's modern pizza."
1889,"November 17","The Brazilian Royal Family is forced to France."
1889,"December 23","The Spanish football team Recreativo de Huelva is formed (currently the oldest club in Spain)."
1889,"circa","An early method of high-voltage direct current (HVDC) transmission as developed by the Swiss engineer Rene Thury  is implemented commercially in Italy by the [i]Acquedotto de Ferrari-Galliera[/i] company. This system transmitsd 630 kW at 14 kV DC over a distance of 120 km."
1890,"January 1","The Kingdom of Italy establishes Eritrea as its colony in the Horn of Africa."
1890,"February 17","The British steamship [i]Duburg[/i] wrecks in the China Seas; 400 lives are lost.."
1890,"March 4","The longest bridge in Britain, the Forth Bridge (8,296 ft) in Scotland, is opened."
1890,"March 20","Wilhelm II of Germany fires Otto von Bismarck."
1890,"June 1","The United States Census Bureau begins using Herman Hollerith's tabulating machine to count census returns."
1890,"July 1","Heligoland-Zanzibar Treaty is signed by Great Britain and Germany."
1890,"December 27","The British steamship [i]Shanghai[/i] burns in the China Seas; 101 lives are lost.."
1890,"circa","William II of Prussia opposes Bismarck's attempt to renew the law outlawing the Social Democratic Party."
1891,"January 1","Paying of old age pensions begins in Germany."
1891,"May 1","Troops fire on a workers' May Day demonstration in support of the 8-hour workday in Fourmies, France, killing 9 and wounding 30."
1891,"May 11","Otsu Incident: Czarevich Nikolai Alexandrovich of Russia survives an assassination attempt while visiting Japan."
1891,"August 27","France and Russia conclude a defensive alliance."
1891,"October 27","An 8.0 earthquake strikes the village of Utsuzumi in rural Gifu, Japan, killing over 7,000 across the region and creating a 3-meter-tall surface fault that is still visible."
1892,"January 1","Ellis Island begins accommodating immigrants to the United States."
1892,"February 12","Former President Abraham Lincoln's birthday is declared a national holiday in the United States."
1892,"September 15","Sergei Witte replaces Ivan Vyshnegradsky as Russian finance minister."
1892,"circa","A cholera outbreak occurs in Hamburg, Germany."
1892,"circa","Viruses are discovered by the Russian-Ukrainian biologist Dimitri Ivanovski."
1893,"March 4","President of the United States Benjamin Harrison is succeeded by Stephen Grover Cleveland."
1893,"April 1","The rank of Chief Petty Officer is established in the United States Navy."
1893,"May 10","The United States Supreme Court legally declares the tomato to be a vegetable."
1893,"July 11","Kokichi Mikimoto, in Japan, develops the method to seed and grow cultured pearls."
1893,"September 11","Standing ovation to Hindu monk Swami Vivekanda for his address in Response to the welcome at the World Parliament of Religions in Chicago."
1893,"September 19","Swami Vivekananda delivers an inspiring speech on his paper at the World Parliament of Religions in Chicago."
1893,"September 19","The Russian ironclad [i]Rusalka[/i] disappears in a storm en route from Tallinn to Helsinki; her hulk is eventually discovered in July 2003, off Helsinki."
1893,"September 27","The World Parliament of Religions holds its closing meeting in Chicago."
1893,"October 30","The 1893 World's Fair, also known as the World's Columbian Exposition, closes."
1893,"circa","France conquers Laos."
1893,"circa","Small anti-Semitic parties secure 2.9% of votes in Germany."
1894,"March 4","First Sino-Japanese War: A great fire in Shanghai destroys over 1,000 buildings."
1894,"April 21","A bituminous coal miners' strike closes mines across the United States."
1894,"May 14","A meteor shower is seen in Southern France."
1894,"June 24","Sadi Carnot, president of France, is assassinated."
1894,"November 1","Russian Tsar Alexander III is succeeded by his son Nicholas II."
1894,"circa","Western countries give up their extraterritorial rights in Japan."
1894,"circa","In Korea, peasant unrest erupts in the Donghak Peasant Revolution, a massive revolt of followers of the Donghak movement. Both China and Japan send military forces, claiming to come to the Korean government's aid. They end up fighting each other instead."
1895,"March 1","William L. Wilson is appointed United States Postmaster General."
1895,"March 4","Japanese troops capture Liaoyang and land in Taiwan."
1895,"May 24","Anti-Japanese officials led by Tang Ching-sung in Taiwan declare independence from the Qing Dynasty, forming the short-lived Republic of Formosa."
1895,"May 27","[i]In re Debs[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States decides that the federal government has the right to regulate interstate commerce, legalizing the military suppression of the Pullman Strike."
1895,"October 23","The city of Tainan, last stronghold of the Republic of Formosa, capitulates to the forces of the Empire of Japan, ending the short-lived republic and beginning the Japanese rule era."
1895,"circa","The gold reserve of the U.S. Treasury is saved when J. P. Morgan and the Rothschilds loan $65 million worth of gold to the United States government."
1895,"circa","The huge indemnity exacted from China is used to establish the Yawata Iron and Steel Works."
1896,"January 5","An Austrian newspaper reports that Wilhelm Röntgen has discovered a type of radiation later known as X-rays."
1896,"February 1","The opera [i]La bohème[/i] premieres in Turin, Italy."
1896,"March 1","Battle of Adwa: Ethiopia defends its independence from Italy."
1896,"March 9","Responding to national outrage at the defeat at Adowa, Italian Prime Minister Francesco Crispi resigns."
1896,"June 15","An earthquake and tsunami in Sanriku, Japan, kills 27,000."
1896,"July 9","William Jennings Bryan delivers his Cross of gold speech at the Democratic National Convention, which nominates him for President of the United States."
1896,"circa","France establishes an administrative post in Abengourou, Côte d'Ivoire."
1896,"circa","The Republican Party of the United States of America is realigned."
1897,"March 4","William McKinley succeeds Grover Cleveland as President of the United States."
1897,"April 5","The [i]Ordinance of April 5,[/i] equalizing German and Czech in Bohemia, is signed in Austria-Hungary."
1897,"May 16","The Teatro Massimo is built in Palermo, the largest opera theatre in Italy, the 3rd largest in Europe."
1897,"September 20","Greece and Turkey sign a peace treaty to end the Greco-Turkish War."
1897,"October 13","The HMS Canopus (1898), a pre-Dreadnought battleship of the Royal Navy, is launched at Portsmouth, England (will be deployed widely in World War I)."
1897,"November 25","Spain grants Puerto Rico autonomy."
1897,"circa","France allows women to study at the [i]Ecole des Beaux-Arts[/i]."
1898,"February 15","Spanish-American War: The USS [i]Maine[/i] explodes and sinks in Havana harbor, Cuba for then unknown reasons, killing 266 men. This event helps lead the United States to declare war on Spain."
1898,"April 22","Spanish-American War: The United States Navy begins a blockade of Cuban ports and the USS [i]Nashville[/i] captures a Spanish merchant ship."
1898,"April 25","Spanish-American War: The United States declares war on Spain; the U.S. Congress announces that a state of war has existed since April 21 (later backdating this one more day to April 20)."
1898,"May 7","(May 7 - May 9) Bava-Beccaris massacre: Hundreds of demonstrators are killed when General Fiorenzo Bava-Beccaris orders troops to fire on a rally in Milan, Italy (in 1900, King Umberto I of Italy is killed in an act of vengeance for his praise of the shooting)."
1898,"June 1","The Trans-Mississippi Exposition World's Fair opens in Omaha, Nebraska."
1898,"June 12","Philippine Declaration of Independence: General Emilio Aguinaldo declares the Philippines' independence from Spain."
1898,"July 7","The United States annexes the Hawaiian Islands."
1898,"July 17","Spanish-American War - Battle of Santiago Bay: Troops under United States General William R. Shafter take the city of Santiago de Cuba from the Spanish."
1898,"July 25","Spanish-American War: The United States invasion of Puerto Rico begins with a landing at Guánica Bay."
1898,"September 10","Luigi Lucheni assassinates Empress Elisabeth of Austria-Hungary."
1898,"September 18","Fashoda incident: A diplomatic dispute between France and the United Kingdom ends in victory for the British."
1898,"September 21","Empress Dowager Cixi of China engineers a coup d'etat, marking the end of the Hundred Days' Reform; the Guangxu Emperor is arrested."
1898,"circa","Exploits of Louis de Rougemont begin to appear in [i]Wide World Magazine[/i]."
1899,"January 17","The United States takes possession of Wake Island."
1899,"February 6","Spanish-American War: A peace treaty between the United States and Spain is ratified by the United States Senate."
1899,"May 18","The First Hague Peace Conference was opened in The Hague by Willem de Beaufort, Minister of Foreign Affairs of The Netherlands."
1899,"June 25","Three Denver, Colorado newspapers publish a story (later proved to be a fabrication) that the Chinese government under the Guangxu Emperor is going to demolish the Great Wall of China."
1899,"August 28","At least 512 are killed when a debris hill from the Sumitomo Besshi copper mine at Niihama, Shikoku, Japan, collapses after heavy rain; 122 houses, a smelting factory, hospital and many other facilities are destroyed.."
1899,"circa","Japan gets the right of extraterritoriality."
1900,"circa","World Population: 1,650,000,000."
1900,"circa","Japan Population: c. 45,000,000."
1900,"January 2","John Hay announces the Open Door Policy to promote trade with China."
1900,"January 3","The United States Census estimates the country's population was 70 million."
1900,"January 4","Strikes in Belgium and Germany lead to mining riots."
1900,"January 8","United States President William McKinley places Alaska under military rule."
1900,"January 14","The United States Senate accepts the Anglo-German treaty of 1899, in which the United Kingdom renounces its claims to the Samoan islands."
1900,"January 17","Brigham H. Roberts is refused a seat in the United States House of Representatives because of his polygamy."
1900,"January 23","Austrian miners go on strike."
1900,"January 27","Boxer Rebellion: Foreign diplomats in Peking, China demand that the Boxer rebels be disciplined."
1900,"February 5","Britain and the United States sign a treaty for the building of a Central American shipping canal through Nicaragua."
1900,"February 6","The international arbitration court at The Hague is created when the Netherlands' Senate ratifies an 1899 peace conference decree."
1900,"February 14","Russia responds to international pressure to free Finland by tightening imperial control over the country."
1900,"March 9","Women in Germany demand the right to participate in university entrance exams."
1900,"March 27","The arrival of a Russian fleet in Korea causes concern to the Japanese government."
1900,"March 31","In France, the legal length of a workday for women and children is limited to 11 hours."
1900,"April 14","The Paris World Exhibition opens."
1900,"May 14","The second Modern Olympic Games opens in Paris (as part of the Paris World Exhibition)."
1900,"May 21","Russia invades Manchuria."
1900,"May 31","Boxer Rebellion: Peacekeepers from various European countries arrive in China."
1900,"July 25","The Robert Charles Riots occur in New Orleans, Louisiana, United States."
1900,"July 29","King Umberto I of Italy is assassinated by Italian-born anarchist Gaetano Bresci."
1900,"circa","Japan participates with the European powers in occupying Beijing to suppress the Boxer Rebellion."
1901,"March 4","United States President William McKinley begins his 2nd term. Theodore Roosevelt is sworn in as Vice President of the United States."
1901,"March 6","In Bremen, an assassin attempts to kill Wilhelm II of Germany."
1901,"June 2","Katsura Taro becomes Prime Minister of Japan."
1901,"September 7","The Boxer Rebellion in China officially ends with the signing of the Boxer Protocol."
1901,"September 14","Theodore Roosevelt succeeds William McKinley as President of the United States."
1902,"January 23","A snowstorm at Mount Hakkoda, northern Honshu, Japan, kills 199 during a military training exercise."
1902,"April 13","A new car speed record of 74 mph is set in Nice, France, by Leon Serpollet."
1902,"May 13","Alfonso XIII of Spain begins his reign."
1902,"May 20","Cuba gains independence from the United States."
1902,"June 2","The Anthracite Coal Strike begins in the United States."
1902,"July 11","The Order of the Garter is conferred on Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria."
1902,"October 21","In the United States, a five month strike by the United Mine Workers ends."
1903,"February 17","El Yunque National Forest in Puerto Rico becomes part of the United States National Forest System as the Luquillo Forest Reserve."
1903,"February 23","Cuba leases Guantanamo Bay to the United States ""in perpetuity""."
1903,"March 5","Turkey and Germany sign an agreement to build the Constantinople-Baghdad Railway."
1903,"March 14","The Hay-Herran Treaty, granting the United States the right to build the Panama Canal, is ratified by the United States Senate. The Colombian Senate later rejects the treaty."
1903,"July 30","(July 30 - August 23) Second Congress of the All-Russian Social Democratic Labour Party held in exile in Brussels, transferring to London."
1903,"August 2","The Ilinden Uprising of the Macedonians in the Ottoman Empire breaks out."
1903,"November 4","With the encouragement of the United States, Panama proclaims itself independent from Colombia."
1903,"November 13","The United States recognizes the independence of Panama."
1903,"November 17","The Russian Social Democratic Labor Party splits into two groups; the Bolsheviks (Russian for ""majority"") and Mensheviks (Russian for ""minority"")."
1903,"November 18","The Hay-Bunau-Varilla Treaty is signed by the United States and Panama, giving the U.S. exclusive rights over the Panama Canal Zone."
1904,"February 8","A Japanese surprise attack on Port Arthur (Lushun) starts the Russo-Japanese War."
1904,"February 23","For $10 million, the United States gains control of the Panama Canal Zone."
1904,"March 4","Russo-Japanese War: Russian troops in Korea retreat toward Manchuria, followed by 100,000 Japanese troops."
1904,"April 8","The Entente Cordiale is signed between the UK and France."
1904,"April 30","The Louisiana Purchase Exposition World's Fair opens in St. Louis, Missouri (closes December 1)."
1904,"July 1","The third Modern Olympic Games opens in St. Louis, Missouri, United States as part of the World's Fair."
1904,"August 17","Russo-Japanese War: A Japanese infantry charge fails to take Port Arthur."
1904,"October 21","Russo-Japanese War - Dogger Bank incident: The Russian Baltic Fleet fires on British trawlers it mistakes for Japanese torpedo boats in the North Sea."
1904,"circa","Russo-Japanese War (1904-1905)"
1905,"January 2","Russo-Japanese War: The Russian Army surrenders at Port Arthur, China."
1905,"January 22","The Bloody Sunday massacre of Russian demonstrators, at the Winter Palace in Saint Petersburg, helps trigger the abortive Russian Revolution of 1905."
1905,"February 19","Russo-Japanese War: The Battle of Mukden begins in Manchuria."
1905,"March 3","Tsar Nicholas II of Russia agrees to create an elected assembly (the Duma)."
1905,"March 5","Russo-Japanese War: Russian troops begin to retreat from Mukden after losing 100,000 troops in 3 days."
1905,"March 10","Russo-Japanese War: The Japanese capture of Mukden (now Shenyang) completes the rout of Russian armies in Manchuria."
1905,"March 31","German Emperor William II asserts German equality with France in Morocco, triggering the Tangier or First Moroccan Crisis."
1905,"April 6","[i]Lochner v. New York[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States invalidates New York's 8-hour-day law."
1905,"May 15","The Russian minelayer [i]Amur[/i] laid a minefield about 15 miles off Port Arthur and sank Japan's battleship Hatsuse, 15,000 tons, with 496 crew."
1905,"May 27","(May 27 - May 28) Russo-Japanese War - Battle of Tsushima: The Japanese fleet under Admiral Heihachiro Togo destroys the Russian fleet under Admiral Zinovi Petrovich Rozhdestvenski in a 2-day battle."
1905,"June 7","The Norwegian Parliament declares the union with Sweden dissolved, and Norway achieves full independence."
1905,"June 15","Princess Margaret of Connaught marries Prince Gustaf Adolf of Sweden, Duke of Skåne (Gustaf VI Adolf of Sweden)."
1905,"June 27","Mutiny breaks out on the Russian ironclad [i]Potemkin[/i]."
1905,"September 5","Russo-Japanese War - Treaty of Portsmouth: In New Hampshire, a treaty mediated by U.S. President Theodore Roosevelt is signed by victor Japan and Russia. Russia cedes the island of Sakhalin and port and rail rights in Manchuria to Japan."
1905,"October 16","Russian Revolution of 1905: The Russian army opens fire in a meeting on a street market in Estonia, killing 94 and injuring over 200."
1905,"October 26","Sweden agrees to the repeal of the union with Norway."
1905,"circa","Wolves become extinct in Japan."
1905,"circa","Civil service examinations are abolished in China."
1905,"circa","Germany insists on an international conference on the whole Moroccan question."
1905,"circa","Russo-Japanese War."
1906,"March 10","An explosion in a coal mine in Courrières, France kills 1,060."
1906,"August 23","Unable to control a rebellion Cuban President Tomás Estrada Palma requests United States intervention. The subsequent provisional occupation administration lasts until 1909.."
1906,"October 11","A United States diplomatic crisis with Japan arises when the San Francisco public school board orders Japanese students to be taught in racially segregated schools."
1906,"October 16","Imposter Wilhelm Voigt impersonates a Prussian officer and takes over city hall in Köpenick for a short time."
1906,"November 22","Russian Prime Minister Peter Stolypin introduces agrarian reforms aimed at creating a large class of land-owning peasants."
1907,"March 5","At the opening of the new State Duma in St. Petersburg, Russia, 40,000 demonstrators are dispersed by Russian troops."
1907,"July 25","Korea becomes a protectorate of Japan."
1907,"December 6","Monongah Mining Disaster: A coal mine explosion kills 362 workers in Monongah, West Virginia, United States."
1908,"February 18","Japanese immigration to the U.S.A. is forbidden."
1908,"June 30","The Tunguska event, also known as the [i]Russian explosion[/i], occurs near the Podkamennaya Tunguska River in Krasnoyarsk Krai, Siberia, Russian Empire."
1908,"July 3","Young Turk Revolution in the Ottoman Empire: Major Ahmed Niyazi, with 200 followers (Ottoman troops and civilians), begins an open revolution by defecting from the 3rd Army Corps in Macedonia, decamping into the hill country."
1908,"July 11","(July 11 - July 12) The steamship [i]Amalthea[/i], housing 80 British strikebreakers while in Malmö harbour, Sweden, is bombed by Anton Nilson; 1 is killed, 20 injured."
1908,"July 23","Young Turk Revolution: The Committee of Union and Progress (CUP) issues a formal ultimatum to Sultan Abdul Hamid II to restore the constitution of 1876, within the Ottoman Empire. It is restored the following day."
1908,"October 5","Bulgaria declares its independence from the Ottoman Empire; Ferdinand I of Bulgaria becomes Tsar."
1908,"circa","Henri Matisse opens his own art academy in France."
1909,"January 28","United States troops leave Cuba after being there since the Spanish-American War."
1909,"March 4","William Howard Taft succeeds Theodore Roosevelt to become the 27th President of the United States."
1909,"March 31","Serbia accepts Austrian control over Bosnia and Herzegovina."
1909,"April 27","Sultan of the Ottoman Empire Abdul Hamid II is overthrown and succeeded by his brother, Mehmed V. He is sent to the Ottoman port city of Thessaloniki (Selanik) the next day."
1909,"June 22","Construction begins on the Cape Cod Canal, which would separate Cape Cod from mainland Massachusetts, United States."
1909,"July 16","A revolution forces Mohammad Ali Shah, Persian Shah of the Qajar dynasty to abdicate in favor of his son Ahmad Shah Qajar. He proceeds to leave Persia for Imperial Russia, reportedly seeking the assistance of Nicholas II of Russia in regaining the throne."
1909,"September 4","Japan and China sign the Jiandao/Gando Treaty, which gives Imperial Japan a way to receive railroad concessions in Manchuria."
1909,"October 13","An agreement by Germany, Italy and Switzerland gives the Germans and Italians access to the Gotthard Rail Tunnel."
1909,"October 26","Korean nationalist An Jung-geun assassinates Ito Hirobumi, a former Prime Minister of Japan, in Harbin, China, in protest of the Japanese annexation of Korea."
1909,"November 18","Two United States warships are sent to Nicaragua after 500 revolutionaries (including 2 Americans) are executed by order of dictator Jose Santos Zelaya."
1909,"circa","Ottoman Empire slaughters thousands of Armenian Christians.."
1910,"July 4","African-American boxer Jack Johnson defeats American boxer James J. Jeffries in a heavyweight boxing match, sparking race riots across the United States."
1910,"August 14","A fire at the World Exhibition in Brussels destroys exhibitions of Britain and France."
1910,"August 22","The Japan-Korea Annexation Treaty is signed."
1910,"November 23","The last execution in Sweden (by guillotine) is carried out against murderer Johan Alfred Ander."
1910,"circa","The electric streetcars of Austria-Hungary, France, Germany and Great Britain are carrying 6.7 million riders per year."
1911,"March 29","The United States Army formally adopts the M1911 pistol as its standard sidearm, thus giving the gun its 1911 designation."
1911,"April 27","Following the resignation and death of William P. Frye, a compromise is reached to rotate the office of President pro tempore of the United States Senate."
1911,"May 25","Mexican Revolution: Porfirio Diaz signs his resignation and leaves for Veracruz; on May 31 he leaves for exile in France."
1911,"June 14","A national seamen's strike begins in Britain."
1911,"July 1","The presence of the German warship [i]Panther[/i] in the Moroccan port of Agadir triggers the Agadir Crisis, escalating pre-World War I tensions; a subsequent climbdown rallies German militancy."
1911,"August 8","[i]Public Law 62-5[/i] sets the number of representatives in the United States House of Representatives at 435 (the law takes effect in 1913)."
1911,"September 29","Italy declares war on Turkey."
1911,"October 18","Revolutionaries under Sun Yat-sen overthrow China's Qing Dynasty."
1911,"November 5","Italy annexes Tripoli and Cyrenaica (this act is confirmed by an act of the Italian Parliament on February 25, 1912)."
1911,"November 11","A record cold snap hits the United States Midwest; many cities break record highs and lows on the same day."
1911,"November 16","An earthquake strikes Swab, South Germany."
1911,"circa","1 out of every 7 employed persons is a domestic servant in Great Britain.."
1911,"circa","Japan gains control of its own tariffs."
1912,"January 1","The Republic of China is established."
1912,"January 5","Prague Party Conference: Vladimir Lenin and the Bolshevik Party break away from the rest of the Russian Social Democratic Labour Party."
1912,"March 30","France establishes a protectorate over Morocco."
1912,"April 19","The United States Senate initiates an official inquiry into the [i]Titanic[/i] disaster, hastily issuing subpoenas for White Star personnel before they can return to the United Kingdom."
1912,"May 5","The 1912 Summer Olympics open in Stockholm, Sweden."
1912,"October 8","The First Balkan War begins: Montenegro declares war against Turkey."
1912,"October 16","The Boston Red Sox, assisted by a famous error, defeat the New York Giants in extra innings to win the 1912 World Series, in what is considered one of the greatest games of baseball ever played."
1912,"November 28","Albania declares independence from the Ottoman Empire."
1912,"December 30","The First Balkan War ends temporarily: Bulgaria, Greece, Montenegro, and Serbia (the Balkan League) sign an armistice with Turkey, ending the two-month long war."
1913,"February 3","The 16th Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, authorizing the Federal government to impose and collect income taxes."
1913,"March 4","Woodrow Wilson succeeds William Howard Taft as the 28th President of the United States."
1913,"March 13","Mexican Revolution: Pancho Villa returns to Mexico from his self-imposed exile in the United States."
1913,"April 8","The Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is passed, dictating the direct election of senators."
1913,"July 10","Death Valley, California hits 134 °F (~56.7 °C) which is the highest temperature recorded in the United States (as of 2008[update])."
1913,"August 4","In China, the province of Chungking declares independence; Chinese Republican forces crush the rebellion in a couple of weeks."
1913,"August 20","700 feet above Buc, France, parachutist Adolphe Pegond jumps from an airplane and lands safely."
1913,"September 23","French aviator Roland Garros crosses the Mediterranean in an airplane flying from Fréjus, France to Bizerte, Tunisia."
1913,"December 30","Italy returns the [i]Mona Lisa[/i] to France."
1913,"circa","The United States Soccer Federation is formed."
1914,"March 1","The Republic of China joins the Universal Postal Union."
1914,"June 28","Serb nationalist Gavrilo Princip assassinates Austrian Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria and his wife, Duchess Sophie, in Sarajevo."
1914,"June 29","Austria-Hungary: The Secretary of the Legation at Belgrade sends a dispatch to Vienna suggesting Serbian complicity in the crime of Sarajevo. Anti-Serb riots erupt in Sarajevo and throughout Bosnia generally."
1914,"June 30","In Great Britain, addresses in Parliament on the murdered Archduke include Lords Crewe & Lansdowne in the House of Lords, and Messrs. Asquith & Law in the House of Commons."
1914,"July 4","The Archduke's funeral takes place at Artstetten (50 miles west of Vienna), Austria-Hungary."
1914,"July 7","Austria-Hungary convenes a Council of Ministers, including Ministers for Foreign Affairs and War, the Chief of the General Staff and Naval Commander-in-Chief; the Council lasts from 11.30 a.m. to 6.15 p.m."
1914,"July 9","The Emperor of Austria-Hungary receives the report of Austro-Hungarian investigation into the Sarajevo crime. The Times publishes an account of the Austro-Hungarian press campaign against the Serbians (who are described as ""pestilent rats"")."
1914,"July 19","Austria-Hungary - A press scare concerning an alleged ""Greater Serbia"" conspiracy occurs."
1914,"July 23","Austria-Hungary presents Serbia with an unconditional ultimatum."
1914,"July 28","Austria-Hungary declares war on Serbia and its army bombards Belgrade."
1914,"July 28","Tsar Nicholas II of Russia orders a partial mobilization against Austria-Hungary."
1914,"July 29","Russia orders full mobilization."
1914,"August 1","Germany declares war on Russia, following Russia's military mobilization in support of Serbia; Germany also begins mobilization."
1914,"August 1","France orders general mobilization."
1914,"August 2","A secret treaty between Turkey and Germany secures Turkish neutrality."
1914,"August 2","At 7:00 pm (local time) Germany issues a 12-hour ultimatum to Belgium to allow German passage into France."
1914,"August 3","Germany declares war on Russia's ally, France."
1914,"August 3","At 7:00 am (local time) Belgium declines to accept Germany's ultimatum of August 2."
1914,"August 4","German troops invade neutral Belgium at 8:02 am (local time). Britain declares war on Germany for this violation of Belgian neutrality. This move effectively means a declaration of war by the whole British Commonwealth and Empire against Germany. The United States declares neutrality."
1914,"August 5","Montenegro declares war on Austria-Hungary."
1914,"August 6","Austria-Hungary declares war on Russia."
1914,"August 17","(August 17 - September 2) World War I: The Battle of Tannenberg begins between German and Russian forces."
1914,"August 20","World War I: German forces occupy Brussels."
1914,"August 23","Japan declares war on Germany."
1914,"August 26","(August 26 - August 30) The Russian Second Army is surrounded and defeated in the Battle of Tannenberg."
1914,"September 1","St. Petersburg, Russia changes its name to [i]Petrograd[/i]."
1914,"September 5","London Agreement: No member of the Triple Entente (Britain, France, or Russia) may seek a separate peace with the Central Powers."
1914,"September 5","World War I - First Battle of the Marne: Northeast of Paris, the French 6th Army under General Maunoury attacks German forces nearing Paris. Over 2 million fight (500,000 killed/wounded) in the Allied victory."
1914,"October 3","World War I: 33,000 Canadian troops depart for Europe, the largest force to ever cross the Atlantic Ocean at the time."
1914,"October 9","World War I - Siege of Antwerp: Antwerp, Belgium falls to German troops."
1914,"October 27","World War I: The British super-dreadnought battleship HMS Audacious (23,400 tons), is sunk off Tory Island, north-west of Ireland, by a minefield laid by the armed German merchant-cruiser [i]Berlin[/i]."
1914,"October 28","World War I - Battle of Penang, Malaya: The German cruiser [i]Emden[/i] sinks a Russian cruiser and French destroyer before escaping."
1914,"October 29","World War I: Ottoman warships shell Russian Black Sea ports; Russia, France, and Britain declare war between November 1st and November 5th."
1914,"November 4","Britain and France declare war on Turkey."
1914,"November 5","The United Kingdom annexes Cyprus, and together with France declares war on the Ottoman Empire."
1914,"November 7","The Japanese seize Jiaozhou Bay in China, the base of the German East Asia Squadron."
1914,"November 9","World War I - Battle of Cocos: The German cruiser [i]Emden[/i] is sunk by the Australian cruiser [i]Sydney[/i]."
1914,"November 16","World War I - The Battle of Kolubara begins: Serbian forces engaged by Austro-Hungarian forces."
1914,"November 28","World War I: Following a war-induced closure in July, the New York Stock Exchange re-opens for bond trading."
1914,"December 15","A gas explosion at the Mitsubishi Hojyo coal mine, Kyushu, Japan, kills 687 (the worst coal mine disaster in Japanese history)."
1914,"December 19","The Battle of Kolubara ends, resulting in a decisive Serbian victory over Austria-Hungary."
1914,"circa","The capital of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region of China is moved from Guilin to Nanning."
1914,"circa","The Port of Orange, Texas is dredged for the fabrication of vessels for the United States Navy."
1914,"circa","The United States Power Squadrons is formed."
1914,"circa","China declares its neutrality in World War I."
1914,"circa","World War I (1914-1918)"
1915,"January 1","World War I: The battleship HMS [i]Formidable[/i] is sunk off Lyme Regis, Dorset, England, by a German U-Boat."
1915,"January 12","The United States House of Representatives rejects a proposal to give women the right to vote."
1915,"January 13","An earthquake (6.8 in Richter scale) in Avezzano, Italy, kills more than 29,000."
1915,"January 18","Twenty-One Demands from Japan to China are made."
1915,"January 28","An act of the U.S. Congress designates the United States Coast Guard, begun in 1790, as a military branch."
1915,"January 31","World War I: Germany uses poison gas against the Russians."
1915,"March 14","World War I: Off the coast of Chile, the Royal Navy force SMS [i]Dresden[/i] to scuttle."
1915,"March 14","Britain, France and Russia agree to give Constantinople and the Bosporus to Russia in case of victory (the treaty is later nullified by the Bolshevik Revolution)."
1915,"March 18","World War I: A British attack on the Dardanelles fails."
1915,"April 24","The murder of 1.5 million Armenians by Ottoman Turks; the Armenian Genocide, started. Lasted until approximately 1918."
1915,"April 25","World War I: Start of the Gallipoli Campaign. Lasted until January 1916."
1915,"May 5","World War I: The Turks begin shelling Anzac Cove from a new position behind their lines."
1915,"May 7","World War I: The RMS [i]Lusitania[/i] is sunk by a German U-boat, killing 1,198."
1915,"May 9","World War I - Second Battle of Artois: German and French forces fight to a standstill."
1915,"May 23","World War I: Italy joins the Allies after they declare war on Austria-Hungary."
1915,"May 25","China agrees to Twenty-One Demands."
1915,"July 28","The United States occupation of Haiti begins."
1915,"August 6","World War I - Battle of Sari Bair: The Allies mount a diversionary attack timed to coincide with a major Allied landing of reinforcements at Suvla Bay."
1915,"October 15","World War I: Austria-Hungary invades the Kingdom of Serbia. Kingdom of Bulgaria enters the war, invading Kingdom of Serbia. The retreat of the Serbian First Army towards Greece begins the Serbian Campaign (World War I)."
1915,"December 23","The [i]HMHS Britannic[/i], the largest individual British loss in World War I, departs Liverpool on her maiden voyage."
1915,"December 25","British and German forces get out of the trenches in World War I and have a free-for-all kick-around football game in no-man's land."
1915,"circa","World War I (1914-1918)."
1916,"January 24","[i]Brushaber v. Union Pacific Railroad[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States upholds the national income tax."
1916,"February 21","World War I: The Battle of Verdun begins in France."
1916,"March 15","President Woodrow Wilson sends 12,000 United States troops over the U.S.-Mexico border to pursue Pancho Villa; the 13th Cavalry regiment enters Mexican territory."
1916,"March 22","The last Emperor of China, Yuan Shikai, abdicates the throne and the Republic of China is restored."
1916,"April 24","(April 24 - April 30) The Easter Rising occurs in Ireland. The Rising was an attempt by militant Irish republicans to win independence from Britain."
1916,"April 27","World War I - Battle of Hulluch: The 47th Brigade, 16th Irish Division is decimated in one of the most heavily concentrated German gas attacks of the war."
1916,"May 5","United States Marines invade the Dominican Republic."
1916,"May 16","Britain and France conclude the secret Sykes-Picot Agreement, which is to divide Arab areas of the Ottoman Empire, following the conclusion of World War I, into French and British spheres of influence."
1916,"May 21","Britain initiates daylight saving time."
1916,"May 22","The case of [i]United States v. Forty Barrels and Twenty Kegs of Coca-Cola[/i] is decided."
1916,"June 4","The Brusilov Offensive, the height of Russian operations in World War I, begins with their breaking through Austro-Hungarian lines."
1916,"June 5","Louis Brandeis is sworn in as a Justice of the United States Supreme Court."
1916,"July 2","Battle of Erzincan: Russian forces defeat troops of the Ottoman Empire in Armenia."
1916,"August 7","World War I: Portugal joins the Allies."
1916,"October 21","Friedrich Adler shoots Karl von Stürgkh, Prime Minister of Austria."
1916,"November 1","Paul Miliukov delivers the famous ""stupidity or treason"" speech in the Russian State Duma, precipitating the downfall of the Boris Stürmer government."
1916,"November 5","The Kingdom of Poland is proclaimed by a joint act of the emperors of Germany and Austria."
1916,"November 18","World War I - Battle of the Somme: In France, British Expeditionary Force commander Douglas Haig calls off the battle, which started on July 1."
1916,"November 23","World War I - Eastern Front: Bucharest, the capital of Romania, is occupied by troops of the Central Powers."
1916,"December 23","World War I - Battle of Magdhaba: In the Sinai desert, Australian and New Zealand mounted troops capture the Turkish garrison."
1916,"circa","The Summer Olympic Games in Berlin, Germany, are cancelled."
1916,"circa","Food is rationed in Germany."
1916,"circa","The Netherlands is hit by a North Sea storm that floods the lowlands and kills 10,000 people."
1916,"circa","World War I (1914-1918)"
1917,"January 11","German saboteurs set off the Kingsland Explosion at Kingsland, NJ (now Lyndhurst, NJ), one of the events leading to U.S. involvement in World War I."
1917,"January 13","World War I: The Battle of Wadi occurs between Allied British and Ottoman Empire forces, during the Mesopotamian campaign in modern-day Iraq."
1917,"January 22","World War I: President Woodrow Wilson calls for ""peace without victory"" in Europe."
1917,"January 28","The United States ends its search for Pancho Villa."
1917,"January 30","Pershing's troops in Mexico begin withdrawing back to the United States. They reach Columbus, Ohio February 5."
1917,"January 31","World War I: Germany announces its U-boats will engage in unrestricted submarine warfare."
1917,"February 3","World War I: The United States severs diplomatic relations with Germany."
1917,"February 24","World War I: United States ambassador to the United Kingdom, Walter H. Page, is shown the intercepted Zimmermann Telegram, in which Germany offers to give the American Southwest back to Mexico if Mexico declares war on the United States."
1917,"February 23","O.S.) - The Russian February Revolution begins with the overthrow of the Tsar."
1917,"March 11","Mexican Revolution: Venustiano Carranza is elected president of Mexico; the United States gives [i]de jure[/i] recognition of his government."
1917,"March 15","N.S.) (March 2, O.S.) - Tsar Nicholas II of Russia abdicates his throne for his son."
1917,"March 17","N.S.) (March 4, O.S.) - Grand Duke Michael Alexandrovich of Russia refuses the throne, and power passes to the newly formed Provisional Government under Prince Georgy Lvov."
1917,"March 25","The Georgian Orthodox Church restores the autocephaly abolished by Imperial Russia in 1811."
1917,"March 26","World War I: First Battle of Gaza: British cavalry troops retreat after 17,000 Turks block their advance."
1917,"April 2","World War I: U.S. President Woodrow Wilson asks the U.S. Congress for a declaration of war on Germany."
1917,"April 6","World War I: The United States declares war on Germany."
1917,"April 9","(April 9 - April 12) World War I: Canadian troops win the Battle of Vimy Ridge."
1917,"April 11","World War I: Brazil severs diplomatic relations with Germany."
1917,"April 16","World War I: The Nivelle Offensive commences."
1917,"April 19","World War I: The Second Battle of Gaza, a fiasco for the British, causes the dismissal of the commander of the Eastern Expeditionary Force, General Archibald Murray."
1917,"May 9","World War I: The Nivelle Offensive is abandoned."
1917,"May 23","A month of civil violence in Milan, Italy ends after the Italian army forcefully takes over the city from anarchists and anti-war revolutionaries. Fifty people are killed and 800 people are arrested."
1917,"May 27","World War I: Over 30,000 French troops refuse to go to the trenches in Missy-aux-Bois."
1917,"June 5","World War I: Conscription begins in the United States."
1917,"July 1","Russian General Brusilov begins a major offensive in Galicia, initially advancing towards Lemberg."
1917,"July 6","World War I: Arabian troops led by T. E. Lawrence capture Aqaba from the Turks."
1917,"July 16","(July 16 - July 17) Russian troops mutiny, abandon the Austrian front, and retreat to the Ukraine; hundreds are shot by their commanding officers during the retreat."
1917,"July 20","Alexander Kerensky becomes premier of the Russian Provisional Government, replacing Prince Georgy Lvov."
1917,"July 20","(July 20 - July 28) World War I: Austrian and German forces repulse the Russian advance into Galicia."
1917,"July 31","World War I: The Battle of Passchendaele: Allied offensive operations commence in Flanders."
1917,"August 10","A general strike begins in Spain; it is smashed after 3 days with 70 left dead, hundreds of wounded and 2,000 arrests."
1917,"October 12","World War I: The biggest loss of life in a single day for New Zealand. Over 800 men and 45 officers were killed at the First Battle of Passchendaele, roughly 1 in 1000 of the nation's population at the time."
1917,"October 15","World War I: At Vincennes outside of Paris, Dutch dancer Mata Hari is executed by firing squad for spying for Germany."
1917,"October 26","World War I: Brazil declares war against the Central Powers."
1917,"November 15","In the United States, a ""Night of Terror"" results in the injury of several influential suffragettes."
1917,"November 15","Finland takes a step towards full sovereignty, ending the personal union with Russia."
1917,"November 15","Georges Clemenceau becomes prime minister of France."
1917,"November 20","World War I - Battle of Cambrai: British forces make early progress in an attack on German positions but are soon beaten back."
1917,"December 11","British troops take Jerusalem from the Ottoman Empire."
1917,"circa","Female suffrage is enacted in the Netherlands."
1917,"circa","World War I (1914-1918)"
1917,"circa","Russian Revolution."
1918,"January 18","Constituent Assembly meet in Russia."
1918,"January 19","Russian Constituent Assembly proclaims Russian Democratic Federative Republic, but was dissolved by Bolshevik government on same day."
1918,"January 25","The Ukrainian people declare independence from Bolshevik Russia."
1918,"February 14","Russia switches from the Julian calendar to the Gregorian calendar; the date skips from February 1 to February 14."
1918,"February 24","After 7 centuries of foreign rule, Estonia declares its independence from the Russian Empire. Armenia, Azerbaijan, and Georgia also declare their independence from the Russian Empire but as the Transcaucasian Democratic Federative Republic."
1918,"March 3","World War I: Germany, Austria and Bolshevist Russia sign the Treaty of Brest-Litovsk, ending Russia's involvement in the war."
1918,"March 5","Soviet Russia moves its national capital from Petrograd to Moscow."
1918,"March 7","World War I: Finland forms an alliance with Germany."
1918,"March 12","Moscow becomes the capital of Soviet Russia."
1918,"March 21","World War I: The Second Battle of the Somme begins."
1918,"June 1","World War I: The Battle for Belleau Wood begins."
1918,"July 3","The Siberian Expedition is launched to extract the Czechoslovak Legion from the Russian Civil War."
1918,"July 4","Mehmed VI (1918-1922) succeeds Mehmed V (Resad) (1909-1918) as Ottoman Emperor."
1918,"July 12","The Japanese Imperial Navy battle ship [i]Kawachi[/i] blows up at Shunan, western Honshu, Japan killing at least 621."
1918,"July 15","World War I - Second Battle of the Marne: The battle begins near the River Marne with a German attack."
1918,"July 17","By order of the Bolshevik Party and carried out by the Cheka, Emperor Nicholas II of Russia, his immediate family, and retainers are executed at the Ipatiev House in Ekaterinburg, Russia."
1918,"August 1","British anti-Bolshevik forces occupy Archangel, Russia."
1918,"August 8","World War I - Battle of Amiens: Canadian and Australian troops, begin a string of almost continuous victories with a push through the German front lines. German General Erich Ludendorff later calls this the ""black day of the German Army""."
1918,"August 10","Russian Revolution: The British commander in Archangel is told to help the White Russians."
1918,"August 30","Russian Revolution: Vladmir Lenin is shot by Fanya Kaplan, but he survives. Moisei Uritsky, the Petrograd head of the Cheka, is assassinated the same day."
1918,"September 11","The Boston Red Sox defeat the Chicago Cubs for the 1918 World Series championship, their last World Series win until 2004."
1918,"September 29","Bulgaria requests an armistice in World War I."
1918,"October 3","Kaiser Wilhelm II of Germany makes Max von Baden German chancellor."
1918,"October 3","King Ferdinand I of Bulgaria abdicates in the wake of the Bulgarian military collapse in World War I. He is succeeded by his son, Boris III."
1918,"October 4","William II of Germany forms a new more liberal government to sue for peace."
1918,"October 28","Czechoslovakia declares its independence from Austria-Hungary."
1918,"October 30","The Mutawakkilite Kingdom of Yemen is granted independence from the Ottoman Empire by the Armistice of Mudros."
1918,"October 31","The Hungarian government terminates the personal union with Austria, officially dissolving the Austro-Hungarian empire."
1918,"November 3","World War I: Austria-Hungary enters an armistice with the Allies."
1918,"November 3","Poland declares its independence from Russia."
1918,"November 4","World War I: Austria-Hungary surrenders to Italy."
1918,"November 9","Kaiser Wilhelm II of Germany abdicates and chooses to live in exile in the Netherlands."
1918,"November 11","World War I ends: Germany signs an armistice agreement with the Allies between 5:12 AM and 5:20 AM in Marshal Foch's railroad car in Compiègne Forest in France. It becomes official on the 11th hour of the 11th day of the 11th month."
1918,"November 11","Emperor Charles I of Austria gives up his absolute power but does not abdicate."
1918,"November 12","Austria becomes a republic."
1918,"November 16","Hungary declares independence from Austria."
1918,"November 18","Latvia declares its independence from Russia."
1918,"November 28","Estonian Freedom War: Bolshevist Russia invades Estonia, beginning the war. A socialist republic is established in Narva the next day."
1918,"December 1","New voting laws in Sweden makes votes no longer dependent on taxable assets; one person, one vote."
1919,"January 1","Spartacist uprising: Socialist demonstrations in Berlin, Germany turn into an attempted communist revolution."
1919,"January 16","The 18th Amendment to the United States Constitution, authorizing Prohibition, goes into effect in the United States."
1919,"January 18","World War I: A peace conference opens in Versailles, France."
1919,"February 23","The Fascist Party is formed in Italy by Benito Mussolini."
1919,"February 26","An act of the United States Congress establishes most of the Grand Canyon as a United States National Park ([i]Grand Canyon National Park[/i])."
1919,"March 1","The March 1st Movement against Japanese colonial rule in Korea is formed."
1919,"March 3","The Supreme Court of the United States upholds the conviction of Charles Schenck."
1919,"March 5","A. Mitchell Palmer becomes Attorney General of the United States through recess appointment."
1919,"April 13","Eugene V. Debs enters prison at the Atlanta Federal Penitentiary in Atlanta, Georgia for speaking out against the draft during World War I."
1919,"April 14","The Emperor of Austria moves to exile in Switzerland."
1919,"May 1","A large left-wing demonstration in France leads to a violent confrontation with the police."
1919,"May 4","The May Fourth Movement opposes foreign colonizers in China."
1919,"June 2","Several mail bombs are sent to prominent figures as part of the 1919 United States anarchist bombings."
1919,"June 4","Women's rights: The United States Congress approves the 19th Amendment to the United States Constitution, which would guarantee suffrage to women, and sends it to the U.S. states for ratification."
1919,"June 28","The Treaty of Versailles is signed, ending World War I."
1919,"August 11","In Germany, the Weimar Constitution is passed into law."
1919,"September 10","The Treaty of Saint-Germain is signed, ending World War I with Austria."
1919,"September 22","The Steel strike of 1919 begins across the United States."
1919,"September 27","The last British troops leave Archangel, Russia and leave the fighting to the Russians."
1919,"October 9","Black Sox scandal: The Cincinnati Reds ""win"" the World Series."
1919,"November 11","The Centralia Massacre in Centralia, Washington results in the deaths of four members of the American Legion, and the lynching of a local leader of the Industrial Workers of the World (IWW)."
1919,"December 21","United States deports 249 people, including Emma Goldman to Russia, during the Red Scare."
1919,"circa","Various strikes occur in the United States: Strike of US railroad workers; The Longshoreman's strike; The Great Steel Strike; and a general strike in Seattle, Washington."
1919,"circa","Female suffrage is enacted in Germany and Luxembourg."
1919,"circa","The World League Against Alcoholism is established by the Anti-Saloon League."
1919,"circa","Ethnic cleansing in Turkey: The Armenian Genocide."
1920,"January 7","The forces of Russian White Admiral Kolchak surrender in Krasnoyarsk. The Great Siberian Ice March ensues."
1920,"January 16","Prohibition begins in the United States with the Eighteenth Amendment to the Constitution coming into effect."
1920,"January 16","The World War I Allies demand that the Netherlands extradite the German Kaiser Wilhelm II, who has fled there."
1920,"January 19","The United States Senate votes against joining the League of Nations."
1920,"January 23","The Netherlands refuses to extradite the German Kaiser."
1920,"January 28","Turkey gives up the Ottoman Empire and most of the non-Turkish areas."
1920,"February 2","France occupies Memel."
1920,"February 17","A woman named Anna Anderson tries to commit suicide in Berlin and is taken to a mental hospital, where she claims she is Grand Duchess Anastasia of Russia."
1920,"March 1","The United States Railroad Administration returns control of American railroads to its constituent railroad companies."
1920,"March 13","(March 13 - March 17) Wolfgang Kapp fails in his coup attempt in Germany due to public resistance and a general strike."
1920,"March 15","The Ruhr Red Army, a communist army 60,000 men strong, is formed in Germany."
1920,"March 19","The United States Congress refuses to ratify the Treaty of Versailles."
1920,"March 26","The German government asks France for permission to use its own troops against the rebellious Ruhr Red Army in the French-occupied area."
1920,"April 19","Germany and Bolshevist Russia agree to the exchange of prisoners of war."
1920,"April 26","The Khorezm People's Soviet Republic is officially created by Bolshevist Russia as the successor to the Khanate of Khiva."
1920,"May 7","Treaty of Moscow (1920): Soviet Russia recognizes independence of the Democratic Republic of Georgia only to invade the country six months later."
1920,"May 17","French and Belgian troops leave the cities they have occupied in Germany."
1920,"June 13","The United States Post Office Department rules that children may not be sent via parcel post."
1920,"June 15","A new border treaty between Germany and Denmark gives northern Schleswig to Denmark."
1920,"July 1","Germany declares its neutrality in the war between Poland and Soviet Russia."
1920,"July 12","Bolshevist Russia recognizes independent Lithuania."
1920,"July 22","Polish-Soviet War: Poland sues for peace with Bolshevist Russia."
1920,"July 29","The United States Bureau of Reclamation begins construction of the Link River Dam as part of the Klamath Reclamation Project."
1920,"July 31","France prohibits the sale or prescription of contraceptives."
1920,"August 10","Ottoman Sultan Mehmed VI's representatives sign the Treaty of Sèvres."
1920,"August 11","Bolshevik Russia recognizes independent Estonia and Latvia."
1920,"August 26","The Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution is passed, guaranteeing women's suffrage."
1920,"September 4","[i]El Tercio de Extranjeros[/i], the ""Regiment of Foreigners"" (modern-day Spanish Legion) is inaugurated in Spain."
1920,"October 10","Carinthian Plebiscite: A large part of Carinthia Province votes to become part of Austria rather than Yugoslavia."
1920,"December 16","An 8.6 Richter scale Haiyuan earthquake causes a landslide in Gansu Province, China, killing 180,000."
1920,"December 22","The 8th Congress of Soviets of the Russian SFSR adopts the GOELRO plan, the major plan of the economical development of the country."
1920,"December 23","The United Kingdom and France ratify the border between French-held Syria and British-held Palestine."
1920,"circa","Because there are so many mixed-race persons and because so many Americans with some black ancestry appear white, the United States Census stops counting mixed-race peoples and the [i]one drop rule[/i] becomes the national legal standard."
1921,"January 21","Suffrage for women is obtained in Sweden."
1921,"February 12","The Democratic Republic of Georgia is invaded by Bolshevist Russia."
1921,"February 28","Russian sailors rebel in Kronstadt."
1921,"March 4","Warren G. Harding is inaugurated as the 29th President of the United States."
1921,"March 13","The Russian White Army captures Mongolia from China. Roman Ungern von Sternberg declares himself ruler."
1921,"March 14","Armenian Soghomon Tehlirian assassinates Mehmed Talaat, former Interior Minister of Turkey, in Charlottenburg, Berlin."
1921,"March 23","A plebiscite in Silesia votes for re-annexation to Germany."
1921,"April 14","In Britain, labour unions for mining, railway and transportation workers call for a strike; the government threatens to call in the army."
1921,"May 8","The death penalty is abolished in Sweden."
1921,"July 2","U.S. President Warren Harding signs a joint congressional resolution declaring an end to America's state of war with Germany, Austria and Hungary."
1921,"July 4","A new conservative government is formed in Italy by Ivanoe Bonomi."
1921,"July 22","The Irish Truce is declared in Britain."
1921,"September 21","The Oppau explosion occurs at BASF's nitrate factory in Oppau, Germany; 500-600 are killed."
1921,"November 7","The Partito Nazionale Fascista (PNF), National Fascist Party, comes into existence in Italy."
1921,"December 13","In the Four Power Treaty on Insular Possessions, Japan, the United States, United Kingdom, and France agree to recognize the status quo in the Pacific."
1921,"circa","Regular radio broadcasting services begin in Italy."
1921,"circa","Ethnic cleansing in Turkey:."
1922,"January 13","The flu epidemic has claimed 804 victims in Britain."
1922,"February 6","Five Power Naval Disarmament Treaty signed between United States, Britain, Japan, France, and Italy."
1922,"February 22","Following intense nationalist agitation after World War I, Great Britain proclaims Egypt formally independent but continues to occupy the country militarily and control its politics."
1922,"February 27","A challenge to the Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution, allowing women the right to vote, is rebuffed by the Supreme Court of the United States."
1922,"April 7","Teapot Dome scandal: The United States Secretary of the Interior leases Teapot Dome oil reserves in Wyoming."
1922,"April 10","The historic Genoa Conference commences in Genoa. The representatives of 34 countries convene to speak about monetary economics in the wake of World War I."
1922,"April 15","England's Prince of Wales visits the Japanese paramilitary youth group [i]Seinendan[/i] in annexed Korea."
1922,"April 16","The Treaty of Rapallo marks a rapprochement between the Weimar Republic and Bolshevik Russia."
1922,"August 28","Japan agrees to withdraw its troops from Siberia."
1922,"September 17","Dutch cyclist Piet Moeskops becomes World Champion Sprinter."
1922,"October 1","G.I. Gurdjieff opens his Institute for the Harmonious Development of Man at Fontainebleau in France."
1922,"October 28","In Italy, with the March on Rome, Fascism obtains power and Benito Mussolini becomes prime minister."
1922,"October 30","Benito Mussolini becomes the youngest Premier in the history of Italy."
1922,"November 1","The Ottoman Empire is abolished and its last sultan Mehmed VI Vahdettin abdicates."
1922,"November 17","Former Ottoman sultan Mehmed VI leaves for exile in Italy."
1922,"November 19","Abdul Mejid II, Crown Prince of the Ottoman Empire, is elected Caliph."
1922,"December 30","Russia, Ukraine, Belarus, and the Transcaucasia come together to form the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics."
1922,"circa","The Molly Pitcher Club is formed to promote the repeal of prohibition in the United States."
1922,"circa","Japan signs a naval arms limitation treaty with the Western powers and returns some of its control over the Shandong Peninsula to China."
1923,"January 11","Despite strong British protests, troops from France and Belgium occupy the Ruhr area to force Germany to pay its reparation payments."
1923,"February 23","Albert Einstein visits Barcelona, Spain, at the invitation of scientist Esteban Terradas i Illa."
1923,"June 13","China President Li abandons his residence because a warlord has commanded forces to surround the mansion and cut off its water and electric supplies, in order to force him to abandon his post."
1923,"June 16","The storming of Ayan in Siberia concludes the Yakut Revolt and the Russian Civil War."
1923,"June 18","Mount Etna erupts in Italy, making 60,000 homeless."
1923,"July 24","The Treaty of Lausanne, settling the boundaries of modern Turkey, is signed in Switzerland by Greece, Bulgaria and other countries that fought in the First World War."
1923,"September 1","The Great Kanto earthquake devastates Tokyo and Yokohama, killing an estimated 142,807 people, but according to a Japanese construction research center report in 2005, 105,000 are confirmed dead."
1923,"September 13","Military coup in Spain: Miguel Primo de Rivera takes over, setting up a dictatorship. Trade unions are banned for 10 years."
1923,"October 13","Ankara replaces Istanbul as the capital of Turkey."
1923,"October 29","Turkey becomes a republic following the dissolution of the Ottoman Empire. Kemal Atatürk is elected as the president."
1923,"November 15","The hyperinflation in Germany reaches its height. One United States dollar is worth 4,200,000,000,000,000 Papiermark (4.2 quadrillion). Gustav Stresemann abolishes the old currency."
1923,"November 23","Gustav Stresemann's coalition government collapses in Germany."
1923,"December 12","In Italy, the Po River dam bursts, killing 600."
1923,"December 27","The crown prince of Japan survives an assassination attempt in Tokyo."
1923,"circa","The Moderation League of New York becomes part of the movement for the repeal of prohibition in the United States."
1923,"circa","Struggling for a foothold in southern China, Sun Yatsen decides to ally his Nationalist party or Guomindang (Kuomintang) with the Communist Third International and Chinese Communist Party."
1923,"circa","United States occupation of Haiti (1915-1934)"
1924,"January 25","The 1924 Winter Olympics open in Chamonix, France (in the French Alps)."
1924,"April 6","Fascists win the elections in Italy with a - majority."
1924,"May 4","The 1924 Summer Olympics opening ceremonies are held in Paris, France."
1924,"August 18","France begins to withdraw its troops from Germany."
1924,"November 21","Ali Fethi Okyar forms new government in Turkey. (3rd government)"
1924,"circa","The powerful opiate hydromorphone is developed in Germany."
1925,"January 3","Benito Mussolini ([i]Il Duce[/i]) announces he is taking dictatorial powers over Italy."
1925,"March 4","Ismet Inönü is appointed as the prime minister in Turkey (Turkey's 4th and Inönü's 3rd government)."
1925,"April 25","Fritz Haarmann, a serial killer convicted of the murder of 24 boys and young men, is beheaded in Germany."
1925,"May 5","The General Election Law is passed in Japan."
1925,"August 25","The French evacuate the Ruhr region of Germany."
1926,"January 1","Turkey switches to the Gregorian calendar after reforms set by Kemal Atatürk."
1926,"February 25","Francisco Franco becomes General of Spain."
1926,"April 12","By a vote of 45-41, the United States Senate unseats Iowa Senator Smith W. Brookhart and seats Daniel F. Steck, after Brookhart had already served for over one year."
1926,"April 24","Treaty of Berlin: Germany and the Soviet Union each pledge neutrality in the event of an attack on the other by a third party for the next 5 years."
1926,"May 1","A coal miners' strike begins in Britain."
1926,"May 9","Martial law is declared in Britain because of the general strike."
1926,"July 1","The Kuomingtang begins a military unification campaign in northern China."
1926,"July 26","The National Bar Association incorporates in the United States."
1926,"September 11","Spain leaves the League of Nations."
1926,"October 23","A decree in Italy bans women from holding public office."
1926,"November 25","The death penalty is re-established in Italy."
1926,"December 18","Turkey converts to the Gregorian calendar, making 'tomorrow' January 1 1927."
1926,"December 26","In Japanese History, the Showa era begins from this day due to the demise of Emperor Taisho on the day before."
1927,"January 19","Britain sends troops to China."
1927,"January 30","Right-wing veterans and the [i]Republican Schutzbund[/i] clash in Schattendorf, Burgenland, Austria. One man and a child are killed by gunshots."
1927,"March 7","A Richter Scale 7.6 magnitude earthquake kills at least 2,925 at Toyooka and Mineyama area, western Honshu, Japan."
1927,"March 13","Fritz Lang's culturally influential [i]Metropolis (film)[/i] debuts in Germany."
1927,"April 18","The Kuomintang sets up a government in Nanking, China."
1927,"April 21","A banking crisis hits Japan."
1927,"May 13","George V proclaims the change of his title from King of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland to King of Great Britain and Ireland."
1927,"May 22","An 8.6 magnitude earthquake in Xining, China kills 200,000."
1927,"May 24","Britain severs diplomatic relations with the Soviet Union because of revelations of espionage and underground agitation."
1927,"June 13","Leon Daudet, leader of the French monarchists, is arrested in France."
1927,"July 15","85 protesters and 5 policemen are dead after left-wing protesters and the Austrian police clash in Vienna. More than 600 people are injured."
1927,"September 14","An underwater earthquake in Japan kills over 100 people."
1927,"October 6","[i]The Jazz Singer[/i] movie opens in the United States and becomes a huge success, although it would be awhile before silent films are completely gone."
1927,"October 8","[i]Murderer's Row[/i]: The New York Yankees complete a 4-game sweep of the Pittsburgh Pirates in the World Series."
1927,"November 1","Ismet Inönü forms the new government in Turkey. (5th government)"
1927,"December 17","The [i]U.S. submarine S-4[/i] is accidentally rammed and sunk by the United States Coast Guard destroyer [i]John Paulding[/i] off Provincetown, Massachusetts, killing everyone aboard after several unsuccessful attempts to raise the sub."
1927,"circa","World population reaches 2 billion."
1928,"February 20","A swung parliament is produced in Japan after the general election."
1928,"May 3","Jinan Incident, an armed conflict between the Japanese Imperial Army allied with Northern Chinese warlords against the Kuomintang's southern army, occurs in Jinan, China."
1928,"June 4","Huanggutun Incident: Zhang Zuolin, President of the Republic of China and warlord, is killed by Japanese agents."
1928,"July 25","The United States recalls its troops from China."
1928,"August 2","Italy and Ethiopia sign the Italo-Ethiopian Treaty."
1928,"October 8","Chiang Kai-shek is named as Generalissimo (Chairman of the National Military Council) of the Nationalist Government of the Republic of China."
1928,"November 10","Enthronement ceremony of Japanese Emperor Hirohito is held, after some two years since he actually took the Imperial throne on December 26, 1926, the following day of the demise of Emperor Taisho."
1928,"circa","Turkey switches from the Arabic to the Latin-based modern Turkish alphabet."
1928,"circa","The Episcopal Church in the United States of America ratifies a new revision of the Book of Common Prayer."
1929,"February 11","Italy and the Vatican sign the Lateran Treaty."
1929,"March 28","Japanese forces withdraw from Shandong province to their garrison in Tsingtao bringing an end to the Jinan Incident."
1929,"July 11","In Russia, a secret decree of the Sovnarkom creates the backbone of the Gulag system."
1929,"August 31","The Young Plan, which set the total World War I reparations owed by Germany at US$26,350,000,000 to be paid over a period of 58½ years, is finalized."
1929,"September 5","Aristide Briand presents his plan for the [i]United States of Europe[/i]."
1929,"October 18","Women are announced to be persons by the Judicial Committee of the Privy Council in Britain. Women can be appointed to the Canadian Senate, an achievement by five Canadian women called the Famous Five."
1929,"October 22","The government of Aristide Briand falls in France."
1930,"April 22","The United Kingdom, Japan and the United States sign the London Naval Treaty regulating submarine warfare and limiting shipbuilding."
1930,"June 21","One-year conscription comes into force in France."
1930,"September 27","Ismet Inönü forms new government in Turkey. (6th government)"
1930,"October 5","British [i]Airship R101[/i] crashes in France en-route to India on its maiden voyage."
1930,"November 25","An earthquake in the Izu Peninsula of Japan kills 223 people and destroys 650 buildings."
1930,"December 28","Mahatma Gandhi leaves for Britain for negotiations."
1930,"circa","A Jake paralysis outbreak occurs in United States."
1931,"January 27","Pierre Laval forms a government in France."
1931,"March 3","[i]The Star-Spangled Banner[/i] is adopted as the United States National anthem."
1931,"April 22","Austria, Britain, Denmark, Germany, Italy, Sweden and the USA recognize the Spanish Republic."
1931,"May 4","Kemal Atatürk is re-elected president of Turkey."
1931,"May 5","Ismet Inönü forms new government in Turkey. (7th government)"
1931,"November 21","Ali Fethi Okyar forms new government in Turkey. (3rd government)"
1931,"May 11","The [i]Creditanstalt[/i], Austria's largest bank, goes bankrupt, beginning the banking collapse in Central Europe that causes a worldwide financial meltdown."
1931,"May 13","Paul Doumer is elected president of France."
1931,"June 5","German Chancellor Dr. Heinrich Brüning visits London, where he warns the British Prime Minister Ramsay MacDonald that the collapse of the Austrian banking system, caused by the bankruptcy of the [i]Creditanstalt[/i], has left the entire German banking system on the verge of collapse."
1931,"June 14","The overloaded pleasure craft [i]Saint-Philibert[/i], carrying trippers home to Nantes from Île de Noirmoutier, sinks at the mouth of the river Loire in France; over 450 drown."
1931,"July 1","Milan Central Station officially opens in Italy."
1931,"August 24","The Labour Government of Ramsay MacDonald resigns in Britain, replaced by a National Government of people drawn from all parties, also under MacDonald."
1931,"September 18","Japan stages the Mukden Incident as a pretext to occupy Manchuria."
1931,"December 8","Carl Friedrich Goerdeler is appointed Reich Price Commissioner in Germany to enforce the deflationary policies of the Brüning government."
1931,"December 13","Wakatsuki Reijiro resigns as Prime Minister of Japan."
1932,"January 1","The United States Post Office Department issues a set of 12 stamps commemorating the 200th anniversary of George Washington's birth."
1932,"January 7","The Stimson Doctrine is proclaimed, in response to the Japanese invasion of Manchuria."
1932,"January 8","In Britain the Archbishop of Canterbury forbids church remarriage of divorced persons."
1932,"January 15","About 6 million are unemployed in Germany."
1932,"January 28","Conflict between Japan and China in the Battle of Shanghai."
1932,"January 29","The minority government of Karl Buresch in Austria ends the governmental crisis."
1932,"January 31","Japanese warships arrive in Nanking."
1932,"February 2","The League of Nations again recommends negotiations between the Republic of China and Japan."
1932,"February 4","Japan occupies Harbin, China."
1932,"February 18","Japan declares Manzhouguo (Japanese name for Manchuria) formally independent from China."
1932,"March 18","Peace negotiations between China and Japan begin."
1932,"April 10","Paul von Hindenburg is elected president of Germany."
1932,"May 10","Albert Lebrun becomes the new president of France."
1932,"May 15","Japanese troops leave Shanghai; the May 15 Incident, the assassination of Japanese prime minister Tsuyoshi Inukai, occurs."
1932,"June 14","Bans against the SS and SA are overturned in Germany."
1932,"July 17","Bloody Sunday: In Altona, Germany, armed communists attack a National Socialist demonstration; 18 are killed. Many other political street fights follow."
1932,"July 28","U.S. President Herbert Hoover orders the U.S. Army to forcibly evict the Bonus Army of World War I veterans gathered in Washington, D.C.. Troops disperse the last of the Bonus Army the next day."
1932,"August","A farmers' revolt begins in the Midwestern United States."
1932,"October 19","Prince Gustav Adolf of Sweden marries Princess Sibylla of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha."
1932,"November 16","New York City's Palace Theatre fully converts to a cinema, which is considered the final death knell of vaudeville as a popular entertainment in the United States."
1932,"December 12","Japan and the Soviet Union reform their diplomatic connections."
1932,"December 19","BBC World Service begins broadcasting as the BBC Empire Service."
1932,"December 25","An earthquake in the Kansu Province in China kills 70,000."
1933,"January 15","Political violence causes almost 100 deaths in Spain."
1933,"January 23","The Twentieth Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, changing Inauguration Day from March 4 to January 20."
1933,"January 30","Nazi leader Adolf Hitler is appointed Chancellor of Germany by President of Germany Paul von Hindenburg."
1933,"February 6","The 20th Amendment to the United States Constitution goes into effect."
1933,"February 27","Germany's parliament building in Berlin, the Reichstag, is set on fire."
1933,"March 3","A powerful earthquake and tsunami hit Honshu, Japan, killing some 3,000."
1933,"March 4","U.S. President Herbert Hoover is succeeded by Franklin D. Roosevelt, who in reference to the Great Depression, proclaims ""The only thing we have to fear, is fear itself"" in his inauguration speech. FDR is sworn in by Chief Justice Charles Evans Hughes. It is also the last time Inauguration Day in the United States occurs on March 4."
1933,"March 4","The Parliament of Austria is suspended because of a quibble over procedure; Chancellor Engelbert Dollfuss initiates authoritarian rule by decree."
1933,"March 15","Austrian Chancellor Engelbert Dollfuss keeps members of the National Council from convening, starting the Austrofascist dictatorship."
1933,"March 27","Japan leaves the League of Nations."
1933,"April 1","The recently elected Nazis under Julius Streicher organize a one-day boycott of all Jewish-owned businesses in Germany."
1933,"April 7","Beer is legalized in the United States, eight months before the full repeal of Prohibition in December."
1933,"April 7","The Law for the Restoration of the Professional Civil Service is passed in Germany."
1933,"April 19","The United States officially goes off the gold standard."
1933,"April 21","Nazi Germany outlaws the kosher ritual shechita."
1933,"April 26","The Gestapo is established in Germany."
1933,"May 10","In Germany, the Nazis stage massive public book burnings."
1933,"May 26","The Nazi Party in Germany introduces a law to legalize eugenic sterilization."
1933,"May 27","The [i]Century of Progress[/i] World's Fair opens in Chicago."
1933,"June 5","The U.S. Congress abrogates the United States' use of the gold standard by enacting a joint resolution (48 Stat. 112) nullifying the right of creditors to demand payment in gold."
1933,"June 21","All non-Nazi parties are forbidden in Germany."
1933,"July 14","Forming new political parties is forbidden in Germany."
1933,"August 25","The Diexi earthquake shakes Mao County, Sichuan, China and kills 9,000 people."
1933,"August 30","[i]Air France[/i] begins operations with 250 planes."
1933,"September 3","Alejandro Lerroux forms a new government in Spain."
1933,"October 12","The United States Army Disciplinary Barracks on Alcatraz is acquired by the United States Department of Justice, which plans to incorporate the island into its Federal Bureau of Prisons as a federal penitentiary."
1933,"October 16","Germany announces its intention to officially leave the League of Nations."
1933,"October 17","Albert Einstein arrives in the United States as a refugee from Nazi Germany."
1933,"November 16","The United States and the Soviet Union establish formal diplomatic relations."
1933,"December 5","The 21st Amendment to the United States Constitution, repealing Prohibition, goes into effect."
1933,"December 24","A train crash in Lagny, France kills over 200."
1933,"December 26","The Nissan Motor Company is organized in Tokyo, Japan."
1933,"circa","The United States Federal Government ends Prohibition and outlaws cannabis."
1933,"circa","A coup attempt against Franklin Delano Roosevelt fails in the United States (see Smedley Butler)."
1933,"circa","Nazi Germany forms the [i]Expert Committee on Questions of Population and Racial Policy[/i] under Reich Interior Minister Wilhelm Frick."
1933,"circa","5 coalition cabinets form and fall in France."
1933,"circa","Turkey concluded a treaty with the creditors of former Ottoman Empire to schedule the payments in Paris. (Turkey succeeded to clear all the debts of Ottoman Empire in less than 20 years.)"
1934,"January 1","Nazi Germany passes the ""Law for the Prevention of Hereditarily Diseased Offspring""."
1934,"January 10","Marinus van der Lubbe is executed in Germany."
1934,"January 26","The 10 year German-Polish Non-Aggression Pact is signed by Germany and the Second Polish Republic."
1934,"February 9","Gaston Doumergue forms a new government in France."
1934,"February 12","(February 12 - February 16) Austrian Civil War."
1934,"March 1","Manchuria becomes Manchukuo, following an invasion by the Japanese."
1934,"March 8","Prince Sigvard of Sweden loses his titles because of his marriage."
1934,"March 24","The Philippine Commonwealth becomes established allowing for more self-government from the United States."
1934,"May 15","The United States Department of Justice offers a $25,000 reward for John Dillinger."
1934,"May 29","(May 29 - May 31) The Confessional Synod of the German Evangelical Church meets in Barmen, Germany to write the Barmen Declaration."
1934,"June 10","Italy beats Czechoslovakia 2-1 after extra time to win the 1934 World Cup."
1934,"July 1","The Hays Office censorship code for motion pictures goes into full effect in the United States."
1934,"July 25","Austrian Nazis assassinate chancellor Engelbert Dollfuss during a failed coup attempt."
1934,"August 2","Adolf Hitler becomes [i]Führer[/i] of Germany, becoming head of state as well as Chancellor."
1934,"September 21","A typhoon in Honshu, Japan kills 3,036 people, and destroys the temple, schools, and other buildings in Osaka."
1934,"October 5","Miners rebel in Asturias, Spain (Asturian miners' strike of 1934)."
1934,"October 6","Catalonian separatists rebel in Spain."
1934,"December 29","Japan renounces the Washington Naval Treaty of 1922 and the London Naval Treaty of 1930."
1934,"circa","This year is the hottest year in the United States on record."
1935,"January 13","A plebiscite in the Saarland shows that 90.3% of those voting wish to join Germany."
1935,"March 1","Ismet Inönü forms the new government in Turkey. (8th government; During Atatürk's presidency, Inönü had served seven times as a prime minister.)"
1935,"June 9","He-Umezu Agreement: China's Kuomintang government concedes Japanese military control of north-eastern China."
1935,"June 18","Anglo-German Naval Agreement: Britain agrees to a German navy equal to 35% of her own naval tonnage."
1935,"September 2","Labor Day Hurricane of 1935: The strongest hurricane ever to strike the United States landfalls in the Upper Florida Keys as a Category 5 storm with 185 mph winds, killing 423."
1935,"September 15","The Nuremberg Laws go into effect in Germany."
1935,"October 2","(October 2 - October 3) The Second Italo-Abyssinian War begins as General Emilio de Bono of Italy invades Ethiopia."
1935,"October 10","A tornado destroys the 160 metre tall wooden radio tower in Langenberg, Germany. As a result of this catastrophe wooden radio towers are phased out."
1935,"November 14","In the General Election in Britain, Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin returns to office at the head of a National Government led by the Conservative Party with a large but reduced majority."
1935,"December 27","Mao Zedong issues the Wayaopao Manifesto, [i]On Tactics Against Japanese Imperialism[/i], calling for a National United Front against the Japanese Invasion."
1936,"February 6","The IV Olympic Winter Games open in Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany."
1936,"February 26","The Imperial Way Faction engineers a failed coup against the Japanese government; some politicians are killed."
1936,"February 29","Emperor Hirohito orders the Japanese army to arrest 123 conspirators in Tokyo government offices; 19 of them are executed in July."
1936,"March 7","In violation of the Treaty of Versailles, Nazi Germany reoccupies the Rhineland."
1936,"March 9","Pro-democratic militarist Keisuke Okada steps down as Prime Minister of Japan and is replaced by radical militarist Koki Hirota."
1936,"May 2","[i]Peter and the Wolf[/i], a Russian fairy tale of Sergei Prokofiev's composition, debuts at the Nezlobin Theater in Moscow, Soviet Union."
1936,"May 7","Italy annexes Ethiopia."
1936,"May 12","The Santa Fe railroad in the United States inaugurates the all-Pullman [i]Super Chief[/i] passenger train between Chicago, Illinois and Los Angeles, California."
1936,"June 7","The general strike in France is ended by the Matignon Agreements."
1936,"August 14","Rainey Bethea was hanged in Owensboro, Kentucky, in the last public execution in the United States."
1936,"August 30","Ernest Nash flees Germany for Rome."
1936,"October 19","H.R. Ekins, reporter for the [i]New York World-Telegram[/i], wins a race to travel around the world on commercial airline flights, beating out Dorothy Kilgallen of the [i]New York Journal[/i] and Leo Kieran of the [i]New York Times[/i]. The flight takes 18½ days."
1936,"November 20","A levee failure and continued massive rain at the Mitsubishi Osarizawa mine, Kazuno, northeastern Akita, Japan, results in at least 375 deaths."
1936,"November 26","The Anti-Comintern Pact is signed by Germany and Japan."
1936,"December 11","The abdicated King Edward VIII, now HRH Prince Edward, makes a broadcast to the nation explaining his decision to abdicate. He leaves the country for Austria."
1936,"December 12","Xi'an Incident: Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek of the Republic of China is kidnapped by Zhang Xueliang."
1937,"February 5","President Franklin D. Roosevelt proposes a plan to enlarge the Supreme Court of the United States."
1937,"March 10","The Encyclical [i]Mit brennender Sorge[/i] of Pope Pius XI is published in Nazi Germany."
1937,"March 18","Mother Frances Hospital opens 1 day later in Tyler, Texas in response to the New London School explosion."
1937,"April 26","Spanish Civil War: Guernica, Spain is bombed. In his report of the Falangist attack on Guernica, British journalist George Steer reports finding German bomb casings, connecting Luftwaffe planes with the attack."
1937,"May 1","A general strike occurs in Paris, France."
1937,"May 6","In the United States, the German airship Hindenburg bursts into flame when mooring to a mast in Lakehurst, New Jersey."
1937,"May 7","Spanish Civil War: The German Condor Legion Fighter Group, equipped with Heinkel He 51 biplanes, arrives in Spain to assist Francisco Franco's forces."
1937,"June 8","Carl Orff's [i]Carmina Burana[/i] premieres in Frankfurt, Germany."
1937,"June 21","The coalition government of Léon Blum resigns in France."
1937,"July 7","Sino-Japanese War - Battle of Lugou Bridge (aka Marco Polo Bridge Incident): Japanese forces invade China (often seen as the beginning of World War II in Asia)."
1937,"July 20","The Geibeltbad Pirna is opened in Dresden, Germany."
1937,"July 22","New Deal: The United States Senate votes down President Franklin D. Roosevelt's proposal to add more justices to the Supreme Court of the United States."
1937,"August 26","Sino-Japanese War: Japanese aircraft attack the car carrying the ambassador of Great Britain during a raid on Shanghai."
1937,"September 25","Sino-Japanese War - Battle of Pingxingguan: The Communist Chinese National Revolutionary Army defeats the Japanese."
1937,"October 3","Japanese troops advance toward Nanking."
1937,"October 13","Germany, in a note to Brussels, guarantees the inviolability and integrity of Belgium so long as the latter abstains from military action against Germany."
1937,"October 25","Celal Bayar forms the new government of Turkey. (9th government)"
1937,"October 27","Spanish Civil War: Republican forces in Gijon, Spain, set fire to petrol reserves before they retreat before the advancing Falangists."
1937,"November 5","World War II: In the Reich Chancellery, Adolf Hitler holds a secret meeting and states his plans for acquiring ""living space"" for the German people (Hossbach Memorandum)."
1937,"November 6","Italy joins the Anti-Comintern Pact."
1937,"November 9","Japanese troops take Shanghai."
1937,"November 11","The Kogushi sulfur mine collapse, in western Gunma, Japan, kills at least 245 people."
1937,"December 11","Italy withdraws from the League of Nations."
1937,"December 12","Panay incident: Japanese bombers sink the American gunboat USS Panay (PR-5)"
1937,"December 13","The Battle of Nanjing ends and the Nanjing Massacre begins. Japanese troops slaughter over 300,000 civilians and prisoners over 3 months."
1937,"circa","Japan occupies Beijing."
1937,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1938,"February 12","Chancellor Kurt von Schuschnigg of Austria meets Adolf Hitler at Berchtesgaden and, under threat of invasion, is forced to yield to German demands for greater Nazi participation in the Austrian government."
1938,"February 20","Sir Anthony Eden resigns as British Foreign Secretary following major disagreements with Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain over the best policy to follow in regards to Italy, and is succeeded by Lord Halifax."
1938,"March 3","Sir Nevile Henderson, British Ambassador to Germany, presents a proposal to Hitler for an international consortium to rule much of Africa (in which Germany would be assigned a leading role) in exchange for a German promise never to resort to war to change her frontiers; Hitler rejects the British offer."
1938,"March 12","[i]Anschluss:[/i] German troops occupy Austria; annexation is declared the following day."
1938,"March 14","French Premier Leon Blum reassures the Czechoslovak government that France will honor its treaty obligations to aid Czechoslovakia in event of German invasion."
1938,"April 10","In a result that astonished even Hitler, the Austrian electorate in a national referendum approved Anschluss by an overwhelming 99.73%."
1938,"April 16","London and Rome sign an agreement that sees Britain recognise Italian control of Ethiopia in return for an Italian pledge to withdraw all it's troops from Spain at the conclusion of the civil war there."
1938,"May 5","The Vatican recognizes Franco's government in Spain."
1938,"May 5","General Ludwig Beck, Chief of the German Army's General Staff, submits a memorandum to Hitler opposing [i]Fall Grün[/i] (Case Green), the plan for a war with Czechoslovakia, under the grounds that Germany is ill-prepared for the world war likely to result from such an attack."
1938,"May 12","U.S. Secretary of State Cordell Hull rejects Russia's offer of a joint defence pact to counter rise of Nazi Germany."
1938,"May 25","Spanish Civil War: Alicante, Spain is bombed, resulting in 313 deaths."
1938,"May 25","The Soviet ambassador to the United States A.A. Troyanovsky declared that Moscow was ready to defend Czechoslovakia. This offer was ignored by Britain and the U.S.A."
1938,"June 15","László Bíró patents the ballpoint pen in Britain."
1938,"June 19","Italy beats Hungary 4-2 to win the 1938 World Cup."
1938,"July","The Mauthausen concentration camp is built in Austria."
1938,"July 5","The Non-Intervention Committee reaches an agreement to withdraw all foreign volunteers from the Spanish Civil War. The agreement is respected by most Republican foreign volunteers, notably by those from England and the United States, but is ignored by the governments of Germany and Italy."
1938,"July 12","The Turkish army carries out the Kurdish Genocide in Dersim, Turkey."
1938,"August","In the face of overwhelming Japanese military pressure, Chiang Kai-shek withdraws his government to Chungking."
1938,"August 18","The Thousand Islands Bridge, connecting the United States with Canada, is dedicated by U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt."
1938,"August 31","Winston Churchill, still believing France and Britain mean to honor their promises to defend Czechoslovakia against Nazi aggression, suggests in a personal note to Neville Chamberlain that His Majesty's Government may want to set up a broad international alliance including the United States (specifically mentioning U.S. President Franklin Delano Roosevelt as possibly receptive to the idea) and the Soviet Union."
1938,"September 2","Soviet Ambassador to Britain Ivan Maisky calls on Winston Churchill, to tell him that Soviet Foreign Commissar Maxim Litvinov has expressed to the French charge d'affaire in Moscow that the Soviet Union is willing to fight over the territorial integrity of Czechoslovakia."
1938,"September 4","During the ceremony marking the unveiling of a plaque at Pointe de Grave, France celebrating Franco-American friendship, American Ambassador William Bullitt in a speech states, ""France and the United States were united in war and peace"", leading to much speculation in the press that if war did break out over Czechoslovakia, then the United States would join the war on the Allied side."
1938,"September 7","[i]The Times[/i] publishes a lead article which calls on Czechoslovakia to cede the Sudetenland to Germany."
1938,"September 21","In the early hours of the day, representatives of the French and British governments call on Czechoslovak President Edvard Bene to tell him France and Britain will not fight Hitler if he decides to annex the Sudetenland by force. Late in the afternoon the Czechoslovak government capitulates to the French and British demands."
1938,"September 30","Neville Chamberlain returns to Britain from meeting with Adolf Hitler and declares ""Peace for our time""."
1938,"October","The Japanese Imperial Army largely overruns Canton."
1938,"October 16","Winston Churchill, in a broadcast address to the United States, condemns the Munich Agreement as a defeat and calls upon America and western Europe to prepare for armed resistance against Hitler."
1938,"October 24","The minimum wage is established by law in the United States."
1938,"October 24","At a ""friendly luncheon"" in Berchtesgaden, German foreign minister Joachim von Ribbentrop tells Józef Lipski, the Polish ambassador to Germany, that the Free City of Danzig must return to Germany, that the Germans must be given extraterritorial rights in the Polish Corridor, and that Poland must sign the Anti-Comintern Pact."
1938,"October 30","Orson Welles's radio adaptation of [i]The War of the Worlds[/i] is broadcast, causing panic in various parts of the United States."
1938,"November 9","Holocaust - Kristallnacht: In Germany, the ""night of broken glass"" begins as Nazi activists and sympathizers loot and burn Jewish businesses (the all night affair sees 7,500 Jewish businesses destroyed, 267 synagogues burned, 91 Jews killed, and at least 25,000 Jewish men arrested)."
1938,"November 11","Celal Bayar forms the new government of Turkey. (10 th government; Celal Bayar had served twice as a prime minister)"
1938,"November 30","Benito Mussolini and his Foreign Minister Count Galeazzo Ciano order ""spontaneous"" demonstrations in the Italian Chamber of Deputies, demanding that France cede Tunisia, Nice, Corsica and French Somaliland to Italy. This begins an acute crisis in Franco-Italian relations that lasts until March 1939."
1938,"November 30","A general strike is called in France by the French Communist Party to protest the laws of November 12."
1938,"December","President Roosevelt agrees to loan $25 million to Chiang Kai-shek, cementing the Sino-American relationship and angering the Japanese government."
1938,"December 6","German Foreign Minister Joachim von Ribbentrop visits Paris, where he is allegedly informed by French Foreign Minister Georges Bonnet that France now recognizes all of Eastern Europe as being in Germany's exclusive sphere of influence. Bonnet's alleged statement (Bonnet always denied making the remark) to Ribbentrop is a major factor in German policy in 1939."
1938,"December 27","A massive avalanche of snow hits a construction worker dormitory site in Kurobe, Japan, killing 87."
1938,"circa","The Walther P38 pistol is introduced in Germany."
1938,"circa","Women are limited by law to a maximum of 10% of the better-paying jobs in industry and government in Italy."
1938,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)."
1938,"circa","Under regime of Nazi Germany, many countries cease participation in the ICPC organization. (1938-1945)"
1939,"January 23","Dutch War Scare"": Admiral Wilhelm Canaris of the [i]Abwehr[/i] leaks misinformation to the effect that Germany plans to invade the Netherlands in February, with the aim of using Dutch air-fields to launch a strategic bombing offensive against Britain. The ""Dutch War Scare"" leads to a major change in British policies towards Europe."
1939,"January 25","Refik Saydam forms the new government of Turkey. (11 th government)"
1939,"January 26","Spanish Civil War: Spanish Nationalist troops, aided by Italy, take Barcelona."
1939,"January 30","Hitler gives a speech before the [i]Reichstag[/i] calling for an ""export battle"" to increase German foreign exchange holdings. The same speech also sees Hitler's ""prophecy"" where he warns that if ""Jewish financers"" start a war against Germany, the ""...result will be the annihilation of the Jewish race in Europe""."
1939,"February 6","British Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain states in the House of Commons that any German attack on France will be automatically considered an attack on Britain."
1939,"February 6","In a response to Georges Bonnet's speech of January 26, German Foreign Minister Joachim von Ribbentrop, referring to Bonnet's alleged statement of December 6, 1938 accepting Eastern Europe as being in Germany's exclusive sphere of influence, protests that all French security commitments in that region are ""now off limits""."
1939,"February 27","The United Kingdom and France recognize Franco's government."
1939,"February 27","Sit-down strikes are outlawed by the Supreme Court of the United States."
1939,"March 1","A Japanese Imperial Army ammunition dump explosion on the outskirts of Osaka kills 94."
1939,"March 17","British Prime Minister Neville Chamberlain gives a speech in Birmingham, stating that Britain will oppose any effort at world domination on the part of Germany."
1939,"March 22","After an ultimatum of March 20, Nazi Germany takes Memelland from Lithuania."
1939,"April 3","Refik Saydam forms the new government in Turkey. (12 th government; Refik Saydam had served twice as a prime minister )"
1939,"April 7","Italy invades Albania; King Zog flees."
1939,"April 13","Britain offers a ""guarantee"" to Romania and Greece."
1939,"April 14","At a meeting in Paris, French Foreign Minister Georges Bonnet meets with Soviet Ambassador Jakob Suritz, and suggests that a ""peace front"" comprising France, the Soviet Union, Great Britain, Poland and Romania would deter Germany from war."
1939,"April 30","The 1939 New York World's Fair opens."
1939,"May 9","Spain leaves the League of Nations."
1939,"May 17","Sweden, Norway, and Finland refuse Germany's offer of non-aggression pacts."
1939,"May 22","Germany and Italy sign the Pact of Steel."
1939,"June 14","Tientsin Incident: The Japanese blockade the British concession in Tianjin, China, beginning a crisis which almost causes an Anglo-Japanese war in the summer of 1939."
1939,"June 17","In the last [i]public[/i] guillotining in France, murderer Eugen Weidmann is decapitated by the guillotine."
1939,"June 23","Talks are completed in Ankara between French Ambassador René Massigli and Turkish Foreign Minister Sükrü Saracoglu, resolving the Hatay dispute in Turkey's favor. Turkey annexes Hatay."
1939,"July 2","The 1st World Science Fiction Convention opens in New York City."
1939,"July 6","The last remaining Jewish enterprises in Germany are closed by the Nazis."
1939,"August 19","Hitler, after evaluating the pace of the non-aggression negotiations with the Soviet Union, orders the Kriegsmarine to begin the opening operations for Fall Weiss, the invasion of Poland. The [i]Graf Spee[/i], along with the [i]Deutschland[/i], as well as dozens of u-boats, cast off for their advance positions. According to William L. Shirer, Hitler spends the next few days worrying that the Russians will not come to terms in time for the rest of the invasion plans to unfold as scheduled."
1939,"August 20","Armored forces under the command of Soviet General Georgi Zhukov deliver a decisive defeat to Japanese Imperial Army forces in the Japanese-Soviet border war in Inner Mongolia."
1939,"August 23","Molotov-Ribbentrop Pact: Hitler and Stalin agree to divide Europe between themselves (Finland, Estonia, Latvia, eastern Poland and Basarabia (today Moldavia), north-east province of Romania to the USSR; Lithuania and western Poland to Germany)."
1939,"August 25","The German Foreign Ministry cuts off all telegraph and telephone communication with the outside world in accordance with the plan for Fall Weiss. At approximately 1830 Central European time, Adolf Hitler postpones [i]Fall Weiss[/i] for 5 days, after receiving a message from Benito Mussolini that he will not honor the Pact of Steel if Germany attacks Poland, and because Chamberlain's government has not fallen as a result of the German-Soviet Non-Aggression Pact. Some units already in their forward positions (the attack is scheduled for 0430 the next day) do not get the word in time and attack various targets along the border. That same day, Neville Chamberlain gives Edward Rydz-Smigly his ""ironclad guarantee"" of assistance if Poland is attacked by Germany."
1939,"August 30","Poland begins a mobilization against Nazi Germany."
1939,"September 3","World War II: The United Kingdom, France, New Zealand and Australia declare war on Germany."
1939,"September 4","World War II: Nepal declares war on Germany."
1939,"September 5","World War II: The United States declares its neutrality in the war."
1939,"September 6","World War II: South Africa declares war on Germany."
1939,"September 8","World War II: Forward elements of General Hoeppner's XVI Panzerkorps take up positions outside Warsaw. The world is stunned by the rapidity of the German advance and the Polish High Command is effectively isolated, but lack of infantry support and effective civilian resistance cause Hoeppner to halt outside the city itself."
1939,"September 8","World War II: Polish troops on the Westerplatte are forced, due to lack of food and ammunition, to surrender. The garrison of about two hundred had held out against thousands of German forces (many of them Naval officer cadets from the [i]Schleswig-Holstein,[/i]) for seven days."
1939,"September 10","World War II: Canada declares war on Germany."
1939,"September 15","World War II: Diverse elements of the German Wehrmacht surround Warsaw and demand its surrender. The Poles refuse and the siege begins in earnest."
1939,"September 16","A ceasefire ends the undeclared Border War between The Soviet Union (and Mongolian allies) and Japan."
1939,"September 17","World War II: The Soviet Union invades Poland and then occupies eastern Polish territories."
1939,"September 19","World War II: The Poznan pocket collapses, and the Germans capture, according to many sources, over 150,000 men. Many elements of General Kutrzeba's forces work their way into Warsaw under extreme difficulty."
1939,"September 22","World War II: Joint victory parade of Wehrmacht and Red Army in Brest-Litovsk at the end of the Invasion of Poland."
1939,"October 8","World War II: Germany annexes Western Poland."
1939,"October 11","Manhattan Project: U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt is presented a letter signed by Albert Einstein, urging the United States to rapidly develop the atomic bomb."
1939,"November 6","World War II - Sonderaktion Krakau: Germans take action against scientists from the University of Kraków and other Kraków universities at the beginning of World War II."
1939,"November 30","Sweden declares non-belligerency in the Winter War."
1939,"December 4","World War II: [i]HMS Nelson[/i] is struck by a mine (laid by [i]U-31[/i]) off the Scottish coast and is laid up for repairs until August 1940."
1939,"December 12","World War II: [i]HMS Duchess[/i] sinks after a collision with [i]HMS Barham[/i] off the coast of Scotland with the loss of 124 men."
1939,"December 13","World War II - Battle of the River Plate: The German pocket battleship, [i]Admiral Graf Spee[/i] is trapped by cruisers HMS [i]Ajax[/i], HMNZS [i]Achilles[/i], and HMS [i]Exeter[/i] after a running battle off the coast of Uruguay. [i]Admiral Graf Spee[/i] is scuttled by its crew off Montevideo harbor on December 17."
1939,"December 27","The 1939 Erzincan earthquake in Eastern Anatolia, Turkey, kills 30,000."
1939,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1939,"circa","World War II (1939-1945)"
1940,"January 4","World War II - (Axis powers): Luftwaffe General Hermann Göring assumes control of all war industries in Germany."
1940,"January 6","World War II - Winter War: General Semyon Timoshenko takes command of all Russian forces."
1940,"January 8","World War II - Winter War - Battle of Suomussalmi: The Russian 44th Assault Division is destroyed by Finnish forces."
1940,"January 8","World War II - Food rationing begins in Great Britain."
1940,"January 10","World War II - Mechelen Incident: A German plane carrying secret plans for the invasion of western Europe makes a forced landing in Belgium, leading to mobilization of defense forces in the Low Countries."
1940,"January 27","World War II: A peace resolution introduced in the Parliament of South Africa is defeated 81-59."
1940,"January 29","Three gasoline-powered trains carrying factory workers crash and explode while approaching Ajikawaguchi station, Yumesaki Line (Nishinari Line), Osaka, Japan, killing at least 181 people and injuring at least 92."
1940,"February 1","World War II: Winter War - Russian forces launch a major assault on Finnish troops occupying the Karelian Isthmus."
1940,"February 16","World War II - Altmark Incident: The British destroyer [i]Cossack[/i] pursues the German tanker [i]Altmark[/i] into Jøssingfjord in southwestern Norway."
1940,"March 3","In Sweden, a time bomb destroys the office of [i]Norrskenflamman[/i] (a Swedish communist newspaper), killing 5."
1940,"March 18","World War II - Axis powers: Adolf Hitler and Benito Mussolini meet at Brenner Pass in the Alps and agree to form an alliance against France and the United Kingdom."
1940,"April 9","World War II: Germany invades Denmark and Norway in Operation [i]Weserübung.[/i] The British campaign in Norway is simultaneously commenced."
1940,"April 12","The Faroe Islands are occupied by British troops, following the taking over of Denmark by Nazi Germany. This action is taken to avert a possible German occupation of the islands, which would have had very grave consequences for the course of the Battle of the Atlantic."
1940,"May 13","World War II: German armies open a 60-mile wide breach in the Maginot Line at Sedan, France."
1940,"May 14","Queen Wilhelmina of the Netherlands and her government flee to London; Rotterdam is subjected to savage terror bombing by the Luftwaffe; 980 are killed, and 20,000 buildings destroyed."
1940,"May 14","Recruitment begins in Britain for a home defence force: the Local Defence Volunteers, later known as the Home Guard."
1940,"May 15","World War II: The Dutch army surrenders."
1940,"May 18","Marshal Philippe Pétain is named vice-premier of France."
1940,"May 20","World War II: German forces (2nd Panzer division), under General Rudolf Veiel, reach Noyelles on the English Channel."
1940,"May 26","World War II: The Dunkirk evacuation of the British Expeditionary Force starts."
1940,"May 28","World War II: King Leopold III of Belgium orders the Belgian forces to cease fighting. Leaders of the Belgian government on French territory declare Leopold deposed."
1940,"June 4","The Dunkirk evacuation ends - British forces complete evacuating 300,000 troops from Dunkirk in France."
1940,"June 9","World War II: The British Commandos are created."
1940,"June 10","World War II: Italy declares war on France and the United Kingdom."
1940,"June 10","U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt denounces Italy's actions with his ""Stab in the Back"" speech during the graduation ceremonies of the University of Virginia."
1940,"June 10","Canada declares war on Italy."
1940,"June 12","World War II: 13,000 British and French troops surrender to Field Marshal Erwin Rommel at St. Valery-en-Caux."
1940,"June 13","World War II: Paris is declared an open city."
1940,"June 15","World War II: Verdun falls to German forces."
1940,"June 17","Philippe Pétain becomes Prime Minister of France and immediately asks Germany for peace terms."
1940,"June 17","Operation Ariel begins: Allied troops start to evacuate France, following Germany's takeover of Paris and most of the nation."
1940,"June 17","A Luftwaffe Junkers 88 bomber sinks the British ship [i]RMS Lancastria[/i], which was evacuating troops from near Saint-Nazaire, France, killing some 5,800 men. (Wartime censorship prevents the story from becoming public.)"
1940,"June 18","Winston Churchill says to the House of Commons: ""The Battle of France is over. The Battle of Britain is about to begin""."
1940,"June 18","General Charles de Gaulle broadcasts from London, calling on all French people to continue the fight against Nazi Germany: ""France has lost a battle. But France has not lost the war""."
1940,"June 21","World War II: Vichy France and Germany sign an armistice at Compiegne, in the same wagon-lit railroad car used by Marshal Ferdinand Foch to accept the surrender of Germany in 1918."
1940,"June 23","World War II: German leader Adolf Hitler surveys newly defeated Paris in now occupied France."
1940,"June 24","World War II: Vichy France signs armistice terms with Italy."
1940,"June 28","General Charles de Gaulle is officially recognized by Britain as the ""Leader of all Free Frenchmen, wherever they may be""."
1940,"June 30","World War II: German forces land in Guernsey, marking the start of the 5-year Occupation of the Channel Islands."
1940,"July 3","World War II: British naval units sink or seize ships of the French fleet anchored in the Algerian ports of Oran and Mers-el-Kebir. The following day, Vichy France breaks off diplomatic relations with Britain."
1940,"July 10","World War II: The Battle of Britain begins."
1940,"July 10","World War II: Vichy France begins with a constitutional law which only 80 members of the parliament vote against."
1940,"July 14","Winston Churchill, in a worldwide broadcast, proclaims the intention of Great Britain to fight alone against Germany whatever the outcome: ""We shall seek no terms. We shall tolerate no parley. We may show mercy. We shall ask none""."
1940,"July 19","World War II: Adolf Hitler makes a peace appeal to Britain in an address to the Reichstag. Lord Halifax, British foreign minister, flatly rejects peace terms in a broadcast reply on July 22."
1940,"August 30","Second Vienna Award: Germany and Italy compel Romania to cede half of Transylvania to Hungary."
1940,"September","The U.S. Army 45th Infantry Division (previously a National Guard Division in Arizona, Colorado, New Mexico, and Oklahoma), is activated and ordered into federal service for 1 year, to engage in a training program in Ft. Sill and Louisiana, prior to serving in World War II."
1940,"September 12","In Lascaux, France, 17,000-year-old cave paintings are discovered by a group of young Frenchmen hiking through Southern France. The paintings depict animals and date to the Stone Age."
1940,"September 26","World War II: The United States imposes a total embargo on all scrap metal shipments to Japan."
1940,"September 27","World War II: Germany, Italy and Japan sign the Tripartite Pact."
1940,"October 16","The draft registration of approximately 16 million men begins in the United States."
1940,"October 18","(October 18 - October 19) World War II: Thirty-two ships are sunk from Convoy SC 7 and Convoy HX 79 by the most effective Wolf pack of the war including U-boat aces Kretschmer, Prien and Schepke."
1940,"October 28","World War II: Italian troops invade Greece, meeting strong resistance from Greek troops and civilians. This action signals the beginning of the Balkans Campaign."
1940,"November 9","Joaquin Rodrigo's [i]Concierto de Aranjuez[/i] premieres in Barcelona, Spain."
1940,"November 11","The German [i]Hilfskreuzer[/i] (commerce raider) [i]Atlantis[/i] captures top secret British mail, and sends it to Japan."
1940,"November 14","World War II: The city of Coventry, England is destroyed by 500 German Luftwaffe bombers (150,000 fire bombs, 503 tons of high explosives, and 130 parachute mines level 60,000 of the city's 75,000 buildings; 568 people are killed)."
1940,"November 18","World War II: German leader Adolf Hitler and Italian Foreign Minister Galeazzo Ciano meet to discuss Benito Mussolini's disastrous invasion of Greece."
1940,"November 20","World War II: Hungary, Romania and Slovakia join the Axis Powers."
1940,"November 27","World War II: The Royal Navy and Regia Marina fight the Battle of Cape Spartivento."
1940,"December 12","(December 12 - December 15) World War II ""Sheffield Blitz"": The City of Sheffield is badly damaged by German air-raids."
1940,"December 23","Winston Churchill, in a broadcast address to the people of Italy, squarely blames Benito Mussolini for leading his nation to war against the British, contrary to Italy's historic friendship with them: ""One man has arrayed the trustees and inheritors of ancient Rome upon the side of the ferocious pagan barbarians""."
1940,"December 24","Mahatma Gandhi, Indian spiritual non-violence leader writes his second letter to Adolf Hitler addressing him ""My friend"", requesting him to stop the war Germany had begun."
1940,"December 29","Franklin D. Roosevelt, in a fireside chat to the nation, declares that the United States must become ""the great arsenal of democracy""."
1940,"December 29","World War II - ""Second Great Fire of London"": Luftwaffe carries out a massive incendiary bombing raid, starting 1,500 fires. Many famous buildings, including the Guildhall and Trinity House, are either damaged or destroyed."
1940,"circa","Olympic Games are suspended due to World War II."
1940,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1940,"circa","World War II (1939-1945)"
1941,"January 19","World War II: British troops attack Italian-held Eritrea."
1941,"January 21","World War II - Battle of Tobruk: Australian and British forces attack Tobruk, Libya."
1941,"January 22","World War II: British troops capture Tobruk from the Italians."
1941,"January 23","Aviator Charles Lindbergh testifies before the U.S. Congress and recommends that the United States negotiate a neutrality pact with Adolf Hitler."
1941,"January 27","World War II - Attack on Pearl Harbor: Joseph C. Grew, the U.S. ambassador to Japan, reports to Washington a rumor overheard at a diplomatic reception concerning a planned surprise attack on Pearl Harbor, Hawaii."
1941,"January 30","World War II - Australians capture Derna, Libya from the Italians."
1941,"February 3","World War II: The Nazis forcibly restore Pierre Laval to office in occupied Vichy France."
1941,"February 4","World War II: The United Service Organization (USO) is created to entertain American troops."
1941,"February 6","World War II - Fall of Benghazi to the Western Desert Force. Lieutenant-General Erwin Rommel is appointed commander of Afrika Korps."
1941,"February 9","Winston Churchill, in a worldwide broadcast, tells the United States to show its support by sending arms to the British: ""Give us the tools, and we will finish the job""."
1941,"February 12","World War II: Erwin Rommel arrives in Tripoli."
1941,"February 14","World War II - Admiral Kichisaburo Nomura begins his duties as Japanese Ambassador to the United States."
1941,"February 19","(February 19 - February 22) World War II: Three Nights' Blitz over Swansea, South Wales: Over these 3 nights of intensive bombing, which last a total of 13 hours and 48 minutes, Swansea's town centre is almost completely obliterated by the 896 high explosive bombs employed by the Luftwaffe. A total of 397 casualties and 230 deaths are reported."
1941,"March 1","World War II: Bulgaria signs the Tripartite Pact, thus joining the Axis powers."
1941,"March 4","World War II: British Commandos carry out a successful raid on the Lofoten Islands off the north coast of Norway."
1941,"March 25","World War II: The Kingdom of Yugoslavia joins the Axis powers in Vienna."
1941,"March 27","World War II: An anti-Axis coup d'état in Yugoslavia forces Prince Paul into exile; 17-year-old King Peter II assumes power."
1941,"March 27","World War II - Attack on Pearl Harbor: Japanese spy Takeo Yoshikawa arrives in Honolulu, Hawaii and begins to study the Pacific Fleet at Pearl Harbor."
1941,"March 27","World War II - Battle of Cape Matapan: Off the Peloponnesus coast in the Mediterranean, British naval forces defeat those of Italy, sinking 5 warships. Battle ends on March 29."
1941,"March 30","All German, Italian, and Danish ships anchored in United States waters are taken into ""protective custody""."
1941,"April 4","World War II: Axis forces capture Benghazi."
1941,"April 6","World War II: Germany invades Yugoslavia and Greece."
1941,"April 12","World War II: German troops enter Belgrade."
1941,"April 13","The Soviet Union and Japan sign a neutrality pact."
1941,"April 15","World War II: Axis forces reach Halfaya Pass on the Libyan-Egyptian frontier."
1941,"April 17","World War II: The Yugoslav Royal Army capitulates."
1941,"April 18","World War II: Prime Minister of Greece Alexandros Koryzis commits suicide as German troops approach Athens."
1941,"April 21","World War II: Greece capitulates. Commonwealth troops and some elements of the Greek Army withdraw to Crete."
1941,"April 27","World War II: German troops enter Athens."
1941,"May 5","World War II: Emperor Haile Selassie enters Addis Ababa, which had been liberated from Italian forces; this date has been since commemorated as Liberation Day in Ethiopia."
1941,"May 9","World War II: The German submarine [i]U-110[/i] is captured by the British Royal Navy. On board is the latest Enigma cryptography machine, which Allied cryptographers later use to break coded German messages."
1941,"May 10","World War II: The British House of Commons is damaged by the Luftwaffe in an air raid."
1941,"May 20","World War II: The Battle of Crete begins as Germany launches an airborne invasion of Crete."
1941,"May 24","World War II: In the North Atlantic, the German battleship [i]Bismarck[/i] sinks battlecruiser HMS [i]Hood[/i], killing all but 3 crewmen aboard the pride of the Royal Navy."
1941,"May 26","World War II: In the North Atlantic, Fairey Swordfish aircraft from the carrier HMS [i]Ark Royal[/i] cripple the steering of [i]Bismarck[/i] in an aerial torpedo attack."
1941,"May 27","World War II: President Roosevelt proclaims an ""unlimited national emergency""."
1941,"May 27","World War II:[i]Bismarck[/i] is sunk in the North Atlantic, killing 2,300."
1941,"May 30","World War II: Manolis Glezos and Apostolos Santas tear down the Nazi swastika on the Acropolis in Athens, and replace it with the Greek flag."
1941,"June 8","World War II: British and Free French forces invade Syria."
1941,"June 13","TASS, the official Soviet news agency, denies reports of tension between Germany and the Soviet Union."
1941,"June 14","All German and Italian assets in the United States are frozen."
1941,"June 16","All German and Italian consulates in the United States are ordered closed and their staffs to leave the country by July 10."
1941,"June 22","World War II: Italy and Romania declare war on the Soviet Union."
1941,"June 22","World War II: Germany invades the Soviet Union under Operation Barbarossa."
1941,"June 22","World War II: Winston Churchill promises all possible British assistance to the Soviet Union in a worldwide broadcast: ""Any man or state who fights against Nazidom will have our aid. Any man or state who marches with Hitler is our foe""."
1941,"June 23","World War II: Hungary and Slovakia declare war on the Soviet Union."
1941,"June 25","World War II: Finland attacks the Soviet Union to seek the opportunity of revenge in the Continuation War."
1941,"June 28","World War II: Albania declares war on the Soviet Union."
1941,"July 2","World War II: Japan calls up 1 million men for military service."
1941,"July 5","World War II: German troops reach the Dnieper River."
1941,"July 7","World War II: American forces take over the defense of Iceland from the British."
1941,"July 7","World War II: German troops take over Estonia from the Soviets."
1941,"July 14","World War II: Vichy France signs armistice terms, ending all fighting in Syria and Lebanon."
1941,"July 19","World War II: A BBC broadcast by ""Colonel Britton"" calls on the people of occupied Europe to resist the Nazis under the slogan ""V for Victory""."
1941,"July 26","World War II: In response to the Japanese occupation of French Indo-China, U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt orders the seizure of all Japanese assets in the United States."
1941,"July 26","World War II: General Douglas MacArthur is named commander of all U.S. forces in the Philippines; the Philippines Army is ordered nationalized by President Roosevelt."
1941,"July 31","World War II - Holocaust: Under instructions from Adolf Hitler, Nazi official Hermann Göring orders S.S. General Reinhard Heydrich to ""submit to me as soon as possible a general plan of the administrative material and financial measures necessary for carrying out the desired final solution of the Jewish question""."
1941,"August 18","Adolf Hitler orders a temporary halt to Nazi Germany's systematic euthanasia of the mentally ill and handicapped due to protests. However, graduates of the T-4 Euthanasia Program are then transferred to concentration camps, where they continue in their trade."
1941,"August 24","World War II: A Luftwaffe bomb hits an Estonian steamer with 3,500 Soviet-mobilized Estonian men on board, killing 598 of them."
1941,"August 25","World War II: Operation Countenance begins with United Kingdom and Soviet forces invading Iran."
1941,"August 27","World War II - Pierre Laval is shot in an assassination attempt at Versailles, France."
1941,"August 28","World War II: The Soviets announce the destruction of the massive Dnieper River dam at Zaporozhye, to prevent its capture by the Germans."
1941,"September 8","World War II - The Siege of Leningrad begins: German forces begin a siege against the Soviet Union's second-largest city, Leningrad. Stalin orders the Volga Germans deported to Siberia."
1941,"September 11","World War II: Charles Lindbergh, at an America First Committee rally in Des Moines, Iowa, accuses ""the British, the Jewish, and the Roosevelt administration"" of leading the United States toward war. Widespread condemnation of Lindbergh follows."
1941,"September 14","The State of Vermont declares war on Germany."
1941,"September 29","World War II: The Moscow Conference begins; U.S. representative Averill Harriman and British representative Lord Beaverbrook meet with Soviet foreign minister Molotov to arrange urgent assistance for Russia."
1941,"October 2","World War II: Operation Typhoon begins as Germany launches an all-out offensive against Moscow."
1941,"October 8","World War II: In their invasion of the Soviet Union, Germany reaches the Sea of Azov with the capture of Mariupol."
1941,"October 16","World War II: The Soviet Union government moves to Kuibyshev (modern Samara), but Stalin remains in Moscow."
1941,"October 18","General Hideki Tojo becomes the 40th Prime Minister of Japan."
1941,"October 21","World War II: The Germans rampage in Yugoslavia, killing thousands of civilians."
1941,"October 30","World War II: Franklin Delano Roosevelt approves US$1 billion in Lend-Lease aid to the Soviet Union."
1941,"October 31","World War II: The destroyer USS [i]Reuben James[/i] is torpedoed by a German U-boat near Iceland, killing more than 100 United States Navy sailors."
1941,"November 10","In a speech at the Mansion House in London, Winston Churchill promises, ""should the United States become involved in war with Japan, the British declaration will follow within the hour""."
1941,"November 13","World War II: The aircraft carrier HMS [i]Ark Royal[/i] is hit by German U-boat [i]U-81[/i]."
1941,"November 14","World War II: The HMS [i]Ark Royal[/i] capsizes and sinks, having been torpedoed by [i]U-81[/i]."
1941,"November 17","World War II - Attack on Pearl Harbor: Joseph Grew, the United States ambassador to Japan, cables to Washington a warning that Japan may strike suddenly and unexpectedly at any time."
1941,"November 18","World War II: Operation Crusader in North Africa begins."
1941,"November 19","World War II: The Australian cruiser HMAS [i]Sydney[/i] sinks off the coast of Western Australia, killing 645 sailors."
1941,"November 26","World War II - Attack on Pearl Harbor: A fleet of 6 aircraft carriers commanded by Japanese Vice Admiral Chuichi Nagumo leaves Hitokapu Bay for Pearl Harbor under strict radio silence."
1941,"November 27","World War II: Germans reach their closest approach to Moscow. They are subsequently frozen by cold weather and attacks by the Soviets."
1941,"December 1","World War II: Fiorello La Guardia, Mayor of New York City and Director of the Office of Civilian Defense, signs Administrative Order 9, creating the Civil Air Patrol under the authority of the United States Army Air Force."
1941,"December 1","World War II: A state of emergency is declared in Malaya and the Straits Settlements."
1941,"December 2","World War II - Attack on Pearl Harbor: The code message ""Climb Mount Niitaka"" is transmitted to the Japanese task force, indicating that negotiations have broken down and that the attack is to be carried out according to plan."
1941,"December 6","World War II - Soviet counterattacks begin against German troops encircling Moscow. Wehrmacht is subsequently pushed back over 200 miles."
1941,"December 6","World War II - The United Kingdom declares war on Finland."
1941,"December 7","The Japanese Navy launches a surprise attack on the United States fleet at Pearl Harbor, thus drawing the United States into World War II. Tobruk's garrison is relieved."
1941,"December 8","World War II: The United States officially declares war on Japan."
1941,"December 8","World War II: The United Kingdom declares war on Japan."
1941,"December 8","World War II: China declares war on Japan."
1941,"December 8","World War II: The Netherlands declares war on Japan."
1941,"December 8","World War II: Japan launches invasions in Hong Kong, Malaya, Manila, and Singapore."
1941,"December 8","World War II: Japan launches invasions in the Philippines."
1941,"December 10","World War II: The British battleships HMS [i]Prince of Wales[/i] and HMS [i]Repulse[/i] are sunk by Japanese aircraft in the South China Sea north of Singapore."
1941,"December 11","World War II: Germany and Italy declare war on the United States. The U.S. responds in kind."
1941,"December 12","World War II: Hungary and Romania declare war on the United States."
1941,"December 12","World War II: India declares war on Japan."
1941,"December 12","World War II: The Kimura Detachment of the Japanese Imperial forces was occupied in Legaspi, Albay in Eastern Philippines."
1941,"December 13","Sweden's low temperature record of -53°C is set in a village within the Vilhelmina Municipality."
1941,"December 19","World War II: Hitler becomes Supreme Commander-in-Chief of the German Army."
1941,"December 23","World War II: A second Japanese landing attempt on Wake Island is successful, and the American garrison surrenders after a full night and morning of fighting."
1941,"December 24","World War II: British forces capture Benghazi."
1941,"December 25","World War II: The British and Canadians are defeated by the Japanese at Hong Kong."
1941,"December 27","World War II: British Commandos raid the Norwegian port of Vaagso, causing Hitler to reinforce the garrison and defenses, drawing vital troops away from other areas."
1941,"circa","The Valley of Geysers is discovered in Russia."
1941,"circa","In Sweden, Victor Hasselblad forms the Hasselblad Camera Company."
1941,"circa","Japanese Occupation of the Philippines (1941-1945)"
1941,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1941,"circa","World War II (1939-1945)"
1942,"January 1","World War II: The United States and Philippines troops fight the Battle of Bataan."
1942,"January 2","World War II: Manila is captured by Japanese forces."
1942,"January 7","World War II: The siege of the Bataan Peninsula begins."
1942,"January 10","World War II: The last German air-raid on Liverpool destroys the home of William Patrick Hitler, Adolf Hitler's nephew. After his house is destroyed, William Hitler goes to the USA and joins the navy to fight against his uncle."
1942,"January 19","World War II: Japanese forces invade Burma. Establishment of United States VIII Bomber Command, later to become the Eighth Air Force in Savannah, Georgia."
1942,"January 20","World War II: Nazis at the Wannsee conference in Berlin decide that the ""final solution to the Jewish problem"" is relocation, and later extermination."
1942,"January 21","World War II: Erwin Rommel launches his new offensive in Cyrenaica."
1942,"January 23","World War II: The Battle of Rabaul begins."
1942,"January 25","World War II: Thailand declares war on the United States and United Kingdom."
1942,"January 31","World War II: The last organized Allied forces leave Malaya, ending the 54-day campaign."
1942,"February 1","World War II: The Command staff of the Eighth Air Force reaches England."
1942,"February 2","World War II: President Franklin Delano Roosevelt signs an executive order directing the internment of Japanese Americans and the seizure of their property."
1942,"February 3","World War II: Rommel suspends his offensive in Cyrenaica."
1942,"February 8","Daylight saving time goes into effect in the United States."
1942,"February 15","World War II: Singapore surrenders to Japanese forces."
1942,"February 22","World War II: President Franklin Delano Roosevelt orders General Douglas MacArthur out of the Philippines as American defense of the nation collapses."
1942,"February 23","The Japanese submarine [i]I-17[/i] fires 17 high-explosive shells toward an oil refinery near Santa Barbara, California, causing little damage."
1942,"February 26","The worst coal dust explosion to date, in Honkeiko, China, claims 1,549 lives."
1942,"March 9","World War II: Executive order 9082 (February 28, 1942) reorganizes the United States Army into three major commands: Army Ground Forces, Army Air Forces, and Services of Supply, later redesignated Army Service Forces."
1942,"March 28","World War II: British Commandos raid St. Nazaire on the coast of Western France."
1942,"April 3","World War II: Japanese forces begin an all-out assault on the United States and Filipino troops on the Bataan Peninsula."
1942,"April 5","World War II: the Japanese Navy attacks Colombo in Ceylon (Sri Lanka). Royal Navy Cruisers HMS Cornwall and HMS Dorsetshire are sunk southwest of the island."
1942,"April 9","World War II: The Japanese Navy launches an air raid on Trincomalee in Ceylon (Sri Lanka); the Royal Navy aircraft carrier [i]HMS Hermes[/i] and Royal Australian Navy destroyer [i]HMAS Vampire[/i] are sunk off the country's East Coast."
1942,"April 15","World War II: King George VI awards the George Cross to Malta, saying, ""To honour her brave people I award the George Cross to the Island Fortress of Malta, to bear witness to a heroism and a devotion that will long be famous in history (from January 1 to July 24, there is only one 24-hour period during which no bombs fall on this tiny island)""."
1942,"April 18","Tokyo, Japan is bombed by B-25 Mitchells commanded by then-Lieutenant Colonel James Doolittle."
1942,"April 27","World War II: A national plebiscite is held in Canada on the issue of conscription."
1942,"April 27","The Jewish Star of David is required wearing for all Jews in the Netherlands and Belgium. Other Jews in Nazi countries had been wearing it for longer."
1942,"April 29","World War II: An explosion at a chemical factory in Tessenderlo, Belgium leaves 200 dead and 1,000 injured."
1942,"May 5","World War II - Operation Ironclad: United Kingdom forces invade the French colony of Madagascar."
1942,"May 6","World War II: On Corregidor, the last American and Filipino forces in the Philippines surrender to the Japanese."
1942,"May 12","World War II - Second Battle of Kharkov: In the eastern Ukraine, the Soviet Army initiates a major offensive. During the battle the Soviets capture the city of Kharkov from the German Army, only to be encircled and destroyed."
1942,"May 15","World War II: In the United States, a bill creating the Women's Auxiliary Army Corps (WAAC) is signed into law."
1942,"May 21","World War II: Mexico declares war against Nazi Germany after the sinking of the Mexican tanker [i]Faja de Oro[/i] by the German U-boat, U-160, off Key West."
1942,"May 26","World War II - Battle of Bir Hakeim: The Free French and British troops slow the German advance in North Africa."
1942,"May 27","World War II - Operation Anthropoid: Czech paratroopers attempt to assassinate Reinhard Heydrich in Prague."
1942,"May 31","(May 31 - June 1) World War II - Attack on Sydney Harbour: Japanese submarines infiltrate Sydney Harbour in an attempt to attack Allied warships."
1942,"June 1","World War II: Mexico declares war on Germany, Italy and Japan."
1942,"June 4","World War II: Reinhard Heydrich succumbs to wounds sustained on May 27 from Czechoslovakian paratroopers acting in Operation Anthropoid."
1942,"June 4","(June 4 - June 7) World War II - The Battle of Midway: The Japanese naval advance in the Pacific is halted."
1942,"June 8","World War II: Attack on Sydney Harbour: The Australian cities of Sydney and Newcastle are shelled by Japanese submarines. The eastern suburbs of both cities are damaged and the east coast is blacked out."
1942,"June 9","World War II: Nazis burn the Czech village of Lidice in reprisal for the killing of Reinhard Heydrich."
1942,"June 10","World War II: The Gestapo massacres 173 male residents of Lidice, Czechoslovakia in retaliation for the killing of a Nazi official."
1942,"June 13","The United States opens its Office of War Information, a propaganda center."
1942,"June 21","World War II: Axis forces capture Tobruk."
1942,"June 21","Fort Stevens, Oregon is fired upon by a Japanese submarine."
1942,"July 1","(July 1 - July 27) World War II: the First Battle of El Alamein."
1942,"July 3","Guadalcanal, occupied only by aborigines falls to the Japanese Naval construction force deployed to construct an air field on the island."
1942,"July 9","Sükrü Saracoglu forms the new government in Turkey. (13 th government)"
1942,"July 13","World War II: German U-Boats sink 3 more merchant ships in the Gulf of St. Lawrence."
1942,"July 14","World War II: Germany introduces the Ostvolk Medal for Soviet personnel in Wehrmacht."
1942,"July 16","Holocaust: By order of the Vichy France government headed by Pierre Laval, French police officers round-up 13,000-20,000 Jews and imprison them in the Winter Velodrome."
1942,"July 19","World War II - Battle of the Atlantic: German Grand Admiral Karl Dönitz orders the last U-boats to withdraw from their United States Atlantic coast positions, in response to an effective American convoy system."
1942,"July 21","The Japanese establish a beachhead on the north coast of New Guinea in the Buna-Gona area; a small Australian force begins a rearguard action on the Kokoda Track Campaign."
1942,"August 8","World War II: In Washington, DC, six Germans would-be saboteurs are executed (Two others were cooperative and received sentences of life imprisonment instead. One was spared because of his quite young age: execution was considered to be too harsh for such a young man. The imprisoned ones were freed a few years after the end of the war.)"
1942,"August 15","World War II: The American tanker [i]SS Ohio[/i] reaches Malta as part of the convoy of [i]Operation Pedestal[/i]."
1942,"August 19","World War II - Dieppe Raid: Allied forces raid Dieppe, France."
1942,"August 22","World War II: Brazil declares war on Germany and Italy."
1942,"August 25","World War II: Japanese marines land at Milne Bay."
1942,"August 31","(August 31 - September 5) World War II: Battle of Alam Halfa."
1942,"October 11","World War II - Battle of Cape Esperance: On the northwest coast of Guadalcanal, United States Navy ships intercept and defeat a Japanese fleet on their way to reinforce troops on the island."
1942,"October 23","(October 23 - November 4) World War II - Second Battle of El Alamein: British troops go on the offensive against the Axis forces."
1942,"October 26","World War II - Battle of the Santa Cruz Islands: two Japanese aircraft carriers are heavily damaged and one U.S.N. carrier is sunk."
1942,"October 29","Holocaust: In the United Kingdom, leading clergymen and political figures hold a public meeting to register outrage over Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews."
1942,"November 3","World War II - Second Battle of El Alamein: German forces under Erwin Rommel are forced to retreat during the night."
1942,"November 9","World War II: U.S serviceman Edward Leonski is hanged at Melbourne's Pentridge Prison for the ""Brown-Out"" murders of 3 women in May."
1942,"November 10","World War II: In violation of a 1940 armistice, Germany invades Vichy France, following French Admiral François Darlan's agreement to an armistice with the Allies in North Africa."
1942,"November 12","World War II - Battle of Guadalcanal: A naval battle near Guadalcanal starts between Japanese and American forces."
1942,"November 19","World War II - Battle of Stalingrad: Soviet Union forces under General Georgy Zhukov launch the Operation Uranus counter-attacks at Stalingrad, turning the tide of the battle in the USSR's favor."
1942,"November 20","World War II - British forces capture Benghazi."
1942,"November 22","World War II - Battle of Stalingrad: The situation for the German attackers of Stalingrad seems desperate during the Soviet counter-attack Operation Uranus, and General Friedrich Paulus sends Adolf Hitler a telegram saying that the German Sixth Army is surrounded."
1942,"November 27","World War II: At Toulon, the French navy scuttles its ships and submarines to keep them out of Nazi hands."
1942,"December 1","Gasoline rationing begins in the United States."
1942,"December 7","World War II: British commandos conduct Operation Frankton, a raid on shipping in Bordeaux harbour."
1942,"circa","Japanese Occupation of the Philippines (1941-1945)"
1942,"circa","World War II (1939-1945)"
1942,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1943,"January 11","The United States and United Kingdom give up territorial rights in China."
1943,"January 15","World War II: The Japanese are driven off Guadalcanal."
1943,"January 18","World War II: Soviet officials announce they have broken the Wehrmacht's siege of Leningrad."
1943,"January 23","World War II: British forces capture Tripoli from the Italians."
1943,"February 2","World War II: In Russia, the Battle of Stalingrad comes to an end with the surrender of the German 6th Army."
1943,"February 7","World War II: In the United States, it is announced that shoe rationing will go into effect in 2 days."
1943,"February 8","World War II - Battle of Guadalcanal: United States forces defeat Japanese troops."
1943,"February 16","World War II: The Soviet Union reconquers Kharkov, but is later driven out in the Third Battle of Kharkov."
1943,"February 22","Members of White Rose are executed in Nazi Germany."
1943,"February 27","The Smith Mine #3 in Bearcreek, Montana, United States explodes, killing 74 men."
1943,"March 2","World War II: Battle of the Bismarck Sea - United States and Australian forces sink Japanese convoy ships."
1943,"March 8","World War II: American forces are attacked by Japanese troops on Hill 700 in Bougainville, in a battle that will last 5 days."
1943,"March 9","Sükrü Saracoglu forms the new government of Turkey. (14th government; Sükrü Saracoglu had served twice as a prime minister)"
1943,"March 13","World War II: On Bougainville, Japanese troops end their assault on American forces at Hill 700."
1943,"March 16","(March 16 - March 19) World War II: 22 ships from Convoys HX 229/SC 122 and 1 U-boat are sunk in the largest North Atlantic U-boat Wolf pack attack of the war."
1943,"March 22","World War II: The entire population of Khatyn in Belarus is burnt alive by the German occupation forces."
1943,"March 23","The drugs [i]Vicodin[/i] and [i]Lortab[/i] are made in Germany."
1943,"March 26","World War II - Battle of the Komandorski Islands: In the Aleutian Islands, the battle begins when United States Navy forces intercept Japanese troops attempting to reinforce a garrison at Kiska."
1943,"March 28","In Italy a ship full of weapons and ammunition explodes in the port of Naples, killing 600."
1943,"April 13","World War II: Radio Berlin announces the discovery by Wehrmacht of mass graves of Poles killed by Soviets in the Katyn massacre."
1943,"April 21","Worst Bombing of Aberdeen in World War II."
1943,"May 6","World War II: Six U-boats are sunk after sinking 12 ships from Convoy ONS 5 in the last major North Atlantic U-boat Wolf pack attack of the war."
1943,"May 9","(May 9 - May 12) Japanese troops carry out the Changjiao massacre in Changjiao, Hunan, China."
1943,"May 11","World War II: American troops invade Attu in the Aleutian Islands, in an attempt to expel occupying Japanese forces."
1943,"May 13","World War II: German Afrika Korps and Italian troops in North Africa surrender to Allied forces."
1943,"May 14","The [i]Australian Hospital Ship Centaur[/i] is sunk off the coast of Queensland, by a Japanese submarine."
1943,"May 16","World War II: Operation Chastise by RAF 617 Sqdn are carried out on German dams."
1943,"May 16","The United States Army contracts with the University of Pennsylvania's Moore School to develop the computer ENIAC."
1943,"July 6","World War II: Americans and Japanese fight the Battle of Kula Gulf off Kolombangara."
1943,"July 10","World War II - Allied invasion of Sicily: The allied invasion of Axis-controlled Europe begins with landings on the island of Sicily off mainland Italy, by the U.S. Army 45th Infantry Division and a number of Allied paratroopers."
1943,"July 11","United States Army forces assault the village of Piano Lupo, just outside of Gela, Sicily."
1943,"July 12","World War II - Battle of Prokhorovka: The Wehrmacht and the Red Army fight to a draw."
1943,"July 13","World War II: The invasion of Sicily begins with British landings at Augusta on the island's eastern side and American landings to the south."
1943,"July 22","World War II: Beeing Operation Husky Palermo is liberated by the Allies."
1943,"July 24","World War II: Operation Gomorrah begins: British and Canadian aeroplanes bomb Hamburg by night, those of the Americans by day. By the end of the operation in November, 9,000 tons of explosives will have killed more than 30,000 people and destroyed 280,000 buildings."
1943,"July 25","In Italy the Gran Consiglio del Fascismo withdraws its support of Mussolini; Mussolini is arrested and the power is given to Maresciallo d'Italia Gen. Pietro Badoglio."
1943,"July 28","World War II: Operation Gomorrah - The British bomb Hamburg, causing a firestorm that kills 42,000 German civilians."
1943,"August 3","World War II: John F. Kennedy's PT-109 is rammed by a destroyer."
1943,"August 4","World War II: The [i]USS Intrepid (CV-11)[/i] is launched."
1943,"August 6","World War II - Battle of Vella Gulf: Americans defeat a Japanese convoy off Kolombangara, as the U.S. Army drives the Japanese out of Munda airfield on New Georgia."
1943,"August 13","World War II: Rome is declared an open city."
1943,"August 17","World War II: The US 7th Army under General George S. Patton arrives in Messina, Sicily, followed several hours later by the British 8th Army under Field Marshal Bernard L. Montgomery, thus completing the Allied conquest of Sicily."
1943,"August 24","World War II: - Heinrich Himmler is named Reichminister of the Interior in Germany ."
1943,"August 26","World War II: Lord Louis Mountbatten is named Supreme Allied Commander for Southeast Asia."
1943,"August 29","World War II: Germany dissolves the Danish government after it refuses to deal with a wave of strikes and disturbances to the satisfaction of the German authorities."
1943,"September 5","World War II: The 503rd Parachute Regiment under American General Douglas MacArthur lands and occupies Nadzab, just east of the port city of Lae in northeastern Papua New Guinea."
1943,"September 12","World War II: German paratroopers rescue Mussolini from imprisonment, in ""Operation Oak""."
1943,"September 16","World War II: The Salerno Mutiny occurs within the British X Corps."
1943,"September 17","World War II: The Villefranche-de-Rouergue uprising takes place."
1943,"September 27","World War II: The 4-day Naples Uprising begins."
1943,"October 1","World War II: American forces enter liberated Naples."
1943,"October 6","World War II: Americans and Japanese fight the naval Battle of Vella Lavella."
1943,"October 7","World War II: The Naples post office explosion kills 100."
1943,"October 13","World War II: The new government of Italy sides with the Allies and declares war on Germany."
1943,"October 18","Chiang Kai-shek takes the oath of office as president of China."
1943,"October 22","World War II: The RAF delivers a highly destructive airstrike on the German industrial and population center of Kassel."
1943,"November 1","World War II - Operation Goodtime: United States Marines land on Bougainville in the Solomon Islands."
1943,"November 2","World War II: In the early morning hours, American and Japanese ships fight the inconclusive Battle of Empress Augusta Bay off Bougainville."
1943,"November 2","World War II: British troops in Italy reach the Garigliano River."
1943,"November 16","World War II: After flying from Britain, 160 American bombers strike a hydro-electric power facility and heavy water factory in German-controlled Vemork, Norway."
1943,"November 16","World War II: A Japanese submarine sinks the surfaced U.S. submarine [i]USS Corvina[/i] near Truk."
1943,"November 18","World War II: 440 Royal Air Force planes bomb Berlin, causing only light damage and killing 131. The RAF loses 9 aircraft and 53 aviators."
1943,"November 20","World War II: Battle of Tarawa: United States Marines land on Tawara and Makin atolls in the Gilbert Islands and take heavy fire from Japanese shore guns."
1943,"November 22","World War II: War in the Pacific: U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt, British Prime Minister Winston Churchill, and ROC leader Chiang Kai-Shek met at the Cairo Conference to discuss ways to defeat Japan."
1943,"November 22","Lebanon gains independence from France."
1943,"November 25","World War II: Americans and Japanese fight the naval Battle of Cape St. George between Buka and New Ireland."
1943,"November 28","World War II - Tehran Conference: U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt, British Prime Minister Winston Churchill and Soviet leader Joseph Stalin meet in Tehran to discuss war strategy (on November 30 they establish an agreement concerning a planned June 1944 invasion of Europe codenamed Operation Overlord)."
1943,"December 2","A Luftwaffe bombing raid on the harbour of Bari, Italy, sinks an American ship with a mustard gas stockpile, causing numerous fatalities (though the exact death toll is unresolved, as the bombing raid itself causes hundreds of deaths too)."
1943,"December 4","World War II: In Yugoslavia, resistance leader Marshal Tito proclaims a provisional democratic Yugoslav government in-exile."
1943,"December 4","The Great Depression officially ends in the United States: With unemployment figures falling fast due to World War II-related employment, U.S. President Franklin D. Roosevelt closes the Works Progress Administration."
1943,"December 24","World War II: U.S. General Dwight D. Eisenhower becomes the Supreme Allied Commander in Europe."
1943,"December 30","Subhash Chandra Bose sets up a pro-Japanese Indian government at Port Blair, India."
1943,"circa","The Mondragón Cooperative Corporation begins in Basque Country in Spain."
1943,"circa","Japanese Occupation of the Philippines (1941-1945)"
1943,"circa","Second World War (1939-1945)"
1943,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1944,"January 4","World War II: The Battle of Monte Cassino begins."
1944,"January 8","World War II: Philippine Commonwealth troops enter the province of Ilocos Sur in Northern Luzon and attack Japanese forces."
1944,"January 14","World War II: Soviet troops start the offensive at Leningrad and Novgorod."
1944,"January 15","World War II: The 27th Polish Home Army Infantry Division is re-created, marking the start of Operation Tempest by the Polish Home Army."
1944,"January 15","British forces in Italy cross the Garigliano River."
1944,"January 15","The U.S. Army 36th Infantry Division, in Italy, attempts to cross the Rapido River."
1944,"January 22","World War II - Operation Shingle: The Allies begin the assault on Anzio, Italy. The U.S. Army 45th Infantry Division stands their ground at Anzio against violent assaults for 4 months."
1944,"January 27","World War II: The 2-year Siege of Leningrad is lifted."
1944,"January 29","World War II: The Battle of Cisterna takes place."
1944,"January 30","World War II: United States troops invade Majuro, Marshall Islands."
1944,"January 31","World War II: American forces land on Kwajalein Atoll and other islands in the Japanese-held Marshall Islands."
1944,"February 1","World War II: United States troops land in the Marshall Islands."
1944,"February 3","World War II: United States troops capture the Marshall Islands."
1944,"February 7","World War II: In Anzio, Italian forces launch a counteroffensive."
1944,"February 15","World War II - Battle of Monte Cassino: The monastery atop Monte Cassino is destroyed by Allied bombing."
1944,"February 17","World War II: The Battle of Eniwetok Atoll begins; it ends in an American victory on February 22."
1944,"February 22","United States Strategic Air Forces in Europe organized from the Eighth Air Force's strategic planning staff; subsuming strategic planning for all US Army Air Forces in Europe and Africa."
1944,"February 23","World War II: The Chechens and Ingush are forcibly deported to Central Asia."
1944,"February 29","World War II - Battle of Los Negros and Operation Brewer: The Admiralty Islands are invaded by U.S. forces."
1944,"March 2","World War II: A train stalls inside a railway tunnel outside Salerno, Italy; 521 choke to death."
1944,"March 3","World War II: The Order of Nakhimov and the Order of Ushakov are instituted in the USSR."
1944,"March 6","World War II: Soviet Army planes attack Narva, Estonia, destroying almost the entire old town."
1944,"March 9","World War II: Soviet Army planes attack Tallinn, Estonia."
1944,"March 12","World War II: The Political Committee of National Liberation is created in Greece."
1944,"March 17","World War II: The Nazis execute almost 400 prisoners, Soviet citizens and anti-fascist Romanians at Rîbnita."
1944,"March 19","World War II: German forces Operation occupy Hungary."
1944,"March 18","The eruption of Mount Vesuvius in Italy kills 26 and causes thousands to flee their homes."
1944,"March 20","World War II: RAF Flight Sergeant Nicholas Alkemade's bomber is hit over Germany, and he has to bail out without a parachute from a height of over 4,000 meters. Tree branches interrupt his fall and he lands safely on deep snow."
1944,"March 23","World War II: Members of the Italian Resistance attack Nazis marching in Via Rasella, killing 33."
1944,"April 25","World War II: The United Negro College Fund is incorporated."
1944,"April 28","World War II: 749 American troops are killed in Exercise Tiger at Start Bay, Devon, England."
1944,"May 5","World War II: Mohandas Gandhi is released in India."
1944,"May 9","World War II: In the Ukrainian city of Sevastopol, Soviet troops completely drive out German forces, who had been ordered by Hitler to ""fight to the last man""."
1944,"May 12","World War II: Soviet troops finalize the liberation of the Crimea."
1944,"June 2","World War II: The provisional French government is established."
1944,"June 9","World War II: Soviet leader Stalin launches the Vyborg-Petrozavodsk Offensive against Finland, with the intent of defeating Finland before pushing for Berlin."
1944,"June 10","World War II: 642 men, women and children are killed in the Oradour-sur-Glane Massacre in France."
1944,"June 13","World War II: Germany launches a V1 Flying Bomb attack on England."
1944,"June 17","Operation Bagration: A general attack by Soviet forces clears the German forces from Belarus, resulting in the destruction of German Army Group Centre, possibly the greatest defeat of the Wehrmacht during World War II."
1944,"June 25","World War II: The Battle of Tali-Ihantala (the largest battle ever in the Nordic countries) begins between Finnish and Soviet troops."
1944,"June 26","World War II: American troops enter Cherbourg."
1944,"July 6","World War II: At Camp Hood, Texas, future baseball star and 1st Lt. Jackie Robinson is arrested and later court-martialed for refusing to move to the back of a segregated U.S. Army bus. He is eventually acquitted."
1944,"July 9","World War II: British and Canadian forces capture Caen."
1944,"July 10","World War II: Soviet troops begin operations to occupy the Baltic countries."
1944,"July 13","World War II: Vilnius is liberated."
1944,"July 18","World War II: Hideki Tojo resigns as Prime Minister of Japan due to numerous setbacks in the war effort."
1944,"July 20","World War II: Adolf Hitler survives an assassination attempt."
1944,"July 21","World War II: Battle of Guam: American troops land on Guam (the battle ends on August 10th)."
1944,"July 21","World War II: The Polish Committee for National Liberation is created."
1944,"August 1","World War II: The Warsaw Uprising begins."
1944,"August 5","Over 500 Japanese prisoners-of-war attempt a mass breakout from the Cowra POW Camp."
1944,"August 15","World War II: Operation Dragoon lands Allies in southern France. The U.S. Army 45th Infantry Division participates in its fourth assault landing at St. Maxime, spearheading the drive for the Belfort Gap."
1944,"August 19","World War II: An insurrection starts in Paris."
1944,"August 20","World War II: American forces successfully defeat Nazi forces at Chambois, closing the Falaise Gap."
1944,"August 22","World War II: Tsushima Maru, a Japanese unmarked passenger/cargo ship, is sunk by torpedoes launched by the submarine USS Bowfin off Akuseki-jima, killing 1,484 civilians including 767 schoolchildren."
1944,"August 23","World War II: Ion Antonescu, prime minister of Romania, is arrested and a new government established. Romania exits the war against Soviet Union, joining the Allies."
1944,"August 24","World War II: The Allies liberate Paris, successfully completing Operation Overlord."
1944,"August 24","World War II : Japanese attack the USS Harder."
1944,"August 25","World War II: Hungary decides to continue the war together with Germany."
1944,"August 29","World War II: The Slovak National Uprising against the Axis powers begins."
1944,"September 1","World War II: In Bulgaria, the Bagrianov government resigns."
1944,"September 3","World War II: The Allies liberate Brussels."
1944,"September 5","World War II: The Soviets declare war on Bulgaria."
1944,"September 7","World War II: The Belgian government in exile returns to Brussels from London."
1944,"September 9","World War II: An insurrection breaks out in Sofia."
1944,"September 11","World War II: Northern and Southern France invasion forces link up near Dijon."
1944,"September 15","World War II: The Battle of Peleliu begins."
1944,"September 17","World War II: Operation Market Garden begins."
1944,"September 19","World War II: An armistice between Finland and the Soviet Union is signed, ending the Continuation War."
1944,"September 20","World War II: Jüri Uluots, prime minister in capacity of president of Estonia, escapes to Sweden; 2 days later, Tallinn is taken by the Red Army."
1944,"September 24","World War II: The U.S. Army 45th Infantry Division takes the strongly defended city of Epinal before crossing the Moselle River and entering the western foothills of the Vosges."
1944,"October 6","World War II: The Battle of Debrecen starts on the Eastern Front (it lasts until October 29)."
1944,"October 8","[i]The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet[/i] radio show debuts in the United States."
1944,"October 9","World War II: British Prime Minister Winston Churchill and Soviet Union Premier Joseph Stalin begin a 9-day conference in Moscow to discuss the future of Europe."
1944,"October 12","World War II: The Allies land in Athens."
1944,"October 13","World War II: Riga, the capital of Latvia, is taken by the Red Army."
1944,"October 14","World War II: German Field Marshal Erwin Rommel commits suicide rather than face execution for allegedly conspiring against Adolf Hitler."
1944,"October 23","World War II: The Naval Battle of Leyte Gulf in the Philippines begins (lasts until October 26)."
1944,"November 3","World War II: Two supreme commanders of the Slovak National Uprising, Generals Ján Golian and Rudolf Viest, are captured, tortured and later executed by German forces."
1944,"December 3","World War II: Fighting breaks out between Communists and royalists in newly liberated Greece, eventually leading to a full-scale Greek Civil War."
1944,"December 12","(December 12 - December 13) World War II: British units attempt to take the hilltop town of Tossignano, but are repulsed."
1944,"December 13","Battle of Mindoro: United States, Australian and Philippine Commonwealth troops land in Mindoro Island, the Philippines."
1944,"December 14","The Soviet government changes Turkish place names to Russian in the Crimea."
1944,"December 17","World War II: German troops carry out the Malmedy massacre."
1944,"December 24","World War II: The Bulge reaches its deepest point at Celles."
1944,"December 26","World War II: American troops repulse German forces at Bastogne."
1944,"December 31","World War II: Hungary declares war on Germany."
1944,"December 31","World War II: Battle of Leyte: Over hundreds of thousands of Japanese Imperial forces are killed in action, in a significant Filipino and Allied military victory."
1944,"circa","In Sweden, the law of 1864 that criminalizes homosexuality is abolished."
1944,"circa","Olympic Games are suspended due to World War II."
1944,"circa","In Sweden, Erik Wallenberg and Ruben Rausing invent a way to package milk in paper and start the company Tetra Pak."
