1944,"circa","Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945)"
1944,"circa","Second World War (1939-1945)"
1945,"January 9","World War II: The Soviet Union begins the Vistula-Oder Offensive in Eastern Europe against the Nazis."
1945,"January 17","World War II: A Soviet patrol arrests Raoul Wallenberg in Hungary."
1945,"January 22","Franklin D. Roosevelt is inaugurated to an unprecedented 4th term as President of the United States. No president before, or since, has ever reached a third term in office."
1945,"January 23","Hungary drops out of World War II, agreeing to an armistice with the Allies."
1945,"January 28","World War II: Supplies begin to reach China over the newly reopened Burma Road."
1945,"February 2","World War II: President Franklin D. Roosevelt and British Prime Minister Winston Churchill leave to meet with Soviet leader Joseph Stalin at the Yalta Conference."
1945,"February 4","World War II: President Franklin D. Roosevelt, Prime Minister of the United Kingdom Winston Churchill and Soviet leader Joseph Stalin begin the Yalta Conference (ends February 11)."
1945,"February 7","World War II: General Douglas MacArthur returns to Manila."
1945,"February 10","World War II: The [i]SS General von Steuben[/i] is sunk by the [i]Soviet submarine S-13[/i]."
1945,"February 19","World War II - Battle of Iwo Jima: About 30,000 United States Marines land on Iwo Jima."
1945,"March 7","World War II: American troops seize the bridge over the Rhine River at Remagen, Germany and begin to cross."
1945,"March 9","(March 9 - March 10) World War II: American B-29 bombers attack Japan with incendiary bombs; Tokyo is fire-bombed killing 100,000 citizens."
1945,"March 16","World War II: The Battle of Iwo Jima unofficially ends, with small pockets of guerrilla resistance persisting past the official conclusion of the battle."
1945,"March 17","World War II: Kobe, Japan is fire-bombed by 331 B-29 bombers, killing over 8,000 people."
1945,"March 18","World War II: 1,250 American bombers attack Berlin."
1945,"March 21","World War II: British troops liberate Mandalay, Burma."
1945,"March 24","World War II - Operation Varsity: Two airborne divisions capture bridges across the Rhine River to aid the Allied advance."
1945,"March 26","World War II: The Battle of Iwo Jima officially ends, with the mopping up of the remaining areas of Japansese resistance."
1945,"April 1","World War II - Battle of Okinawa: United States troops land on Okinawa."
1945,"April 6","World War II: Sarajevo is liberated from the Nazi Germany and Nazi Croatia (German puppet state) by the Yugoslav Partisans."
1945,"April 9","World War II: The Battle of Königsberg, in East Prussia, ends."
1945,"April 16","World War II: The [i]Goya[/i] is sunk by the [i]Soviet submarine L-3[/i]."
1945,"April 17","Brazilian forces liberate the town of Montese, Italy, from German forces."
1945,"April 18","The American war correspondent Ernie Pyle is killed by Japanese machine gun fire on the island of Ie Shima off Okinawa."
1945,"April 25","World War II - Elbe Day: United States and Soviet troops link up at the Elbe River, cutting Germany in two."
1945,"April 26","Battle of Bautzen (World War II): The last ""successful"" German panzer-offensive in Bautzen ends with the city recaptured."
1945,"April 27","The Western Allies flatly reject any offer of surrender by Germany other than unconditional on all fronts."
1945,"April 29","Operation Manna: British Lancaster bombers drop food into the Netherlands to prevent the starvation of the civilian population.Adolf Hitler marries his long time mistress Eva Braun in a close civil ceremony in Berlin Fuehrerbunker."
1945,"April 29","Brazilian forces liberate the commune of Fornovo di Taro, Italy, from German forces."
1945,"April 30","Adolf Hitler and his wife of one day, Eva Braun, commit suicide as the Red Army approaches the [i]Führerbunker[/i] in Berlin. Karl Dönitz succeeds Hitler as President of Germany. Joseph Goebbels succeeds Hitler as Chancellor of Germany."
1945,"May 7","World War II: General Alfred Jodl signs unconditional surrender terms at Reims, France, ending Germany's participation in the war. The document takes effect the next day."
1945,"May 14","(May 14 - May 15) World War II - Battle of Poljana: The last battle of World War II in Europe is fought at Poljana near Slovenj Gradec, Slovenia."
1945,"May 23","President of Germany Karl Dönitz and Chancellor of Germany Count Lutz Graf Schwerin von Krosigk are arrested by British forces at Flensburg. They are respectively the last German Head of state and Head of government until 1949."
1945,"June 5","The Allied Control Council, military occupation governing body of Germany, formally takes power."
1945,"June 11","The Franck Committee recommends against a surprise nuclear bombing of Japan."
1945,"June 21","World War II: The Battle of Okinawa ends."
1945,"June 24","World War II: A victory parade is held in Red Square in Moscow."
1945,"July 1","World War II: Germany is divided between the Allied occupation forces."
1945,"July 5","World War II: The Philippines are declared liberated."
1945,"July 8","World War II: Harry S. Truman is informed that Japan will talk peace if it can retain the reign of the Emperor."
1945,"July 16","World War II: A train collision near Munich, Germany kills 102 war prisoners."
1945,"July 17","World War II - Potsdam Conference: At Potsdam, the 3 main Allied leaders begin their final summit of the war (meeting ends August 2)."
1945,"July 21","World War II: President Harry S. Truman approves the order for atomic bombs to be used against Japan."
1945,"July 23","World War II: French marshal Philippe Pétain, who headed the Vichy government during World War II, goes on trial for treason."
1945,"July 26","The Potsdam Declaration demands Japan's unconditional surrender; Article 12 permitting Japan to retain the reign of the Emperor has been deleted by President Truman."
1945,"July 28","World War II: Japan ambiguously rejects the Potsdam Declaration. ."
1945,"August 6","World War II: Atomic bombing of Hiroshima: A United States B-29 Superfortress, the Enola Gay, drops an atomic bomb, codenamed ""Little Boy,"" on Hiroshima, Japan, at 8:15 a.m. (local time)."
1945,"August 8","The United Nations Charter is ratified by the United States Senate, and this nation becomes the third one to join the new international organization."
1945,"August 8","The Soviet Union declares war on Japan."
1945,"August 8","A United States B-29 Bomber, the Bockscar, drops an atomic bomb, codenamed ""Fat Man,"" on Nagasaki, Japan, at 11:02 a.m. (local time)."
1945,"August 8","The Soviet Union begins its army offensive against Japan in the northern part of the Japanese-held Chinese region of Manchuria."
1945,"August 8","Japan offers to surrender to the Allies, ""provided this does not prejudice the sovereignty of the Emperor""."
1945,"August 11","World War II: The Allies reply to the Japanese surrender offer by saying that Emperor Hirohito will be subject to the authority of the Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces."
1945,"August 14","World War II: Emperor Hirohito accepts the terms of the Potsdam Declaration."
1945,"September 2","Japanese general Tomoyuki Yamashita surrenders to Filipino and American forces at Kiangan, Ifugao."
1945,"September 2","World War II ends: The final official surrender of Japan is accepted by the Supreme Allied Commander, General Douglas MacArthur, and Fleet Admiral Chester Nimitz for the United States, and delegates from Australia, New Zealand, the United Kingdom, The Netherlands, China, and others from a Japanese delegation led by Mamoru Shigemitsu, on board the American battleship USS [i]Missouri[/i] in Tokyo Bay (but in Japan August 14 is recognized as the day the Pacific War ended)."
1945,"September 4","World War II: Japanese forces surrender on Wake Island after hearing word of their country's surrender."
1945,"September 5","Iva Toguri D'Aquino, a Japanese-American suspected of being wartime radio propagandist ""Tokyo Rose,"" is arrested in Yokohama."
1945,"September 5","The Russian code clerk Igor Gouzenko comes forward with numerous documents implicating the Soviet Union in numerous spy rings in North America: both in the United States and in Canada."
1945,"September 8","Hideki Tojo, Japanese prime minister during most of World War II, attempts suicide to avoid facing a war crimes tribunal."
1945,"September 12","The Japanese Army formally surrenders to the British in Singapore."
1945,"September 18","Typhoon Makurazaki in Japan kills 3,746 people."
1945,"October","Arthur C. Clarke puts forward the idea of a communications satellite in a [i]Wireless World[/i] magazine article."
1945,"October 3","(October 3 - October 10) The Detroit Tigers win the World Series against the Chicago Cubs, who haven't made it to the World Series since."
1945,"October 15","World War II: Pierre Laval, the former premier of Vichy France, is shot to death by a firing squad for treason against France."
1945,"October 24","ICJ (""World Court"") established by the United Nations Charter."
1945,"November 16","Cold War: The United States controversially imports 88 German scientists to help in the production of rocket technology."
1945,"November 20","The Nuremberg Trials begin: Trials against 24 Nazi war criminals of World War II start at the Nuremberg Palace of Justice."
1945,"December 4","By a vote of 65-7, the United States Senate approves the entry of the United States into the United Nations."
1945,"December 27","Twenty-eight nations sign an agreement creating the World Bank."
1945,"circa","Female suffrage is enacted in Guatemala and Japan."
1945,"circa","High-altitude, west-to-east winds across the Pacific Ocean (discovered by the Japanese in 1942 and by U.S. Army Air Forces in 1944) are dubbed the [i]jet stream[/i]."
1946,"January 7","The Allies recognize the Austrian republic with 1937 borders, and divide the country into 4 occupation zones."
1946,"January 20","Charles De Gaulle resigns as president of France."
1946,"February 20","An explosion kills more than 400 coal miners in West Germany."
1946,"March 6","Vietnam War: Ho Chi Minh signs an agreement with France which recognizes Vietnam as an autonomous state in the Indochinese Federation and the French Union."
1946,"March 19","French Guiana, Guadeloupe, Martinique and Réunion become overseas départements of France."
1946,"April 3","Japanese Lt. General Masaharu Homma is executed outside Manila, the Philippines for leading the Bataan Death March."
1946,"April 17","Syria's independence from France is officially recognized."
1946,"April 18","The United States recognizes Josip Broz Tito's government in Yugoslavia."
1946,"May 9","King Victor Emmanuel III of Italy abdicates, and is succeeded by his son Humbert II."
1946,"June 10","Italy is declared a republic."
1946,"June 13","Humbert II of Italy leaves the country and goes into exile in Portugal; Alcide de Gasperi becomes head of state."
1946,"June 25","International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (IBRD) (World Bank) begins operations."
1946,"July 21","An Irgun bomb explodes in Jerusalem because of secretive talks between Jews and Britain to consolidate the state of Israel."
1946,"July 25","In the last mass lynching in the United States, a mob of white men shoot and kill two African-American couples near Moore's Ford Bridge in Georgia."
1946,"August 3","Holiday World, originally called [i]Santa Claus Land[/i], opens to the public. It became the 1st themed park preceding Disneyland by 9 years."
1946,"October 13","France adopts the constitution of the Fourth Republic."
1946,"November 6","Senate and House elections in the United States both give majorities to the Republicans."
1946,"November 15","The Netherlands recognizes the Republic of Indonesia."
1946,"November 19","Afghanistan, Iceland and Sweden join the United Nations."
1946,"November 27","Cold War: Indian Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru appeals to the United States and the Soviet Union to end nuclear testing and to start nuclear disarmament, stating that such an action would ""save humanity from the ultimate disaster""."
1946,"December 7","A fire at the Winecoff Hotel in Atlanta, United States kills 119."
1946,"December 12","The United Nations severs relations with Franco's Spain and recommends that member countries sever diplomatic relations."
1946,"December 20","At least 1,362 people are killed in an earthquake and associated tsunami in Japan."
1946,"December 31","President Harry Truman delivers Proclamation 2714, which officially ends hostilities in World War II."
1946,"circa","The Chinese Civil War intensifies between the Kuomintang and the Communist Party of China."
1946,"circa","Eva Perón tours Spain, Italy and France on behalf of Argentina, a circuit called the Rainbow Tour."
1947,"January 16","Vincent Auriol is inaugurated as president of France."
1947,"February 8","A dance hall fire in Berlin, Germany, kills over 80 people."
1947,"February 10","In Paris, France, peace treaties are signed between the World War II Allies and Italy, Hungary, Romania, Bulgaria, and Finland. Italy cedes most of Istria to the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia."
1947,"February 25","The state of Prussia officially ceases to exist."
1947,"February 25","The worst-ever train crash in Japan kills 184 people."
1947,"February 28","The United States grants France a military base in Casablanca."
1947,"March 28","A World War II Japanese booby trap explodes on Corregidor island, killing 28 people."
1947,"April 18","The British Royal Navy detonates 6,800 tonnes of explosives in a deliberate attempt to demolish the fortified island of Heligoland, Germany, thus creating one of the largest man-made non-nuclear explosions in history."
1947,"May 3","The new post-war Japanese constitution goes into effect."
1947,"May 22","David Lean's film [i]Great Expectations[/i], based on the novel by Charles Dickens, opens in the United States. Critics call it the finest film ever made from a Charles Dickens novel."
1947,"July 11","The [i]Exodus (ship)[/i] leaves France for Palestine, with 4,500 Jewish Holocaust survivor refugees on board."
1947,"August 5","The Netherlands stops all political actions in Indonesia."
1947,"August 30","A fire at a movie theater in Rueil, a suburb of Paris, France kills 87 people."
1947,"September 10","Hasan Saka forms the new government of Turkey. (16 th government)"
1947,"October 20","A civil-war begins in Kashmir, along the border between India and Pakistan, leading to the Indo-Pakistani War of 1947 in the following year. Also, Pakistan established diplomatic relations with the United States of America."
1947,"November 6","The program [i]Meet the Press[/i] makes its television debut on the NBC-TV network in the United States."
1947,"November 16","Great Britain begin withdrawing its army troops from Palestine."
1947,"November 27","In Paris, France, police occupy the editorial offices of the communist newspapers."
1947,"December 22","The Italian Constituent Assembly votes to accept the new Constitution of Italy."
1948,"January 22","British foreign secretary Bevin proposes the formation of a Western Union between Britain, France and the Benelux countries to stand up against the Soviet Union. The Treaty of Brussels is signed March 17 as a consequence, a predecessor to NATO."
1948,"March 8","[i]McCollum v. Board of Education[/i]: The United States Supreme Court rules that religious instruction in public schools violates the U.S. Constitution."
1948,"April 7","The World Health Organization is established by the United Nations."
1948,"May 26","The U.S. Congress passes [i]Public Law 557[/i], which permanently establishes the Civil Air Patrol as the auxiliary of the United States Air Force."
1948,"June 10","Hasan Saka forms the new government of Turkey. (17th government; Hasan Saka had served twice as a prime minister)"
1948,"June 21","The Deutsche Mark becomes official currency of the future Federal Republic of Germany."
