1950,"January 13","Finland forms diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China."
1950,"January 29","Lord Balfour criticizes the fact that rationing is still in force in Britain."
1950,"January 31","The last Kuomintang troops surrender in mainland China."
1950,"February 1","Chiang Kai-shek is re-elected as a president of the Republic of China."
1950,"February 9","Second Red Scare: In his speech to the Republican Women's Club at the McClure Hote in Wheeling, West Virginia, Senator Joseph McCarthy accuses the United States Department of State of being filled with 205 Communists."
1950,"February 19","Konrad Adenauer tries unsuccessfully to negotiate with East Germany to begin unification."
1950,"March 1","Klaus Fuchs is convicted in London of spying against both Britain and the United States for the Soviet Union, by giving to the latter top secret atomic bomb data."
1950,"March 22","Egypt demands that Britain remove all its troops in the Suez Canal."
1950,"March 23","World Meteorological Organization (WMO)"
1950,"April 27","Britain formally recognises Israel."
1950,"May 22","Celal Bayar becomes the third president of Turkey."
1950,"May 22","Adnan Menderes of DP forms the new government of Turkey (19th government)"
1950,"June 6","Turkey: The Adhan in Arabic is legalized."
1950,"June 29","United States defeats England 1-0 in the 1950 FIFA World Cup."
1950,"July 16","Uruguay beat Brazil 2-1 to win the 1950 World Cup."
1950,"September 19","West Germany decides to purge communist officials."
1950,"September 22","World Dance Council inaugurated."
1950,"October 7","The 1950-1951 invasion of Tibet by People's Republic of China begins."
1950,"October 15","In East Germany, the Communists win 99.7% of the vote."
1950,"October 30","The Jayuya Uprising is started by Puerto Rican Nationalists against the United States."
1950,"November 4","The United Nations ends the diplomatic isolation of Spain."
1950,"November 25","A phenomenal winter storm ravages the northeastern United States, brings 30 to 50 inches of snow, temperatures below zero, and kills 323 people."
1950,"November 26","Korean War: Troops from the People's Republic of China move into North Korea and launch a massive counterattack against South Korean and American forces at Chosin, dashing any hopes for a quick end to the conflict."
1950,"December 16","The Office of Defense Mobilization is established in the United States."
1950,"circa","President Harry Truman sends United States military advisers to Vietnam to aid French forces."
1950,"circa","France institutes a government-guaranteed minimum wage."
1951,"January 15","Ilse Koch, The ""Witch of Buchenwald,"" wife of the commandant of the Buchenwald concentration camp, is sentenced to life imprisonment in a court in West Germany."
1951,"January 20","Avalanches in the Alps kill 240 and bury 45,000 for a time in Switzerland, Austria and Italy."
1951,"February 1","The United Nations General Assembly declares that China is the aggressor in the Korean War."
1951,"February 27","The Twenty-second Amendment to the United States Constitution, limiting Presidents to two terms, is ratified."
1951,"March 14","West Germany joins UNESCO."
1951,"April 23","The Philippines win the Battle of Yultong Bridge having casualties of an average of 10 dead, 26 wounded and 14 missing compared to 12,000 killed on the Republic of China's side."
1951,"April 24","In Yokohama, Japan a fire on a train kills more than 100."
1951,"May 3","The Festival of Britain opens."
1951,"May 23","Tibetans are forced to sign the Seventeen Point Agreement for the Peaceful Liberation of Tibet with the People's Republic of China."
1951,"July 13","The Great Flood of 1951 reaches its highest point in Northeast Kansas, culminating in the greatest flood damage to date in the Midwestern United States."
1951,"July 30","David Lean's [i]Oliver Twist[/i] is finally shown in the United States, after 10 minutes of supposedly anti-Semitic references and closeups of Alec Guinness as Fagin are cut. It will not be shown uncut in the U.S. until 1970."
1951,"August 11","René Pleven becomes Prime Minister of France."
1951,"September 1","The United States, Australia and New Zealand all sign a mutual defense pact, called the ANZUS Treaty."
1951,"September 8","Treaty of San Francisco: In San Francisco, California, 48 nations sign a peace treaty with Japan to formally end the Pacific War."
1951,"September 8","Japan-U.S. Security Treaty, which allows United States Armed Forces being stationed in Japan after the occupation of Japan, is signed by Japan and the United States."
1951,"September 20","NATO accepts Greece and Turkey as members."
1951,"October 3","Shot Heard 'Round the World"": One of the greatest moments in Major League Baseball history occurs when the New York Giants' Bobby Thomson hits a game winning home run in the bottom of the 9th inning off of Brooklyn Dodgers pitcher Ralph Branca, to win the National League pennant after being down 14 games."
1951,"October 21","A Storm in southern Italy kills over 100."
1951,"October 23","Sheffield artist Ian Ernest Markham is born in Hannover, West Germany."
1951,"October 24","U.S. President Harry Truman declares an official end to war with Germany."
1951,"November 10","Direct dial coast-to-coast telephone service begins in the United States."
1951,"November 20","The Po River floods in northern Italy."
1951,"November 28","[i]Scrooge[/i], starring Alastair Sim, premieres in the United States under the title of Charles Dickens's original novel, [i]A Christmas Carol[/i]."
1951,"December 24","Libya becomes independent from Italy."
1952,"January 8","West Germany has 8 million refugees inside its borders."
1952,"February 18","Turkey joins the North Atlantic Treaty Organization."
1952,"March 20","The United States Senate ratifies a peace treaty with Japan."
1952,"March 21","The last two executions in The Netherlands take place."
1952,"April 4","In the Hague Tribunal, Israel demands reparations worth $3 billion from Germany."
1952,"April 8","[i]Youngstown Sheet & Tube Co. v. Sawyer[/i]: The U.S. Supreme Court limits the power of the President to seize private business, after President Harry S. Truman nationalizes all steel mills in the United States, just before the 1952 steel strike begins."
1952,"April 11","Battle of Nanri Island: The Republic of China seizes the island from the Peoples' Republic of China."
1952,"April 18","West Germany and Japan form diplomatic relations."
1952,"April 28","The Treaty of San Francisco goes into effect, formally ending the war between Japan and the Allies, and simultaneously ending the occupation of the four main Japanese islands."
1952,"April 29","Lever House officially opens in New York City, heralding a new age of commercial architecture in the United States."
1952,"May 1","East Germany threatens to form its own army."
1952,"May 15","Diplomatic relations are established between the governments of Israel and Japan at the level of legations."
1952,"June 19","[i]The United States Army Special Forces is created[/i]."
