1952,"July 13","East Germany announces the formation of its National People's Army."
1952,"July 25","Puerto Rico becomes a self-governing commonwealth of the United States."
1952,"August 5","The Treaty of Taipei between Japan and the Republic of China goes into effect, to officially end the Second Sino-Japanese War."
1952,"August 13","Japan joins IMF."
1952,"August 14","West Germany joins the IMF and the World Bank."
1952,"August 27","Reparation negotiations between West Germany and Israel end in Luxembourg; Germany will pay 3 billion Deutsche Marks."
1952,"August 31","The Grenzlandring racetrack closes in Wegberg, Germany."
1952,"September 18","The Soviet Union vetoes Japan's application for membership in the United Nations."
1952,"November 4","United States presidential election, 1952: Republican Dwight D. Eisenhower defeats Democrat Adlai Stevenson (correctly predicted by the UNIVAC computer)."
1953,"January 7","President Harry S. Truman announces the United States has developed a hydrogen bomb."
1953,"January 15","Georg Dertinger, foreign minister of East Germany, is arrested for spying."
1953,"January 19","71.1% of all television sets in the United States are tuned in to [i]I Love Lucy[/i] to watch Lucy give birth."
1953,"January 20","Dwight D. Eisenhower succeeds Harry S. Truman as President of the United States."
1953,"January 26","Walter Ulbricht announces that the agriculture will be collectivized in East Germany."
1953,"January 31","(January 31 - February 1) The North Sea flood of 1953 kills 1,835 people in the southwestern Netherlands (especially Zeeland), 307 in the United Kingdom."
1953,"February 28","Greece, Turkey, and Yugoslavia sign the Balkan Pact."
1953,"March 18","An earthquake hits western Turkey, killing 250."
1953,"May 9","France agrees to the provisional independence of Cambodia with King Norodom Sihanouk."
1953,"May 10","The town of Chemnitz in East Germany becomes [i]Karl Marx Stadt[/i]."
1953,"June 8","Austria and the Soviet Union form diplomatic relations."
1953,"June 17","Workers Uprising: In East Germany, the Soviet Union orders a division of troops into East Berlin to quell a rebellion."
1953,"July 27","The Korean War ends: The United States, People's Republic of China, North Korea, and South Korea sign an armistice agreement."
1953,"August 13","4 million workers go on strike in France to protest austerity measures."
1953,"August 20","The United States gives West Germany 382 ships it had captured during World War II."
1953,"August 25","The general strike ends in France."
1953,"September 5","The United Nations rejects the Soviet Union's suggestion to accept China as a member."
1953,"October 5","Earl Warren is appointed Chief Justice of the United States by U.S. president Dwight D. Eisenhower."
1953,"October 30","Cold War: U.S. President Dwight D. Eisenhower formally approves the top secret document of the United States National Security Council NSC 162/2, which states that the United States' arsenal of nuclear weapons must be maintained and expanded to counter the communist threat."
1953,"November 9","Cambodia becomes independent from France."
1953,"December 25","Amami Islands are returned to Japan after 8 years of United States Military occupation."
1953,"circa","The Japanese 10 yen coin is issued with serrated edges for a 5-year period, beginning in 1953. All 10 yen coins since have had smooth edges."
1953,"circa","Heavy massive rain, landslides, and flooding in western and southwestern Japan kill an estimated 2,566, and injure 9,433, mainly at Kizugawa, Wakayama, Kumamoto and Kitakyushu (June-August)."
1954,"January 1","The Soviet Union ceases to demand war reparations from East Germany."
1954,"January 12","Avalanches in Austria kill more than 200."
1954,"January 20","The coldest day ever recorded in the contiguous United States at -56.5 °C (-100 °F)."
1954,"January 25","The foreign ministers of the United States, Britain, France and the Soviet Union meet at the Berlin Conference."
1954,"February 10","After authorizing $385 million over the $400 million already budgeted for military aid to Vietnam, U.S. President Dwight Eisenhower warns against United States intervention in Vietnam."
1954,"March 1","U.S. Capitol shooting incident: Four Puerto Rican nationalists open fire in the United States House of Representatives chamber and wound five; they are apprehended by security guards."
1954,"March 12","Finland and Germany officially end their state of war."
1954,"March 25","The Soviet Union recognizes the sovereignty of East Germanysuck Soviet troops remain in the country."
1954,"April 16","Vice President Richard Nixon announces that the United States may be ""putting our own boys in Indochina regardless of Allied support""."
1954,"April 22","Senator Joseph McCarthy begins hearings investigating the United States Army for being ""soft"" on Communism."
1954,"April 26","International conference on Korea and Indo-China opens in Geneva."
1954,"April 28","U.S. Secretary of State John Foster Dulles accuses Communist China of sending combat troops to Indo-China to train the Viet Minh guerrillas."
1954,"May 11","U.S. Secretary of State John Foster Dulles declares that Indochina is important but not essential to the security of Southeast Asia thus ending any prospect of American intervention on the side of France."
1954,"May 17","[i]Brown v. Board of Education[/i] (347 US 483 1954): The United States Supreme Court rules that segregated schools are unconstitutional."
1954,"May 17","Adnan Menderes of DP forms the new government of Turkey (21st government)"
1954,"May 20","Chiang Kai-shek is reelected president of the Republic of China by the National Assembly."
1954,"June 9","McCarthyism: Joseph Welch, special counsel for the United States Army, lashes out at Senator Joseph McCarthy, during hearings on whether Communism has infiltrated the Army, saying, 'Have you, at long last, no decency?'."
1954,"June 14","The words ""under God"" are added to the United States Pledge of Allegiance."
1954,"June 18","Pierre Mendès-France becomes prime minister of France."
1954,"July 1","The United States officially begins using the international unit of the nautical mile, equal to 6,076.11549 ft. or 1,852 meters."
1954,"July 4","Food rationing in Great Britain ends with the lifting of restrictions on sale and purchase of meat, 14 years after it began early in World War II and nearly a decade after the war's end."
1954,"July 4","West Germany beats Hungary 3-2 to win the 1954 FIFA World Cup."
1954,"September 26","The Japanese ferry [i]Toya Maru[/i] sinks during a typhoon in the Tsugaru Strait. More than 1,100 people are killed."
1954,"October 23","West Germany joins NATO."
1954,"October 25","Landslides caused by heavy rains hit Salerno, Italy, killing about 300."
1954,"November 5","Japan and Burma sign a separate peace treaty in Rangoon, to end their formal state of war."
1954,"November 22","The United States Supreme Court decides the landmark case Berman v. Parker (348 U.S. 26), upholding the federal slum clearance and urban renewal program."
1954,"December 2","Red Scare: The United States Senate votes 67-22 to condemn Joseph McCarthy for ""conduct that tends to bring the Senate into dishonor and disrepute""."
1954,"December 2","The Taiwan-United States Mutual Defense Treaty is signed."
1954,"December 24","Laos gains full independence from France."
1954,"circa","Gerbils (Meriones Unguiculatus) are brought to the United States by Dr. Victor Schwentker."
1955,"January 18","(January 18 - January 20) Battle of Yijiangshan Islands: The Chinese Communist People's Liberation Army seizes the islands from the Republic of China (Taiwan)."
1955,"January 25","Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the Soviet Union announces the end of the war between the USSR and Germany, which began during World War II in 1941."
1955,"January 28","United States Congress authorizes President Dwight D. Eisenhower to use force to protect Formosa from the People's Republic of China."
1955,"February 10","Seventh Fleet of the United States Navy helps the Republic of China evacuate Chinese Nationalist army and residents from the Tachen Islands to Taiwan."
1955,"March 19","KXTV of Stockton, California, signs on the air in the United States, being the 100th commercial television station in this country."
1955,"March 20","Evan Hunter's movie adaptation of the novel [i]Blackboard Jungle[/i] premieres in the United States, featuring the famous single, [i]Rock Around the Clock[/i], by Bill Haley and His Comets. Teenagers jump from their seats to dance to the song."
1955,"April 11","The Taiwanese Kuomintang sabotage the ship [i]Kashmir Princess[/i], killing 16 but failing to assassinate the People's Republic of China leader, Zhou Enlai."
1955,"April 12","The Salk polio vaccine, having passed large-scale trials earlier in the United States, receives full approval by the FDA."
1955,"April 16","Burma-Japanese peace treaty, signed in Rangoon on November 5, 1954, comes into effect, formally ending a state of war between the two countries that had not existed for a long time."
1955,"May 5","West Germany becomes a sovereign country recognized by important Western foreign countries, such as France, the United Kingdom, Canada, and the United States."
1955,"May 9","West Germany joins the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)."
1955,"May 11","Japanese National Railways' ferry [i]Shiun Maru[/i] sinks after collision with sister ship [i]Uko Maru[/i] in thick fog off Takamatsu, Shikoku, in the Seto Inland Sea of Japan; 166 passengers (many children) and two crew are killed. This event is influential in plans to construct the Akashi-Kaikyo Bridge (built 1986-98)."
1955,"May 15","Austrian State Treaty, which restores Austria's national sovereignty, is concluded between the four occupying powers following World War II (the United Kingdom, the United States, the Soviet Union, and France) and Austria, setting it up as a neutral country."
1955,"June 7","The TV quiz program [i]The $64,000 Question[/i] premieres on CBS-TV in the United States, with Hal March as the host."
1955,"June 11","Le Mans disaster: eighty-three people are killed and at least 100 are injured after two race cars collide in Le Mans, France."
1955,"July 27","El Al Flight 402 from Vienna, Austria to Tel Aviv-Yafo via Istanbul is shot down over Bulgaria. All 58 passengers and crewmen aboard the Lockheed Constellation airplane are killed."
1955,"August 19","Hurricane Diane hits the northeastern United States, killing over 200 people, and causing over $1.0 billion in damage."
1955,"August 25","The last Soviet Army occupation forces leave Austria."
1955,"October 2","[i]Alfred Hitchcock Presents[/i] TV program debuts on the NBC-TV network in the United States."
1955,"October 3","[i]The Mickey Mouse Club[/i] TV program debuts on the ABC-TV network in the United States."
1955,"October 4","The Brooklyn Dodgers finally win the World Series, defeating the New York Yankees 2-0 in Game 7 of the 1955 baseball playoff."
1955,"October 26","After the last Allied troops have left the country and following the provisions of the Austrian Independence Treaty, Austria declares its permanent neutrality."
1955,"November 5","Racial segregation is outlawed on trains and buses in Interstate Commerce in the United States."
1955,"December 9","Adnan Menderes of DP forms the new government of Turkey (22nd government)"
1955,"December 14","Albania, Austria, Bulgaria, Cambodia, Finland, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Jordan, Laos, Libya, Nepal, Portugal, Romania, Spain, and Sri Lanka join the United Nations simultaneously, after several years of morotorium on admitting new members that began during the Korean War."
1956,"January 26","The 1956 Winter Olympic Games open in Cortina d'Ampezzo, Italy."
1956,"March 2","Morocco declares its independence from France."
1956,"March 20","Tunisia gains independence from France."
1956,"April 7","Spain relinquishes its protectorate in Morocco."
1956,"May 8","Austria and Israel form diplomatic relations. [i]Confirmation needed[/i]."
1956,"May 8","The constitutional union between Indonesia and the Netherlands is dissolved."
1956,"May 23","French minister Pierre Mendès France resigns due to his government's policy on Algeria."
1956,"May 25","India announces the institution of diplomatic relations with Spain (still under Franco's rule)"
1956,"June 10","1956 Summer Olympics: Equestrian events open in Stockholm, Sweden (all other events are held in November in Melbourne, Australia)."
1956,"June 30","A TWA Lockheed Constellation and United Airlines Douglas DC-7 collide in mid-air over the Grand Canyon in Arizona, killing all 128 people aboard both aircraft in the deadliest civil aviation disaster to date; the accident leads to sweeping changes in the regulation of cross-country flight and air traffic control over the United States."
1956,"August 17","West Germany bans the Communist Party of Germany."
1956,"October 8","Baseball pitcher Don Larsen of the New York Yankees throws the only perfect game in World Series history in Game 5 of the 1956 World Series against the Brooklyn Dodgers. Yogi Berra caught the game. Dale Mitchell was the final out. The New York Yankees won the series. Larsen was named series MVP."
1956,"October 22","Suez Crisis: Britain, France, and Israel secretly meet in and make plans to invade Egypt."
1956,"October 31","Suez Crisis: The United Kingdom and France begin bombing Egypt to force the reopening of the Suez Canal."
1956,"November 6","United States presidential election, 1956: Republican incumbent Dwight D. Eisenhower defeats Democrat challenger Adlai E. Stevenson in a rematch of their contest 4 years earlier."
1956,"November 7","Suez Crisis: The United Nations General Assembly adopts a resolution calling for the United Kingdom, France, and Israel to withdraw their troops from Arab lands immediately."
1956,"November 13","The United States Supreme Court declares Alabama and Montgomery, Alabama laws requiring segregated buses illegal, thus ending the Montgomery Bus Boycott."
1956,"November 23","The Suez Crisis causes petrol rationing in Britain."
1956,"December 12","Japan becomes a member of the United Nations."
1956,"December 19","John Bodkin Adams is arrested for the murder of 2 patients in Eastbourne, Great Britain."
1957,"January 1","The Saarland joins West Germany."
1957,"January 20","Dwight D. Eisenhower is inaugurated for a second term as President of the United States."
1957,"February 4","France prohibits U.N. involvement in Algeria."
1957,"February 16","Ingmar Bergman's film The Seventh Seal opens in Sweden."
1957,"March 3","[i]Net als toen[/i] by Corry Brokken (music by Guus Jansen, text by Willy van Hemert) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1957 for the Netherlands."
1957,"March 7","The United States Congress approves the Eisenhower Doctrine."
1957,"March 13","The United States Federal Bureau of Investigation arrests Jimmy Hoffa and charges him with bribery."
1957,"July 16","United States Marine Major John Glenn flies an F8U supersonic jet from California to New York in 3 hours, 23 minutes and 8 seconds, setting a new transcontinental speed record."
1957,"July 28","The 6th World Festival of Youth and Students, a high point of the Khruschev Thaw, kicks off in Moscow."
1957,"July 28","Heavy rains and mudslides at Isahaya, western Kyushu, Japan kill 992."
1957,"August 28","United States Senator Strom Thurmond (D-SC) sets the record for the longest filibuster with his 24-hour, 18-minute speech railing against a civil rights bill."
1957,"September 29","Kyshtym disaster occurs in Russia."
1957,"October 9","Neil H. McElroy is sworn in as United States Secretary of Defense."
1957,"October 27","Celal Bayar is re-elected president of Turkey."
1957,"November 7","Cold War: In the United States, the Gaither Report calls for more American missiles and fallout shelters."
1957,"November 13","Flooding in the Po River valley of Italy leads to flooding also in Venice."
1957,"November 15","Yugoslavia announces the end of an economic boycott of Franco's Spain (although it does not reinstitute diplomatic relations)."
1957,"November 25","Adnan Menderes of DP forms the new government of Turkey (23rd government,last government formed by DP and Adnan Menderes)"
1957,"circa","The Asian Flu pandemic begins in China."
