1958,"May 12","A formal North American Aerospace Defense Command agreement is signed between the United States and Canada."
1958,"June 1","Charles de Gaulle is brought out of retirement to lead France by decree for 6 months."
1958,"June 29","Brazil beats Sweden 5-2 to win the 1958 World Cup."
1958,"July 15","In Lebanon, 5,000 United States Marines land in the capital Beirut in order to protect the pro-Western government there."
1958,"August 18","Vladimir Nabokov's controversial novel [i]Lolita[/i] is published in the United States."
1958,"August 27","Operation Argus: The United States begins nuclear tests over the South Atlantic."
1958,"September 27","Typhoon Ida kills at least 1,269 in Honshu, Japan."
1958,"September 28","In France, a majority of 79% says yes to the constitution of the Fifth Republic."
1958,"October 2","Guinea declares itself independent from France."
1958,"November 30","Gaullists win parliamentary elections in France."
1958,"December 1","The Central African Republic becomes independent from France."
1958,"December 21","General Charles de Gaulle is elected president of France with 78.5% of the votes."
1958,"circa","Based on birth rates (per 1,000 population), the post-war baby boom ends in the United States as an 11-year decline in the birth rate begins (the longest on record in that country)."
1958,"circa","The last legal female genital cutting occurs in the United States."
1958,"circa","The Japanese 10 yen coin ceases having serrated edges after a 5-year period beginning in 1953. All 10 yen coins since have smooth edges."
1958,"circa","USA, USSR and Great Britain agree to stop testing atomic bombs for 3 years."
