1959,"April 10","Japanese Prince Akihito marries Shoda Michiko."
1959,"April 27","National People's Congress elects Liu Shaoqi as Chairman of the People's Republic of China, as a successor of Mao Zedong."
1959,"June 3","Singapore becomes a self-governing crown colony of Britain with Lee Kuan Yew as Prime Minister."
1959,"June 8","The USS [i]Barbero[/i] and United States Postal Service attempt the delivery of mail via Missile Mail."
1959,"June 23","Convicted Manhattan Project spy Klaus Fuchs is released after only 9 years in a British prison and allowed to emigrate to Dresden, East Germany (where he resumes a scientific career)."
1959,"July 1","The opening of the St. Lawrence Seaway by Canada and the United States, officiated by Her Majesty, Queen Elizabeth II."
1959,"July 4","With the admission of Alaska as the 49th U.S. state earlier in the year, the 49-star flag of the United States debuts in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania."
1959,"August 7","Explorer program: The United States launches Explorer 6 from the Atlantic Missile Range in Cape Canaveral, Florida."
1959,"August 7","United States The Roseburg Oregon Blast kills 14 and causes $12 million worth of damage."
1959,"October 13","The United States launches Explorer 7."
1959,"December 2","Malpasset Dam in southern France collapses and water flows over the town of Frejus, killing 412."
1959,"circa","The current (as of 2006) design of the Japanese 10 yen coin is put into circulation."
1960,"January 19","The Treaty of Mutual Cooperation and Security between the United States and Japan is signed in Washington, DC."
1960,"January 22","In France, President Charles de Gaulle fires Jacques Massu, commander-in-chief for the French troops in Algeria."
1960,"February 1","In Greensboro, North Carolina, four black students from North Carolina Agricultural and Technical State University begin a sit-in at a segregated Woolworth's lunch counter. Although they are refused service, they are allowed to stay at the counter. The event triggers many similar nonviolent protests throughout the Southern United States, and 6 months later the original 4 protesters are served lunch at the same counter."
1960,"March 3","Elvis Presley returns home from Germany, after being away on duty for 2 years."
1960,"March 25","[i]Tom Pillibi[/i] by Jacqueline Boyer (music by André Popp, text by Pierre Cour) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1960 for France."
1960,"April 13","United States launches navigation satellite Transit I-b."
1960,"May 20","In Japan, police carry away Socialist members of the Diet; Parliament then approves a security treaty with the United States."
1960,"May 27","In Turkey, a bloodless military coup d'état removes President Celal Bayar and installs General Cemal Gürsel as head of state."
1960,"May 30","Cemal Gürsel forms the new government of Turkey (24rd government, composed mostly of technocrats)"
1960,"June 9","Typhoon Mary kills 1,600 people in the Fukien province of China."
1960,"June 20","The Mali Federation between Senegal and the Sudanese Republic (now Mali) gains independence from France."
1960,"June 23","Japanese prime minister Nobusuke Kishi announces his resignation."
1960,"July 1","A Soviet MiG fighter north of Murmansk in the Barents Sea shoots down a 6-man RB-47. Two United States Air Force officers survive and are imprisoned in Moscow's dreaded Lubyanka prison."
1960,"July 1","Italian Somaliland gains its independence from Italy, 5 days after British Somaliland."
1960,"July 4","Following the admission of Hawaii as the 50th U.S. state the previous year, the 50-star flag of the United States debuts in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania."
1960,"August 1","Benin becomes independent from France, under the name Dahomey."
1960,"August 5","Burkina Faso (Upper Volta) declares independence from France."
1960,"August 6","Cuban Revolution: In response to a United States embargo against Cuba, Fidel Castro nationalizes American and foreign-owned property in the nation."
1960,"August 17","The newly named Beatles begin a 48-night residency at the Indra Club in Hamburg, West Germany."
1960,"August 17","Gabon gains independence from France."
1960,"August 19","Sputnik program: The Soviet Union launches Sputnik 5, with the dogs Belka and Strelka (Russian for ""Squirrel"" and ""Little Arrow""), 40 mice, 2 rats and a variety of plants. The spacecraft returns to earth the next day and all animals are recovered safely."
1960,"October 12","Otoya Yamaguchi assassinates Inejiro Asanuma, chairman of the Japanese Socialist Party."
1960,"November 8","United States presidential election, 1960: In a close race, John F. Kennedy is elected over Richard M. Nixon, becoming (at 43) the youngest man elected President."
1960,"November 28","Mauritania becomes independent of France."
1960,"December 5","Pierre Lagaillarde, who led 1958 and 1960 insurrections in Algeria, fails to appear in a Paris court. He has reportedly fled with 4 fellow defendants to Spain en route to Algeria."
1960,"December 16","U.S. Secretary of State Christian Herter announces that the United States will commit 5 atomic submarines and 80 Polaris missiles to NATO by the end of 1963."
1960,"December 27","France sets off its 3rd nuclear test blast at its atomic proving grounds at Reggane, Algeria."
1961,"March 1","President of the United States John F. Kennedy establishes the Peace Corps."
1961,"March 13","United States delegate to the UNSC Adlai Stevenson votes against Portuguese policies in Africa."
1961,"March 13","President of the United States John F. Kennedy proposes a long-term ""Alliance for Progress"" between the United States and Latin America."
1961,"March 29","The Twenty-third Amendment to the United States Constitution is ratified, allowing residents of Washington, D.C. to vote in presidential elections."
1961,"May 31","In France, rebel generals Maurice Challe and Andre Zelelr are sentenced to 15 years in prison."
1961,"June 4","Vienna summit: John F. Kennedy and Nikita Khrushchev meet during 2 days in Vienna. They discuss nuclear tests, disarmament and Germany."
1961,"June 21","Russian ballet dancer Rudolf Nureyev requests asylum in France while in Paris with the Kirov Ballet."
1961,"July 1","Diana, Princess of Wales is born in Sandringham, Norfolk, England, to her parents: Frances Spencer, Viscountess Althorp and John Spencer, Viscount Althorp (later the 8th Earl Spencer)."
1961,"August 10","Britain applies for membership in the European Economic Community."
1961,"August 13","Construction of the Berlin Wall begins, restricting movement between East Berlin and West Berlin and forming a clear boundary between West Germany and East Germany, Western Europe and Eastern Europe."
1961,"September 14","The new military government of Turkey sentences 15 members of the previous government to death."
1961,"September 17","Military rulers in Turkey hang former president Adnan Menderes."
1961,"September 21","In France, the OAS slips an anti-de Gaulle message into TV programming."
1961,"October 26","Cemal Gürsel becomes the fourth president of Turkey. ( His former title was head of state and government. By constitution referendum, he is elected as president)."
1961,"October 27","A standoff between Soviet and American tanks in Berlin, Germany heightens Cold War tensions."
1961,"October 27","Fahri Özdiilek becomes the acting prime minister of Turkey."
1961,"November 24","World Food Program (WFP) formed as a temporary UN program."
1961,"December 1","Netherlands New Guinea raises the new Morning Star flag and changes its name to West Papua."
1962,"January 1","The United States Navy SEALs are activated. SEAL Team One is commissioned in the Pacific Fleet and SEAL Team Two in the Atlantic Fleet."
1962,"January 13","Albania allies itself with the People's Republic of China."
1962,"February 3","The United States embargo against Cuba is announced."
1962,"February 6","Negotiations between U.S. Steel and the United States Department of Commerce begin."
1962,"February 7","The United States Government bans all U.S.-related Cuban imports and exports."
1962,"February 7","A coal mine explosion in Saarland, West Germany kills 299."
1962,"March 8","(March 8 - March 12) In Geneva, France and the Algerian FLN begin negotiations."
1962,"March 18","Évian Accords: France and Algeria sign an agreement in Évian-les-Bains ending the Algerian War."
1962,"March 18","[i]Un premier amour[/i], sung by Isabelle Aubret (music by Claude-Henri Vic, text by Roland Stephane Valade), wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1962 for France."
1962,"March 26","France shortens the term for military service from 26 months to 18."
1962,"April 8","In France, the Évian Accords are adopted in a referendum with a majority of 90%."
1962,"April 13","OAS leader Edmond Jouhaud is sentenced to death in France."
1962,"April 21","The Century 21 Exposition World's Fair opens in Seattle, Washington."
1962,"May 14","Juan Carlos of Spain marries the Greek Princess Sophia in Athens."
1962,"May 30","The 1962 FIFA World Cup begins in Chile."
1962,"June 3","Air France charter flight [i]Chateau de Sully[/i], a Boeing 707, over-runs the runway at Orly Airport in Paris; 130 of 132 passengers are killed, 2 flight attendants survive. Most victims are cultural and civic leaders of Atlanta, Georgia."
1962,"June 6","President John F. Kennedy gives the commencement address at the United States Military Academy at West Point, New York."
1962,"June 17","Brazil beats Czechoslovakia 3-1 to win the 1962 FIFA World Cup."
1962,"June 25","[i]Engel v. Vitale[/i]: The United States Supreme Court rules that mandatory prayers in public schools are unconstitutional."
1962,"June 25","[i]MANual Enterprises v. Day[/i]: The United States Supreme Court rules that photographs of nude men are not obscene, decriminalizing nude male pornographic magazines."
1962,"June 25","Ismet Inönü of CHP forms the new government of Turkey (27th government, coalition partners; YTP and CKMP)"
1962,"June 26","A 2-day steel strike begins in Italy, in support of increased wages and a 5-day working week."
1962,"July 2","Charles de Gaulle accepts Algerian independence; France recognizes it the next day."
1962,"July 5","Algeria becomes independent from France."
1962,"July 20","France and Tunisia reestablish diplomatic relations."
1962,"September 21","A border conflict between China and India erupts into fighting."
1962,"September 27","A flash flood in Barcelona, Spain, kills more than 440 people."
1962,"October 10","The Sino-Indian War, a border dispute involving two of the world's largest nations (India and the People's Republic of China), begins."
1962,"October 14","Cuban Missile Crisis begins: A U-2 flight over Cuba takes photos of Soviet nuclear weapons being installed. A stand-off then ensues the next day between the United States and the Soviet Union, threatening the world with nuclear war."
1962,"October 28","Cuban Missile Crisis: Soviet Union leader Nikita Khrushchev announces that he has ordered the removal of Soviet missile bases in Cuba. In a secret deal between Kennedy and Khrushchev Kennedy agrees to the withdrawal of U.S. missiles from Turkey. The fact that this deal is not made public makes it look like the Soviets have backed down."
1962,"October 28","A referendum in France favors the election of the president by universal suffrage."
1962,"November 29","An agreement is signed between Britain and France to develop the [i]Concorde[/i] supersonic airliner."
1962,"December 11","In West Germany, a coalition government of Christian Democrats, Christian Socialists, and Free Democrats is formed."
1962,"December 19","Britain acknowledges the right of Nyasaland (now Malawi) to secede from the Central African Federation."
1962,"December 22","Big Freeze"" in Britain: There are no frost-free nights until March 5, 1963."
1963,"January 22","France and Germany sign the Elysée Treaty."
1963,"February 8","Travel, financial and commercial transactions by United States citizens to Cuba are made illegal by the John F. Kennedy Administration."
1963,"February 10","Five Japanese cities located on the northernmost part of Kyushu are merged and become the city of KitaKyushu, with a population of more than 1 million."
1963,"February 19","The publication of Betty Friedan's [i]The Feminine Mystique[/i] launches the reawakening of the Women's Movement in the United States as women's organizations and consciousness-raising groups spread."
1963,"March 27","In Britain, Dr. Beeching issues a report calling for huge cuts to the UK's rail network."
1963,"April 28","A general election is held in Italy."
1963,"May 2","Berthold Seliger launches near Cuxhaven a 3 stage rocket with a maximum flight altitude of more than 62 miles (the only sounding rocket developed in Germany)."
1963,"May 13","A smallpox outbreak hits Stockholm, Sweden, lasting until July."
1963,"June 3","Hue chemical attacks: The Army of the Republic of Vietnam pours chemicals on the heads of Buddhist protestors. The United States threatens to cut off aid to Ngo Dinh Diem's regime."
1963,"June 13","The cancellation of Mercury 10 effectively ends the Mercury program of United States manned spaceflight."
1963,"July 5","Diplomatic relations between the Israeli and the Japanese governments are raised to embassy level."
1963,"August 5","The United States, United Kingdom, and Soviet Union sign a nuclear test ban treaty."
1963,"September 25","The Denning Report on the Profumo affair is published in Great Britain."
1963,"October 9","In northeast Italy, over 2,000 people are killed when a large landslide behind the Vajont Dam causes a giant wave of water to overtop it."
1963,"October 10","The second James Bond film, [i]From Russia with Love[/i], opens in the U.K."
1963,"November 7","Wunder von Lengede: In Germany, 11 miners are rescued from a collapsed mine after 14 days."
1963,"November 9","Miike Coal Mine explosion: In Japan, a coal mine explosion kills 458 and sends 839 carbon monoxide poisoning victims to the hospital."
1963,"November 9","A triple-train disaster in Yokohama, Japan kills 161."
1963,"November 22","John F. Kennedy assassination: In Dallas, Texas, United States President John F. Kennedy is assassinated, Texas Governor John B. Connally is seriously wounded, and Vice President Lyndon Baines Johnson becomes the 36th President. All television coverage for the next three days is devoted to the assassination, its aftermath, the procession of the horsedrawn casket to the Capitol Rotunda, and the funeral of President Kennedy. Stores and businesses shut down for the entire weekend and Monday, in tribute."
1963,"November 23","John Kilbride, 12, is abducted by Myra Hindley and Ian Brady in Great Britain."
1963,"November 24","Vietnam War: New U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson confirms that the United States intends to continue supporting South Vietnam militarily and economically."
1963,"December 19","Zanzibar gains independence from Great Britain as a constitutional monarchy, under Sultan Jamshid bin Abdullah."
1963,"December 25","Ismet Inönü of CHP forms the new government of Turkey (28th government, coalition partners; independents, Inönü has served 10 ten times as a prime minister, this is his last government)"
1964,"January 7","A British firm, the Leyland Motor Corp., announces the sale of 450 buses to the Cuban government, challenging the United States blockade of Cuba."
1964,"January 12","Routine U.S. naval patrols of the South China Sea begin."
1964,"January 18","Plans to build the New York World Trade Center are announced."
1964,"January 23","Pope Paul VI institutes the ""World Day of Prayer for Vocations"". It is being observed up to now. During this celebration the Popes remind the universal Church that still today salvation comes to us. It is celebrated every Fourth Sunday of Easter also known as Good Shepherd Sunday."
1964,"January 23","Thirteen years after its proposal and nearly 2 years after its passage by the United States Senate, the 24th Amendment to the United States Constitution, prohibiting the use of poll taxes in national elections, is ratified."
1964,"January 27","France and the People's Republic of China announce their decision to establish diplomatic relations."
1964,"January 28","A U.S. Air Force jet training plane that strays into East Germany is shot down by Soviet fighters near Erfurt; all 3 crew men are killed."
1964,"January 29","(January 29 - February 9) The 1964 Winter Olympics are held in Innsbruck, Austria."
1964,"February 4","The Government of the United States authorizes the Twenty-fourth Amendment, outlawing the poll tax."
1964,"February 6","Cuba cuts off the normal water supply to the United States Guantanamo Bay Naval Base, in reprisal for the U.S. seizure 4 days earlier of 4 Cuban fishing boats off the coast of Florida."
1964,"February 11","The Republic of China (Taiwan) drops diplomatic relations with France because of French recognition of the People's Republic of China."
1964,"February 17","[i]Wesberry v. Sanders[/i] (376 US 1 1964): The Supreme Court of the United States rules that congressional districts have to be approximately equal in population."
1964,"February 27","The government of Italy asks for help to keep the Leaning Tower of Pisa from toppling over."
1964,"February 29","U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson announces that the United States has developed a jet airplane (the A-11), capable of sustained flight at more than 2,000 miles per hour (3,200 km/h) and of altitudes of more than 70,000 feet (21,000 m)."
1964,"March 9","[i]New York Times Co. v Sullivan[/i] (376 US 254 1964): The United States Supreme Court rules that under the First Amendment, speech criticizing political figures cannot be censored."
1964,"March 10","Soviet military forces shoot down an unarmed reconnaissance bomber that had strayed into East Germany; the 3 U.S. flyers parachute to safety."
1964,"March 21","[i]Non ho l'età[/i] by Gigliola Cinquetti (music by Nicola Salerno, text by Mario Panzeri) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1964 for Italy."
1964,"April 8","[i]From Russia with Love[/i] is shown in U.S. theaters."
1964,"April 17","In the United States, the Ford Mustang is officially unveiled to the public."
1964,"April 22","The 1964 New York World's Fair opens to celebrate the 300th anniversary of New Amsterdam being taken over by British forces under the Duke of York (later King James II) and being renamed New York in 1664. The fair runs until October 18, 1964 and reopens April 21, 1965, finally closing October 17, 1965. (Not sanctioned, due to being within 10 years of the Seattle World's Fair in 1962, some countries decline, but many countries have pavilions with exotic crafts, art & food.)"
1964,"May 7","At a mail rockets demonstration by Gerhard Zucker on Hasselkopf Mountain near Braunlage (Lower Saxonia, Germany), 3 persons are killed by a rocket explosion."
1964,"May 9","South Korean President Chung Hee Park reshuffles his Cabinet, after a series of student demonstrations against his efforts to restore diplomatic and trade relations with Japan."
1964,"June 9","In Federal Court in Kansas City, Kansas, army deserter George John Gessner, 28, is convicted of passing United States secrets to the Soviet Union."
1964,"June 11","Greece rejects direct talks with Turkey over Cyprus."
1964,"June 11","In Cologne, Germany, Walter Seifert attacks students and teachers in an elementary school with a flamethrower, killing 10 and injuring 21."
1964,"June 26","Moise Tshombe returns to the Democratic Republic of the Congo from exile in Spain."
1964,"July 27","Vietnam War: The U.S. sends 5,000 more military advisers to South Vietnam, bringing the total number of United States forces in Vietnam to 21,000."
1964,"August 4","Vietnam War: United States destroyers USS [i]Maddox[/i] and USS [i]C. Turner Joy[/i] are attacked in the Gulf of Tonkin. Air support from the carrier USS [i]Ticonderoga[/i] sinks 1 gunboat, while the other 2 leave the battle."
1964,"August 7","Vietnam War: The United States Congress passes the Gulf of Tonkin Resolution, giving U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson broad war powers to deal with North Vietnamese attacks on U.S. forces."
1964,"August 17","Margaret Harshaw, Metropolitan Opera soprano, sings the role of Turandot in Puccini's opera [i]Turandot[/i] at the New York World's Fair."
1964,"September 10","Germany receives its 1,000,000th foreign worker."
1964,"October 14","American civil rights movement leader Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. becomes the youngest recipient of the Nobel Peace Prize, which was awarded to him for leading non-violent resistance to end racial prejudice in the United States."
1964,"October 15","The St. Louis Cardinals defeat the visiting New York Yankees, 7-5 to win the World Series in 7 games (4-3), ending a long run of 29 World Series appearances in 44 seasons for the Bronx Bombers (also known as the [i]Yankee Dynasty[/i])."
1964,"October 16","The People's Republic of China explodes an atomic bomb in Sinkiang."
1964,"October 18","The NY World's Fair closes for the year (it reopens April 21, 1965)."
1964,"November 9","The British House of Commons votes to abolish the death penalty for murder in Britain."
1964,"November 19","The United States Department of Defense announces the closing of 95 military bases and facilities, including the Brooklyn Navy Yard, the Brooklyn Army Terminal, and Fort Jay, New York."
1964,"November 28","Vietnam War: United States National Security Council members, including Robert McNamara, Dean Rusk, and Maxwell Taylor, agree to recommend a plan for a 2-stage escalation of bombing in North Vietnam, to President Lyndon B. Johnson."
1965,"February 20","Suat Hayri Ürgüplü forms the new (interim) government of Turkey (29th government)"
1965,"March 18","A United States federal judge rules that SCLC has the lawful right to march to Montgomery, Alabama to petition for 'redress of grievances'."
1965,"March 20","[i]Poupée de cire, poupée de son[/i], sung by France Gall (music and lyrics by Serge Gainsbourg) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1965 for Luxembourg."
1965,"April 21","The NY World's Fair in Flushing Meadows, NY, reopens."
1965,"May 1","The Battle of Dong-Yin occurs as a conflict between Taiwan and the People's Republic of China."
1965,"May 12","West Germany and Israel establish diplomatic relations."
1965,"June 1","A coal mine explosion in Fukuoka, Japan kills 237."
1965,"June 22","The Treaty on Basic Relations between Japan and the Republic of Korea is signed in Tokyo."
1965,"July 26","The Maldives receive full independence from Great Britain."
1965,"July 28","Vietnam War: U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson announces his order to increase the number of United States troops in South Vietnam from 75,000 to 125,000, and to more than double the number of men drafted per month - from 17,000 to 35,000."
1965,"September 7","The People's Republic of China announces that it will reinforce its troops on the Indian border."
1965,"September 7","Vietnam War: In a follow-up to August's Operation Starlite, United States Marines and South Vietnamese forces initiate Operation Piranha on the Batangan Peninsula, 23 miles south of the Chu Lai Marine base."
1965,"September 9","U Thant recommends China for United Nations membership."
1965,"September 15","[i]Mary Poppins[/i] comes out in theaters in France."
1965,"September 16","China protests against Indian provocations in its border region."
1965,"September 27","The largest tanker ship at the time, [i]Tokyo Maru[/i], is launched in Yokohama, Japan."
1965,"September 28","Fidel Castro announces that anyone who wants to can emigrate to the United States."
1965,"October 4","Pope Paul VI visits the United States. He appears for a Mass in Yankee Stadium and makes a speech at the United Nations."
1965,"October 7","Seven Japanese fishing boats are sunk off Guam by super typhoon Carmen; 209 are killed."
1965,"October 8","The International Olympic Committee admits East Germany as a member."
1965,"October 17","The NY World's Fair at Flushing Meadows, NY, closes. Due to financial losses, some of the projected site park improvements fail to materialize."
1965,"October 27","Süleyman Demirel of AP forms the new government of Turkey (30th government)"
1965,"November 6","Freedom Flights begin: Cuba and the United States formally agree to start an airlift for Cubans who want to go to the United States (by 1971 250,000 Cubans take advantage of this program)."
1965,"December 17","The British government begins an oil embargo against Rhodesia; the United States joins the effort."
1965,"December 21","In West Germany, Konrad Adenauer resigns as chairman of the Christian Democratic Party."
1966,"January 4","A gas leak fire at the Feyzin oil refinery near Lyon, France kills 18 and injures 84."
1966,"January 12","United States President Lyndon Johnson states that the United States should stay in South Vietnam until Communist aggression there is ended."
1966,"January 17","A B-52 bomber collides with a KC-135 Stratotanker over Spain, dropping three 70-kiloton hydrogen bombs near the town of Palomares, and 1 into the sea, in the 1966 Palomares B-52 crash."
1966,"February 1","West Germany procures some 2,600 political prisoners from East Germany."
1966,"March 4","The Beatles: In an interview published in The London [i]Evening Standard[/i], John Lennon comments, ""We're more popular than Jesus now,"" eventually sparking a controversy in the United States."
1966,"March 4","Canadian Pacific Airlines Flight 402 crashes while landing at Tokyo International Airport in Japan, killing 64 of 72 persons on board."
1966,"March 5","[i]Merci Chérie[/i] by Udo Jürgens (music by Udo Jürgens, text by Udo Jürgens and Thomas Hörbiger) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1966 for Austria."
1966,"March 7","Charles De Gaulle asks U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson for negotiations about the state of NATO equipment in France."
1966,"March 10","Crown Princess Beatrix of the Netherlands marries Claus von Amsberg. Some spectators demonstrate against the groom because he is German."
1966,"March 17","Off the coast of Spain in the Mediterranean, the [i]DSV Alvin[/i] submarine finds a missing American hydrogen bomb."
1966,"March 26","Demonstrations are held across the United States against the Vietnam War."
1966,"March 28","Cevdet Sunay becomes the fifth president of Turkey."
1966,"April 18","China declares that it will stop economic aid to Indonesia."
1966,"May 3","Swinging Radio England and Britain Radio commence broadcasting on AM, with a combined potential 100,000 watts, from the same ship anchored off the south coast of England in international waters."
1966,"May 14","Turkey and Greece intend to start negotiations about the situation in Cyprus."
1966,"May 16","The Communist Party of China issues the 'May 16 Notice', marking the beginning of the Cultural Revolution."
1966,"May 16","A seamen's strike is called in Britain."
1966,"June 13","[i]Miranda v. Arizona[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that the police must inform suspects of their rights before questioning them."
1966,"June 17","An Air France personnel strike begins."
1966,"June 30","France formally leaves NATO."
1966,"July 11","The 1966 FIFA World Cup begins in England."
1966,"July 19","A Chinese delegate in the Netherlands, Liu en-Tsiu, is declared persona non grata because of the death of a Chinese engineer in unclear circumstances; there are claims that he was kidnapped and taken to the delegate's office."
1966,"July 22","The Chinese government declares Dutch delegate G. J. Jongejans persona non grata, but tells him not to leave the country before a group of Chinese engineers has left the Netherlands."
1966,"July 30","England beats West Germany 4-2 to win the 1966 FIFA World Cup at Wembley after extra time."
1966,"August 10","An East German court sentences Günter Laudahn to life imprisonment for spying for the United States."
1966,"August 13","In the People's Republic of China, Mao Zedong begins the Cultural Revolution to purge and reorganize China's Communist Party."
1966,"August 13","An earthquake in Turkey kills 2,394 and injures 10,000."
1966,"August 19","An earthquake in eastern Turkey destroys whole cities."
1966,"August 30","France offers independence to French Somaliland."
1966,"October 5","UNESCO signs the Recommendation Concerning the Status of Teachers. This event is now celebrated as World Teachers' Day."
1966,"October 9","The Baltimore Orioles defeat the Los Angeles Dodgers in Game 4 of the World Series, 1-0, to sweep the series for their 1st World Championship."
1966,"October 11","France and the Soviet Union sign a treaty for cooperation in nuclear research."
1966,"October 15","U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson signs a bill creating the United States Department of Transportation."
1966,"October 22","Spain demands that the United Kingdom stop military flights to Gibraltar; Britain refuses the next day."
1966,"October 25","Spain closes its Gibraltar border to non-pedestrian traffic."
1966,"November 11","Spain declares general amnesty for crimes committed during the Spanish Civil War (effective only for the Falangists' side)."
1966,"November 15","A Boeing 727 carrying Pan Am Flight 708 crashes near Berlin, Germany, killing all three people on board."
1966,"December 1","Kurt Georg Kiesinger is elected Chancellor of West Germany."
1966,"circa","The Congress of the United States creates the National Council for Marine Resources and Engineering Development."
1966,"circa","The World Buddhist Sangha Council is convened by Theravadins in Sri Lanka, with the hope of bridging differences and working together."
1967,"January 5","Spain and Romania sign in Paris an agreement establishing full consular and commercial relations (not diplomatic ones)."
1967,"January 23","In Munich, the trial begins of Wilhelm Harster, accused of the murder of 82,856 Jews (including Anne Frank) when he led German security police during the German occupation of the Netherlands. He is eventually sentenced to 15 years in prison."
1967,"January 27","The United States, Soviet Union and United Kingdom sign the Outer Space Treaty."
1967,"January 31","West Germany and Romania establish diplomatic relations."
1967,"February 10","The 25th Amendment to the United States Constitution (presidential succession and disability) is ratified."
1967,"February 13","American researchers discover the Madrid Codices by Leonardo da Vinci in the National Library of Spain."
1967,"February 18","China sends 3 People's Liberation Army divisions to Tibet."
1967,"February 23","The 25th Amendment to the United States Constitution is enacted."
1967,"February 24","Moscow forbids its satellite states to form diplomatic relations with West Germany."
1967,"February 25","Britain's second Polaris missile submarine, HMS [i]Renown[/i], is launched."
1967,"March 1","The Red Guards return to schools in China."
1967,"March 19","A referendum in French Somaliland favors the connection to France."
1967,"April 21","An outbreak of tornadoes strikes the upper Midwest section of the United States (in particular the Chicago area, including the suburbs of Belvidere and Oak Lawn, Illinois, where 33 people are killed and 500 injured)."
1967,"April 27","Montreal, Quebec, Expo 67, a World's Fair to coincide with the Canadian Confederation centennial, officially opens with Prime Minister Lester B. Pearson igniting the Expo Flame in the Place des Nations."
1967,"May 4","Lunar Orbiter 4 is launched by the United States."
1967,"May 19","The Soviet Union ratifies a treaty with the United States and the United Kingdom, banning nuclear weapons from outer space."
1967,"June 2","Luis Monge is executed in Colorado's gas chamber, in the last pre-[i]Furman[/i] execution in the United States."
1967,"June 12","[i]Loving v. Virginia[/i]: The United States Supreme Court declares all U.S. state laws prohibiting interracial marriage to be unconstitutional."
1967,"June 17","The People's Republic of China announces a successful hydrogen bomb test."
1967,"July 6","A level crossing collision between a train loaded with children and a tanker-truck near Magdeburg, East Germany kills 94 people, mostly children."
1967,"July 10","Heavy massive rains and a landslide at Kobe and Kure, Hiroshima, Japan, kill at least 371."
1967,"July 21","The town of Winneconne, Wisconsin, announces secession from the United States because it is not included in the official maps and declares war. Secession is repealed the next day."
1967,"July 23","12th Street Riot/Detroit Race Riots: In Detroit, Michigan, one of the worst riots in United States history begins on 12th Street in the predominantly African American inner city: 43 are killed, 342 injured and 1,400 buildings burned."
1967,"August 1","Race riots in the United States spread to Washington, D.C.."
1967,"August 7","Vietnam War: The People's Republic of China agrees to give North Vietnam an undisclosed amount of aid in the form of a grant."
1967,"August 9","Vietnam War - Operation Cochise: United States Marines begin a new operation in the Que Son Valley."
1967,"August 19","West Germany receives 36 East German prisoners it has ""purchased"" through the border posts of Herleshausen and Wartha."
1967,"August 21","The People's Republic of China announces that it has shot down United States planes violating its airspace."
1967,"August 23","Jimi Hendrix's debut album, ""Are You Experienced?"", is released in the United States."
1967,"September 3","H-Day in Sweden: At 5:00 a.m. local time, all traffic in the country switches from left-hand traffic pattern to right-hand traffic."
1967,"September 4","Vietnam War - Operation Swift: The United States Marines launch a search and destroy mission in Quang Nam and Quang Tin Provinces. The ensuing 4-day battle in Que Son Valley kills 114 Americans and 376 North Vietnamese."
1967,"September 10","In Gibraltar, only 44 out of 12,182 voters support union with Spain."
1967,"September 17","A riot during a football match in Kayseri, Turkey leaves 44 dead, about 600 injured."
1967,"October 30","Hong Kong 1967 riots: British troops and Chinese demonstrators clash on the border of China and Hong Kong."
1967,"November 11","Vietnam War: In a propaganda ceremony in Phnom Penh, Cambodia, 3 United States prisoners of war are released by the Viet Cong and turned over to ""New Left"" antiwar activist Tom Hayden."
1967,"November 15","General Grivas and his 10,000 strong Greek Army division are forced to leave Cyprus, after 24 Turkish Cypriot civilians are killed by the Greek Cypriot National Guard in the villages of Kophinou and Ayios Theodhoros; relations sour between Nicosia and Athens. Turkey flies sorties into Greek territory, and masses troops in Thrace on her border with Greece."
1967,"November 21","Vietnam War: United States General William Westmoreland tells news reporters: ""I am absolutely certain that whereas in 1965 the enemy was winning, today he is certainly losing""."
1967,"November 29","Vietnam War: U.S. Secretary of Defense Robert McNamara announces his resignation to become president of the World Bank. This action is due to U.S. President Lyndon B. Johnson's outright rejection of McNamara's early November recommendations to freeze troop levels, stop bombing North Vietnam and hand over ground fighting to South Vietnam."
1967,"December 11","The Concorde is unveiled in Toulouse, France."
1968,"January 8","British Prime Minister Harold Wilson endorses the 'I'm Backing Britain' campaign for working an additional half hour each day without pay."
1968,"February 6","(February 6 - February 18) The 1968 Winter Olympics are held in Grenoble, France."
1968,"March 18","Gold standard: The Congress of the United States repeals the requirement for a gold reserve to back U.S. currency."
1968,"March 22","Daniel Cohn-Bendit (""Danny The Red"") and 7 other students occupy the administrative offices of the University of Nanterre, setting in motion a chain of events that lead France to the brink of revolution in May."
1968,"April 6","[i]La, la, la[/i] by Massiel (music and lyrics by Manuel de la Calva and Ramón Arcusa) wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1968 for Spain, at the Royal Albert Hall in London."
1968,"May 19","A general election is held in Italy."
1968,"June 10","Soccer: Italy beats Yugoslavia 2-0 in a replay to win the 1968 European Championship. The original final on June 8 ended 1-1."
1968,"June 24","Giorgio Rosa declares the independence of his Republic of Rose Island, an artificial island off Rimini, Italy. Italian troops demolish it not long after."
1968,"June 26","Bonin Islands are returned to Japan after 23 years of occupation by the United States Navy."
1968,"August 11","The last steam passenger train service runs in Britain. A selection of British Railways steam locomotives make the 120-mile journey from Liverpool to Carlisle and return to Liverpool, before having their fires dropped for the last time (a working known as the Fifteen Guinea Special)."
1968,"August 18","Two charter buses push into the Hida River on National Highway Route 41 in Japan, in an accident caused by heavy rain; 104 are killed."
1968,"September 13","US Army Maj. Gen. Keith L. Ware, World War II Medal of Honor recipient, is killed when his helicopter is shot down in Vietnam. He is posthumously awarded the Distinguished Service Cross."
1968,"September 30","At Paine Field, near Everett Washington in the United States, Boeing officially rolls out it's new 747 for the media and the public."
1968,"October 8","Vietnam War - Operation Sealords: United States and South Vietnamese forces launch a new operation in the Mekong Delta."
1968,"October 10","The Detroit Tigers win the 1968 World Series, defeating the St. Louis Cardinals 4 games to 3."
1968,"October 12","Equatorial Guinea receives its independence from Spain."
1968,"October 14","Vietnam War: The United States Department of Defense announces that the United States Army and United States Marines will send about 24,000 troops back to Vietnam for involuntary second tours."
1968,"November 26","Vietnam War: United States Air Force First Lieutenant and Bell UH-1F helicopter pilot James P. Fleming rescues an Army Special Forces unit pinned down by Viet Cong fire, earning a Medal of Honor for his bravery."
1968,"December 10","Japan's biggest heist, the still-unsolved ""300 million yen robbery"", occurs in Tokyo."
1968,"December 22","Mao Zedong advocates that educated youth in urban China be re-educated in the country. It marks the start of the ""Up to the mountains and down to the villages"" movement."
1969,"January 1","Australian media baron Rupert Murdoch purchases the largest selling British Sunday newspaper, [i]The News of the World[/i]."
1969,"January 20","Richard Milhous Nixon succeeds Lyndon Baines Johnson as the 37th President of the United States of America."
1969,"March 29","The Eurovision Song Contest 1969 is held in Madrid, and results in four co-winners, with 18 votes each, from Spain, the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, and France."
1969,"April 9","Fermín Monasterio Pérez is killed by the ETA in Biscay, Spain, being the 4th victim in the name of Basque nationalism."
1969,"April 15","The EC-121 shootdown incident: North Korea shoots down the aircraft over the Sea of Japan, killing all 31 on board."
1969,"April 28","Charles de Gaulle steps down as president of France after suffering defeat in a referendum the day before."
1969,"May 20","United States National Guard helicopters spray skin-stinging powder on anti-war protesters in California."
1969,"June 3","Melbourne-Evans collision: The Australian aircraft carrier [i]Melbourne[/i] collides with the U.S. destroyer [i]Frank E. Evans[/i] in the South China Sea; 74 U.S. sailors are killed."
1969,"June 20","Georges Pompidou is elected President of France."
1969,"June 23","Warren E. Burger is sworn in as Chief Justice of the United States by retiring Chief Justice Earl Warren."
1969,"July 25","Vietnam War: U.S. President Richard Nixon declares the Nixon Doctrine, stating that the United States now expects its Asian allies to take care of their own military defense. This starts the ""Vietnamization"" of the war."
1969,"August 13","Serious border clashes occur between the Soviet Union and the People's Republic of China."
1969,"October 1","In Sweden, Olof Palme is elected Labour Party leader, replacing Tage Erlander as prime minister on October 14."
1969,"October 9","(October 9 - October 12) Days of Rage: In Chicago, the United States National Guard is called in to control demonstrations involving the radical Weathermen, in connection with the ""Chicago Eight"" Trial."
1969,"October 15","Vietnam War: Hundreds of thousands of people take part in antiwar demonstrations across the United States."
1969,"October 16","The ""miracle"" New York Mets win the World Series, beating the heavily favored Baltimore Orioles 4 games to 1."
1969,"October 21","Willy Brandt becomes Chancellor of West Germany."
1969,"November 3","Süleyman Demirel of AP forms the new government of Turkey (31st government)"
1969,"November 17","Cold War: Negotiators from the Soviet Union and the United States meet in Helsinki, to begin the SALT I negotiations aimed at limiting the number of strategic weapons on both sides."
1969,"November 21","U.S. President Richard Nixon and Japanese Premier Eisaku Sato agree in Washington, D.C. to the return of Okinawa to Japanese control in 1972. Under the terms of the agreement, the U.S. retains rights to military bases on the island, but they must be nuclear-free."
1969,"December 12","The Piazza Fontana bombing in Italy (Strage di Piazza Fontana) takes place. A U.S. Navy officer and C.I.A. agent called David Carrett is later investigated for possible involvement.\."
1970,"January 5","An earthquake (Richter Scale 7.7 magnitude) at Yunnan, China kills at least 15,621."
1970,"February 10","An avalanche at Val d'Isère, France kills 39 tourists."
1970,"March 6","Süleyman Demirel of AP forms the new government of Turkey (32nd government)"
1970,"March 15","The Expo '70 World's Fair opens in Suita, Osaka, Japan."
1970,"March 17","My Lai massacre: The United States Army charges 14 officers with suppressing information related to the incident."
1970,"March 18","United States Postal Service workers in New York City go on strike; the strike spreads to the state of California and the cities of Akron, Ohio, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, Chicago, Boston, and Denver, Colorado; 210,000 out of 750,000 U.S. postal employees walk out. President Nixon assigns military units to New York City post offices. The strike lasts 2 weeks."
1970,"March 31","Japan Airlines Flight 351, carrying 131 passengers and 7 crew from Tokyo to Fukuoka, is hijacked by Japanese Red Army members. All passengers are eventually freed."
1970,"April 8","A huge gas explosion at a subway construction site in Osaka, Japan kills 79 and injures over 400."
1970,"April 26","World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO)."
1970,"May 31","The 1970 FIFA World Cup is inaugurated in Mexico."
1970,"June 21","Brazil defeats Italy 4-1 to win the 1970 FIFA World Cup."
1970,"June 24","The United States Senate repeals the Gulf of Tonkin Resolution."
1970,"September 5","Vietnam War - Operation Jefferson Glenn: The United States 101st Airborne Division and the South Vietnamese 1st Infantry Division initiate a new operation in Thua Thien Province (the operation ends in October 1971)."
1970,"September 9","Guinea recognizes East Germany."
1970,"September 27","Richard Nixon begins a tour of Europe, visiting Italy, Yugoslavia, Spain, the United Kingdom and Ireland."
1970,"October 12","Vietnam War: U.S. President Richard Nixon announces that the United States will withdraw 40,000 more troops before Christmas."
1970,"October 13","Canada and the People's Republic of China establish diplomatic relations."
1970,"October 15","The Baltimore Orioles defeat the Cincinnati Reds in Game 5 of the World Series, 9-3, to win the series 4 games to 1 for their 2nd World Championship."
1970,"October 15","The domestic Soviet Aeroflot Flight 244 is hijacked and diverted to Turkey."
1970,"October 26","Garry Trudeau's comic strip [i]Doonesbury[/i] debuts in approximately two dozen newspapers in the United States."
1970,"November 1","Club Cinq-Sept fire in Saint-Laurent-du-Pont, France, kills 146."
1970,"November 4","Vietnam War - Vietnamization: The United States turns control of the air base in the Mekong Delta to South Vietnam."
1970,"November 9","Vietnam War: The Supreme Court of the United States votes 6-3 not to hear a case by the state of Massachusetts, about the constitutionality of a state law granting Massachusetts residents the right to refuse military service in an undeclared war."
1970,"November 14","The Soviet Union enters the ICAO, making Russian the fourth official language of the organization."
1970,"November 25","In Tokyo, author and Tatenokai militia leader Yukio Mishima and his followers take over the headquarters of the Japan Self-Defense Forces. When Mishima's speech fails to sway public opinion towards his right-wing political beliefs, he commits seppuku."
1970,"December 1","Ethiopia recognizes the People's Republic of China."
1970,"December 2","The United States Environmental Protection Agency begins operations."
1970,"December 3","Burgos Trial: In Burgos, Spain, the trial of 16 Basque terrorism suspects begins."
1970,"December 23","The North Tower of the World Trade Center is topped out at 1,368 feet (417 m), making it the tallest building in the world."
1970,"December 30","In Viscaya, Spain, Basque county, 15,000 go on strike to protest the Burgos trial death sentences."
1970,"December 31","Paul McCartney sues in Great Britain to dissolve the Beatles' legal partnership."
1970,"circa","Sada Abe, Japanese former prostitute and later actress, disappears."
1971,"January 2","A ban on radio and television cigarette advertisements goes into effect in the United States."
1971,"February 4","In Britain, Rolls-Royce goes bankrupt and is nationalised."
1971,"February 7","An earthquake in the city of Tuscania, Italy kills 31."
1971,"February 16","In Italy, a local parliament elects the city of Catanzaro as the capital of Calabria; residents of Reggio di Calabria riot for 5 days because of the decision."
1971,"March 1","A bomb explodes in the men's room at the United States Capitol. Weather Underground Organization claims responsibility."
1971,"March 26","Nihat Erim (a former CHP member) forms the new government of Turkey (33rd government,composed mostly of technocrats)"
1971,"April 5","Chile and East Germany establish diplomatic relations."
1971,"April 20","[i]Swann v. Charlotte-Mecklenburg Board of Education[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules unanimously that busing of students may be ordered to achieve racial desegregation."
1971,"April 24","A tsunami 85 m high rises over the Ryukyu Islands in Japan. It throws a 750-ton block of coral 2.5 km inland."
1971,"April 25","Franz Jonas is re-elected as chancellor of Austria."
1971,"April 26","The government of Turkey declares a state of siege in 11 provinces, Ankara included, due to violent demonstrations."
1971,"April 30","The Milwaukee Bucks win the NBA World Championship, sweeping the Baltimore Bullets in four straight games."
1971,"May 1","Amtrak begins inter-city rail passenger service in the United States."
1971,"May 5","The US dollar floods the European currency markets and threatens especially the Deutsche Mark; the central banks of Austria, Belgium, Netherlands and Switzerland stop the currency trading."
1971,"May 12","An earthquake in Turkey destroys most of the city of Burdur."
1971,"May 22","An earthquake lasting 20 seconds destroys most of Bingöl, Turkey - more than 1,000 are killed, 10,000 made homeless."
1971,"May 26","Austria and the People's Republic of China establish diplomatic relations."
1971,"June 10","The U.S. ends its trade embargo of China."
1971,"June 17","Representatives of Japan and the United States sign the Okinawa Reversion Agreement, whereby the U.S. will return control of Okinawa."
1971,"June 20","Britain announces that Soviet space scientist Anatoli Fedoseyev has been granted asylum."
1971,"June 21","Britain begins new negotiations for EEC membership in Luxembourg."
1971,"June 30","[i]New York Times Co. v. United States[/i]: The U.S. Supreme Court rules that the Pentagon Papers may be published, rejecting government injunctions as unconstitutional prior restraint."
1971,"July 5","Right to vote: The 26th Amendment to the United States Constitution, formally certified by President Richard Nixon, lowers the voting age from 21 to 18."
1971,"July 17","Italy and Austria sign a treaty that ends the schism about Alto Adige/Südtirol."
1971,"July 19","The South Tower of the World Trade Center is topped out at 1,362 feet, making it the second tallest building in the world."
1971,"July 30","In Japan, an All Nippon Airways Boeing 727 collides with a Japanese fighter jet; 162 people are killed."
1971,"August 15","President Richard Nixon announces that the United States will no longer convert dollars to gold at a fixed value, effectively ending the Bretton Woods system. He also imposes a 90-day freeze on wages, prices and rents."
1971,"September 9","(September 9 - September 13) Attica Prison riots: - A revolt breaks out at the maximum-security prison in Attica, New York. In the end, state police and the United States National Guard storm the facility; 42 are killed, 10 of them hostages."
1971,"September 24","Britain expels 90 KGB and GRU officials; 15 are not allowed to return."
1971,"September 27","(September 27 - October 11) Japanese Emperor Hirohito travels abroad."
1971,"October 1","Walt Disney World opens in Orlando, Florida."
1971,"October 25","The United Nations General Assembly admits the People's Republic of China and expels the Republic of China (or Taiwan)."
1971,"November 23","The People's Republic of China takes the Republic of China's seat on the United Nations Security Council."
1971,"December 11","Nihat Erim forms the new government of Turkey (34th government, Nihat Erim had served two times as a prime minister)"
1971,"December 11","The Libertarian Party (United States) is established."
1971,"December 18","The world's largest hydroelectric plant in Krasnoyarsk, Russia, begins operations."
1971,"circa","Crude oil production peaks in the continental United States at approximately 4.5 million barrels/day."
1972,"February 3","(February 3 - February 13) The 1972 Winter Olympics are held in Sapporo, Japan."
1972,"February 21","(February 21 - February 28) U.S. President Richard M. Nixon makes an unprecedented 8-day visit to the People's Republic of China and meets with Mao Zedong."
1972,"February 28","The Asama-Sanso incident ends in a standoff between 5 members of the Japanese United Red Army and the authorities, in which 2 policemen are killed and 12 injured."
1972,"March 13","The United Kingdom and the People's Republic of China elevate diplomatic exchanges to the ambassadorial level after 22 years."
1972,"March 24","[i]The Godfather[/i] is released in cinemas in the United States."
1972,"April 13","The Universal Postal Union decides to recognize the People's Republic of China as the only legitimate Chinese representative, effectively expelling the Republic of China administering Taiwan."
1972,"April 16","Vietnam War - Nguyen Hue Offensive: Prompted by the North Vietnamese offensive, the United States resumes bombing of Hanoi and Haiphong."
1972,"May 7","General elections are held in Italy."
1972,"May 13","Fire in a nightclub atop the Sennichi department store in Osaka, Japan, kills 115."
1972,"May 15","Okinawa is returned to Japan after 27 years of United States Military occupation."
1972,"May 18","Four troopers of both SAS and SBS are parachuted onto the [i]RMS Queen Elizabeth 2[/i], 1,000 miles (1,600 km) off Britain in the Atlantic, after a bomb threat and ransom demand, which turns out to be bogus."
1972,"May 19","Three out of 6 bombs explode in the Springer Press building in Hamburg, Germany, injuring 17; the Red Army Faction claims responsibility."
1972,"May 22","Ferit Melen forms the new (interim) government of Turkey (35th government)"
1972,"May 30","Three Japanese Red Army members kill 24 and injure 100 in Lod Airport, Israel."
1972,"June 5","(June 5 - June 16) The United Nations Conference on the Human Environment is held in Stockholm, Sweden."
1972,"June 8","Seven men and 3 women hijack a plane from West Germany to Czechoslovakia."
1972,"June 15","Ulrike Meinhof and Gerhard Müller of the Red Army Faction are arrested in a teacher's apartment in Langenhagen, West Germany."
1972,"June 17","The United States returns Okinawa, occupied and governed since the World War II Battle of Okinawa, to Japan."
1972,"June 18","West Germany beats the Soviet Union 3-0 to win Euro 72."
1972,"June 29","[i]Furman v. Georgia[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that the death penalty is unconstitutional."
1972,"July 21","A collision between two trains near Sevilla, Spain kills 76 people."
1972,"July 29","A national dock strike begins in Britain."
1972,"August 4","Dictator Idi Amin declares that Uganda will expel 50,000 Asians with British passports to Britain within 3 months."
1972,"August 26","(August 26 - September 11) The 1972 Summer Olympics are held in Munich, West Germany."
1972,"September 10","The Brazilian driver Emerson Fittipaldi wins the Italian Grand Prix at Monza and becomes the youngest Formula One World Champion."
1972,"September 14","West Germany and Poland renew diplomatic relations."
1972,"September 27","The Joint Communique of the Government of Japan and the Government of the People's Republic of China is signed in Beijing."
1972,"September 29","Sino-Japanese relations: Japan normalizes diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China after breaking official ties with the Republic of China (Taiwan)."
1972,"October 12","En route to the Gulf of Tonkin, a racial riot involving more than 200 sailors breaks out aboard the United States Navy aircraft carrier USS [i]Kitty Hawk[/i]; nearly 50 sailors are injured."
1972,"October 29","The Black September group hijacks a Lufthansa Boeing 727 over Turkey, demanding the release of 3 comrades still held for the massacre of Israeli athletes at the Olympic Games."
1972,"November 11","Vietnam War - Vietnamization: The United States Army turns over the massive Long Binh military base to South Vietnam."
1972,"November 16","The United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization adopts the Convention Concerning the Protection of the World Cultural and Natural Heritage ."
1972,"November 30","Vietnam War: White House Press Secretary Ron Ziegler tells the press that there will be no more public announcements concerning United States troop withdrawals from Vietnam due to the fact that troop levels are now down to 27,000."
1972,"December 21","East Germany and West Germany recognize each other."
1972,"December 22","Australia establishes diplomatic relations with China and West Germany."
1972,"December 24","Swedish Prime minister Olof Palme compares the American bombings of North Vietnam to Nazi massacres. The U.S. breaks diplomatic contact with Sweden."
1972,"circa","The ""tea house"" Mellow Yellow opens on the Amstel River in Amsterdam, pioneering the legal sale of cannabis in the Netherlands."
1973,"January 31","Pan American and Trans World Airlines cancelled their options to buy 13 Concorde airliners."
1973,"February 13","The United States Dollar is devalued by 10%."
1973,"February 22","Sino-American relations: Following President Richard Nixon's visit to mainland China, the United States and the People's Republic of China agree to establish liaison offices."
1973,"March 21","The Lofthouse Colliery disaster occurs in Great Britain."
1973,"March 23","Watergate scandal (United States): In a letter to Judge John Sirica, Watergate burglar James W. McCord Jr. admits that he and other defendants have been pressured to remain silent about the case. He names former Attorney General John Mitchell as 'overall boss' of the operation."
1973,"April 4","The World Trade Center officially opens in New York City with a ribbon cutting ceremony."
1973,"April 5","Fahri Korutürk becomes the sixth president of Turkey."
1973,"April 15","Naim Talu, a former civil servant forms the new government of Turkey (36th government)"
1973,"May 17","Watergate scandal: Televised hearings begin in the United States Senate."
1973,"May 24","Earl Jellicoe, Lord Privy Seal and Leader of the House of Lords in Britain, resign over a separate prostitution scandal."
1973,"July 11","Varig Flight 820 crashes near Orly, France; 123 are killed."
1973,"July 16","Watergate Scandal: Former White House aide Alexander Butterfield informs the United States Senate Watergate Committee that President Richard Nixon had secretly recorded potentially incriminating conversations."
1973,"July 17","King Mohammed Zahir Shah of Afghanistan is deposed by his cousin Mohammed Daoud Khan while in Italy undergoing eye surgery."
1973,"July 20","France resumes nuclear bomb tests in Mururoa Atoll, over the protests of Australia and New Zealand."
1973,"September 18","The two German Republics, the Federal Republic of Germany (West Germany) and the German Democratic Republic (East Germany), are admitted to the United Nations."
1973,"September 22","Henry Kissinger, United States National Security Advisor, starts his term as United States Secretary of State."
1973,"October 10","Spiro T. Agnew resigns as Vice President of the United States and then, in federal court in Baltimore, Maryland, pleads no contest to charges of income tax evasion on $29,500 he received in 1967, while he was governor of Maryland. He is fined $10,000 and put on 3 years' probation."
1973,"November 7","The Congress of the United States overrides President Richard M. Nixon's veto of the War Powers Resolution, which limits presidential power to wage war without congressional approval."
1973,"November 11","Egypt and Israel sign a United States-sponsored cease-fire accord."
1973,"November 27","The United States Senate votes 92-3 to confirm Gerald Ford as Vice President of the United States."
1973,"November 29","104 people are killed in a Taiyo department store fire in Kumamoto, Kyushu, Japan."
1973,"December","Chile breaks diplomatic contacts with Sweden.[i]Confirmation needed[/i]."
1973,"December 6","The United States House of Representatives votes 387-35 to confirm Gerald Ford as Vice President of the United States; he is sworn in the same day."
1973,"circa","Confirming the descriptions of bulkhead hull compartments for Chinese sailing ships in Zhu Yu's [i]Pingzhou Table Talks[/i] of 1119 A.D., a large Song Dynasty trade ship of c. 1277 A.D. is dredged up from the waters near the southern coast of China that had 12 bulkhead compartment rooms in its hull."
1974,"January 26","Bülent Ecevit, of CHP forms the new government of Turkey (37th government, partner MSP )"
1974,"March 8","Charles de Gaulle Airport opens in Paris, France."
1974,"March 18","End of Oil embargo crisis: Most OPEC nations end a 5-month oil embargo against the United States, Europe and Japan."
1974,"May 4","The Expo '74 World's Fair opens in Spokane, Washington."
1974,"June 13","The 1974 FIFA World Cup begins in West Germany."
1974,"July 7","West Germany beats the Netherlands 2-1 to win the 1974 FIFA World Cup."
1974,"August 4","A bomb explodes in an Italicus Expressen train between Italy and West Germany. Italian neo-fascist terrorists take responsibility."
1974,"August 14","Turkey invades for the second time in Cyprus, occupying 37% of the island's territory."
1974,"August 30","An express train bound for Germany from Belgrade derails in Zagreb, Yugoslavia (now Croatia), killing more than 150 passengers."
1974,"September 13","Japanese Red Army members seize the French Embassy in The Hague, Netherlands."
1974,"November 1","World Tourism Organization (WTO or WToO) established."
1975,"January 2","The Federal Rules of Evidence are approved by the United States Congress."
1975,"January 15","International Women's Year is launched in Britain by Princess Alexandra and Barbara Castle."
1975,"February 13","Fire breaks out in the World Trade Center."
1975,"February 21","Watergate scandal: Former United States Attorney General John N. Mitchell, and former White House aides H. R. Haldeman and John Ehrlichman, are sentenced to between 30 months and 8 years in prison."
1975,"February 23","In response to the energy crisis, daylight saving time commences nearly 2 months early in the United States."
1975,"March 22","[i]Ding-a-dong[/i] by Teach-In (music by Dick Bakker, text by Will Luikinga and Eddy Ouwens) wins the 20th Eurovision Song Contest 1975 for the Netherlands."
1975,"March 31","Süleyman Demirel of AP forms the new government of Turkey (39th government, a four party coalition, so called First National Front (Turkish: [i]Milliyetçi cephe[/i]))"
1975,"May 12","Mayaguez incident: Khmer Rouge forces in Cambodia seize the United States merchant ship SS [i]Mayaguez[/i] in international waters."
1975,"July 6","The Comoros declare their independence from France."
1975,"August 8","The Banqiao Dam, in China's Henan Province, fails after a freak typhoon; over 200,000 people perish."
1975,"August 15","The Birmingham Six are wrongfully sentenced to life imprisonment in Great Britain."
1975,"September 6","A Richter Scale 6.7 magnitude earthquake kills at least 2,085 in Diyarbakir and Lice, Turkey."
1975,"September 27","Francoist Spain executes five ETA and FRAP members, the last executions in Spain to date."
1975,"October 21","1975 World Series: The Boston Red Sox defeat the Cincinnati Reds in Game Six off Carlton Fisk's 12th-inning home run to cap off what many consider to be the best World Series game ever played."
1975,"October 30","Juan Carlos I of Spain becomes acting Head of State after dictator Francisco Franco concedes that he is too ill to govern."
1975,"November 3","An independent audit of Mattel, one of the United States' largest toy manufacturers, reveals that company officials fabricated press releases and financial information to ""maintain the appearance of continued corporate growth""."
1975,"November 10","Lev Leshchenko revives [i]Den Pobedy[/i], one of the most popular World War II songs in the USSR."
1975,"November 14","Spain abandons Western Sahara."
1975,"November 22","Juan Carlos is declared King of Spain following the death of dictator Francisco Franco."
1975,"November 25","Suriname gains independence from the Kingdom of the Netherlands."
1975,"circa","The Spanish army quits Spanish (Western) Sahara, the last remnant of Spain's Empire. The Sahrawi Republic (RASD) is created. Morocco invades ex-Spanish Western Sahara."
1975,"circa","In the film [i]The Omega Man[/i] a war involving biological weapons between China and the Soviet Union took place in 1975."
1976,"January 16","The trial against jailed members of the Red Army Faction begins in Stuttgart, West Germany."
1976,"January 27","The United States vetoes a United Nations resolution that calls for an independent Palestinian state."
1976,"February 28","Spain gives up territories in Sahara but retains its enclaves of Melilla and Ceuta."
1976,"March 9","A cable-car disaster in Cavalese, Italy leaves 42 dead."
1976,"April 13","An explosion in an ammunition factory in Lapua, Finland kills 40. Also, the United States Treasury Department reintroduces the two-dollar bill as a Federal Reserve Note on Thomas Jefferson's 233rd birthday as part of the United States Bicentennial celebration."
1976,"May 4","A train crash in Schiedam, the Netherlands, kills 24 people."
1976,"May 6","An earthquake hits the Friuli area in Italy, killing more than 900 people and making another 100,000 homeless."
1976,"June 7","Denis Healey applies for and receives a $5.3 billion loan for Britain from the IMF."
1976,"June 20","General elections are held in Italy."
1976,"June 20","Czechoslovakia beats West Germany 5-3 on penalties to win Euro 76, when the game had ended 2-2 after extra time."
1976,"June 27","Palestinian extremists hijack an Air France plane in Greece with 246 passengers and 12 crew. They take it to Entebbe, Uganda."
1976,"July 3","[i]Gregg v. Georgia[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that the death penalty is not inherently cruel or unusual and is a constitutionally acceptable form of punishment."
1976,"July 4","[i]United States Bicentennial[/i]: From coast to coast, the United States celebrates the 200th anniversary of the Declaration of Independence."
1976,"July 10","An explosion in Seveso, Italy, causes extended pollution to a large area in the neighborhood of Milano, with many evacuations and a large number of people affected by the toxic cloud."
1976,"July 16","(July 16 - July 20) Albert Spaggiari and his gang break into the vault of the Societe Generale Bank in Nice, France."
1976,"July 28","The Tangshan earthquake flattens Tangshan, China, killing 242,769 people, and injuring 164,851."
1976,"August 25","Jacques Chirac resigns as Prime Minister of France; he is succeeded by Raymond Barre."
1976,"August 26","Prince Bernhard of Lippe-Biesterfeld, husband of Queen Juliana of the Netherlands, resigns from various posts over a scandal involving alleged corruption, in connection with business dealings with the Lockheed Corporation."
1976,"September 6","Cold War: Soviet Air Force pilot Lt. Viktor Belenko lands a MiG-25 jet fighter at Hakodate, on the island of Hokkaido in Japan, and requests political asylum in the United States."
1976,"October 12","The People's Republic of China announces that Hua Guofeng is the successor to Mao Zedong, as Chairman of the Communist Party of China."
1976,"October 13","The United States Commission on Civil Rights releases the report, [i]Puerto Ricans in the Continental United States: An Uncertain Future,[/i] that documents that Puerto Ricans in the United States have a poverty rate of 33 percent in 1974 (up from 29 percent in 1970), the highest of all major racial-ethnic groups in the country (not including Puerto Rico, a U.S. territory)."
1976,"October 21","The Cincinnati Reds sweep the New York Yankees in four games to win the 1976 World Series."
1976,"November 24","At least 3,840 are killed in a Richter scale magnitude 7.3 earthquake of Van and Muradiye in Turkey."
1976,"December 8","The Congressional Hispanic Caucus is established by the 5 Latinos in the United States Congress: Herman Badillo of the Bronx, E. de la Garza and Henry B. Gonzalez of Texas, Edward R. Roybal of California, and the nonvoting Resident Commissioner of Puerto Rico, Baltasar Corrada del Rio."
1977,"January 19","Snow falls in Miami, Florida (despite its ordinarily tropical climate) for the only time in its history. Snowfall has occurred farther south in the United States only on the high mountains of the state of Hawaii."
1977,"January 20","Jimmy Carter succeeds Gerald Ford as the 39th President of the United States."
1977,"May 14","In Milan, Italy, during a far-left demonstration, a hooded person shoots at the police, killing a policeman, Antonio Custra. The scene is photographed and the picture of the hooded man shooting in the middle of the street appears in many magazines around the world."
1977,"May 23","Moluccan terrorists take over a school in Bovensmilde, northern Netherlands (105 hostages), and a passenger train on the Bovensmilde-Assen route nearby (90 hostages) at the same time. On June 11, Dutch Royal Marines storm the train; 6 terrorists and 2 hostages are killed."
1977,"May 26","George Willig climbs the South Tower of the World Trade Center."
1977,"June 20","The Supreme Court of the United States rules that states are not required to spend Medicaid funds on elective abortions."
1977,"June 21","Bülent Ecevit, of CHP forms the new government of Turkey, but fails to receive the vote of confidence."
1977,"July 21","Süleyman Demirel, of AP forms the new government of Turkey (41st government a three party coalition, so called second national front (Turkish: [i]Milliyetçi cephe[/i]))"
1977,"July 30","Left-wing German terrorists Susanne Albrecht, Brigitte Mohnhaupt de:Brigitte Mohnhaupt and a third person assassinate Jürgen Ponto, chairman of the Dresdner Bank in Oberursel, West Germany."
1977,"August 3","United States Senate hearings on MKULTRA are held."
1977,"August 4","U.S. President Jimmy Carter signs legislation creating the United States Department of Energy."
1977,"August 20","Voyager program: The United States launches the Voyager 2 spacecraft."
1977,"September 5","German Autumn: Employers Association President Hanns-Martin Schleyer is kidnapped in Cologne, West Germany. The kidnappers kill 3 escorting police officers and his chauffeur. They demand the release of Red Army Faction (RAF) prisoners."
1977,"September 7","Treaties between Panama and the United States on the status of the Panama Canal are signed. The U.S. agrees to transfer control of the canal to Panama at the end of the 20th century."
1977,"September 10","Hamida Djandoubi's is the last guillotine execution in France."
1977,"September 21","A nuclear non-proliferation pact is signed by 15 countries, including the United States and the Soviet Union."
1977,"October 18","Reggie Jackson blasts 3 home runs to lead the New York Yankees to a World Series victory over the Los Angeles Dodgers."
1977,"November 27","The Rankin/Bass animated film [i]The Hobbit[/i] premiers on NBC in the United States."
1977,"circa","The Usu volcano erupts in Japan."
1978,"January 5","Bülent Ecevit, of CHP forms the new government of Turkey (42nd government)"
1978,"January 6","The Holy Crown of Hungary (also known as Stephen of Hungary Crown) is returned to Hungary from the United States, where it was held since World War II."
1978,"January 22","Ethiopia declares the ambassador of West Germany Persona non grata."
1978,"February 1","Hollywood film director Roman Polanski skips bail and flees to France, after pleading guilty to charges of engaging in sex with a 13-year-old girl."
1978,"February 5","(February 5 - February 7) The Northeastern United States blizzard of 1978 hits the New England region and the New York metropolitan area, killing about 100 and causing over US$520 million in damage."
1978,"February 11","The People's Republic of China lifts a ban on works by Aristotle, William Shakespeare and Charles Dickens."
1978,"March 28","[i]Stump v. Sparkman[/i] (435 U.S. 349): The Supreme Court of the United States hands down a 5-3 decision in a controversial case involving involuntary sterilization and judicial immunity."
1978,"April 10","Volkswagen becomes the second (after Rolls-Royce) non-American automobile manufacturer to open a plant in the United States, commencing production of the Rabbit, the North American version of the Volkswagen Golf, in New Stanton, Pennsylvania with a unionized (UAW) workforce (the plant closes in 1992.)"
1978,"May 12","In Zaire, rebels occupy the city of Kolwezi, the mining centre of the province of Shaba. The Zairean government asks the U.S., France and Belgium to restore order."
1978,"June 1","The 1978 FIFA World Cup starts in Argentina."
1978,"June 25","Argentina defeats the Netherlands 3-1 after extra time to win the 1978 FIFA World Cup."
1978,"June 28","[i]University of California Regents v. Bakke[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States bars quota systems in college admissions but affirms the constitutionality of programs which give advantages to minorities."
1978,"October 14","United States President Jimmy Carter signs a bill into law which allows homebrewing of beer in the United States."
1978,"October 17","The New York Yankees clinch their 22nd World Series championship, defeating the Dodgers 7-2 in Los Angeles and winning the Series 4 games to 2."
1978,"December 16","Train 87 from Nanjing to Xining collides with train 368 from Xi'an to Xuzhou near Yangzhuang railway station in China, killing 106, injuring 218."
1978,"December 22","The pivotal Third Plenum of the 11th National Congress of the Communist Party of China is held in Beijing, with Deng Xiaoping reversing Mao-era policies to pursue a program for Chinese economic reform."
1978,"circa","The One Child Policy is introduced in Mainland China."
1979,"January 1","The United States and the People's Republic of China establish full diplomatic relations."
1979,"January 9","The [i]Music for UNICEF Concert[/i] is held at the United Nations General Assembly to raise money for UNICEF and promote the Year of the Child. It is broadcast the following day in the United States and around the world. Hosted by The Bee Gees, other performers include Donna Summer, ABBA, Rod Stewart and Earth, Wind & Fire. A soundtrack album is later released."
1979,"February 17","The People's Republic of China invades northern Vietnam, launching the Sino-Vietnamese War."
1979,"March 14","In China, a Hawker Siddeley Trident crashes into a factory near Beijing, killing at least 200."
1979,"March 28","In Britain, Jim Callaghan's government loses a motion of confidence by 1 vote, forcing a general election."
1979,"March 30","Airey Neave, World War II veteran and Conservative Northern Ireland spokesman, is killed by an Irish National Liberation Army bomb in the British House of Commons car park."
1979,"April 1","(April 1 - April 18) Police lock Andreas Mihavecz in a holding cell in Bregenz, Austria, and forget about him, leaving him there without food or drink."
1979,"June 3","General elections are held in Italy."
1979,"July 1","Sweden outlaws corporal punishment in the home."
1979,"July 9","A car bomb destroys a Renault owned by Nazi hunters Serge and Beate Klarsfeld at their home in France. A note purportedly from ODESSA claims responsibility."
1979,"July 12","A fire at a hotel in Saragossa, Spain leaves 72 dead. Worst hotel fire in Europe in decades."
1979,"August 29","A national referendum is held in which Somali voters approve a new liberal constitution, promulgated by President Siad Barre to placate the United States."
1979,"September 16","Two families flee from East Germany by balloon."
1979,"October 1","(October 1 - October 6) Pope John Paul II visits the United States."
1979,"October 14","A major gay rights march in the United States takes place in Washington, D.C., involving many tens of thousands of people."
1979,"October 16","A tsunami in Nice, France kills 23 people."
1979,"October 17","The Pittsburgh Pirates defeat the Baltimore Orioles in Game 7 of the World Series. Willie Stargell is named the Series MVP."
1979,"November 1","Iran hostage crisis: Iranian Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini urges his people to demonstrate on November 4 and to expand attacks on United States and Israeli interests."
1979,"November 4","Iran hostage crisis begins: 3,000 Iranian radicals, mostly students, invade the U.S. Embassy in Tehran and take 90 hostages (53 of whom are American). They demand that the United States send the former Shah of Iran back to stand trial."
1979,"November 12","Iran hostage crisis: In response to the hostage situation in Tehran, U.S. President Jimmy Carter orders a halt to all oil imports into the United States from Iran."
1979,"November 12","Süleyman Demirel, of AP forms the new government of Turkey (43rd government, a minority government)"
1979,"November 14","Iran hostage crisis: U.S. President Jimmy Carter issues Executive Order 12170, freezing all Iranian assets in the United States and U.S. banks in response to the hostage crisis."
1979,"November 21","After false radio reports from the Ayatollah Khomeini that the Americans had occupied the Grand Mosque in Mecca, the United States Embassy in Islamabad, Pakistan is attacked by a mob and set afire, killing 4."
1979,"December 3","The United States dollar exchange rate with the Deutsche Mark falls to 1.7079 DM, the all-time low so far; this record is not broken until November 5, 1987."
1979,"circa","The One Child Policy is implemented in China in this year."
1979,"circa","Worldwide per capita oil production reaches an historic peak."
1980,"January 27","Canadian caper: Six United States diplomats, posing as Canadians, manage to escape from Tehran, Iran as they board a flight to Zürich, Switzerland."
1980,"January 31","The Spanish Embassy in Guatemala is invaded and set on fire, killing 36 people. It is called ""Spain's own Tehran"", similar to the 1979-80 Iran American U.S. Embassy Hostages of Americans."
1980,"February 2","Abscam: FBI personnel target members of the Congress of the United States in a sting operation.."
1980,"February 22","The United States Olympic Hockey Team defeats the Soviet Union in the semifinals of the Winter Olympics, in the [i]Miracle on Ice[/i]."
1980,"March 18","Fifty people are killed at the Plesetsk Cosmodrome in Russia, when a Vostok-2M rocket explodes on its launch pad during a fueling operation."
1980,"March 21","U.S. President Jimmy Carter announces that the United States will boycott the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow."
1980,"April 7","The United States severs diplomatic relations with Iran and imposes economic sanctions, following the taking of American hostages on November 4, 1979."
1980,"April 10","Spain and the United Kingdom agree to reopen the border between Gibraltar and Spain, closed since 1969."
1980,"April 24","(April 24 - April 25) Operation Eagle Claw, a commando mission in Iran to rescue American embassy hostages, is aborted after mechanical problems ground the rescue helicopters. Eight United States troops are killed in a mid-air collision during the failed operation."
1980,"April 30","Queen Juliana of the Netherlands abdicates, and her daughter Beatrix ascends to the throne."
1980,"June 23","(June 23 - September 6) The 1980 United States heat wave claims 1,700 lives."
1980,"July 19","Former Turkish Prime Minister Nihat Erim is killed by 2 gunmen in Istanbul, Turkey."
1980,"August 2","A terrorist bombing at the railway station in Bologna, Italy kills 85 people and wounds more than 200."
1980,"September 12","Kenan Evren stages a military coup in Turkey. It stops political gang violence, but begins stronger state violence leading to the execution of many young activists."
1980,"September 21","Bülent Ulusu, ex admiral, forms the new government of Turkey (44th government, composed mostly of technocrats)"
1980,"October 21","World Series: The Philadelphia Phillies beat the Kansas City Royals 4-2 in game 6."
1980,"November 4","United States presidential election, 1980: Republican challenger and former Governor Ronald Reagan of California defeats incumbent Democratic President Jimmy Carter, exactly 1 year after the beginning of the Iran hostage crisis."
1980,"November 20","The Gang of Four trial begins in China."
1980,"November 23","Italy Earthquake of 1980: a magnitude 7 earthquake in southern Italy kills approximately 4,800 people and leaves 300,000 homeless."
1980,"circa","Lawrence Klein is awarded the Bank of Sweden Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel."
1981,"January 19","United States and Iranian officials sign an agreement to release 52 American hostages after 14 months of captivity."
1981,"January 20","Ronald Reagan succeeds Jimmy Carter, as the 40th President of the United States. Minutes later, Iran releases the 52 Americans held for 444 days, ending the Iran hostage crisis."
1981,"January 23","An earthquake of 6.8 magnitude in Sichuan, China kills 150."
1981,"January 25","Chiang Ching ('Madame Mao') is sentenced to death in the People's Republic of China."
1981,"March 17","In Italy the Propaganda Due Masonic Lodge is discovered."
1981,"May 10","In the second round of the presidential elections in France, François Mitterrand beats Valéry Giscard d'Estaing."
1981,"May 10","In Italy a popular referendum rejects the abrogation of the law allowing abortion."
1981,"May 21","In France, Socialist François Mitterrand becomes President."
1981,"August 1","MTV (Music Television) is launched on cable television in the United States."
1981,"August 12","The original Model 5150 IBM PC (with a 4.77 MHz Intel 8088 processor) is released in the United States at a base price of $1,565."
1981,"August 31","A bomb explodes at the U.S. Air Force base in Ramstein, West Germany, injuring 20 people."
1981,"September 16","In Britain, the Liberal Party Assembly votes for an electoral pact with the new Social Democratic Party."
1981,"September 18","France abolishes capital punishment."
1981,"September 27","TGV high speed rail service between Paris and Lyon, France begins."
1981,"October 10","The Ministry for Education of Japan issues the joyo kanji."
1981,"October 13","James Tobin wins the Bank of Sweden Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel."
1981,"October 16","Gas explosions at a coal mine at Hokutan, Yubari, Hokkaido, Japan kill 93."
1981,"October 27","A Soviet submarine runs aground outside the Karlskrona, Sweden military base."
1981,"November 30","Cold War: In Geneva, representatives from the United States and the Soviet Union begin negotiating intermediate-range nuclear weapon reductions in Europe (the meetings end inconclusively on Thursday, December 17)."
1981,"December 10","During the Ministerial Session of the North Atlantic Council in Brussels, Spain signs the Protocol of Accession to NATO."
1981,"circa","Heavy massive snow causes many houses and buildings to collapse in northwestern Japan; 152 are killed (from January to March)."
1981,"circa","The State Council of the People's Republic of China lists the 4 cities (Beijing, Hangzhou, Suzhou and Guilin) as those where the protection of historical and cultural heritage, as well as natural scenery, should be treated as a priority project."
1982,"January 11","(January 11 - January 17) A brutal cold snap sends temperatures to all-time record lows in dozens of cities throughout the Midwestern United States."
1982,"January 17","Cold Sunday sweeps over the northern United States."
1982,"February 9","Japan Airlines Flight 350 crashes in Tokyo Bay due to thrust reversal on approach to Tokyo International Airport, killing 24 among the 174 people on board."
1982,"March 10","The United States places an embargo on Libyan oil imports, alleging Libyan support for terrorist groups."
1982,"March 18","Mary Whitehouse's private prosecution of [i]The Romans in Britain[/i] collapses."
1982,"April 6","A blizzard unprecedented in size for April dumps 1-2 feet of snow on the northeastern United States, closing schools and businesses, snarling traffic, and canceling several major league baseball games."
1982,"April 24","German singer Nicole wins the Eurovision Song Contest 1982 for Germany, with the song [i]Ein Bisschen Frieden[/i]."
1982,"May 30","Spain becomes the 16th member of NATO and the 1st nation to enter the alliance since West Germany's admission in 1955."
1982,"June 13","The 1982 FIFA World Cup begins in Spain."
1982,"July 11","Italy beats West Germany 3-1 to win the 1982 FIFA World Cup in Spain."
1982,"July 23","Torrential rain and mudslides in Nagasaki, Japan destroy bridges and kill 299."
1982,"October 1","Helmut Kohl replaces Helmut Schmidt as Chancellor of Germany through a Constructive Vote of No Confidence."
1982,"October 20","World Series: The St. Louis Cardinals defeat the Milwaukee Brewers 6-3 in game 7."
1982,"October 28","The Socialist Party wins the election in Spain; Felipe González is elected Prime Minister."
1982,"November 2","United States general elections, 1982."
1982,"November 8","Kenan Evren becomes the seventh president of Turkey as a result of constitution referandum. His former title was head of state]."
1982,"November 27","Yasuhiro Nakasone becomes Prime minister of Japan."
1982,"December 4","The People's Republic of China adopts its current constitution."
1982,"December 23","The United States Environmental Protection Agency recommends the evacuation of Times Beach, Missouri due to dangerous levels of dioxin contamination."
1982,"circa","A brief but severe recession begins in the United States."
1982,"circa","George Stigler is awarded The Bank of Sweden Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel."
1983,"February 13","A cinema fire in Turin, Italy kills 64."
1983,"February 23","The United States Environmental Protection Agency announces its intention to buy out and evacuate the dioxin-contaminated community of Times Beach, Missouri."
1983,"February 24","A special commission of the Congress of the United States releases a report critical of the practice of Japanese internment during World War II."
1983,"March 1","The Balearic Islands and Madrid become Autonomous communities of Spain."
1983,"March 9","Anne Burford resigns as head of the United States Environmental Protection Agency amid scandal."
1983,"March 16","The Transmitter Ismaning (last wooden radio tower in Germany) is demolished."
1983,"April 22","Reactor shut-down due to failure of fuel rods at Kursk Nuclear Power Plant, Russia."
1983,"May 17","Lebanon, Israel, and the United States sign an agreement on Israeli withdrawal from Lebanon."
1983,"May 26","A powerful earthquake and tsunami in northern Honshu, Japan kills 104 and injures 163."
1983,"July 1","Technical failure causes release of Iodine-131 from Philippsburg Nuclear Power Plant, Germany."
1983,"July 15","The Nintendo Entertainment System goes on sale in Japan."
1983,"July 23","Heavy massive rain and mudslides at western Shimane prefecture, Japan, kill 117."
1983,"August 26","Heavy rain triggers flooding at Bilbao(Spain) and surrounding areas, killing 45 people and causing millions in damages."
1983,"September 25","Maze Prison escape: 38 Irish republican prisoners, armed with 6 handguns, hijack a prison meals lorry and smash their way out of HMP Maze, in the largest prison escape since World War II and in British history."
1983,"October 22","In Bonn, West Germany, people demonstrate for nuclear disarmament."
1983,"October 23","Simultaneous suicide truck-bombings destroy both the French and the United States Marine Corps barracks in Beirut, killing 241 U.S. servicemen, 58 French paratroopers and 6 Lebanese civilians."
1983,"October 25","United States troops invade Grenada at the behest of Eugenia Charles of Dominica, a member of the Organization of American States."
1983,"November 27","Colombian Avianca Flight 11 crashes near Barajas Airport in Madrid, Spain, killing 181 of the 192 on board."
1983,"December 4","Lt. Bobby Goodman of the United States Navy is shot down over Lebanon and captured by the Syrians."
1983,"December 13","Turgut Özal, of ANAP forms the new government of Turkey (45rd government) beginning of new civilian regime."
1983,"December 17","A discotheque fire in Madrid, Spain, kills 83 people."
1983,"December 31","Two bombs explode in France; 1 on the Paris train kills 3 and injures 19. The other at Marseille station kills 2 and injures 34."
1983,"circa","Gerard Debreu wins the Bank of Sweden Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel."
1984,"January 10","The United States and the Vatican establish full diplomatic relations."
1984,"January 18","The Mitsui Miike coal mine explosion at Omuta, Kyushu, Japan kills 83."
1984,"February 26","United States Marines pull out of Beirut, Lebanon."
1984,"May 5","The Herreys win the Eurovision Song Contest 1984 for Sweden, with the song [i]Diggi-Loo, Diggi-Ley[/i]."
1984,"May 12","The Louisiana World's Fair opens."
1984,"June 27","France beats Spain 2-0 to win the Euro 84."
1984,"August 11","United States President Ronald Reagan, during a voice check for a radio broadcast remarks, ""My fellow Americans, I'm pleased to tell you today that I've signed legislation that will outlaw Russia forever. We begin bombing in five minutes""."
1984,"August 28","Josef Fritzl drugs and incarcerates his daughter Elisabeth in secret cellar, in Amstetten, Austria; she was released only after 24 years of sexual abuse and mental ordeal."
1984,"September 26","The United Kingdom and the People's Republic of China sign the initial agreement to return Hong Kong to China in 1997."
1984,"November 6","United States presidential election, 1984: Ronald Reagan defeats Walter F. Mondale with 59% of the popular vote, the highest since Richard Nixon's 61% victory in 1972. Reagan carries 49 states in the electoral college; Mondale wins only his home state of Minnesota by a mere 3,761 vote margin and the District of Columbia."
1984,"November 28","Over 250 years after their deaths, William Penn and his wife Hannah Callowhill Penn are made Honorary Citizens of the United States."
1984,"December 19","The People's Republic of China and United Kingdom sign the Sino-British Joint Declaration on the future of Hong Kong."
1985,"January 28","In Hollywood, California, the charity single ""We Are the World"" is recorded by USA for Africa. Like the enormously successful, ""Do They Know It's Christmas?"", that was recorded by Band Aid in Britain two months earlier, the single raises money to combat the ongoing famine in Ethiopia. The American act consists of high profile performers including Michael Jackson, Lionel Richie, Tina Turner, Cyndi Lauper and Diana Ross."
1985,"February 19","China Airlines Flight 006 is involved in a mid-air incident; while there are two injuries, no one is killed."
1985,"March 4","The Food and Drug Administration approves a blood test for AIDS, used since then to screen all blood donations in the United States."
1985,"March 17","Expo '85, a World's Fair, is held in Tsukuba, Ibaraki, Japan, until September 16."
1985,"April 1","Two Japanese government-owned corporations, Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Public Corporation, and Japan Tobacco and Salt Public Corporation, are privatized and change their names to Nippon Telegraph and Telephone, and Japan Tobacco."
1985,"April 12","1985 El Descanso bombing: A terrorist bombing attributed to the Islamic Jihad Organization in the [i]El Descanso[/i] restaurant near Madrid, Spain, mostly attended by U.S. personnel of the Torrejon Air Force Base, causes 18 dead (all Spaniards) and 82 injured."
1985,"May 4","The 30th Eurovision Song Contest takes place in Gothenburg, Sweden."
1985,"May 5","U.S. President Ronald Reagan joins German Chancellor Helmut Kohl for a controversial funeral service at a cemetery in Bitburg, Germany, which includes the graves of 59 elite S.S. troops from World War II."
1985,"June 17","John Hendricks launches the Discovery Channel in the United States."
1985,"July 19","The Val di Stava Dam in Italy collapses."
1985,"August 12","Japan Airlines Flight 123 crashes in Japan, killing 520 people (the worst single-aircraft disaster in history)."
1985,"circa","Multiple cases of espionage in the United States prompt the media to label this ""The Year of the Spy""."
1985,"circa","The Famine in Ethiopia continues; USA for Africa (""We Are the World"") and Live Aid raise funds for famine relief."
1986,"January 1","Spain and Portugal enter the [i]European Community[/i], which later becomes the European Union."
1986,"January 1","Aruba gains increased autonomy from the Netherlands and is separated from the Netherlands Antilles."
1986,"January 1","The Province of Flevoland is established in the Netherlands."
1986,"January 20","The United Kingdom and France announce plans to construct the Channel Tunnel."
1986,"February 19","After waiting 37 years, the United States Senate approves a treaty outlawing genocide."
1986,"February 27","The United States Senate allows its debates to be televised on a trial basis."
1986,"March 8","The Japanese Suisei probe flies by Halley's Comet, studying its UV hydrogen corona and solar wind."
1986,"March 26","An article in the [i]New York Times[/i] charges that Kurt Waldheim, former United Nations Secretary General and candidate for president of Austria, may have been involved in Nazi war crimes during World War II."
1986,"April 2","A bomb explodes on a Trans World Airlines flight from Rome to Athens, killing 4 people."
1986,"April 17","A treaty ends the Three Hundred and Thirty Five Years' War between the Netherlands and the Isles of Scilly."
1986,"May 2","The 1986 World Exposition opens in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada."
1986,"May 16","The Seville Statement on Violence is adopted by an international meeting of scientists, convened by the Spanish National Commission for UNESCO, in Seville, Spain."
1986,"May 31","The 1986 FIFA World Cup begins in Mexico."
1986,"June 4","Jonathan Pollard pleads guilty to espionage for selling top secret United States military intelligence to Israel."
1986,"June 8","Former United Nations Secretary-General Kurt Waldheim is elected president of Austria."
1986,"June 29","Argentina defeats West Germany 3-2 to win the 1986 FIFA World Cup."
1986,"July 27","Greg LeMond wins the Tour de France."
1986,"August 20","In Edmond, Oklahoma, United States Postal Service employee Patrick Sherrill guns down 14 of his co-workers before committing suicide."
1986,"October 9","United States District Court Judge Harry E. Claiborne becomes the fifth federal official to be removed from office through impeachment."
1986,"October 12","Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom and Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh visit the People's Republic of China."
1986,"October 16","The International Olympic Committee chooses Albertville, France to be the host city of the 1992 Winter Olympics and Barcelona, Spain to be the host city of the 1992 Summer Olympics."
1986,"October 27","The International World Day of Prayer is held in Assisi, Italy."
1986,"October 27","World Series: The New York Mets defeat the Boston Red Sox in 7 games. This is the second world series title in the Mets franchise. It is also remembered for Game 6, when Bill Buckner lets an easy ground ball hit by Mookie Wilson roll through his legs, letting the Mets win and pull even with the Red Sox in the series."
1986,"November 3","Iran-Contra affair: The Lebanese magazine [i]Ash-Shiraa[/i] reports that the United States has been selling weapons to Iran in secret, in order to secure the release of 7 American hostages held by pro-Iranian groups in Lebanon."
1986,"circa","Average per capita income in Japan exceeds that in the USA."
1987,"February 11","The United States military detonates an atomic weapon at the Nevada Test Site."
1987,"March 24","Michael Eisner, CEO of The Walt Disney Company, and French President Jacques Chirac sign the agreement to construct the 4,800 acre Euro Disney Resort (now called Disneyland Paris) and to develop the Val d'Europe area of the new town Marne-la-Vallée in Paris, France."
1987,"April 13","Portugal and the People's Republic of China sign an agreement in which Macau will be returned to China in 1999."
1987,"April 27","The United States Department of Justice declares incumbent Austrian president Kurt Waldheim an ""undesirable alien""."
1987,"May 11","Klaus Barbie goes on trial in Lyon for war crimes committed during World War II."
1987,"June 12","During a visit to Berlin, Germany, U.S. President Ronald Reagan challenges Soviet Premier Mikhail Gorbachev to tear down the Berlin Wall."
1987,"June 19","Edwards v. Aguillard: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that a Louisiana law requiring that creation science be taught in public schools whenever evolution is taught is unconstitutional."
1987,"June 28","An accidental explosion at Hohenfels Training Area in West Germany kills 3 U.S. troopers."
1987,"July 11","World population reaches five billion people with a child born in Zagreb, Croatia, according to the United Nations."
1987,"August 4","The World Commission on Environment and Development, also known as the Brundtland Commission, publishes its report, [i]Our Common Future.[/i]."
1987,"October 14","(October 14 - October 16) The United States is caught up in a drama that unfolds on television as a young child, Jessica McClure, falls down a well in Midland, Texas, and is later rescued."
1987,"October 23","On a vote of 58-42, the United States Senate rejects President Ronald Reagan's nomination of Robert Bork to the Supreme Court."
1987,"December 18","Square Co., Ltd. releases [i]Final Fantasy[/i] in Japan for the Famicom."
1987,"December 21","Turgut Özal, of ANAP forms the new government of Turkey (46th government)."
1987,"December 29","Prozac makes its debut in the United States."
1987,"circa","The Pendolino train makes its debut in Italy."
1988,"January 1","The Evangelical Lutheran Church in America is established, creating the largest Lutheran denomination in the United States."
1988,"February 3","The Democratic-controlled United States House of Representatives rejects President Ronald Reagan's request for $36.25 million to support the Nicaraguan Contras."
1988,"February 12","Anthony M. Kennedy is appointed to the Supreme Court of the United States."
1988,"February 24","[i]Hustler Magazine v. Falwell[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States sides with [i]Hustler[/i] magazine by overturning a lower court decision to award Jerry Falwell $200,000 for defamation."
1988,"February 29","A Nazi document implicates Kurt Waldheim in World War II deportations."
1988,"March 16","Iran-Contra Affair: Lieutenant Colonel Oliver North and Vice Admiral John Poindexter are indicted on charges of conspiracy to defraud the United States."
1988,"April 10","The Great Seto Bridge opens to traffic in Japan."
1988,"April 16","In Forlì, Italy, the brigate rosse kill Senator Roberto Ruffilli, an advisor of Prime Minister Ciriaco de Mita."
1988,"April 18","The United States Navy retaliates for the [i]Roberts[/i] mining with Operation Praying Mantis, in a day of strikes against Iranian oil platforms and naval vessels."
1988,"April 25","In Israel, Ivan Demjanjuk is sentenced to death for war crimes committed in World War II. He was accused by survivors of being the notorious guard at the Treblinka extermination camp known as ""Ivan the Terrible"". The conviction is later overturned by the Israeli Supreme Court."
1988,"April 30","World Expo '88 opens in Brisbane Queensland, Australia."
1988,"June 25","The Netherlands defeats the Soviet Union 2-0 to win Euro 88."
1988,"June 26","Air France Flight 296 crashes into the tops of trees beyond the runway on a demonstration flight at Habsheim, France; three passengers are killed."
1988,"June 29","[i]Morrison v. Olson[/i]: The United States Supreme Court upholds the law allowing special prosecutors to investigate suspected crimes by executive branch officials."
1988,"July 3","The Fatih Sultan Mehmet Bridge in Istanbul, Turkey is completed, providing the second connection between the continents of Europe and Asia over the Bosporus."
1988,"August 18","The Republican National Convention in New Orleans, Louisiana nominates George H.W. Bush for President and Dan Quayle for Vice President of the United States of America."
1988,"August 28","Seventy-five people are killed and 346 injured in one of the worst airshow disasters in history at Germany's Ramstein Air Base, when three jets from the Italian air demonstration team, [i]Frecce Tricolori[/i], collide, sending one of the aircraft crashing into the crowd of spectators."
1988,"September 5","With US$2 billion in federal aid, the Robert M. Bass Group agrees to buy the United States' largest thrift, American Savings and Loan Association."
1988,"September 24","(September 24 - September 26) Large, militant protests against the 1988 World Bank and IMF meetings take place in West Berlin."
1988,"October 15","Kirk Gibson hits a dramatic home run to win Game 1 of the World Series for the Los Angeles Dodgers, over the Oakland Athletics, by a score of 5-4."
1988,"October 23","[i]Super Mario Bros. 3[/i] is released in Japan."
1988,"November 8","United States presidential election, 1988: George H. W. Bush is elected over Michael Dukakis."
1988,"November 21","Ted Turner officially buys Jim Crockett Promotions, known as NWA Crockett, and turns it into World Championship Wrestling (WCW)."
1988,"circa","The U.S. Drought of 1988 causes big crop damage in many states, impacts many portions of the United States and causes around $60 billion in damage. Multiple regions suffer in the conditions. Heat waves cause 4,800 to 17,000 deaths while scorching many areas of the United States during 1988."
1989,"January 20","George H. W. Bush succeeds Ronald Reagan as the 41st President of the United States of America."
1989,"March 1","The Berne Convention, an international treaty on copyrights, is ratified by the United States."
1989,"March 1","The Politieke Partij Radicalen, Pacifistisch Socialistische Partij, Communistische Partij Nederland and the Evangelical People's Party amalgamate to form Netherlands political party GroenLinks (GL, GreenLeft)."
1989,"March 3","Portugal wins the FIFA U-20 World Cup, defeating Nigeria on the final by 2-0 in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia."
1989,"March 13","A geomagnetic storm causes the collapse of the Hydro-Québec power grid. Six million people are left without power for 9 hours. Some areas in the northeastern U.S. and in Sweden also lose power, and aurorae are seen as far as Texas."
1989,"March 14","Gun control: U.S. President George H. W. Bush bans the importation of certain guns deemed assault weapons into the United States."
1989,"June 4","Ufa train disaster: A natural gas explosion near Ufa, Russia kills 645 as 2 trains passing each other throw sparks near a leaky pipeline."
1989,"June 13","The wreck of the German battleship [i]Bismarck[/i], which was sunk in 1941, is located 600 miles (970 km) west of Brest, France."
1989,"July 14","France celebrates the 200th anniversary of the French Revolution."
1989,"August 19","The Pan-European Picnic, a peace demonstration held on the Austrian-Hungarian border."
1989,"August 23","Hungary removes border restrictions with Austria."
1989,"September 6","England holds Sweden to a 0-0 draw in Sweden, qualifying for the 1990 FIFA World Cup. The game becomes famous after Terry Butcher sustains a deep cut to his forehead early in the game. He receives stitches but plays on the entire game. By the end of the game, the front of Butcher's white shirt and shorts are almost entirely covered in blood."
1989,"September 14","An agreement of cooperation between Leningrad oblast (Russia) and Nordland County (Norway) is signed in Leningrad, by chairmen Lev Kojkolainen and Sigbjørn Eriksen."
1989,"October 9","In Leipzig, East Germany, protesters demand the legalization of opposition groups and democratic reforms."
1989,"October 17","The Loma Prieta earthquake, measuring 7.1 on the Richter scale, strikes the San Francisco-Oakland region of Northern California, killing 67 people and delaying the 1989 World Series for ten days."
1989,"October 18","The Communist leader of East Germany, Erich Honecker, is forced to step down as leader of the country after a series of health problems."
1989,"October 19","The Wonders of Life pavilion opens at Epcot in Walt Disney World, Florida."
1989,"October 31","The Grand National Assembly of Turkey elects Prime Minister Turgut Özal as the eighth President of Turkey."
1989,"November 7","Cold War: The Communist government of East Germany resigns, although SED leader Egon Krenz remains head of state."
1989,"November 9","Yildirim Akbulut, of ANAP forms the new government of Turkey (47th government)"
1989,"November 11","Louie Espinoza inaugurated as WBO World Featherweight Champion."
1989,"December 1","Cold War: East Germany's parliament abolishes the constitutional provision granting the Communist-dominated SED its monopoly on power. Egon Krenz, the Politburo and the Central Committee resign 2 days later."
1989,"December 25","Bank of Japan governors announce a major interest rate hike, eventually leading to the peak and fall of the [i]bubble economy[/i]."
1989,"circa","Kamchatka opens to Russian civilian visitors."
1989,"circa","The Japan Fantasy Novel Award is established."
1989,"circa","[i]World in Conflict[/i] (computer game) - The Soviet Union invades Europe and the United States."
1989,"circa","The events of the arcade version of [i]Final Fight[/i] occurs in 1989 according to the original Japanese version. The English localization changes the setting to an unspecified year in the 1990s."
1990,"February 5","Manuel Fraga becomes the president of Galicia, Spain."
1990,"February 11","James ""Buster"" Douglas knocks out Mike Tyson to win the World Heavyweight Boxing crown."
1990,"February 13","German reunification: An agreement is reached for a two-stage plan to reunite Germany."
1990,"March 27","The United States begins broadcasting TV Martí to Cuba."
1990,"April 1","Strangeways Prison riot: The longest prison riot in Britain's history begins at Strangeways Prison in Manchester, and continues for 3 weeks and 3 days, until April 25."
1990,"April 24","Cold War: West Germany and East Germany agree to merge currency and economies on July 1."
1990,"May 1","The former Philippine Episcopal Church (supervised by the Episcopal Church of the United States of America) is granted full autonomy and raised to the states of an Autocephalous Anglican Province and renamed the Episcopal Church of the Philippines."
1990,"May 17","The World Health Organization removes homosexuality from its list of diseases."
1990,"June 1","Members of the Provisional Irish Republican Army shoot and kill Major Michael Dillon-Lee and Private William Robert Davies of the British Army. Dillon-Lee is killed outside his home in Dortmund, Germany and Davies is killed at a railway station in Lichfield, England."
1990,"June 8","The 1990 FIFA World Cup begins in Italy."
1990,"June 12","Cold War: The parliament of the Russian Federation formally declares its sovereignty."
1990,"July 8","West Germany defeats Argentina 1-0 to win the 1990 FIFA World Cup."
1990,"July 27","The parliament building and a government television house in Port of Spain, Trinidad and Tobago are stormed by the Jamaat al Muslimeen in a coup d'état attempt which lasts 5 days. Approximately 26 to 30 people are killed and several wounded (including then Prime Minister, A. N. R. Robinson, who is shot in the leg)."
1990,"August 23","Cold War: East Germany and West Germany announce they will unite on October 3. Cockiest captain born."
1990,"September 12","Cold War: The two German states and the Four Powers sign the Treaty on the Final Settlement With Respect to Germany in Moscow, paving the way for German reunification."
1990,"October 3","Cold War: East Germany and West Germany reunify into a single Germany."
1990,"November 12","Akihito is enthroned as the 125th emperor of Japan."
1990,"November 12","Tim Berners-Lee publishes a more formal proposal for the World Wide Web."
1990,"November 14","Germany and Poland sign a treaty confirming the border at the Oder-Neisse line."
1990,"December 31","Russian Garry Kasparov holds his title by winning the World Chess Championship match against his countryman Anatoly Karpov."
1990,"circa","The New Revised Standard Version of the Bible is published in the United States."
1990,"circa","Metropolitan Alexy of Leningrad is elected Russian Orthodox Patriarch of Moscow and all Russia."
1991,"January 12","Gulf War: The Congress of the United States passes a resolution authorizing the use of military force to liberate Kuwait."
1991,"February 11","UNPO, the Unrepresented Nations & Peoples Organization, forms in The Hague, Netherlands."
1991,"February 13","Gulf War: Two laser-guided ""smart bombs"" destroy an underground bunker in Baghdad, killing hundreds of Iraqis. United States military intelligence claims it was a military facility but Iraqi officials identify it as a bomb shelter."
1991,"February 22","Gulf War: Iraq accepts a Russian-proposed cease fire agreement. The U.S. rejects the agreement, but says that retreating Iraqi forces will not be attacked if they leave Kuwait within 24 hours."
1991,"March 1","Clayton Keith Yeutter finishes as the United States Secretary of Agriculture."
1991,"March 13","The United States Department of Justice announces that Exxon has agreed to pay $1 billion for the clean-up of the Exxon Valdez oil spill in Alaska."
1991,"March 15","Germany formally regains complete independence after the 4 post-World War II occupying powers (France, the United Kingdom, the United States and the Soviet Union) relinquish all remaining rights."
1991,"April 5","Former Senator John Tower and 22 others are killed in an airplane crash in Brunswick, Georgia, United States."
1991,"April 10","The Italian ferry [i]Moby Prince[/i] collides with an oil tanker in dense fog off Livorno, Italy killing 140."
1991,"April 26","Tornadoes break out in the central United States, killing 17. The most notable tornado of the day strikes Andover, Kansas."
1991,"May 4","Sweden wins the 36th Eurovision Song Contest."
1991,"June 12","Boris Yeltsin is elected President of Russia, the largest and most populous of the 15 Soviet republics."
1991,"June 23","Mesut Yilmaz, of ANAP forms the new government of Turkey (48th government)"
1991,"August 6","Tim Berners-Lee announces the World Wide Web project and software on the alt.hypertext newsgroup."
1991,"August 13","The Super Nintendo Entertainment System (or ""Super Nintendo"") is released in the United States."
1991,"September 2","The United States recognizes the independence of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania."
1991,"September 6","The name [i]Saint Petersburg[/i] is restored to Russia's second-largest city, which had been renamed [i]Leningrad[/i] in 1924."
1991,"October 2","Arkansas Governor Bill Clinton announces he will seek the 1992 Democratic nomination for President of the United States."
1991,"October 11","In Russia, the KGB is replaced by the SVR."
1991,"October 15","United States Senate votes 52-48 to confirm Judge Clarence Thomas to the Supreme Court of the United States."
1991,"October 27","The Minnesota Twins win the World Series against the Atlanta Braves."
1991,"October 28","The 1991 Perfect Storm Strikes the northeastern United States, causing over 200 million dollars of damage and resulting in 12 direct fatalities."
1991,"November 6","CPSU, and its republic-level division, Communist Party of the Russian SFSR, banned in the Russian SFSR by Presidential decree N 169."
1991,"November 20","An Azerbaijani MI-8 helicopter carrying 19 peacekeeping mission team with officials and journalists from Russia, Kazakhstan and Azerbaijan is shot down by Armenian military forces in Khojavend district of Azerbaijan."
1991,"November 20","Süleyman Demirel of DYP forms the new government of Turkey (49th government, coalition partner CHP)."
1991,"December 4","Pan American World Airways ends operations."
1991,"December 8","Leaders of Russia, Belarus, and Ukraine meet and sign an agreement ending the Soviet Union and establishing the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), in the Bialowieza Forest Nature Reserve in Belarus."
1991,"December 12","Supreme Soviet of the Russian SFSR denounced Union Treaty of 1922 and ratified Belavezha Accords instead."
1991,"December 24","Russian SFSR President Boris Yeltsin send a letter to UN Secretary-General, stating that Russian Federation (RSFSR) should be a successor to collapsing Soviet Union."
1991,"December 25","Russian SFSR officially changed its name to [i]Russian Federation (Russia)[/i]."
1992,"January 8","George H. W. Bush is televised falling violently ill at a state dinner in Japan, vomiting into the lap of Prime Minister Kiichi Miyazawa and fainting."
1992,"January 13","Japan apologizes for forcing Korean women into sexual slavery during World War II."
1992,"January 26","Boris Yeltsin announces that Russia will stop targeting United States cities with nuclear weapons."
1992,"February 8","The opening ceremony for the 1992 Winter Olympics is held in Albertville, France."
1992,"February 11","An F-16 jet crashes into a residential district of Hengelo, the Netherlands; no casualties are reported."
1992,"March 3","Turkey's worst coal mine disaster leaves 263 dead near Zonguldak."
1992,"March 9","The People's Republic of China ratifies the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty."
1992,"March 13","In eastern Turkey, an earthquake registering 6.8 on the Richter scale, kills over 500."
1992,"April 13","Roermond, the Netherlands, is rocked by an earthquake along the Peel Fault."
1992,"April 20","Seville, Spain's 6-month Universal Exhibition, called Seville Expo '92, opens."
1992,"April 21","The death of Grand Duke Vladimir Cyrillovich of Russia results in a succession dispute between Nicholas Romanov, Prince of Russia and Vladimir's daughter Maria for the leadership of the Imperial Family of Russia."
1992,"April 28","The two remaining constituent republics of the former Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia - Serbia and Montenegro - form a new state, named the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (after 2003, Serbia and Montenegro), bringing to an end the official union of Serbs, Croats, Slovenes, Montenegrins, Bosnian Muslims and Macedonians that existed from 1918 (with the exception of the period during World War II)."
1992,"May 5","Alabama ratifies a 202-year-old proposed amendment to the United States Constitution making the 27th Amendment law. This amendment bars the U.S. Congress from giving itself a midterm or retroactive pay raise."
1992,"May 5","Russian leaders in Crimea declare their separation from Ukraine as a new republic. They withdraw the secession on May 10."
1992,"May 10","Sweden wins the Ice Hockey World Championships in Prague."
1992,"May 13","Falun Gong is introduced by Li Hongzhi in China."
1992,"May 15","The Genoa Expo '92 World's Fair opens in Genoa, Italy."
1992,"June 17","A 'Joint Understanding' agreement on arms reduction is signed by U.S. President George H. W. Bush and Russian President Boris Yeltsin (this is later codified in START II)."
1992,"June 22","Two skeletons excavated in Yekaterinburg are identified as Czar Nicholas II of Russia and Tsarina Alexandra."
1992,"June 26","Denmark beats Germany 2-0 to win the 1992 UEFA European Football Championship at Ullevi Stadium in Gothenburg, Sweden."
1992,"July 22","Near Medellín, Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar escapes from his luxury prison, fearing extradition to the United States."
1992,"July 25","(July 25 - August 9) The 1992 Summer Olympics are held in Barcelona, Spain."
1992,"September 15","Mihkel Mathiesen assumes the presidency of the pre-World War II Republic of Estonia in exile, and appoints a new government in pursuit to avoid abolition of the government in exile."
1992,"October 4","The Bijlmerramp disaster: An Israeli plane crashes in Amsterdam, the Netherlands; 43 are killed, many more injured."
1992,"October 17","Yoshihiro Hattori, a 16-year-old Japanese exchange student, mistakes the address of a party and is shot dead after knocking on the wrong door in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. The shooter, Rodney Peairs, is later acquitted, sparking outrage in Japan."
1992,"October 29","The Food and Drug Administration approves Depo-Provera for use as a contraceptive in the United States."
1992,"November 18","Russian President Boris Yeltsin, in a goodwill gesture to South Korea during a visit to Seoul to ratify a new treaty, released the 9 years concealed flight data recorder (FDR) and cockpit voice recorder (CVR) of KAL 007, shot down near Moneron Island by the Soviets on Sept. 1, 1983."
1992,"November 24","In the People's Republic of China, a China Southern Airlines domestic flight crashes, killing all 141 people on-board."
1992,"December 3","UN Security Council Resolution 794 is unanimously passed, approving a coalition of United Nations peacekeepers led by the United States to form UNITAF, tasked with ensuring humanitarian aid gets distributed and establishing peace in Somalia."
1992,"December 3","The Greek oil tanker [i]Aegean Sea[/i], carrying 80,000 tonnes of crude oil, runs aground in a storm while on approach to La Coruña, Spain, and spills much of its cargo."
1992,"December 5","Kent Conrad of North Dakota resigns his seat in the United States Senate and is sworn into the other seat from North Dakota, becoming the only U.S. Senator ever to have held 2 seats on the same day."
1992,"December 8","The last blast is fired at the Falu Copper Mine in Falun, Sweden, after a millennium of continuous operation."
1992,"December 20","The Folies Bergère music hall in Paris, France closes."
1992,"circa","Deng Xiaoping accelerates market reforms to establish a socialist market economy in the People's Republic of China."
1993,"January 19","IBM announces a $4.97 billion loss for 1992, the largest single-year corporate loss in United States history to date."
1993,"January 20","Bill Clinton succeeds George H.W. Bush as the 42nd President of the United States."
1993,"January 24","In Turkey, thousands protest the murder of journalist Ugur Mumcu."
1993,"February 4","Members of the right-wing Austrian FPÖ split to form the Liberal Forum in protest against the increasing nationalistic bent of the party."
1993,"February 10","Lien Chan is named by Lee Teng-Hui to succeed Hau Pei-tsun as Premier of the Republic of China."
1993,"February 11","Janet Reno is selected by President Clinton as Attorney General of the United States."
1993,"February 26","World Trade Center bombing: In New York City, a van bomb parked below the North Tower of the World Trade Center explodes, killing 6 and injuring over 1,000."
1993,"March 4","Authorities announce the capture of suspected World Trade Center bombing conspirator Mohammad Salameh."
1993,"March 27","Jiang Zemin becomes President of the People's Republic of China."
1993,"April 6","A nuclear accident occurs at Tomsk 7 in Russia."
1993,"April 23","The World Health Organization declares tuberculosis a Global Emergency."
1993,"April 26","Oscar Luigi Scalfaro appoints Carlo Azeglio Ciampi Prime Minister of Italy."
1993,"April 28","An executive order requires the United States Air Force to allow women to fly war planes."
1993,"April 30","Tennis star Monica Seles is stabbed in the back by an obsessed fan of rival Steffi Graf at a tournament in Hamburg, Germany."
1993,"May 1","Pierre Bérégovoy, former prime minister of France, commits suicide."
1993,"May 16","The Grand National Assembly of Turkey elects Prime Minister Süleyman Demirel as President of Turkey."
1993,"May 16","After Demirel becomes the president the acting prime minister of Turkey is Erdal Inönü of SHP for 40 days."
1993,"May 19","International Civil Aviation Organization of U.N., based on Russian Federation handover of KAL 007's Black Box and Soviet military communications, reopens investigation of Soviet shootdown of KAL 007 near Moneron Island on Sept. 1, 1983."
1993,"June 5","[i]Minnesota v. Dickerson[/i]: The United States Supreme Court rules that the seizure of evidence during a pat-down search is unconstitutional."
1993,"June 20","A 7.5 earthquake hits Japan, killing 385 people."
1993,"June 22","Japan's New Party Sakigake breaks away from the Liberal Democratic Party."
1993,"June 25","Tansu Çiller of DYP forms the new government of Turkey."
1993,"June 26","(June 26 - June 28) Typhoon Koryn causes important damages in the Philippines, China and Macau."
1993,"June 27","In Bad Kleinen, Germany, GSG 9 troopers arrest terrorists Birgit Hogefeld and Wolfgang Grams."
1993,"July 2","An integrist mob sets fire to the hotel where [i]The Satanic Verses[/i] translator Aziz Nesin resides in Sivas, Turkey, killing 37."
1993,"July 7","(July 7 - July 9) The 19th G7 summit is held in Tokyo, Japan."
1993,"July 12","A magnitude 7.8 earthquake off Hokkaido, Japan launches a devastating tsunami that kills 202 on the small island of Okushiri, Hokkaido."
1993,"July 16","(July 16 - July 17) In Estonia, the majority Russian cities of Narva and Sillamäe organize illegal referendums on ""territorial autonomy"" to protest new citizenship laws."
1993,"July 19","Japanese general election, 1993: The loss of majority of the Liberal Democratic Party results in a coalition taking power."
1993,"July 26","Miguel Indurain wins the 1993 Tour de France."
1993,"August 4","The Japanese government issues the Kono Statement, acknowledging the comfort women's deportation."
1993,"August 6","According to Japanese government and TBS networks reports, torrential rain and mudslides kill 72 in Kagoshima, Japan."
1993,"August 30","Russia completes removing its troops from Lithuania."
1993,"September 17","Russian troops withdraw from Poland."
1993,"September 27","War in Abkhazia - Fall of Sukhumi: Eduard Shevardnadze accuses Russia of passive complicity."
1993,"October 2","(October 2 - October 5) The Russian constitutional crisis of 1993 culminates with Russian military and security forces clearing the White House of Russia Parliament building by force, squashing a mass uprising against President Boris Yeltsin."
1993,"October 5","China performs a nuclear test, ending a worldwide [i]de facto[/i] moratorium."
1993,"October 8","David Miscavige announces the IRS has granted full tax exemption to the Church of Scientology International and affiliated churches and organizations, ending the Church's 40-year battle with the IRS and resulting in religious recognition in the United States."
1993,"November 17","(November 17 - November 22) The North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) passes the legislative houses in the United States, Canada and Mexico."
1993,"November 20","Savings and loan crisis: The United States Senate Ethics Committee issues a stern censure of California senator Alan Cranston for his dealings with savings-and-loan executive Charles Keating."
1993,"circa","The second World Parliament of Religions is held in Chicago."
1993,"circa","Over a dozen people are killed by the new Hantavirus cardiopulmonary syndrome, mainly in the Southwestern United States."
1994,"January 14","U.S. President Bill Clinton and Russian President Boris Yeltsin sign the Kremlin Accords, which stop the preprogrammed aiming of nuclear missiles toward each country's targets, and also provide for the dismantling of the nuclear arsenal in Ukraine."
1994,"January 19","Record cold temperatures hit the eastern United States. The coldest temperature ever measured in Indiana state history, -36°F (-38°C), is recorded in New Whiteland, Indiana."
1994,"February 3","William J. Perry is sworn in as the United States Secretary of Defense."
1994,"February 22","Aldrich Ames and his wife are charged with spying for the Soviet Union by the United States Department of Justice. Ames is later convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment; his wife receives 5 years in prison."
1994,"February 28","United States F-16 pilots shoot down 4 Serbian fighter aircraft over Bosnia and Herzegovina for violation of the Operation Deny Flight and its no-fly zone."
1994,"March 1","Mary Ellen Withrow begins her term of office as Treasurer of the United States, serving under President Bill Clinton."
1994,"March 27","The biggest tornado outbreak in 1994 occurs in the southeastern United States; 1 tornado hits a Goshen United Methodist Church in Piedmont, Alabama, killing 22 people."
1994,"April 25","The largest high school arson ever in the United States is started at Burnsville High School, in Burnsville, Minnesota, resulting in over 15 million dollars in damages. The same arsonist also goes on to set arsons at Edina High School and Minnetonka High School."
1994,"April 26","China Airlines Flight 140, an Airbus A300, crashes while landing at Nagoya, Japan, killing 264 people."
1994,"May 1","Three-time Formula One world champion Ayrton Senna is killed in an accident during the San Marino Grand Prix in Imola, Italy."
1994,"May 3","Japan signs the 200th treaty between itself and the African nation of Chad, making this day known as JapaTreaty 200."
1994,"May 6","The Channel Tunnel, which took 15,000 workers over 7 years to complete, opens between England and France, enabling passengers to travel between the 2 countries in 35 minutes."
1994,"June 28","Members of the Aum Shinrikyo cult release a sarin gas attack at Matsumoto, Japan, killing 7 and injuring 660."
1994,"June 30","An Airbus A330 crashes during a test flight near Toulouse, France, where Airbus is based, killing the seven-person crew. The test was meant to simulate an engine failure at low speed with maximum angle of climb."
1994,"July 2","Colombian footballer Andrés Escobar, 27, is shot dead in Medellín. His murder is commonly attributed as retaliation for the own goal Escobar scored in the 1994 FIFA World Cup against the United States."
1994,"July 17","Brazil wins the 1994 FIFA World Cup, defeating Italy by 3-2 in penalties (full time 0-0)."
1994,"August 23","Eugene Bullard is posthumously commissioned as a Second Lieutenant in the United States Air Force, 33 years after his death, and 77 years to the day after his rejection for U.S. military service in 1917."
1994,"August 31","The Russian army leaves Estonia."
1994,"September 3","Cold War: Russia and the People's Republic of China agree to de-target their nuclear weapons against each other."
1994,"September 4","Kansai International Airport in Osaka, Japan opens. All international services are transferred from Itami to Kansai."
1994,"October 5","UNESCO inaugurates World Teachers' Day to celebrate and commemorate the signing of the Recommendation Concerning the Status of Teachers on October 5, 1966."
1994,"October 31","The Duke of Edinburgh attends a ceremony in Israel, where his late mother, Princess Alice of Battenberg, is honoured as ""Righteous among the Nations"" for sheltering Jewish families from the Nazis in Athens, during World War II."
1994,"November 5","George Foreman wins the WBA and IBF World Heavyweight Championships by KO'ing Michael Moorer becoming the oldest heavyweight champion in history."
1994,"November 6","A flood in Piedmont, Italy, kills dozens of people."
1994,"November 13","Voters in Sweden decide to join the European Union in a referendum."
1994,"December 11","Russian president Boris Yeltsin orders troops into Chechnya."
1994,"December 11","A small bomb explodes on Philippine Airlines Flight 434, killing a Japanese businessman. The bombing was a field test done by Ramzi Yousef to test explosives that would have been used in Project Bojinka."
1994,"December 19","Civil unions between homosexuals are legalized in Sweden."
1994,"circa","Tropical Storms Alberto & Gordon cause very damaging floods, intense winds and extensive problems directly over the Southeastern United States and the Caribbean Islands. The death tolls are unusually severe and damages are extreme in both tropical storms."
1995,"January 1","The World Trade Organization (WTO) is established to replace the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT)."
1995,"January 1","Austria, Finland & Sweden act to join the European Union."
1995,"January 17","A magnitude 6.8 earthquake called the ""Great Hanshin earthquake"" occurs near Kobe, Japan, causing great property damage and killing 6,434 people."
1995,"January 25","Norwegian rocket incident: A rocket launched from the space exploration centre at Andøya, Norway is briefly interpreted by the Russians as an incoming attack."
1995,"February 15","Hacker Kevin Mitnick is arrested by the FBI and charged with penetrating some of the United States' most ""secure"" computer systems."
1995,"February 21","Ibrahim Ali, a 17-year-old Comorian living in France, is murdered by 3 far-right National Front activists."
1995,"February 27","In Denver, Colorado, Stapleton Airport closes and is replaced by the new Denver International Airport, the largest in the United States."
1995,"March 1","In Moscow, Russian anti-corruption journalist Vladislav Listyev is killed by a gunman."
1995,"March 30","A police officer tries to assassinate Takaji Kunimatsu, chief of the National Police Agency of Japan."
1995,"May 1","Jacques Chirac is elected president of France."
1995,"May 16","Japanese police besiege the headquarters of Aum Shinrikyo near Mount Fuji and arrest cult leader Shoko Asahara."
1995,"May 28","A 7.6 magnitude earthquake in Neftegorsk, Russia kills at least 2,000."
1995,"June 2","Mrkonjic Grad incident: A United States Air Force F-16 piloted by Captain Scott O'Grady is shot down over Bosnia and Herzegovina while patrolling the NATO no-fly zone. O'Grady is rescued by U.S. Marines six days later."
1995,"June 2","Waffen-SS Hauptsturmführer Erich Priebke is extradited from Argentina to Italy."
1995,"June 6","U.S. astronaut Norman Thagard breaks NASA's space endurance record of 14 days, 1 hour and 16 minutes, aboard the Russian space station Mir."
1995,"June 22","Japanese police rescue 365 hostages from a hijacked All Nippon Airways Flight 857 (Boeing 747-200) at Hakodate airport. The hijacker was armed with a knife and demanded the release of Shoko Asahara."
1995,"June 24","South Africa wins the Rugby World Cup."
1995,"June 29","Iraq disarmament crisis: According to UNSCOM, the unity of the UN Security Council begins to fray, as a few countries, particularly France and Russia, become more interested in making financial deals with Iraq than in disarming the country."
1995,"September 4","The Fourth World Conference on Women opens in Beijing with over 4,750 delegates from 181 countries in attendance."
1995,"September 23","Argentine national Guillermo ""Bill"" Gaede is arrested in Phoenix, Arizona on charges of industrial espionage. His sales to Cuba, China, North Korea and Iran are believed to have involved Intel and AMD trade secrets worth USD$10-20 million."
1995,"October 1","Ten people are convicted of bombing the World Trade Center in 1993."
1995,"October 5","Tansu Çiller of DYP forms the new government of Turkey (51st government, a minority government which failed to receive the vote of confidence)"
1995,"October 30","Tansu Çiller of DYP forms the new government of Turkey."
1995,"November 10","Iraq disarmament crisis: With help from Israel and Jordan, UNSCOM inspector Scott Ritter intercepts 240 Russian gyroscopes and accelerometers on their way to Iraq from Russia."
1995,"November 14","A budget standoff between Democrats and Republicans in the Congress of the United States, forces the federal government to temporarily close national parks and museums, and run most government offices with skeleton staff."
1995,"December 16","Iraq disarmament crisis: Iraqi scuba divers, under the direction of the United Nations Special Commission, dredge the Tigris near Baghdad. The divers find over 200 prohibited Russian-made missile instruments and components."
1996,"January 9","Art forger Eric Hebborn is assassinated in Rome, Italy."
1996,"January 11","Ryutaro Hashimoto, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party, becomes Prime Minister of Japan."
1996,"January 13","Italy's prime minister, Lamberto Dini, resigns after the failure of all-party talks to confirm him. New talks are initiated by president Oscar Luigi Scalfaro to form a new government."
1996,"January 31","An explosion in Shaoyang, China kills 122 and injures over 400 when 10 tons of dynamite in an illegal explosives warehouse underneath an apartment building detonate."
1996,"February 4","An earthquake near Lijiang in southwest China, measuring up to 7 on the Richter scale, kills at least 240 people, injures more than 14,000 and makes hundreds of thousands homeless."
1996,"February 6","A Birgenair Boeing 757 (Flight 301), on an unauthorised charter flight from the Caribbean to Germany, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of the Dominican Republic, killing all 189 passengers and crew."
1996,"February 15","A Long March 3 rocket at the Xichang Satellite Launch Center in China crashes into a rural village after liftoff, killing as many as 500.."
1996,"March 3","José María Aznar, leader of the Popular Party, is elected prime minister of Spain, replacing Felipe González."
1996,"March 6","Mesut Yilmaz, of ANAP forms the new government of Turkey (53rd government)"
1996,"March 8","The People's Republic of China begins surface-to-surface missile testing and military exercises off Taiwanese coastal areas. The United States government condemns the act as provocation, and the Taiwanese government warns of retaliation."
1996,"March 17","Sri Lanka wins the Cricket World Cup by storming to a famous victory against the tournament favourite Australia."
1996,"March 26","The International Monetary Fund approves a $10.2 billion loan to Russia for economic reform."
1996,"April 6","Turkish authorities begin Operation Hawk, an army offensive against rebels from the Kurdish Worker's Party in southeastern Turkey."
1996,"April 11","Jessica Dubroff, 7, is killed in a crash near Cheyenne, Wyoming while attempting to set a record as the youngest person to pilot an airplane across the United States."
1996,"April 21","A general election in Italy proclaims a new government headed by Romano Prodi and his Olive Tree coalition, replacing Silvio Berlusconi."
1996,"May 20","Gay rights - [i]Romer v. Evans[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules against a law that prevents any city, town or county in the state of Colorado from taking any legislative, executive, or judicial action to protect the rights of homosexuals."
1996,"May 23","Swede Göran Kropp reaches the Mount Everest summit alone without oxygen, after having bicycled there from Sweden."
1996,"May 30","The Hoover Institution releases an optimistic report that global warming will probably reduce mortality in the United States and provide Americans with valuable benefits."
1996,"June 23","The Nintendo 64 video game system is released in Japan."
1996,"June 28","A new government is formed in Turkey, with Necmettin Erbakan of Refah Partisi becoming prime minister of the coalition government, and deputy and foreign minister Tansu Çiller of the True Path Party succeeding him after two years."
1996,"June 29","An explosion in a firecrackers factory in Sichuan Province, China kills at least 36 people and injures another 52."
1996,"July 3","Boris Yeltsin is reelected as President of Russia after the second round of elections."
1996,"July 12","Hurricane Bertha: made landfall in North Carolina as a Category 2 storm, causing $270 million in damage to the United States and its possessions and many indirect deaths."
1996,"July 19","The 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, Georgia, United States, begin."
1996,"August 7","Heavy rains kill more than 80 campers near Huesca, Spain."
1996,"August 9","Boris Yeltsin is sworn in at the Kremlin for a second term as President of Russia."
1996,"August 15","Bob Dole is nominated for President of the United States, and Jack Kemp for Vice President, at the Republican National Convention in San Diego, California."
1996,"August 29","A Russian Tupolev 143 jetliner crashes into a mountain as it approaches the airport at Spitsbergen, Norway, killing all 141 people on board."
1996,"October 10","Pokémon Blue was released in a limit version in Japan."
1996,"November 17","A bomb explosion in Kaspiysk, Russia kills 32 people."
1996,"November 18","World-renowned bird expert Tony Silva is sentenced to 7 years in prison without parole, for leading an illegal parrot smuggling ring."
1996,"November 23","The Republic of Angola officially joins the World Trade Organization, as [i]Angola[/i]."
1996,"December 17","The Túpac Amaru Revolutionary Movement takes 72 hostages in the Japanese Embassy in Lima, Peru."
1996,"December 18","The [i]loi Carrez[/i], or Carrez law governing property transactions was enacted in France."
1997,"February 23","A small fire occurs on the Russian space station Mir."
1997,"March 11","An explosion at the Tokaimura nuclear waste reprocessing plant in Japan exposes 35 workers to low-level radioactive contamination, in the worst nuclear accident in Japan's history."
1997,"March 13","The National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China creates a new Chongqing Municipality, out of part of Sichuan."
1997,"March 18","The tail of a Russian An-24 charter plane breaks off while en-route to Turkey, causing the plane to crash, killing all 50 on board, and resulting in the grounding of all An-24s."
1997,"April 11","Fire damages the Turin Cathedral in Italy."
1997,"April 22","France supports the new transitional government in Zaire, withdrawing its support of Mobutu Sese Seko."
1997,"April 29","Two trains crash at Hunan, China; 126 are killed."
1997,"May 12","The Russian-Chechen Peace Treaty is signed."
1997,"May 15","The United States government acknowledges existence of the ""Secret War"" in Laos, and dedicates the Laos Memorial in honor of Hmong and other ""Secret War"" veterans."
1997,"May 25","Strom Thurmond becomes the longest-serving member in the history of the United States Senate (41 years and 10 months)."
1997,"June 8","A United States Coast Guard helicopter crashes near Humboldt Bay, California; all 4 crewmembers perish."
1997,"June 12","The United States Department of the Treasury unveils a new $50 bill, meant to be more difficult to counterfeit."
1997,"June 25","An unmanned Progress spacecraft collides with the Russian space station Mir."
1997,"July 1","The United Kingdom hands sovereignty of Hong Kong to the People's Republic of China."
1997,"July 10","Miguel Ángel Blanco is kidnapped in Ermua, Spain and murdered by the ETA."
1997,"October 11","The mixed martial arts organization PRIDE Fighting Championships holds its inaugural event at the Tokyo Dome in Tokyo, Japan. In the main event Rickson Gracie defeats Nobuhiko Takada by armbar."
1997,"November 3","In France, striking truck drivers blockade ports during a pay dispute."
1997,"November 10","Telecom companies WorldCom and MCI Communications announce a US$37 billion merger to form MCI WorldCom (the largest merger in U.S. history)."
1997,"December 3","In Ottawa, Canada, representatives from 121 countries sign a treaty prohibiting the manufacture and deployment of anti-personnel land mines. However, the United States, the People's Republic of China, and Russia do not sign the treaty."
1997,"December 16","""Denno Senshi Porygon"", an episode of the Pokémon TV series, is aired in Japan, inducing seizures in hundreds of Japanese children."
1997,"circa","John Carpenter's 1981 film [i]Escape from New York[/i] is set in 1997 of a United States so crime-ridden that Manhattan Island in New York City has become a maximum security prison."
1998,"January 2","Russia begins to circulate new rubles to stem inflation and promote confidence."
1998,"February","Iraq disarmament crisis: The United States Senate passes Resolution 71, urging U.S. President Bill Clinton to ""take all necessary and appropriate actions to respond to the threat posed by Iraq's refusal to end its weapons of mass destruction programs""."
1998,"February 3","Cavalese cable-car disaster: a United States Military pilot causes the deaths of 20 people near Trento, Italy, when his low-flying plane severs the cable of a cable-car."
1998,"February 7","(February 7 - February 22) The 1998 Winter Olympics are held in Nagano, Japan."
1998,"February 16","China Airlines Flight 676 crashes into a residential area near Chiang Kai-shek International Airport, killing 202 people (all 196 on board and 6 on the ground)."
1998,"February 20","Iraq disarmament crisis: Iraqi President Saddam Hussein negotiates a deal with U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan, allowing weapons inspectors to return to Baghdad, preventing military action by the United States and Britain."
1998,"March 4","Gay rights: [i]Oncale v. Sundowner Offshore Services[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States rules that federal laws banning on-the-job sexual harassment also apply when both parties are the same sex."
1998,"April 5","In Japan, the Akashi-Kaikyo Bridge linking Shikoku with Honshu and costing about US$3.8 billion, opens to traffic, becoming the largest suspension bridge in the world."
1998,"April 25","A waste reservoir at the Los Frailes mine in Andalusia, Spain ruptures, discharging heavy metal waste into the Guadiamar River. The pollution threatens the sensitive ecosystem and endangered species of Doñana National Park, Spain's largest nature reserve, but is diverted into the Guadalquivir River. Up to 100 km² of farmland are ruined by the spill."
1998,"May 13","India carries out 2 more nuclear tests at Pokhran. The United States and Japan impose economic sanctions on India."
1998,"May 18","[i]United States v. Microsoft[/i]: The United States Department of Justice and 20 U.S. states file an antitrust case against Microsoft."
1998,"May 28","Nuclear testing: In response to a series of Indian nuclear tests, Pakistan explodes 5 nuclear devices of its own in the Chaghai hills of Baluchistan, prompting the United States, Japan and other nations to impose economic sanctions."
1998,"June 3","Eschede train disaster: An InterCityExpress high speed train derails between Hannover and Hamburg, Germany, causing 101 deaths."
1998,"July","The Yangtze River experiences massive flooding as the government of the People's Republic of China sends in the Army for flood relief efforts."
1998,"July 5","Japan launches a probe to Mars, joining the United States and Russia as an outer space-exploring nation."
1998,"July 10","The DNA-identified remains of United States Air Force 1st Lt. Michael Joseph Blassie arrive home to his family in St. Louis, Missouri, after being in the Tomb of the Unknowns since 1984."
1998,"July 17","In Saint Petersburg, Nicholas II of Russia and his family are buried in St. Catherine Chapel, 80 years after he and his family were killed by Bolsheviks."
1998,"July 24","Russell Eugene Weston Jr. bursts into the United States Capitol and opens fire, killing 2 police officers. He is later ruled incompetent to stand trial."
1998,"July 25","The United States Navy commissions the aircraft carrier USS [i]Harry S. Truman[/i] and puts her into service."
1998,"July 25","Wakayama Arsenic poison case: 63 are sickened and 4 killed by arsenic in a festival in the town in Wakayama Prefecture in Japan; Masumi Hayashi is arrested for murder."
1998,"August 7","Yangtze River Floods: In China the Yangtze River breaks through the main bank; before this, from August 1-5, periphery levees collapsed consecutively in Jiayu County Baizhou Bay. The death toll exceeds 12,000, with many thousands more injured."
1998,"August 7","1998 U.S. embassy bombings: The bombings of the United States embassies in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania, and Nairobi, Kenya kill 224 people and injure over 4,500; they are linked to terrorist Osama Bin Laden, an exile of Saudi Arabia."
1998,"August 19","1998 Russian financial crisis: Russia defaults on the state short-term bonds, and devalues the ruble. The ruble loses 70% of its value against U.S. dollar in the next 6 months. Several of the largest Russians banks collapse, and millions of people lose their savings."
1998,"August 20","1998 U.S. embassy bombings: The United States military launches cruise missile attacks against alleged Al-Qaeda camps in Afghanistan and a suspected chemical plant in Sudan in retaliation for the August 7 bombings of American embassies in Kenya and Tanzania. The al-Shifa pharmaceutical factory in Khartoum is destroyed in the attack."
1998,"September 15","Telecommunications companies MCI Communications and WorldCom complete their $37 billion merger to form MCI WorldCom."
1998,"September 27","In Germany, SPD's Gerhard Schröder defeats 4-term CDU Chancellor Helmut Kohl."
1998,"October 27","Germany: New Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and his liberal SPD-Green coalition takes office."
1998,"October 28","An Air China jetliner is hijacked by disgruntled pilot Yuan Bin and flown to Taiwan. After landing the plane safely, Yuan Bin is arrested."
1998,"October 29","In Gothenburg, Sweden, 2 arsonists burn down a local Macedonian Society disco, killing 63 and injuring 200, most of them children of refugees."
1998,"November 9","In the largest civil settlement in United States history, a federal judge approves a US$1.03 billion settlement requiring dozens of brokerage houses (including Merrill Lynch, Goldman Sachs, and Salomon Smith Barney) to pay investors who claim they were cheated in a widespread price-fixing scheme on the NASDAQ."
1998,"November 20","Galina Starovoitova, Russian legislator and democracy advocate, is assassinated in Saint Petersburg, Russia."
1998,"November 26","Japan and China sign the Japan-China Joint Declaration On Building a Partnership of Friendship and Cooperation for Peace and Development."
1998,"December 19","Lewinsky scandal: Bill Clinton is impeached by the United States House of Representatives. (He was later acquitted of any wrongdoing.)"
1998,"December 21","Iraq disarmament crisis: UN Security Council members France, Germany and Russia call for sanctions to end against Iraq. The 3 Security Council members also call for UNSCOM to either be disbanded or for its role to be recast. The U.S. says it will veto any such proposal."
1999,"January 6","Dennis Hastert becomes Speaker of the United States House of Representatives."
1999,"January 11","Bülent Ecevit, of DSP forms the new government of Turkey (56th government, an interim government )"
1999,"January 20","The China News Service announces new government restrictions on Internet use aimed especially at Internet cafes."
1999,"January 21","In one of the largest drug busts in American history, the United States Coast Guard intercepts a ship with over 9,500 pounds (4.3 tons) of cocaine aboard, headed for Houston, Texas."
1999,"February 16","Across Europe, Kurdish rebels take over embassies and hold hostages after Turkey arrests one of their rebel leaders."
1999,"February 23","Kurdish rebel leader Abdullah Öcalan is charged with treason in Ankara, Turkey."
1999,"February 23","An avalanche destroys the village of Galtür, Austria, killing 31."
1999,"February 24","LaGrand Case: The State of Arizona executes Karl LaGrand, a German national involved in an armed robbery that led to a death. Karl's brother Walter is executed a week later, in spite of Germany's legal action in the International Court of Justice to attempt to save him."
1999,"March 4","In a military court, United States Marine Corps Captain Richard J. Ashby is acquitted of the charge of reckless flying which resulted in the deaths of 20 skiers in the Italian Alps, when his low-flying jet hit a gondola cable."
1999,"April 5","Two Libyans suspected of bringing down Pan Am flight 103 in 1988 are handed over to Scottish authorities for eventual trial in the Netherlands. The United Nations suspends sanctions against Libya."
1999,"April 7","A bomb explodes at the Valley of the Fallen Church in Spain; GRAPO claims responsibility."
1999,"May 13","Carlo Azeglio Ciampi is elected President of Italy."
1999,"May 27","The International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia in The Hague, Netherlands indicts Slobodan Miloevic and four others for war crimes and crimes against humanity committed in Kosovo."
1999,"May 28","Bülent Ecevit, of DSP forms the new government of Turkey (57th government, coalition partners MHP and ANAP) This is Ecevit's fifth and last term."
1999,"May 28","After 22 years of restoration work, Leonardo de Vinci's [i]The Last Supper[/i] is placed back on display in Milan, Italy."
1999,"June 12","Texas Governor George W. Bush announces he will seek the Republican Party nomination for President of the United States."
1999,"June 19","Turin, Italy is awarded the 2006 Winter Olympics."
1999,"July 20","Falun Gong is banned in the People's Republic of China under Jiang Zemin."
1999,"August 7","Hundreds of Chechen guerrillas invade the Russian republic of Dagestan, triggering a short war."
1999,"August 9","Russian President Boris Yeltsin fires his Prime Minister, Sergei Stepashin, and for the fourth time fires his entire cabinet."
1999,"October 1","Pudong International Airport opens in Shanghai, China, taking over all international flights to Hongqiao."
1999,"October 12","World population reaches 6 billion people, as the 6 billionth person (according to the UN) is born in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina."
1999,"October 13","The United States Senate rejects ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT)."
1999,"November 12","A 7.2-magnitude earthquake strikes Duzce and northwestern Turkey, killing 845 and injuring 4,948."
1999,"December 20","The sovereignty of Macau is transferred from the Portuguese Republic to the People's Republic of China after 422 years of Portuguese rule."
1999,"December 31","Boris Yeltsin resigns as President of Russia, leaving Prime Minister Vladimir Putin as the acting President."
2000,"circa","World Population: ~6,080,000,000."
2000,"March 7","George W. Bush and Al Gore emerge victorious in the Republican and Democratic caucuses and primaries of the United States presidential election."
2000,"March 26","Vladimir Putin is elected President of Russia."
2000,"April 3","[i]United States v. Microsoft[/i]: Microsoft is ruled to have violated United States antitrust laws by keeping ""an oppressive thumb"" on its competitors."
2000,"May 13","A fireworks factory disaster in Enschede Netherlands, kills 23."
2000,"May 16","The Grand National Assembly of Turkey elects Ahmet Necdet Sezer as the tenth President of Turkey."
2000,"July 22","[i]News of the World[/i] urges its readers to sign a petition for Sarah's Law, new legislation in response to the murder of Sarah Payne, which would give parents the right to know whether a convicted paedophile was living in their area."
2000,"July 25","Air France Flight 4590, a Concorde aircraft, crashes into a hotel in Gonesse just after takeoff from Paris, killing all 109 aboard and 4 in the hotel."
2000,"August 3","Rioting erupts on the Paulsgrove estate in Portsmouth, Hampshire, England, after more than 100 people besiege the home of a block of flats allegedly housing a convicted paedophile. This is the latest vigilante violence against suspected sex offenders since the beginning of the ""naming and shaming"" anti-paedophile campaign by the tabloid newspaper [i]News of the World[/i]."
2000,"August 12","The [i]Russian submarine K-141 Kursk[/i] sinks in the Barents Sea, resulting in the deaths of all 118 men on board."
2000,"August 14","Tsar Nicholas II and his family are canonized by the synod of the Russian Orthodox Church."
2000,"September 6","(September 6 - September 8) World leaders attend the Millennium Summit at UN Headquarters."
2000,"September 8","Albania officially joins the World Trade Organization."
2000,"September 26","Anti-globalization protests in Prague (some 15,000 protesters) turn violent during the IMF and World Bank summits."
2000,"October 12","In Aden, Yemen, the [i]USS Cole[/i] is badly damaged by two Al-Qaeda suicide bombers, who place a small boat laden with explosives alongside the United States Navy destroyer, killing 17 crew members and wounding at least 39."
2000,"October 22","The [i]Mainichi Shinbun[/i] newspaper exposes Japanese archeologist Shinichi Fujimura as a fraud; Japanese archaeologists had based their treatises on his findings."
2000,"November 7","United States presidential election, 2000: Republican candidate Texas Governor George W. Bush defeats Democratic Vice President Al Gore in one of the closest elections in history, but the final outcome is not known for over a month because of disputed votes in Florida."
2000,"November 11","Kaprun disaster, Austria: A cable car fire in an Alpine tunnel kills 155 skiers and snowboarders."
2000,"December 25","A shopping center fire at Luoyang, Henan, China kills 309."
2001,"January 20","George W. Bush succeeds Bill Clinton, becoming the 43rd President of the United States."
2001,"February 9","The submarine USS [i]Greeneville[/i] accidentally strikes and sinks the Japanese fishing vessel [i]Ehime-Maru[/i] near Hawaii."
2001,"February 18","FBI agent Robert Hanssen is arrested and charged with spying for Russia for 15 years."
2001,"March 23","The Russian space station Mir re-enters the atmosphere near Nadi, Fiji, and falls into the Pacific Ocean."
2001,"April 1","Hainan Island incident: A Chinese fighter jet bumps into a U.S. EP-3E surveillance aircraft, which is forced to make an emergency landing in Hainan, China. The U.S. crew is detained for 10 days and the F-8 Chinese pilot, Wang Wei, goes missing and is presumed dead."
2001,"April 26","Junichiro Koizumi becomes Prime Minister of Japan."
2001,"May 22","(May 22 - May 23) The Bahá'í Terraces officially open on Mount Carmel in Haifa, Israel (site of the Shrine of the Báb and the Bahá'í World Centre)."
2001,"July 3","A Vladivostokavia Tupolev Tu-154 jetliner crashes on approach to landing at Irkutsk, Russia, killing 145."
2001,"July 16","The People's Republic of China and the Russian Federation sign the Treaty of Good-Neighborliness and Friendly Cooperation."
2001,"July 20","(July 20 - July 22) The 27th G8 summit takes place in Genoa, Italy. Massive demonstrations are held against the meeting by anti-globalisation groups. One demonstrator, Carlo Giuliani, is shot dead by a carabiniere. Several others are badly injured during a police attack on a school used by the protesters as their headquarters."
2001,"September 6","[i]United States v. Microsoft[/i]: The United States Justice Department announces that it no longer seeks to break up software maker Microsoft, and will instead seek a lesser antitrust penalty."
2001,"September 11","Almost 3,000 are killed in the September 11, 2001 attacks at the World Trade Center in New York City; the Pentagon in Arlington, Virginia; and in rural Shanksville, Pennsylvania after American Airlines Flight 11 and United Airlines Flight 175 crash into the World Trade Center's Twin Towers, American Airlines Flight 77 crashes into the Pentagon, and United Airlines Flight 93 crashes into grassland in Shanksville."
2001,"September 21","The AZote Fertilisant chemical factory in Toulouse, France explodes, killing 29 and seriously wounding over 2,500."
2001,"October 4","Siberia Airlines Flight 1812 crashes over the Black Sea en route from Tel Aviv, Israel to Novosibirsk, Russia; 78 are killed."
2001,"October 7","War in Afghanistan (2001-present): The United States invades Afghanistan, with participation from other nations."
2001,"November 10","The People's Republic of China is admitted to the World Trade Organization after 15 years of negotiations."
2001,"November 13","Doha Round: The World Trade Organization ends a 4-day ministerial conference in Doha, Qatar."
2001,"December 11","The United States government indicts Zacarias Moussaoui for involvement in the September 11, 2001 attacks."
2001,"December 13","U.S. President George W. Bush announces the United States' withdrawal from the 1972 Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty."
2001,"December 27","The People's Republic of China is granted permanent normal trade status with the United States."
2002,"January 1","Euro notes and coins are issued in France, Spain, Germany, Italy, Portugal, Greece, Finland, Luxembourg, Belgium, Austria, Ireland and the Netherlands."
2002,"January 9","The United States Department of Justice announces it will pursue a criminal investigation of Enron."
2002,"February 12","The U.S. Secretary of Energy makes the decision that Yucca Mountain is suitable to be the United States' nuclear repository."
2002,"March 1","The Peseta is discontinued as the official currency of Spain and is replaced with the euro."
2002,"March 6","France agrees to return the remains of Saartjie Baartman to South Africa."
2002,"April 15","An Air China Boeing 767-200 crashes into a hillside during heavy rain and fog near Pusan, South Korea, killing 128."
2002,"May 6","In the Netherlands, politician Pim Fortuyn is assassinated."
2002,"May 9","In Kaspiysk, Russia, a remote-control bomb explodes during a holiday parade, killing 43 and injuring at least 130."
2002,"May 12","The Russian Shuttle [i]Buran[/i] is destroyed in the Buran hangar collapse, killing 8 workers."
2002,"May 25","China Airlines Flight 611 disintegrates near the Penghu Islands at Taiwan Strait, killing all 225 people on board."
2002,"July 1","A Russian passenger jet (Flight 2937) and a cargo plane collide over the town of Überlingen, Germany; 72 are killed."
2002,"July 21","Telecommunications giant WorldCom files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection (the largest such filing in United States history)."
2002,"September 2","The United Nations World Summit on Sustainable Development, successor of the 1972 Conference on the Human Environment, 1983 World Commission on Environment and Development, and the 1992 Conference on Environment and Development, opens."
2002,"September 11","The World Summit on Sustainable Development comes to a close."
2002,"September 25","The Vitim event, a possible bolide impact, occurs in Siberia, Russia."
2002,"October 2","The Congress of the United States passes a joint resolution, which authorizes the President to use the United States Armed Forces as he deems necessary and appropriate, against Iraq."
2002,"November 5","The U.S. Republican Party maintains control of the House of Representatives and gains control of the United States Senate."
2002,"November 7","Iran bans the advertising of United States products."
2002,"November 14","Argentina defaults on a US $805 million World Bank loan payment."
2002,"November 15","Hu Jintao becomes General Secretary of the Communist Party of China."
2002,"November 16","A Campaign against Climate Change march takes place in London from Lincoln's Inn Fields, past Esso offices to the United States Embassy."
2002,"November 22","In Nigeria, more than 100 are killed at an attack aimed at the Miss World contestants."
2003,"January 3","The 108th United States Congress is sworn in, including incoming freshmen Senators Saxby Chambliss (R-GA), Lindsey Graham (R-SC), John Sununu (R-NH), Lamar Alexander (R-TN), Elizabeth Dole (R-NC), Norm Coleman (R-MN), and Mark Pryor (D-AR)."
2003,"January 15","[i]Eldred v. Ashcroft[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States allows the extension of copyright terms in the U.S."
2003,"January 24","The new United States Department of Homeland Security begins operation."
2003,"February 9","The Cricket World Cup begins in South Africa."
2003,"March 15","Hu Jintao becomes President of the People's Republic of China, replacing Jiang Zemin."
2003,"March 23","The 2003 Cricket World Cup ends as Australia beats India by 125 runs in Johannesburg, South Africa."
2003,"April 29","The United States announces the withdrawal of troops stationed in Saudi Arabia, and the redeployment of some at the Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar."
2003,"May 15","The date predicted by Pana-Wave Laboratory, a Japanese cult, on which a close encounter with an unknown planet would result in the extinction of most of humankind."
2003,"May 21","F.C. Porto defeats Celtic 3-2 (AET) in the UEFA Cup Final in Seville, Spain."
2003,"May 24","Sertab Erener wins the Eurovision Song Contest 2003 for Turkey with the song [i]Every Way That I Can[/i], in Riga, Latvia."
2003,"May 25","After docking in Miami at 05:00, the [i]SS Norway[/i] (old [i]SS France[/i]) is severely damaged by a boiler explosion at 06:30, that kills 7, and injures 17 crew members. A few weeks later it is announced by NCL that she will never sail again as a commercial ocean liner."
2003,"June 1","The 29th G8 summit opens in Évian-les-Bains, France, to tight security and tens of thousands of protesters."
2003,"June 1","The People's Republic of China begins filling the lake behind the massive Three Gorges Dam, raising the water level near the dam over 100 metres."
2003,"June 23","[i]Grutter v. Bollinger[/i]: The Supreme Court of the United States upholds affirmative action in university admissions."
2003,"July 7","Corsica voters reject a referendum for increased autonomy from France by a very narrow margin."
2003,"August 1","A suicide bomber rams a truck filled with explosives into a military hospital near Chechnya, killing 50 people, including Russian troops wounded in Chechnya."
2003,"August 14","A widespread power outage affects the northeastern United States and South-Central Canada."
2003,"September 14","Sweden rejects adopting the Euro in a referendum."
2003,"September 28","A power failure affects all of Italy except Sardinia, cutting service to more than 56 million people."
2003,"October 12","Michael Schumacher wins the 2003 FIA Formula One World Championship in Suzuka, Japan, beating Kimi Räikkönen to the title."
2003,"October 25","The Florida Marlins defeat the New York Yankees to win their second World Series title."
2003,"November 15","Two car bombs explode simultaneously in Istanbul, Turkey, targeting 2 synagogues, killing at least 25 people and wounding more than 300; Al-Qaida claims responsibility."
2003,"November 20","Several bombs explode in Istanbul, Turkey, destroying the Turkish head office of HSBC and the British consulate."
2003,"November 22","2003 Rugby World Cup: England defeats Australia 20-17 after extra time."
2003,"November 28","Kalev Ots succeeds to the presidency of the pre-World War II Republic of Estonia in exile, after the death of Mihkel Mathiesen."
2003,"December 5","A suicide bombing on a commuter train in southern Russia kills 44 people. President Vladimir Putin condemns the attack as a bid to destabilize the country 2 days before parliamentary elections."
2003,"December 7","Parliamentary elections are held in Russia."
2003,"December 7","The new Government in Exile of the pre-World War II Republic of Estonia, headed by Ahti Mänd, assumes office."
2003,"December 23","A PetroChina Chuandongbei natural gas field explosion in Guoqiao, Kai County, Chongqing, China kills 234."
2003,"December 24","A BSE (mad cow disease) outbreak in Washington State is announced. Several countries including Brazil, Australia and Taiwan ban the import of beef from the United States."
2003,"December 24","At the request of the U.S. Embassy in Paris, the French Government orders Air France to cancel several flights between France and the U.S. in response to terrorist concerns."
2004,"February 2","An 11-story apartment building collapses in Konya, Turkey, killing more than 90 residents."
2004,"February 26","The United States lifts a 23-year travel ban against Libya."
2004,"March 14","Russian presidential election, 2004: Vladimir Putin easily wins a second term."
2004,"March 15","The new Spanish Government announces that it will withdraw Spain's 1,300 troops in Iraq."
2004,"March 20","President Chen Shui-bian wins the Taiwanese presidential election by 0.2% of the vote. The day before, he and Vice President Annette Lu were shot. Lien Chan refuses to concede and demands a recount. A controversial peace referendum opposed by the People's Republic of China is invalidated."
2004,"March 28","In France, the government of prime minister Jean-Pierre Raffarin suffers a stunning and unprecedented defeat in regional elections."
2004,"April 5","Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom begins a state visit to France to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the Entente Cordiale."
2004,"April 22","The last coal mine in France closes, ending nearly 300 years of coal mining."
2004,"May 9","Chechen president Akhmad Kadyrov is killed by a landmine placed under a VIP stage during a World War II memorial parade in Grozny."
2004,"May 9","Canada wins the World Ice Hockey Championship in Prague."
2004,"May 15","South Africa is awarded the 2010 FIFA World Cup."
2004,"May 15","Ruslana wins the Eurovision Song Contest 2004 for Ukraine, with the song [i]Wild Dances[/i] in Istanbul, Turkey."
2004,"May 23","Japanese prime minister Junichiro Koizumi visits North Korea, to secure the release of the families of the 9 abducted Japanese citizens returned earlier."
2004,"May 29","The National World War II Memorial is dedicated in Washington, DC."
2004,"June 1","Sasebo slashing: Satomi Mitarai, a 12-year-old Japanese schoolgirl attending Okubo Elementary School in Sasebo, Japan, is murdered. Her killer is an 11-year-old classmate identified by Japanese authorities as ""Girl A""."
2004,"June 8","The pickled heart of Louis XVII of France is buried in the royal crypt at Saint-Denis."
2004,"June 16","The National Commission on Terrorist Attacks Upon the United States (or ""9/11 Commission"") issues an initial report of its findings."
2004,"July 25","Lance Armstrong of Austin, Texas wins an unprecedented 6th consecutive Tour de France cycling title."
2004,"August 2","Monday demonstrations against social cutbacks began in Germany."
2004,"August 9","At the Mihama Nuclear Power Plant, a pipe leaking hot water and steam kills 5 and injures 6 others, in the 2nd worst nuclear disaster in Japan."
2004,"August 13","Hurricane Charley kills 27 people in Florida, after killing 4 in Cuba and 1 in Jamaica. Charley makes landfall near Cayo Costa, FL as a Category 4 hurricane. Charley is the most intense hurricane to strike the United States since Hurricane Andrew in 1992."
2004,"August 24","Two airliners in Russia, carrying a total of 89 passengers, crash within minutes of each other after flying out of Domodedovo International Airport, leaving no survivors. Authorities suspect suicide attacks by rebels from Chechnya to be the cause of the crashes."
2004,"August 31","A woman commits a suicide attack near a subway station in northern Moscow, Russia, killing at least 10 people and injuring at least 50. Authorities hold Chechen rebels responsible."
2004,"September 1","Chechen terrorists take between 1,000 and 1,500 people hostage, mostly children, in a school in the Beslan school hostage crisis. The hostage-takers demand the release of Chechen rebels imprisoned in neighbouring Ingushetia and the independence of Chechnya from Russia."
2004,"September 3","Russian forces end the siege at a school in Beslan, Northern Ossetia. At least 335 people (among which are 32 of the approximately 40 hostage-takers) are killed and at least 700 people injured."
2004,"September 3","Hurricane Frances makes landfall in Florida. After killing 2 people in the Bahamas, Hurricane Frances kills 10 people in Florida, 2 in Georgia and 1 in South Carolina."
2004,"September 9","Typhoon Songda hits western Japan, killing 45 and injuring another 1,352."
2004,"September 17","Mexico and Japan finish 2-year-long negotiations and sign a Free Trade Agreement in Mexico City."
2004,"September 25","Hurricane Jeanne makes landfall near Port Saint Lucie, Florida, near the location Hurricane Frances hit 2 weeks earlier. Jeanne kills over 3,030, mostly in Haiti."
2004,"October 21","Typhoon Tokage kill 98, injured 552 in western Japan."
2004,"October 23","A Magnitude 6.7 earthquake and aftershocks of similar scale occur in the Tokamachi area. A huge landslide occurs on the outskirts of Nagaoka. According to Japanese officials, 68 people are killed, 4,085 are injured, and 103,000 are rendered homeless."
2004,"October 24","Michael Schumacher wins his 7th Formula One World Drivers Championship (5th consecutive), making him the most successful driver in the history of Formula One."
2004,"November 2","Dutch film maker Theo van Gogh is assassinated in Amsterdam, Netherlands by Mohammed Bouyeri."
2004,"November 14","United States Secretary of State Colin Powell submits his resignation. He is replaced by Condoleezza Rice after her confirmation by the United States Congress."
2004,"November 16","The People's Republic of China agrees to invest $20 billion dollars in Argentina, a deal signed days before the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation forum to be held in Santiago, Chile."
2004,"November 28","An coal mine explosion in China kills over 150."
2004,"December 3","The Colombian government extradites Gilberto Rodríguez Orejuela, one of the most powerful drug dealers in the world, arrested in 1995 and 2003, to the United States."
2004,"December 14","The world's tallest bridge, the Millau bridge over the River Tarn in the Massif Central mountains, France, is opened by President Jacques Chirac."
2004,"December 31","Simón Trinidad, high-profile FARC leader, is extradited to the United States, following the second extradition of a high drug dealer in a month and in 2004."
2005,"January 20","George W. Bush is inaugurated in Washington, D.C. for his second term as the 43rd President of the United States."
2005,"February 10","North Korea announces that it possesses nuclear weapons as a protection against the hostility it feels from the United States."
2005,"February 16","The Kyoto Protocol goes into effect, without the support of the United States and Australia."
2005,"March 14","The People's Republic of China ratifies an anti-secession law, aimed at preventing Taiwan from declaring independence."
2005,"March 26","The Taiwanese government calls on 1 million Taiwanese to demonstrate in Taipei, in opposition to the Anti-Secession Law of the People's Republic of China. Between 200,000 and 300,000 attend the walk."
2005,"April 8","A referendum is held in Curaçao on independence vs. integration with the Netherlands."
2005,"April 20","An earthquake (5.8 on the Richter scale) hits Fukuoka and Kasuga, Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan, injuring 56."
2005,"April 25","Amagasaki rail crash: A passenger train derails in Amagasaki Hyogo Prefecture, Japan, killing 104 people and injuring at least another 450."
2005,"May 16","George Galloway appears before a United States Senate committee, to answer allegations of making money from the Iraqi Oil-for-Food Programme."
2005,"July 4","The Italy-USA Foundation is established in Rome, Italy."
2005,"September 11","Japan general election, 2005: Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi and the Liberal Democratic Party are returned to power."
2005,"September 14","(September 14 - September 16) The largest UN World Summit in history is held in New York City."
2005,"October 1","The world's largest bank, Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group, is formed by the merger of 2 Japanese banking conglomerates."
2006,"January 1","Russia cuts natural gas to Ukraine over a price dispute."
2006,"February 10","(February 10 - February 26) The 2006 Winter Olympics are held in Turin, Italy."
2006,"April 20","Iran announces a deal with Russia, involving a joint uranium enrichment firm on Russian soil; 9 days later Iran announces that it will not move all activity to Russia, thus leading to a de-facto termination of the deal."
2006,"June 9","(June 9 - July 9) The 2006 FIFA World Cup is held in Germany."
2006,"July 6","The Nathula Pass between India and China, sealed during the Sino-Indian War, re-opens for trade after 44 years."
2006,"August 22","Pulkovo Airlines Flight 612 crashes near the Russian border in Ukraine, killing 171 people, including 45 children."
2007,"January 3","China conducts an anti-terror raid in Xinjiang."
2007,"January 8","Russian oil supplies to Poland, Germany, and Ukraine are cut as the Russia-Belarus energy dispute escalates; they are restored 3 days later."
2007,"February 27","The Chinese Correction: World stock markets plummet after China and Europe release less-than-expected growth reports."
2007,"March 27","Prime Minister of Latvia Aigars Kalvitis and Prime minister of Russia Mikhail Fradkov finally sign a border treaty between Latvia and Russia."
2007,"May 17","The Russian Orthodox Church Abroad and the Moscow Patriarchate re-unite after 80 years of schism."
2007,"June 1","A 2,100-year-old melon is discovered by archaeologists in western Japan."
2007,"August 17","Vladimir Putin issues a statement, revealing that Russia is to resume the flight exercises of its strategic bombers in remote areas. The flights were suspended in 1991 after the Collapse of the Soviet Union."
2007,"October 31","The World Economic Forum releases The Global Competitiveness Report 2007-2008."
2007,"December 19","Vladimir Putin, President of Russia, is announced as Time magazine's 2007 Person of the Year."
2008,"January 3","A car bomb detonates, killing at least 4 and injuring 68, in Diyarbakir, Turkey. Police blame Kurdish rebels."
2008,"January 15","The Federal Court of Australia orders a Japanese whaling company to stop research whaling within their Exclusive Economic Zone."
2008,"January 22","Russia stages the largest naval exercise since the fall of the Soviet Union in the Bay of Biscay. The Russian aircraft carrier Admiral Kuznetsov, along with 11 support vessels and 47 long-range bomber aircraft, practises strike tactics off the coast of France and Spain, and test-launches nuclear-capable missiles in foreign waters."
2008,"January 25","China's worst snowstorm since 1954 kills 133, delays traffic, and causes massive power outages in central and southern parts of the country."
2008,"February 5","(February 5 - February 6) A tornado outbreak, the deadliest in 23 years, kills 58 in the Southern United States."
2008,"February 12","Bridgestone, under investigation for an alleged price-fixing cartel, uncovers improper payments of at least 150 million Japanese yen to foreign governments and withdraws from the marine hose business."
2008,"February 20","The United States Navy destroys a spy satellite containing toxic fuel, by shooting it down with a missile launched from the [i]USS Lake Erie[/i] in the Pacific Ocean."
2008,"May 7","Dmitry Medvedev takes office as President of Russia, replacing Vladimir Putin."
2008,"May 12","Over 69,000 are killed in central south-west China by the Wenchuan quake, an earthquake measuring 7.9 Moment magnitude scale. The epicenter is 90 kilometers (55 miles) west-northwest of the provincial capital Chengdu, Sichuan province."
2008,"June 8","In the Akihabara area of Tokyo, Japan, a 25-year-old man stabs seven to death and wounds 10, before being arrested."
2008,"June 14","A 6.9 magnitude earthquake in Iwate Prefecture, Japan, kills 12 and injures more than 400."
2008,"June 14","(June 14 - September 14) Expo 2008 is held in Zaragoza, Spain, with the topic of [i]""Water and sustainable development""[/i]."
2008,"July 7","(July 7 - July 9) The 34th G8 summit is held in Toyako, Hokkaido, Japan."
2008,"July 15","(July 15 - July 20) World Youth Day takes place in Sydney, Australia. Pope Benedict XVI appears at the event."
2008,"August 1","A total eclipse of the Sun is visible from Canada and extends across northern Greenland, the Arctic, central Russia, Mongolia, and China."
2008,"August 4","Two members of the East Turkestan Islamic Movement, which had threatened to attack the Beijing Olympics, kill 16 and injure another 16 officers at a police station in Kashgar, Xinjiang, China."
2008,"August 7","The 2008 South Ossetia war begins, as Georgia and Russia launch a major offensive inside the separatist region of South Ossetia after days of border skirmishes between the two sides."
2008,"August 8","(August 8 - August 24) The 2008 Summer Olympics take place in Beijing, China."
2008,"August 22","Pirates hijack German, Iranian, and Japanese cargo ships off the coast of Somalia, in seven such attacks since June 20."
2008,"August 26","Russia unilaterally recognizes the independence of Georgian breakaway republics Abkhazia and South Ossetia."
2008,"August 26","(August 26 - September 1) Hurricane Gustav makes landfall on Louisiana as Category 2 and kills seven in the United States, after making landfall on western Cuba as Category 4, and killing 66 in Haiti, eight in the Dominican Republic, and 11 in Jamaica."
2008,"August 28","(August 28 - September 7) Hurricane Hanna kills seven in the United States, and 529 in Haiti, mostly due to floods and mudslides."
2008,"September 1","(September 1 - September 14) Hurricane Ike makes landfall on Texas as Category 2 and kills 27 in the United States, after killing four in Cuba, one in the Dominican Republic, and 75 in Haiti."
2008,"September 2","Prime Minister of Japan Yasuo Fukuda resigns, less than a year after taking office following Shinzo Abe's resignation."
2008,"September 14","Aeroflot Flight 821 crashes near the city of Perm, Russia, killing all 88 on board."
2008,"September 19","(September 19 - September 25) Typhoon Hagupit kills 17 in China, eight in the Philippines, one in Taiwan, and 41 in Vietnam."
2008,"September 24","The Diet of Japan elects Taro Aso as the new Prime Minister of Japan."
2008,"October 7","Global financial crisis: Russia agrees to provide Iceland with a four-billion-euro loan."
2008,"October 17","The United Nations General Assembly elects Turkey, Austria, Japan, Uganda, and Mexico to two-year terms on the Security Council."
2008,"October 29","Global financial crisis: Hungary's currency and stock markets rise on the news that it will receive an international economic bailout package worth $25 billion from the IMF, European Union, and World Bank."
2008,"November 8","An accident aboard Russian submarine K-152 Nerpa kills 20."
2008,"November 25","A car bomb in St. Petersburg, Russia, kills three people and injures one."
2009,"January 1","Austria, Japan, Mexico, Turkey, and Uganda assume their seats on the United Nations Security Council."
2009,"January 1","The Czech Republic takes over the presidency of the Council of the European Union from France."
2009,"January 7","Russia shuts off all gas supplies to Europe through Ukraine. Prime Minister Vladimir Putin publicly endorses the move and urges greater international involvement in the energy dispute."
2009,"February 1","Patriarch Kirill I of Moscow is enthroned as the Patriarch of the Russian Orthodox Church."
2009,"February 10","A Russian and an American satellite collide over Siberia, creating a large amount of space debris."
2009,"April 6","A 6.3 magnitude earthquake strikes near L'Aquila, Italy, killing nearly 300 and injuring more than 1,500."
2009,"April 17","Thirty-four heads of state and government meet in Port of Spain, Trinidad for the 5th Summit of the Americas."
2009,"April 21","UNESCO launches The World Digital Library."
2009,"April 24","The World Health Organization expresses concern at the spread of influenza from Mexico and the United States to other countries. International cases and resulting deaths are confirmed."
2009,"April 29","Amidst Russia's effort to improve relations with NATO and with the West in general, NATO expels two Russian diplomats from NATO headquarters in Brussels over a spy scandal in Estonia. Russia's Foreign Ministry criticises the expulsions."
2009,"June 1","Air France Flight 447, en route from Rio de Janeiro, Brazil to Paris, crashes into the Atlantic Ocean, killing all 228 on board."
2009,"July 1","Sweden assumes the presidency of the European Union."
2009,"September 10","British Prime Minister Gordon Brown issues an official apology on behalf of the British government for the treatment of Alan Turing following World War II."
2010,"January 1","Spain takes over the Presidency of the Council of the European Union from Sweden."
2010,"March 16","The Kasubi Tombs, Uganda's only cultural World Heritage Site, are destroyed by fire."
2010,"April 10","The President of Poland, Lech Kaczynski, is among 96 killed when their airplane crashes in western Russia."
2010,"April 13","A 6.9-magnitude earthquake occurs in Qinghai, China, killing at least 2,000 and injuring more than 10,000."
2010,"May 1","(May 1 - October 31) The 2010 World Expo is held in Shanghai."
2010,"June 11","(June 11 - July 11) 2010 FIFA World Cup is held in South Africa."
2010,"July 1","Belgium takes over the Presidency of the Council of the European Union from Spain."
2010,"July 25","Wikileaks, an international organization based in Sweden, leaks over 90,000 internal reports about the United States-led involvement in the War in Afghanistan from 2004-2010 as public information."
2010,"August 10","The World Health Organization declares the H1N1 influenza pandemic over, saying worldwide flu activity has returned to typical seasonal patterns."
2010,"October 10","The Netherlands Antilles are dissolved and the islands are split up into a new constitutional status."
2010,"November 29","The European Union agree to an 85 billion rescue deal for Ireland from the European Financial Stability Facility, the International Monetary Fund and bilateral loans from the United Kingdom, Denmark and Sweden."
2011,"January 24","At least 36 people are killed and more than 100 others wounded in a bombing at Domodedovo International Airport in Moscow, Russia."
2011,"March 11","A 9.1-magnitude earthquake and subsequent tsunami hit eastern Japan, killing over 15,000 and leaving another 9,000 missing. Tsunami warnings are issued in 50 countries and territories. Emergencies are declared at four nuclear power plants affected by the quake."
2011,"May 20","2 are killed and 16 injured following an explosion at major electronic components manufacturer, Foxconn, in Chengdu, China."
2011,"June 12","Arab Spring: Thousands of Syrians flee to Turkey as Syrian troops lay siege to Jisr ash-Shugur."
2011,"July 31","In Thailand over 12.8 million people are affected by severe flooding. The World Bank estimates damages at 1,440 billion baht (US $45 billion)."
2011,"September 17","Occupy Wall Street protests begin in the United States. This develops into the Occupy movement which spreads to 82 countries by October."
2011,"October 23","A magnitude 7.2 Mw earthquake jolted eastern Turkey near the city of Van, killing 604 people, and damaging about 2,200 buildings."
2011,"December 15","The United States formally declares an end to the Iraq War."
2012,"February 19","Iran suspends oil exports to Britain and France following sanctions put in place by the European Union and the United States in January."
2012,"April 13","Kwangmyongsong-3, a North Korean Earth observation satellite, explodes shortly after launch. The United States and other countries had called the impending launch a violation of United Nations Security Council demands."
2012,"May 12","(May 12 - August 12) The 2012 World Expo takes place in Yeosu, South Korea."
2012,"September 11","(September 11 - September 27) A series of terrorist attacks are directed against United States diplomatic missions worldwide, as well as diplomatic missions of Germany, Switzerland and the United Kingdom. In the US, opinions are divided over whether the attacks are a reaction to a YouTube trailer for the film Innocence of Muslims. In Libya, among the dead is US ambassador J. Christopher Stevens."
2012,"October 24","(October 24 - October 30) Hurricane Sandy kills at least 209 people in the Caribbean, Bahamas, United States and Canada. Considerable storm surge damage causes major disruption to the eastern seaboard of the United States."
2013,"February 15","A meteor explodes over the Russian city of Chelyabinsk, injuring 1,491 people and damaging over 4,300 buildings. It is the most powerful meteor to strike Earth's atmosphere in over a century. The incident, along with a coincidental flyby of a larger asteroid, prompts international concern regarding the vulnerability of the planet to meteor strikes."
2013,"April 15","Two Chechen Islamist brothers explode two bombs at the Boston Marathon in Boston, Massachusetts, in the United States, killing 3 and injuring 264 others."
2013,"June 6","American Edward Snowden discloses operations engaged in by a U.S. government mass surveillance program to news publications and flees the country, later being granted temporary asylum in Russia."
2013,"November 21","Euromaidan pro-EU demonstrations begin in Ukraine after President Viktor Yanukovych rejects an economic association agreement between the European Union and Ukraine in favor of closer ties to Russia."
2013,"December 7","Ninth Ministerial Conference of the World Trade Organization delegates sign the Bali Package agreement aimed at loosening global trade barriers."
2014,"February 7","(February 7 - February 23) The XXII Olympic Winter Games are held in Sochi, Russia."
2014,"March 21","Russia formally annexes Crimea after President Vladimir Putin signed a bill finalizing the annexation process."
2014,"March 24","During an emergency meeting, the United Kingdom, the United States, Italy, Germany, France, Japan, and Canada temporarily suspend Russia from the G8."
2014,"March 31","The United Nations International Court of Justice rules that Japan's Antarctic whaling program is not scientific but commercial and forbids grants of further permits."
2014,"April 10","In response to the 2014 Crimean crisis, the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) passes a resolution to temporarily strip Russia of its voting rights; its rights to be represented in the Bureau of the Assembly, the PACE Presidential Committee, and the PACE Standing Committee; and its right to participate in election-observation missions."
2014,"April 18","United States President Barack Obama's new economic sanctions against Russia go into effect, targeting companies and individuals close to Russian President Vladimir Putin."
2014,"May 5","The World Health Organization identifies the spread of poliomyelitis in at least 10 countries as a major worldwide health emergency."
2014,"May 13","A coal mine explosion and fire kills 301 miners in Turkey's deadliest mine disaster."
2014,"June 12","(June 12 - July 13) The 2014 FIFA World Cup is held in Brazil, and is won by Germany."
2014,"June 19","King Juan Carlos I of Spain abdicates in favor of his son, who ascends the Spanish throne as King Felipe VI."
2014,"August 8","The United States military begins an air campaign in northern Iraq to stem the influx of ISIS militants."
2014,"September 22","The United States and several Arab partners begin their airstrike campaign in Syria."
2014,"September 26","The 2014 World Summit of Nobel Peace Laureates, to be held in Cape Town from 13 to 15 October, is suspended after a boycott of Nobel Laureates to protest the third time refusal of a visa to the 14th Dalai Lama by a South African Government ""kowtowing to China""."
2015,"January 1","The Eurasian Economic Union comes into effect, creating a political and economic union between Russia, Belarus, Armenia, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan."
2015,"April 25","A major earthquake in Nepal, measuring 7.8 on the Richter scale, results in nearly 9,000 deaths in Nepal, India, China, and Bangladesh."
2015,"April 29","The World Health Organization (WHO) declares that rubella has been eradicated from the Americas."
2015,"May 1","(May 1 - October 31) Expo 2015 is held in Milan, Italy."
2015,"May 12","A second major earthquake in Nepal, measuring 7.3 on the Richter scale, results in more than 200 deaths in Nepal, India, China, and Bangladesh."
2015,"June 25","(June 25 - June 26) ISIL claim responsibility for four attacks around the world during the Ramadan: 1) Kobanî massacre: ISIL fighters detonate three car bombs, enter Kobanî, Syria, and open fire at civilians, killing more than 220, 2) Sousse attacks: 22-year-old Seifeddine Rezgui opens fire at a tourist resort at Port El Kantaoui, Tunisia, killing 40 people, 3) Kuwait mosque bombing: A suicide bomber attacks the Shia Mosque Imam Ja'far as-Sadiq at Kuwait City, Kuwait, killing 27 people and injuring 227 others, and 4) Saint-Quentin-Fallavier attack: an Islamist delivery driver decapitated a man and rammed a company van into gas cylinders at a gas factory near Lyon, France, causing an explosion and injuring two others."
2015,"July 12","A Russian military barracks in the Omsk region of southern Russia collapses, killing 23 people."
2015,"July 20","Cuba and the United States reestablish full diplomatic relations, ending a 54-year stretch of hostility between the nations."
2015,"July 24","Turkey begins a series of airstrikes against PKK and ISIL targets after the 2015 Suruç bombing."
2015,"September 30","Russia begins air strikes against ISIL and anti-government forces in Syria in support of the Syrian government."
2015,"October 10","A suicide bomb kills at least 100 people at a peace rally in Ankara, Turkey, and injures more than 400 others."
2015,"November 13","Multiple attacks claimed by Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) in Paris, France, resulting in 130 fatalities."
